B001C004V017	1	4	17	Cain knew his wife. She conceived, and gave birth to Enoch. He built a city, and called the name of the city, after the name of his son, Enoch.
B001C004V018	1	4	18	To Enoch was born Irad. Irad became the father of Mehujael. Mehujael became the father of Methushael. Methushael became the father of Lamech.
B001C004V019	1	4	19	Lamech took two wives: the name of the one was Adah, and the name of the other Zillah.
B001C004V020	1	4	20	Adah gave birth to Jabal, who was the father of those who dwell in tents and have livestock.
B001C004V021	1	4	21	His brother's name was Jubal, who was the father of all who handle the harp and pipe.
B001C004V022	1	4	22	Zillah also gave birth to Tubal Cain, the forger of every cutting instrument of brass and iron. Tubal Cain's sister was Naamah.
B001C004V023	1	4	23	Lamech said to his wives, "Adah and Zillah, hear my voice.You wives of Lamech, listen to my speech,for I have slain a man for wounding me,a young man for bruising me.
