B001C007V006	1	7	6	Noah was six hundred years old when the flood of waters came on the earth.
B001C007V007	1	7	7	Noah went into the ship with his sons, his wife, and his sons' wives, because of the waters of the flood.
B001C007V008	1	7	8	Clean animals, animals that are not clean, birds, and everything that creeps on the ground
B001C007V009	1	7	9	went by pairs to Noah into the ship, male and female, as God commanded Noah.
B001C007V010	1	7	10	It happened after the seven days, that the waters of the flood came on the earth.
B001C007V011	1	7	11	In the six hundredth year of Noah's life, in the second month, on the seventeenth day of the month, on the same day all the fountains of the great deep were burst open, and the sky's windows were opened.
