B001C007V016	1	7	16	Those who went in, went in male and female of all flesh, as God commanded him; and 
B001C007V017	1	7	17	The flood was forty days on the earth. The waters increased, and lifted up the ship, and it was lifted up above the earth.
B001C007V018	1	7	18	The waters prevailed, and increased greatly on the earth; and the ship floated on the surface of the waters.
B001C007V019	1	7	19	The waters prevailed exceedingly on the earth. All the high mountains that were under the whole sky were covered.
B001C007V020	1	7	20	The waters prevailed fifteen cubits upward, and the mountains were covered.
B001C007V021	1	7	21	All flesh died that moved on the earth, including birds, livestock, animals, every creeping thing that creeps on the earth, and every man.
B001C007V022	1	7	22	All in whose nostrils was the breath of the spirit of life, of all that was on the dry land, died.
B001C007V023	1	7	23	Every living thing was destroyed that was on the surface of the ground, including man, livestock, creeping things, and birds of the sky. They were destroyed from the earth. Only Noah was left, and those who were with him in the ship.
B001C007V024	1	7	24	The waters prevailed on the earth one hundred fifty days.
B001C008V001	1	8	1	God remembered Noah, all the animals, and all the livestock that were with him in the ship; and God made a wind to pass over the earth. The waters subsided.
B001C008V002	1	8	2	The deep's fountains and the sky's windows were also stopped, and the rain from the sky was restrained.
B001C008V003	1	8	3	The waters receded from the earth continually. After the end of one hundred fifty days the waters decreased.
B001C008V004	1	8	4	The ship rested in the seventh month, on the seventeenth day of the month, on Ararat's mountains.
B001C008V005	1	8	5	The waters receded continually until the tenth month. In the tenth month, on the first day of the month, the tops of the mountains were seen.
B001C008V006	1	8	6	It happened at the end of forty days, that Noah opened the window of the ship which he had made,
B001C008V007	1	8	7	and he sent forth a raven. It went back and forth, until the waters were dried up from the earth.
