B001C043V020	1	43	20	and said, "Oh, my lord, we indeed came down the first time to buy food.
B001C043V021	1	43	21	When we came to the lodging place, we opened our sacks, and behold, every man's money was in the mouth of his sack, our money in full weight. We have brought it back in our hand.
B001C043V022	1	43	22	We have brought down other money in our hand to buy food. We do not know who put our money in our sacks."
B001C043V023	1	43	23	He said, "Peace be to you. Do not be afraid. Your God, and the God of your father, has given you treasure in your sacks. I received your money." He brought Simeon out to them.
B001C043V024	1	43	24	The man brought the men into Joseph's house, and gave them water, and they washed their feet. He gave their donkeys fodder.
B001C043V025	1	43	25	They made ready the present for Joseph's coming at noon, for they heard that they should eat bread there.
B001C043V026	1	43	26	When Joseph came home, they brought him the present which was in their hand into the house, and bowed themselves down to him to the earth.
B001C043V027	1	43	27	He asked them of their welfare, and said, "Is your father well, the old man of whom you spoke? Is he yet alive?"
B001C043V028	1	43	28	They said, "Your servant, our father, is well. He is still alive." They bowed the head, and did homage.
B001C043V029	1	43	29	He lifted up his eyes, and saw Benjamin, his brother, his mother's son, and said, "Is this your youngest brother, of whom you spoke to me?" He said, "God be gracious to you, my son."
B001C043V030	1	43	30	Joseph hurried, for his heart yearned over his brother; and he sought a place to weep. He entered into his room, and wept there.
B001C043V031	1	43	31	He washed his face, and came out. He controlled himself, and said, "Serve the meal."
B001C043V032	1	43	32	They served him by himself, and them by themselves, and the Egyptians, that ate with him, by themselves, because the Egyptians do not eat bread with the Hebrews, for that is an abomination to the Egyptians.
