B002C022V021	2	22	21	"You shall not wrong a foreigner, neither shall you oppress him, for you were foreigners in the land of Egypt.
B002C022V022	2	22	22	"You shall not take advantage of any widow or fatherless child.
B002C022V023	2	22	23	If you take advantage of them at all, and they cry at all to me, I will surely hear their cry;
B002C022V024	2	22	24	and my wrath will grow hot, and I will kill you with the sword; and your wives shall be widows, and your children fatherless.
B002C022V025	2	22	25	"If you lend money to any of my people with you who is poor, you shall not be to him as a creditor; neither shall you charge him interest.
B002C022V026	2	22	26	If you take your neighbor's garment as collateral, you shall restore it to him before the sun goes down,
B002C022V027	2	22	27	for that is his only covering, it is his garment for his skin. What would he sleep in? It will happen, when he cries to me, that I will hear, for I am gracious.
B002C022V028	2	22	28	"You shall not blaspheme God, nor curse a ruler of your people.
B002C022V029	2	22	29	"You shall not delay to offer from your harvest and from the outflow of your presses."You shall give the firstborn of your sons to me.
B002C022V030	2	22	30	You shall do likewise with your cattle and with your sheep. Seven days it shall be with its mother, then on the eighth day you shall give it to me.
B002C022V031	2	22	31	"You shall be holy men to me, therefore you shall not eat any flesh that is torn by animals in the field. You shall cast it to the dogs.
B002C023V001	2	23	1	"You shall not spread a false report. Do not join your hand with the wicked to be an unjust witness.
B002C023V002	2	23	2	You shall not follow a crowd to do evil; neither shall you testify in court to side with a multitude to pervert justice;
B002C023V003	2	23	3	neither shall you favor a poor man in his cause.
B002C023V004	2	23	4	"If you meet your enemy's ox or his donkey going astray, you shall surely bring it back to him again.
B002C023V005	2	23	5	If you see the donkey of him who hates you fallen down under his burden, do not leave him, you shall surely help him with it.
B002C023V006	2	23	6	"You shall not deny justice to your poor people in their lawsuits.
B002C023V007	2	23	7	"Keep far from a false charge, and do not kill the innocent and righteous: for I will not justify the wicked.
B002C023V008	2	23	8	"You shall take no bribe, for a bribe blinds the eyes of those who have sight and perverts the words of the righteous.
B002C023V009	2	23	9	"You shall not oppress a foreigner, for you know the heart of a foreigner, seeing you were foreigners in the land of Egypt.
B002C023V010	2	23	10	"For six years you shall sow your land, and shall gather in its increase,
B002C023V011	2	23	11	but the seventh year you shall let it rest and lie fallow, that the poor of your people may eat; and what they leave the animal of the field shall eat. In like manner you shall deal with your vineyard and with your olive grove.
B002C023V012	2	23	12	"Six days you shall do your work, and on the seventh day you shall rest, that your ox and your donkey may have rest, and the son of your handmaid, and the alien may be refreshed.
B002C023V013	2	23	13	"Be careful to do all things that I have said to you; and do not invoke the name of other gods, neither let them be heard out of your mouth.
B002C023V014	2	23	14	"You shall observe a feast to me three times a year.
B002C023V015	2	23	15	You shall observe the feast of unleavened bread. Seven days you shall eat unleavened bread, as I commanded you, at the time appointed in the month Abib (for in it you came out from Egypt), and no one shall appear before me empty.
B002C023V016	2	23	16	And the feast of harvest, the first fruits of your labors, which you sow in the field: and the feast of harvest, at the end of the year, when you gather in your labors out of the field.
B002C023V017	2	23	17	Three times in the year all your males shall appear before the Lord 
B002C023V018	2	23	18	"You shall not offer the blood of my sacrifice with leavened bread, neither shall the fat of my feast remain all night until the morning.
B002C023V019	2	23	19	The first of the first fruits of your ground you shall bring into the house of 
B002C023V020	2	23	20	"Behold, I send an angel before you, to keep you by the way, and to bring you into the place which I have prepared.
B002C023V021	2	23	21	Pay attention to him, and listen to his voice. Do not provoke him, for he will not pardon your disobedience, for my name is in him.
B002C023V022	2	23	22	But if you indeed listen to his voice, and do all that I speak, then I will be an enemy to your enemies, and an adversary to your adversaries.
