B013C002V037	13	2	37	and Zabad became the father of Ephlal, and Ephlal became the father of Obed,
B013C002V038	13	2	38	and Obed became the father of Jehu, and Jehu became the father of Azariah,
B013C002V039	13	2	39	and Azariah became the father of Helez, and Helez became the father of Eleasah,
B013C002V040	13	2	40	and Eleasah became the father of Sismai, and Sismai became the father of Shallum,
B013C002V041	13	2	41	and Shallum became the father of Jekamiah, and Jekamiah became the father of Elishama.
B013C002V042	13	2	42	The sons of Caleb the brother of Jerahmeel were Mesha his firstborn, who was the father of Ziph; and the sons of Mareshah the father of Hebron.
B013C002V043	13	2	43	The sons of Hebron: Korah, and Tappuah, and Rekem, and Shema.
B013C002V044	13	2	44	Shema became the father of Raham, the father of Jorkeam; and Rekem became the father of Shammai.
B013C002V045	13	2	45	The son of Shammai was Maon; and Maon was the father of Beth Zur.
B013C002V046	13	2	46	Ephah, Caleb's concubine, bore Haran, and Moza, and Gazez; and Haran became the father of Gazez.
B013C002V047	13	2	47	The sons of Jahdai: Regem, and Jothan, and Geshan, and Pelet, and Ephah, and Shaaph.
B013C002V048	13	2	48	Maacah, Caleb's concubine, bore Sheber and Tirhanah.
B013C002V049	13	2	49	She bore also Shaaph the father of Madmannah, Sheva the father of Machbena, and the father of Gibea; and the daughter of Caleb was Achsah.
B013C002V050	13	2	50	These were the sons of Caleb, the son of Hur, the firstborn of Ephrathah: Shobal the father of Kiriath Jearim,
B013C002V051	13	2	51	Salma the father of Bethlehem, Hareph the father of Beth Gader.
B013C002V052	13	2	52	Shobal the father of Kiriath Jearim had sons: Haroeh, half of the Menuhoth.
B013C002V053	13	2	53	The families of Kiriath Jearim: The Ithrites, and the Puthites, and the Shumathites, and the Mishraites; of them came the Zorathites and the Eshtaolites.
B013C002V054	13	2	54	The sons of Salma: Bethlehem, and the Netophathites, Atroth Beth Joab, and half of the Manahathites, the Zorites.
B013C002V055	13	2	55	The families of scribes who lived at Jabez: the Tirathites, the Shimeathites, the Sucathites. These are the Kenites who came of Hammath, the father of the house of Rechab.
B013C003V001	13	3	1	Now these were the sons of David, who were born to him in Hebron: the firstborn, Amnon, of Ahinoam the Jezreelitess; the second, Daniel, of Abigail the Carmelitess;
B013C003V002	13	3	2	the third, Absalom the son of Maacah the daughter of Talmai king of Geshur; the fourth, Adonijah the son of Haggith;
B013C003V003	13	3	3	the fifth, Shephatiah of Abital; the sixth, Ithream by Eglah his wife:
B013C003V004	13	3	4	six were born to him in Hebron; and there he reigned seven years and six months. In Jerusalem he reigned thirty-three years;
B013C003V005	13	3	5	and these were born to him in Jerusalem: Shimea, and Shobab, and Nathan, and Solomon, four, of Bathshua the daughter of Ammiel;
B013C003V006	13	3	6	and Ibhar, and Elishama, and Eliphelet,
B013C003V007	13	3	7	and Nogah, and Nepheg, and Japhia,
B013C003V008	13	3	8	and Elishama, and Eliada, and Eliphelet, nine.
B013C003V009	13	3	9	All these were the sons of David, besides the sons of the concubines; and Tamar was their sister.
B013C003V010	13	3	10	Solomon's son was Rehoboam, Abijah his son, Asa his son, Jehoshaphat his son,
B013C003V011	13	3	11	Joram his son, Ahaziah his son, Joash his son,
B013C003V012	13	3	12	Amaziah his son, Azariah his son, Jotham his son,
B013C003V013	13	3	13	Ahaz his son, Hezekiah his son, Manasseh his son,
B013C003V014	13	3	14	Amon his son, Josiah his son.
B013C003V015	13	3	15	The sons of Josiah: the firstborn Yochanan, the second Jehoiakim, the third Zedekiah, the fourth Shallum.
B013C003V016	13	3	16	The sons of Jehoiakim: Jeconiah his son, Zedekiah his son.
B013C003V017	13	3	17	The sons of Jeconiah, the captive: Shealtiel his son,
B013C003V018	13	3	18	and Malchiram, and Pedaiah, and Shenazzar, Jekamiah, Hoshama, and Nedabiah.
B013C003V019	13	3	19	The sons of Pedaiah: Zerubbabel, and Shimei. The sons of Zerubbabel: Meshullam, and Hananiah; and Shelomith was their sister;
B013C003V020	13	3	20	and Hashubah, and Ohel, and Berechiah, and Hasadiah, Jushab Hesed, five.
B013C003V021	13	3	21	The sons of Hananiah: Pelatiah, and Jeshaiah; the sons of Rephaiah, the sons of Arnan, the sons of Obadiah, the sons of Shecaniah.
B013C003V022	13	3	22	The sons of Shecaniah: Shemaiah. The sons of Shemaiah: Hattush, and Igal, and Bariah, and Neariah, and Shaphat, six.
B013C003V023	13	3	23	The sons of Neariah: Elioenai, and Hizkiah, and Azrikam, three.
B013C003V024	13	3	24	The sons of Elioenai: Hodaviah, and Eliashib, and Pelaiah, and Akkub, and Yochanan, and Delaiah, and Anani, seven.
B013C004V001	13	4	1	The sons of Judah: Perez, Hezron, and Carmi, and Hur, and Shobal.
B013C004V002	13	4	2	Reaiah the son of Shobal became the father of Jahath; and Jahath became the father of Ahumai and Lahad. These are the families of the Zorathites.
B013C004V003	13	4	3	These were the sons of the father of Etam: Jezreel, and Ishma, and Idbash; and the name of their sister was Hazzelelponi;
B013C004V004	13	4	4	and Penuel the father of Gedor, and Ezer the father of Hushah. These are the sons of Hur, the firstborn of Ephrathah, the father of Bethlehem.
B013C004V005	13	4	5	Ashhur the father of Tekoa had two wives, Helah and Naarah.
B013C004V006	13	4	6	Naarah bore him Ahuzzam, and Hepher, and Temeni, and Haahashtari. These were the sons of Naarah.
B013C004V007	13	4	7	The sons of Helah were Zereth, Izhar, and Ethnan.
B013C004V008	13	4	8	Hakkoz became the father of Anub, and Zobebah, and the families of Aharhel the son of Harum.
B013C004V009	13	4	9	Jabez was more honorable than his brothers: and his mother named him Jabez, saying, Because I bore him with sorrow.
B013C004V010	13	4	10	Jabez called on the God of Israel, saying, Oh that you would bless me indeed, and enlarge my border, and that your hand might be with me, and that you would keep me from evil, that it not be to my sorrow! God granted him that which he requested.
B013C004V011	13	4	11	Chelub the brother of Shuhah became the father of Mehir, who was the father of Eshton.
B013C004V012	13	4	12	Eshton became the father of Beth Rapha, and Paseah, and Tehinnah the father of Ir Nahash. These are the men of Recah.
B013C004V013	13	4	13	The sons of Kenaz: Othniel, and Seraiah. The sons of Othniel: Hathath.
B013C004V014	13	4	14	Meonothai became the father of Ophrah: and Seraiah became the father of Joab the father of Ge Harashim; for they were craftsmen.
B013C004V015	13	4	15	The sons of Caleb the son of Jephunneh: Iru, Elah, and Naam; and the sons of Elah; and Kenaz.
B013C004V016	13	4	16	The sons of Jehallelel: Ziph, and Ziphah, Tiria, and Asarel.
B013C004V017	13	4	17	The sons of Ezrah: Jether, and Mered, and Epher, and Jalon; and she bore Miriam, and Shammai, and Ishbah the father of Eshtemoa.
B013C004V018	13	4	18	His wife Yehudiyah bore Jered the father of Gedor, and Heber the father of Soco, and Jekuthiel the father of Zanoah. These are the sons of Bithiah the daughter of Pharaoh, whom Mered took.
B013C004V019	13	4	19	The sons of the wife of Hodiah, the sister of Naham, were the father of Keilah the Garmite, and Eshtemoa the Maacathite.
B013C004V020	13	4	20	The sons of Shimon: Amnon, and Rinnah, Ben Hanan, and Tilon. The sons of Ishi: Zoheth, and Ben Zoheth.
B013C004V021	13	4	21	The sons of Shelah the son of Judah: Er the father of Lecah, and Laadah the father of Mareshah, and the families of the house of those who worked fine linen, of the house of Ashbea;
B013C004V022	13	4	22	and Jokim, and the men of Cozeba, and Joash, and Saraph, who had dominion in Moab, and Jashubilehem. The records are ancient.
B013C004V023	13	4	23	These were the potters, and the inhabitants of Netaim and Gederah: there they lived with the king for his work.
B013C004V024	13	4	24	The sons of Simeon: Nemuel, and Jamin, Jarib, Zerah, Shaul;
B013C004V025	13	4	25	Shallum his son, Mibsam his son, Mishma his son.
B013C004V026	13	4	26	The sons of Mishma: Hammuel his son, Zaccur his son, Shimei his son.
B013C004V027	13	4	27	Shimei had sixteen sons and six daughters; but his brothers did not have many children, neither did all their family multiply like the children of Judah.
B013C004V028	13	4	28	They lived at Beersheba, and Moladah, and Hazarshual,
B013C004V029	13	4	29	and at Bilhah, and at Ezem, and at Tolad,
B013C004V030	13	4	30	and at Bethuel, and at Hormah, and at Ziklag,
B013C004V031	13	4	31	and at Beth Marcaboth, and Hazar Susim, and at Beth Biri, and at Shaaraim. These were their cities to the reign of David.
B013C004V032	13	4	32	Their villages were Etam, and Ain, Rimmon, and Tochen, and Ashan, five cities;
B013C004V033	13	4	33	and all their villages that were around the same cities, to Baal. These were their habitations, and they have their genealogy.
B013C004V034	13	4	34	Meshobab, and Jamlech, and Joshah the son of Amaziah,
B013C004V035	13	4	35	and Joel, and Jehu the son of Joshibiah, the son of Seraiah, the son of Asiel,
B013C004V036	13	4	36	and Elioenai, and Jaakobah, and Jeshohaiah, and Asaiah, and Adiel, and Jesimiel, and Benaiah,
B013C004V037	13	4	37	and Ziza the son of Shiphi, the son of Allon, the son of Jedaiah, the son of Shimri, the son of Shemaiah-
B013C004V038	13	4	38	these mentioned by name were princes in their families: and their fathers' houses increased greatly.
B013C004V039	13	4	39	They went to the entrance of Gedor, even to the east side of the valley, to seek pasture for their flocks.
B013C004V040	13	4	40	They found fat pasture and good, and the land was wide, and quiet, and peaceable; for those who lived there before were of Ham.
B013C004V041	13	4	41	These written by name came in the days of Hezekiah king of Judah, and struck their tents, and the Meunim who were found there, and destroyed them utterly to this day, and lived in their place; because there was pasture there for their flocks.
B013C004V042	13	4	42	Some of them, even of the sons of Simeon, five hundred men, went to Mount Seir, having for their leaders Pelatiah, and Neariah, and Rephaiah, and Uzziel, the sons of Ishi.
B013C004V043	13	4	43	They struck the remnant of the Amalekites who escaped, and have lived there to this day.
B013C005V001	13	5	1	The sons of Reuben the firstborn of Israel (for he was the firstborn; but, because he defiled his father's couch, his birthright was given to the sons of Joseph the son of Israel; and the genealogy is not to be reckoned after the birthright.
B013C005V002	13	5	2	For Judah prevailed above his brothers, and of him came the prince; but the birthright was Joseph's:)
B013C005V003	13	5	3	the sons of Reuben the firstborn of Israel: Hanoch, and Pallu, Hezron, and Carmi.
B013C005V004	13	5	4	The sons of Joel: Shemaiah his son, Gog his son, Shimei his son,
B013C005V005	13	5	5	Micah his son, Reaiah his son, Baal his son,
B013C005V006	13	5	6	Beerah his son, whom Tilgath Pilneser king of Assyria carried away captive: he was leader of the Reubenites.
B013C005V007	13	5	7	His brothers by their families, when the genealogy of their generations was reckoned: the chief, Jeiel, and Zechariah,
B013C005V008	13	5	8	and Bela the son of Azaz, the son of Shema, the son of Joel, who lived in Aroer, even to Nebo and Baal Meon:
B013C005V009	13	5	9	and eastward he lived even to the entrance of the wilderness from the river Euphrates, because their livestock were multiplied in the land of Gilead.
B013C005V010	13	5	10	In the days of Saul, they made war with the Hagrites, who fell by their hand; and they lived in their tents throughout all the land east of Gilead.
B013C005V011	13	5	11	The sons of Gad lived over against them, in the land of Bashan to Salecah:
B013C005V012	13	5	12	Joel the chief, and Shapham the second, and Janai, and Shaphat in Bashan.
B013C005V013	13	5	13	Their brothers of their fathers' houses: Michael, and Meshullam, and Sheba, and Jorai, and Jacan, and Zia, and Eber, seven.
B013C005V014	13	5	14	These were the sons of Abihail, the son of Huri, the son of Jaroah, the son of Gilead, the son of Michael, the son of Jeshishai, the son of Jahdo, the son of Buz;
B013C005V015	13	5	15	Ahi the son of Abdiel, the son of Guni, chief of their fathers' houses.
B013C005V016	13	5	16	They lived in Gilead in Bashan, and in its towns, and in all the suburbs of Sharon, as far as their borders.
B013C005V017	13	5	17	All these were reckoned by genealogies in the days of Jotham king of Judah, and in the days of Jeroboam king of Israel.
B013C005V018	13	5	18	The sons of Reuben, and the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh, of valiant men, men able to bear buckler and sword, and to shoot with bow, and skillful in war, were forty-four thousand seven hundred and sixty, that were able to go forth to war.
B013C005V019	13	5	19	They made war with the Hagrites, with Jetur, and Naphish, and Nodab.
B013C005V020	13	5	20	They were helped against them, and the Hagrites were delivered into their hand, and all who were with them; for they cried to God in the battle, and he was entreated of them, because they put their trust in him.
B013C005V021	13	5	21	They took away their livestock; of their camels fifty thousand, and of sheep two hundred fifty thousand, and of donkeys two thousand, and of men one hundred thousand.
B013C005V022	13	5	22	For there fell many slain, because the war was of God. They lived in their place until the captivity.
B013C005V023	13	5	23	The children of the half-tribe of Manasseh lived in the land: they increased from Bashan to Baal Hermon and Senir and Mount Hermon.
B013C005V024	13	5	24	These were the heads of their fathers' houses: even Epher, and Ishi, and Eliel, and Azriel, and Jeremiah, and Hodaviah, and Jahdiel, mighty men of valor, famous men, heads of their fathers' houses.
B013C005V025	13	5	25	They trespassed against the God of their fathers, and prostituted themselves after the gods of the peoples of the land, whom God destroyed before them.
B013C005V026	13	5	26	The God of Israel stirred up the spirit of Pul king of Assyria, and the spirit of Tilgath Pilneser king of Assyria, and he carried them away, even the Reubenites, and the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh, and brought them to Halah, and Habor, and Hara, and to the river of Gozan, to this day.
B013C006V001	13	6	1	The sons of Levi: Gershon, Kohath, and Merari.
B013C006V002	13	6	2	The sons of Kohath: Amram, Izhar, and Hebron, and Uzziel.
B013C006V003	13	6	3	The children of Amram: Aaron, and Moses, and Miriam. The sons of Aaron: Nadab, and Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.
B013C006V004	13	6	4	Eleazar became the father of Phinehas, Phinehas became the father of Abishua,
B013C006V005	13	6	5	and Abishua became the father of Bukki, and Bukki became the father of Uzzi,
B013C006V006	13	6	6	and Uzzi became the father of Zerahiah, and Zerahiah became the father of Meraioth,
B013C006V007	13	6	7	Meraioth became the father of Amariah, and Amariah became the father of Ahitub,
B013C006V008	13	6	8	and Ahitub became the father of Zadok, and Zadok became the father of Ahimaaz,
B013C006V009	13	6	9	and Ahimaaz became the father of Azariah, and Azariah became the father of Yochanan,
B013C006V010	13	6	10	and Yochanan became the father of Azariah, (he it is who executed the priest's office in the house that Solomon built in Jerusalem),
B013C006V011	13	6	11	and Azariah became the father of Amariah, and Amariah became the father of Ahitub,
B013C006V012	13	6	12	and Ahitub became the father of Zadok, and Zadok became the father of Shallum,
B013C006V013	13	6	13	and Shallum became the father of Hilkiah, and Hilkiah became the father of Azariah,
B013C006V014	13	6	14	and Azariah became the father of Seraiah, and Seraiah became the father of Jehozadak;
B013C006V015	13	6	15	Jehozadak went into captivity, when 
B013C006V016	13	6	16	The sons of Levi: Gershom, Kohath, and Merari.
B013C006V017	13	6	17	These are the names of the sons of Gershom: Libni and Shimei.
B013C006V018	13	6	18	The sons of Kohath were Amram, and Izhar, and Hebron, and Uzziel.
B013C006V019	13	6	19	The sons of Merari: Mahli and Mushi. These are the families of the Levites according to their fathers' houses.
B013C006V020	13	6	20	Of Gershom: Libni his son, Jahath his son, Zimmah his son,
B013C006V021	13	6	21	Joah his son, Iddo his son, Zerah his son, Jeatherai his son.
B013C006V022	13	6	22	The sons of Kohath: Amminadab his son, Korah his son, Assir his son,
B013C006V023	13	6	23	Elkanah his son, and Ebiasaph his son, and Assir his son,
B013C006V024	13	6	24	Tahath his son, Uriel his son, Uzziah his son, and Shaul his son.
B013C006V025	13	6	25	The sons of Elkanah: Amasai, and Ahimoth.
B013C006V026	13	6	26	As for Elkanah, the sons of Elkanah: Zophai his son, and Nahath his son,
B013C006V027	13	6	27	Eliab his son, Jeroham his son, Elkanah his son.
B013C006V028	13	6	28	The sons of Samuel: the firstborn Joel, and the second Abijah.
B013C006V029	13	6	29	The sons of Merari: Mahli, Libni his son, Shimei his son, Uzzah his son,
B013C006V030	13	6	30	Shimea his son, Haggiah his son, Asaiah his son.
B013C006V031	13	6	31	These are they whom David set over the service of song in the house of 
B013C006V032	13	6	32	They ministered with song before the tabernacle of the Tent of Meeting, until Solomon had built the house of 
B013C006V033	13	6	33	These are those who waited, and their sons. Of the sons of the Kohathites: Heman the singer, the son of Joel, the son of Samuel,
B013C006V034	13	6	34	the son of Elkanah, the son of Jeroham, the son of Eliel, the son of Toah,
B013C006V035	13	6	35	the son of Zuph, the son of Elkanah, the son of Mahath, the son of Amasai,
B013C006V036	13	6	36	the son of Elkanah, the son of Joel, the son of Azariah, the son of Zephaniah,
B013C006V037	13	6	37	the son of Tahath, the son of Assir, the son of Ebiasaph, the son of Korah,
B013C006V038	13	6	38	the son of Izhar, the son of Kohath, the son of Levi, the son of Israel.
B013C006V039	13	6	39	His brother Asaph, who stood on his right hand, even Asaph the son of Berechiah, the son of Shimea,
B013C006V040	13	6	40	the son of Michael, the son of Baaseiah, the son of Malchijah,
B013C006V041	13	6	41	the son of Ethni, the son of Zerah, the son of Adaiah,
B013C006V042	13	6	42	the son of Ethan, the son of Zimmah, the son of Shimei,
B013C006V043	13	6	43	the son of Jahath, the son of Gershom, the son of Levi.
B013C006V044	13	6	44	On the left hand their brothers the sons of Merari: Ethan the son of Kishi, the son of Abdi, the son of Malluch,
B013C006V045	13	6	45	the son of Hashabiah, the son of Amaziah, the son of Hilkiah,
B013C006V046	13	6	46	the son of Amzi, the son of Bani, the son of Shemer,
B013C006V047	13	6	47	the son of Mahli, the son of Mushi, the son of Merari, the son of Levi.
B013C006V048	13	6	48	Their brothers the Levites were appointed for all the service of the tabernacle of the house of God.
B013C006V049	13	6	49	But Aaron and his sons offered on the altar of burnt offering, and on the altar of incense, for all the work of the most holy place, and to make atonement for Israel, according to all that Moses the servant of God had commanded.
B013C006V050	13	6	50	These are the sons of Aaron: Eleazar his son, Phinehas his son, Abishua his son,
B013C006V051	13	6	51	Bukki his son, Uzzi his son, Zerahiah his son,
B013C006V052	13	6	52	Meraioth his son, Amariah his son, Ahitub his son,
B013C006V053	13	6	53	Zadok his son, Ahimaaz his son.
B013C006V054	13	6	54	Now these are their dwelling places according to their encampments in their borders: to the sons of Aaron, of the families of the Kohathites (for theirs was the first lot),
B013C006V055	13	6	55	to them they gave Hebron in the land of Judah, and its suburbs around it;
B013C006V056	13	6	56	but the fields of the city, and its villages, they gave to Caleb the son of Jephunneh.
B013C006V057	13	6	57	To the sons of Aaron they gave the cities of refuge, Hebron; Libnah also with its suburbs, and Jattir, and Eshtemoa with its suburbs,
B013C006V058	13	6	58	and Hilen with its suburbs, Debir with its suburbs,
B013C006V059	13	6	59	and Ashan with its suburbs, and Beth Shemesh with its suburbs;
B013C006V060	13	6	60	and out of the tribe of Benjamin, Geba with its suburbs, and Allemeth with its suburbs, and Anathoth with its suburbs. All their cities throughout their families were thirteen cities.
B013C006V061	13	6	61	To the rest of the sons of Kohath were given by lot, out of the family of the tribe, out of the half-tribe, the half of Manasseh, ten cities.
B013C006V062	13	6	62	To the sons of Gershom, according to their families, out of the tribe of Issachar, and out of the tribe of Asher, and out of the tribe of Naphtali, and out of the tribe of Manasseh in Bashan, thirteen cities.
B013C006V063	13	6	63	To the sons of Merari were given by lot, according to their families, out of the tribe of Reuben, and out of the tribe of Gad, and out of the tribe of Zebulun, twelve cities.
B013C006V064	13	6	64	The children of Israel gave to the Levites the cities with their suburbs.
B013C006V065	13	6	65	They gave by lot out of the tribe of the children of Judah, and out of the tribe of the children of Simeon, and out of the tribe of the children of Benjamin, these cities which are mentioned by name.
B013C006V066	13	6	66	Some of the families of the sons of Kohath had cities of their borders out of the tribe of Ephraim.
B013C006V067	13	6	67	They gave to them the cities of refuge, Shechem in the hill country of Ephraim with its suburbs; Gezer also with its suburbs,
B013C006V068	13	6	68	and Jokmeam with its suburbs, and Beth Horon with its suburbs,
B013C006V069	13	6	69	and Aijalon with its suburbs, and Gath Rimmon with its suburbs;
B013C006V070	13	6	70	and out of the half-tribe of Manasseh, Aner with its suburbs, and Bileam with its suburbs, for the rest of the family of the sons of Kohath.
B013C006V071	13	6	71	To the sons of Gershom were given, out of the family of the half-tribe of Manasseh, Golan in Bashan with its suburbs, and Ashtaroth with its suburbs;
B013C006V072	13	6	72	and out of the tribe of Issachar, Kedesh with its suburbs, Daberath with its suburbs,
B013C006V073	13	6	73	and Ramoth with its suburbs, and Anem with its suburbs;
B013C006V074	13	6	74	and out of the tribe of Asher, Mashal with its suburbs, and Abdon with its suburbs,
B013C006V075	13	6	75	and Hukok with its suburbs, and Rehob with its suburbs;
