B019C038V001	19	38	1	A Psalm by David, for a memorial.   
B019C038V002	19	38	2	For your arrows have pierced me,your hand presses hard on me.
B019C038V003	19	38	3	There is no soundness in my flesh because of your indignation,neither is there any health in my bones because of my sin.
B019C038V004	19	38	4	For my iniquities have gone over my head.As a heavy burden, they are too heavy for me.
B019C038V005	19	38	5	My wounds are loathsome and corrupt,because of my foolishness.
B019C038V006	19	38	6	I am pained and bowed down greatly.I go mourning all day long.
B019C038V007	19	38	7	For my waist is filled with burning.There is no soundness in my flesh.
B019C038V008	19	38	8	I am faint and severely bruised.I have groaned by reason of the anguish of my heart.
B019C038V009	19	38	9	Lord, all my desire is before you.My groaning is not hidden from you.
B019C038V010	19	38	10	My heart throbs.My strength fails me.As for the light of my eyes, it has also left me.
B019C038V011	19	38	11	My lovers and my friends stand aloof from my plague.My kinsmen stand far away.
B019C038V012	19	38	12	They also who seek after my life lay snares.Those who seek my hurt speak mischievous things,and meditate deceits all day long.
B019C038V013	19	38	13	But I, as a deaf man, do not hear.I am as a mute man who doesn't open his mouth.
B019C038V014	19	38	14	Yes, I am as a man who doesn't hear,in whose mouth are no reproofs.
B019C038V015	19	38	15	For in you, 
B019C038V016	19	38	16	For I said, "Do not let them gloat over me,or exalt themselves over me when my foot slips."
B019C038V017	19	38	17	For I am ready to fall.My pain is continually before me.
B019C038V018	19	38	18	For I will declare my iniquity.I will be sorry for my sin.
B019C038V019	19	38	19	But my enemies are vigorous and many.Those who hate me without reason are numerous.
B019C038V020	19	38	20	They who also render evil for good are adversaries to me,because I follow what is good.
B019C038V021	19	38	21	Do not forsake me, 
B019C038V022	19	38	22	Hurry to help me,Lord, my salvation.
B019C039V001	19	39	1	For the Chief Musician. For Jeduthun. A Psalm by David.   I said, "I will watch my ways, so that I do not sin with my tongue.I will keep my mouth with a bridle while the wicked is before me."
B019C039V002	19	39	2	I was mute with silence.I held my peace, even from good.My sorrow was stirred.
B019C039V003	19	39	3	My heart was hot within me.While I meditated, the fire burned:I spoke with my tongue:
B019C039V004	19	39	4	"
B019C039V005	19	39	5	Behold, you have made my days handbreadths.My lifetime is as nothing before you.Surely every man stands as a breath."Selah.
B019C039V006	19	39	6	"Surely every man walks like a shadow.Surely they busy themselves in vain.He heaps up, and doesn't know who shall gather.
B019C039V007	19	39	7	Now, Lord, what do I wait for?My hope is in you.
B019C039V008	19	39	8	Deliver me from all my transgressions.Do not make me the reproach of the foolish.
B019C039V009	19	39	9	I was mute.I did not open my mouth,because you did it.
B019C039V010	19	39	10	Remove your scourge away from me.I am overcome by the blow of your hand.
B019C039V011	19	39	11	When you rebuke and correct man for iniquity,You consume his wealth like a moth.Surely every man is but a breath."Selah.
B019C039V012	19	39	12	"Hear my prayer, 
B019C039V013	19	39	13	Oh spare me, that I may recover strength,before I go away, and exist no more."
