B019C042V001	19	42	1	For the Chief Musician. A contemplation by the sons of Korah.   As the deer pants for the water brooks,so my soul pants after you, God.
B019C042V002	19	42	2	My soul thirsts for God, for the living God.When shall I come and appear before God?
B019C042V003	19	42	3	My tears have been my food day and night,while they continually ask me, "Where is your God?"
B019C042V004	19	42	4	These things I remember, and pour out my soul within me,how I used to go with the crowd, and led them to the house of God,with the voice of joy and praise, a multitude keeping a holy day.
B019C042V005	19	42	5	Why are you in despair, my soul?Why are you disturbed within me?Hope in God!For I shall still praise him for the saving help of his presence.
B019C042V006	19	42	6	My God, my soul is in despair within me.Therefore I remember you from the land of the Jordan,the heights of Hermon, from the hill Mizar.
B019C042V007	19	42	7	Deep calls to deep at the noise of your waterfalls.All your waves and your billows have swept over me.
B019C042V008	19	42	8	
        
B019C042V009	19	42	9	I will ask God, my rock, "Why have you forgotten me?Why do I go mourning because of the oppression of the enemy?"
B019C042V010	19	42	10	As with a sword in my bones, my adversaries reproach me,while they continually ask me, "Where is your God?"
B019C042V011	19	42	11	Why are you in despair, my soul?Why are you disturbed within me?Hope in God! For I shall still praise him,the saving help of my countenance, and my God.
B019C043V001	19	43	1	Vindicate me, God, and plead my cause against an ungodly nation.Oh, deliver me from deceitful and wicked men.
B019C043V002	19	43	2	For you are the God of my strength. Why have you rejected me?Why do I go mourning because of the oppression of the enemy?
B019C043V003	19	43	3	Oh, send out your light and your truth.Let them lead me.Let them bring me to your holy hill,To your tents.
B019C043V004	19	43	4	Then I will go to the altar of God,to God, my exceeding joy.I will praise you on the harp, God, my God.
B019C043V005	19	43	5	Why are you in despair, my soul?Why are you disturbed within me?Hope in God!For I shall still praise him:my Savior, my helper, and my God.
B019C044V001	19	44	1	For the Chief Musician. By the sons of Korah. A contemplative psalm.   We have heard with our ears, God;our fathers have told us,what work you did in their days,in the days of old.
B019C044V002	19	44	2	You drove out the nations with your hand,but you planted them.You afflicted the peoples,but you spread them abroad.
B019C044V003	19	44	3	For they did not get the land in possession by their own sword,neither did their own arm save them;but your right hand, and your arm, and the light of your face,because you were favorable to them.
B019C044V004	19	44	4	You are my King, God.Command victories for Jacob!
B019C044V005	19	44	5	Through you, will we push down our adversaries.Through your name, will we tread them under who rise up against us.
B019C044V006	19	44	6	For I will not trust in my bow,neither shall my sword save me.
B019C044V007	19	44	7	But you have saved us from our adversaries,and have shamed those who hate us.
B019C044V008	19	44	8	In God we have made our boast all day long,we will give thanks to your name forever.Selah.
B019C044V009	19	44	9	But now you rejected us, and brought us to dishonor,and do not go out with our armies.
B019C044V010	19	44	10	You make us turn back from the adversary.Those who hate us take spoil for themselves.
B019C044V011	19	44	11	You have made us like sheep for food,and have scattered us among the nations.
B019C044V012	19	44	12	You sell your people for nothing,and have gained nothing from their sale.
B019C044V013	19	44	13	You make us a reproach to our neighbors,a scoffing and a derision to those who are around us.
B019C044V014	19	44	14	You make us a byword among the nations,a shaking of the head among the peoples.
B019C044V015	19	44	15	All day long my dishonor is before me,and shame covers my face,
B019C044V016	19	44	16	At the taunt of one who reproaches and verbally abuses,because of the enemy and the avenger.
B019C044V017	19	44	17	All this has come on us,yet have we not forgotten you,Neither have we been false to your covenant.
B019C044V018	19	44	18	Our heart has not turned back,neither have our steps strayed from your path,
B019C044V019	19	44	19	Though you have crushed us in the haunt of jackals,and covered us with the shadow of death.
B019C044V020	19	44	20	If we have forgotten the name of our God,or spread forth our hands to a strange god;
B019C044V021	19	44	21	won't God search this out?For he knows the secrets of the heart.
B019C044V022	19	44	22	Yes, for your sake we are killed all day long.We are regarded as sheep for the slaughter.
B019C044V023	19	44	23	Wake up!Why do you sleep, 
B019C044V024	19	44	24	Why do you hide your face,and forget our affliction and our oppression?
B019C044V025	19	44	25	For our soul is bowed down to the dust.Our body cleaves to the earth.
B019C044V026	19	44	26	Rise up to help us.Redeem us for your loving kindness' sake.
B019C045V001	19	45	1	For the Chief Musician. Set to "The Lilies." A contemplation by the sons of Korah. A wedding song.   My heart overflows with a noble theme.I recite my verses for the king.My tongue is like the pen of a skillful writer.
B019C045V002	19	45	2	You are the most excellent of the sons of men.Grace has anointed your lips,therefore God has blessed you forever.
B019C045V003	19	45	3	Gird your sword on your thigh, mighty one:your splendor and your majesty.
B019C045V004	19	45	4	In your majesty ride on victoriously on behalf of truth, humility, and righteousness.Let your right hand display awesome deeds.
B019C045V005	19	45	5	Your arrows are sharp.The nations fall under you, with arrows in the heart of the king's enemies.
B019C045V006	19	45	6	Your throne, God, is forever and ever.A scepter of equity is the scepter of your kingdom.
B019C045V007	19	45	7	You have loved righteousness, and hated wickedness.Therefore God, your God, has anointed you with the oil of gladness above your fellows.
B019C045V008	19	45	8	All your garments smell like myrrh, aloes, and cassia.Out of ivory palaces stringed instruments have made you glad.
B019C045V009	19	45	9	Kings' daughters are among your honorable women.At your right hand the queen stands in gold of Ophir.
B019C045V010	19	45	10	Listen, daughter, consider, and turn your ear.Forget your own people, and also your father's house.
B019C045V011	19	45	11	So the king will desire your beauty,honor him, for he is your lord.
B019C045V012	19	45	12	The daughter of Tyre comes with a gift.The rich among the people entreat your favor.
B019C045V013	19	45	13	The princess inside is all glorious.Her clothing is interwoven with gold.
B019C045V014	19	45	14	She shall be led to the king in embroidered work.The virgins, her companions who follow her, shall be brought to you.
B019C045V015	19	45	15	With gladness and rejoicing they shall be led.They shall enter into the king's palace.
B019C045V016	19	45	16	Your sons will take the place of your fathers.You shall make them princes in all the earth.
B019C045V017	19	45	17	I will make your name to be remembered in all generations.Therefore the peoples shall give you thanks forever and ever.
B019C046V001	19	46	1	For the Chief Musician. By the sons of Korah. According to Alamoth.  God is our refuge and strength,a very present help in trouble.
