B019C048V013	19	48	13	Consider her defenses.Consider her palaces,that you may tell it to the next generation.
B019C048V014	19	48	14	For this God is our God forever and ever.He will be our guide even to death.
B019C049V001	19	49	1	For the Chief Musician. A Psalm by the sons of Korah.   Hear this, all you peoples.Listen, all you inhabitants of the world,
B019C049V002	19	49	2	both low and high,rich and poor together.
B019C049V003	19	49	3	My mouth will speak words of wisdom.My heart shall utter understanding.
B019C049V004	19	49	4	I will incline my ear to a proverb.I will open my riddle on the harp.
B019C049V005	19	49	5	Why should I fear in the days of evil,when iniquity at my heels surrounds me?
B019C049V006	19	49	6	Those who trust in their wealth,and boast in the multitude of their riches-
B019C049V007	19	49	7	none of them can by any means redeem his brother,nor give God a ransom for him.
B019C049V008	19	49	8	For the redemption of their life is costly,no payment is ever enough,
B019C049V009	19	49	9	That he should live on forever,that he should not see corruption.
B019C049V010	19	49	10	For he sees that wise men die;likewise the fool and the senseless perish,and leave their wealth to others.
B019C049V011	19	49	11	Their inward thought is that their houses will endure forever,and their dwelling places to all generations.They name their lands after themselves.
B019C049V012	19	49	12	But man, despite his riches, doesn't endure.He is like the animals that perish.
B019C049V013	19	49	13	This is the destiny of those who are foolish,and of those who approve their sayings.Selah.
B019C049V014	19	49	14	They are appointed as a flock for Sheol.Death shall be their shepherd.The upright shall have dominion over them in the morning.Their beauty shall decay in Sheol,far from their mansion.
B019C049V015	19	49	15	But God will redeem my soul from the power of Sheol,for he will receive me.Selah.
B019C049V016	19	49	16	Do not be afraid when a man is made rich,when the glory of his house is increased.
B019C049V017	19	49	17	For when he dies he shall carry nothing away.His glory shall not descend after him.
B019C049V018	19	49	18	Though while he lived he blessed his soul-and men praise you when you do well for yourself-
B019C049V019	19	49	19	he shall go to the generation of his fathers.They shall never see the light.
B019C049V020	19	49	20	A man who has riches without understanding,is like the animals that perish.
B019C050V001	19	50	1	A Psalm by Asaph.   The Mighty One, God, 
B019C050V002	19	50	2	Out of Zion, the perfection of beauty,God shines forth.
B019C050V003	19	50	3	Our God comes, and does not keep silent.A fire devours before him.It is very stormy around him.
B019C050V004	19	50	4	He calls to the heavens above,to the earth, that he may judge his people:
B019C050V005	19	50	5	"Gather my holy ones together to me,those who have made a covenant with me by sacrifice."
B019C050V006	19	50	6	The heavens shall declare his righteousness,for God himself is judge.Selah.
B019C050V007	19	50	7	"Hear, my people, and I will speak;Israel, and I will testify against you.I am God, your God.
B019C050V008	19	50	8	I do not rebuke you for your sacrifices.Your burnt offerings are continually before me.
B019C050V009	19	50	9	I have no need for a bull from your stall,nor male goats from your pens.
B019C050V010	19	50	10	For every animal of the forest is mine,and the livestock on a thousand hills.
B019C050V011	19	50	11	I know all the birds of the mountains.The wild animals of the field are mine.
B019C050V012	19	50	12	If I were hungry, I would not tell you,for the world is mine, and all that is in it.
B019C050V013	19	50	13	Will I eat the flesh of bulls,or drink the blood of goats?
B019C050V014	19	50	14	Offer to God the sacrifice of thanksgiving.Pay your vows to the Most High.
B019C050V015	19	50	15	Call on me in the day of trouble.I will deliver you, and you will honor me."
B019C050V016	19	50	16	But to the wicked God says,"What right do you have to declare my statutes,that you have taken my covenant on your lips,
B019C050V017	19	50	17	seeing you hate instruction,and throw my words behind you?
B019C050V018	19	50	18	When you saw a thief, you consented with him,and have participated with adulterers.
B019C050V019	19	50	19	"You give your mouth to evil.Your tongue frames deceit.
B019C050V020	19	50	20	You sit and speak against your brother.You slander your own mother's son.
B019C050V021	19	50	21	You have done these things, and I kept silent.You thought that I was just like you.I will rebuke you, and accuse you in front of your eyes.
B019C050V022	19	50	22	"Now consider this, you who forget God,lest I tear you into pieces, and there be none to deliver.
B019C050V023	19	50	23	Whoever offers the sacrifice of thanksgiving glorifies me,and prepares his way so that I will show God's salvation to him."
B019C051V001	19	51	1	For the Chief Musician. A Psalm by David, when Nathan the prophet came to him, after he had gone in to Bathsheba.   Have mercy on me, God, according to your loving kindness.According to the multitude of your tender mercies, blot out my transgressions.
B019C051V002	19	51	2	Wash me thoroughly from my iniquity.Cleanse me from my sin.
B019C051V003	19	51	3	For I know my transgressions.My sin is constantly before me.
B019C051V004	19	51	4	Against you, and you only, have I sinned,and done that which is evil in your sight;that you may be proved right when you speak,and justified when you judge.
B019C051V005	19	51	5	Behold, I was brought forth in iniquity.In sin my mother conceived me.
B019C051V006	19	51	6	Behold, you desire truth in the inward parts.You teach me wisdom in the inmost place.
B019C051V007	19	51	7	Purify me with hyssop, and I will be clean.Wash me, and I will be whiter than snow.
B019C051V008	19	51	8	Let me hear joy and gladness,That the bones which you have broken may rejoice.
B019C051V009	19	51	9	Hide your face from my sins,and blot out all of my iniquities.
B019C051V010	19	51	10	Create in me a clean heart, O God.Renew a right spirit within me.
B019C051V011	19	51	11	Do not throw me from your presence,and do not take your holy Spirit from me.
B019C051V012	19	51	12	Restore to me the joy of your salvation.Uphold me with a willing spirit.
B019C051V013	19	51	13	Then I will teach transgressors your ways.Sinners shall be converted to you.
B019C051V014	19	51	14	Deliver me from bloodguiltiness, O God, the God of my salvation.My tongue shall sing aloud of your righteousness.
B019C051V015	19	51	15	Lord, open my lips.My mouth shall declare your praise.
B019C051V016	19	51	16	For you do not delight in sacrifice, or else I would give it.You have no pleasure in burnt offering.
B019C051V017	19	51	17	The sacrifices of God are a broken spirit.A broken and contrite heart, O God, you will not despise.
B019C051V018	19	51	18	Do well in your good pleasure to Zion.Build the walls of Jerusalem.
B019C051V019	19	51	19	Then you will delight in the sacrifices of righteousness,in burnt offerings and in whole burnt offerings.Then they will offer bulls on your altar.
B019C052V001	19	52	1	For the Chief Musician. A contemplation by David, when Doeg the Edomite came and told Saul, "David has come to Abimelech's house."   Why do you boast of mischief, mighty man?God's loving kindness endures continually.
B019C052V002	19	52	2	Your tongue plots destruction,like a sharp razor, working deceitfully.
B019C052V003	19	52	3	You love evil more than good,lying rather than speaking the truth.Selah.
B019C052V004	19	52	4	You love all devouring words,you deceitful tongue.
B019C052V005	19	52	5	God will likewise destroy you forever.He will take you up, and pluck you out of your tent,and root you out of the land of the living.Selah.
B019C052V006	19	52	6	The righteous also will see it, and fear,and laugh at him, saying,
B019C052V007	19	52	7	"Behold, this is the man who did not make God his strength,but trusted in the abundance of his riches,and strengthened himself in his wickedness."
B019C052V008	19	52	8	But as for me, I am like a green olive tree in God's house.I trust in God's loving kindness forever and ever.
B019C052V009	19	52	9	I will give you thanks forever, because you have done it.I will hope in your name, for it is good,in the presence of your holy ones.
B019C053V001	19	53	1	For the Chief Musician. To the tune of "Mahalath." A contemplation by David.   The fool has said in his heart, "There is no God."They are corrupt, and have done abominable iniquity.There is no one who does good.
B019C053V002	19	53	2	God looks down from heaven on the children of men,to see if there are any who understood,who seek after God.
B019C053V003	19	53	3	Every one of them has gone back.They have become filthy together.There is no one who does good, no, not one.
B019C053V004	19	53	4	Have the workers of iniquity no knowledge,who eat up my people as they eat bread,and do not call on God?
B019C053V005	19	53	5	There they were in great fear, where no fear was,for God has scattered the bones of him who encamps against you.You have put them to shame,because God has rejected them.
B019C053V006	19	53	6	Oh that the salvation of Israel would come out of Zion!When God brings back his people from captivity,then Jacob shall rejoice,and Israel shall be glad.
B019C054V001	19	54	1	For the Chief Musician. On stringed instruments. A contemplation by David, when the Ziphites came and said to Saul, "Isn't David hiding himself among us?"   Save me, God, by your name.Vindicate me in your might.
B019C054V002	19	54	2	Hear my prayer, God.Listen to the words of my mouth.
B019C054V003	19	54	3	For strangers have risen up against me.Violent men have sought after my soul.They haven't set God before them.Selah.
B019C054V004	19	54	4	Behold, God is my helper.The Lord is the one who sustains my soul.
B019C054V005	19	54	5	He will repay the evil to my enemies.Destroy them in your truth.
B019C054V006	19	54	6	With a free will offering, I will sacrifice to you.I will give thanks to your name, 
B019C054V007	19	54	7	For he has delivered me out of all trouble.My eye has seen triumph over my enemies.
B019C055V001	19	55	1	For the Chief Musician. On stringed instruments. A contemplation by David.   Listen to my prayer, God.Do not hide yourself from my supplication.
B019C055V002	19	55	2	Attend to me, and answer me.I am restless in my complaint, and moan,
B019C055V003	19	55	3	Because of the voice of the enemy,Because of the oppression of the wicked.For they bring suffering on me.In anger they hold a grudge against me.
B019C055V004	19	55	4	My heart is severely pained within me.The terrors of death have fallen on me.
B019C055V005	19	55	5	Fearfulness and trembling have come on me.Horror has overwhelmed me.
B019C055V006	19	55	6	I said, "Oh that I had wings like a dove!Then I would fly away, and be at rest.
B019C055V007	19	55	7	Behold, then I would wander far off.I would lodge in the wilderness."Selah.
B019C055V008	19	55	8	"I would hurry to a shelter from the stormy wind and storm."
B019C055V009	19	55	9	Confuse them, Lord, and confound their language,for I have seen violence and strife in the city.
B019C055V010	19	55	10	Day and night they prowl around on its walls.Malice and abuse are also within her.
B019C055V011	19	55	11	Destructive forces are within her.Threats and lies do not depart from her streets.
B019C055V012	19	55	12	For it was not an enemy who insulted me,then I could have endured it.Neither was it he who hated me who raised himself up against me,then I would have hid myself from him.
B019C055V013	19	55	13	But it was you, a man like me,my companion, and my familiar friend.
B019C055V014	19	55	14	We took sweet fellowship together.We walked in God's house with company.
B019C055V015	19	55	15	Let death come suddenly on them.Let them go down alive into Sheol.For wickedness is in their dwelling, in the midst of them.
B019C055V016	19	55	16	As for me, I will call on God.
B019C055V017	19	55	17	Evening, morning, and at noon, I will cry out in distress.He will hear my voice.
B019C055V018	19	55	18	He has redeemed my soul in peace from the battle that was against me,although there are many who oppose me.
B019C055V019	19	55	19	God, who is enthroned forever,will hear, and answer them.Selah.They never change,who do not fear God.
B019C055V020	19	55	20	He raises his hands against his friends.He has violated his covenant.
B019C055V021	19	55	21	His mouth was smooth as butter,but his heart was war.His words were softer than oil,yet they were drawn swords.
B019C055V022	19	55	22	Cast your burden on 
B019C055V023	19	55	23	But you, God, will bring them down into the pit of destruction.Bloodthirsty and deceitful men shall not live out half their days,but I will trust in you.
B019C056V001	19	56	1	For the Chief Musician. To the tune of "Silent Dove in Distant Lands." A poem by David, when the Philistines seized him in Gath.   Be merciful to me, God, for man wants to swallow me up.All day long, he attacks and oppresses me.
B019C056V002	19	56	2	My enemies want to swallow me up all day long,for they are many who fight proudly against me.
B019C056V003	19	56	3	When I am afraid,I will put my trust in you.
B019C056V004	19	56	4	In God, I praise his word.In God, I put my trust.I will not be afraid.What can flesh do to me?
B019C056V005	19	56	5	All day long they twist my words.All their thoughts are against me for evil.
B019C056V006	19	56	6	They conspire and lurk,watching my steps, they are eager to take my life.
B019C056V007	19	56	7	Shall they escape by iniquity?In anger cast down the peoples, God.
B019C056V008	19	56	8	You number my wanderings.You put my tears into your bottle.Aren't they in your book?
B019C056V009	19	56	9	Then my enemies shall turn back in the day that I call.I know this, that God is for me.
B019C056V010	19	56	10	In God, I will praise his word.In 
B019C056V011	19	56	11	I have put my trust in God.I will not be afraid.What can man do to me?
B019C056V012	19	56	12	Your vows are on me, God.I will give thank offerings to you.
B019C056V013	19	56	13	For you have delivered my soul from death,and prevented my feet from falling,that I may walk before God in the light of the living.
B019C057V001	19	57	1	For the Chief Musician. To the tune of "Do Not Destroy." A poem by David, when he fled from Saul, in the cave.   Be merciful to me, God, be merciful to me,for my soul takes refuge in you.Yes, in the shadow of your wings, I will take refuge,until disaster has passed.
B019C057V002	19	57	2	I cry out to God Most High,to God who accomplishes my requests for me.
B019C057V003	19	57	3	He will send from heaven, and save me,he rebukes the one who is pursuing me.Selah.God will send out his loving kindness and his truth.
B019C057V004	19	57	4	My soul is among lions.I lie among those who are set on fire,even the sons of men, whose teeth are spears and arrows,and their tongue a sharp sword.
B019C057V005	19	57	5	Be exalted, God, above the heavens!Let your glory be above all the earth!
B019C057V006	19	57	6	They have prepared a net for my steps.My soul is bowed down.They dig a pit before me.They fall into its midst themselves.Selah.
B019C057V007	19	57	7	My heart is steadfast, God, my heart is steadfast.I will sing, yes, I will sing praises.
B019C057V008	19	57	8	Wake up, my glory! Wake up, psaltery and harp!I will wake up the dawn.
B019C057V009	19	57	9	I will give thanks to you, Lord, among the peoples.I will sing praises to you among the nations.
B019C057V010	19	57	10	For your great loving kindness reaches to the heavens,and your truth to the skies.
B019C057V011	19	57	11	Be exalted, God, above the heavens.Let your glory be over all the earth.
B019C058V001	19	58	1	For the Chief Musician. To the tune of "Do Not Destroy." A poem by David.   Do you indeed speak righteousness, silent ones?Do you judge blamelessly, you sons of men?
B019C058V002	19	58	2	No, in your heart you plot injustice.You measure out the violence of your hands in the earth.
B019C058V003	19	58	3	The wicked go astray from the womb.They are wayward as soon as they are born, speaking lies.
B019C058V004	19	58	4	Their poison is like the poison of a snake;like a deaf cobra that stops its ear,
B019C058V005	19	58	5	which doesn't listen to the voice of charmers,no matter how skillful the charmer may be.
B019C058V006	19	58	6	Break their teeth, God, in their mouth.Break out the great teeth of the young lions, 
B019C058V007	19	58	7	Let them vanish as water that flows away.When they draw the bow, let their arrows be made blunt.
B019C058V008	19	58	8	Let them be like a snail which melts and passes away,like the stillborn child, who has not seen the sun.
B019C058V009	19	58	9	Before your pots can feel the heat of the thorns,he will sweep away the green and the burning alike.
B019C058V010	19	58	10	The righteous shall rejoice when he sees the vengeance.He shall wash his feet in the blood of the wicked;
B019C058V011	19	58	11	so that men shall say, "Most certainly there is a reward for the righteous.Most certainly there is a God who judges the earth."
B019C059V001	19	59	1	For the Chief Musician. To the tune of "Do Not Destroy." A poem by David, when Saul sent, and they watched the house to kill him.   Deliver me from my enemies, my God.Set me on high from those who rise up against me.
B019C059V002	19	59	2	Deliver me from the workers of iniquity.Save me from the bloodthirsty men.
B019C059V003	19	59	3	For, behold, they lie in wait for my soul.The mighty gather themselves together against me,not for my disobedience, nor for my sin, 
B019C059V004	19	59	4	I have done no wrong, yet they are ready to attack me.Rise up, behold, and help me!
B019C059V005	19	59	5	You, 
B019C059V006	19	59	6	They return at evening, howling like dogs,and prowl around the city.
B019C059V007	19	59	7	Behold, they spew with their mouth.Swords are in their lips,"For," they say, "who hears us?"
B019C059V008	19	59	8	But you, 
B019C059V009	19	59	9	Oh, my Strength, I watch for you,for God is my high tower.
B019C059V010	19	59	10	My God will go before me with his loving kindness.God will let me look at my enemies in triumph.
B019C059V011	19	59	11	Do not kill them, or my people may forget.Scatter them by your power, and bring them down, Lord our shield.
B019C059V012	19	59	12	For the sin of their mouth, and the words of their lips,let them be caught in their pride,for the curses and lies which they utter.
B019C059V013	19	59	13	Consume them in wrath.Consume them, and they will be no more.Let them know that God rules in Jacob,to the ends of the earth.Selah.
B019C059V014	19	59	14	At evening let them return.Let them howl like a dog, and go around the city.
B019C059V015	19	59	15	They shall wander up and down for food,and wait all night if they aren't satisfied.
B019C059V016	19	59	16	But I will sing of your strength.Yes, I will sing aloud of your loving kindness in the morning.For you have been my high tower,a refuge in the day of my distress.
B019C059V017	19	59	17	To you, my strength, I will sing praises.For God is my high tower, the God of my mercy.
B019C060V001	19	60	1	For the Chief Musician. To the tune of "The Lily of the Covenant." A teaching poem by David, when he fought with Aram Naharaim and with Aram Zobah, and Joab returned, and killed twelve thousand of Edom in the Valley of Salt.   God, you have rejected us.You have broken us down.You have been angry.Restore us, again.
B019C060V002	19	60	2	You have made the land tremble.You have torn it.Mend its fractures,for it quakes.
B019C060V003	19	60	3	You have shown your people hard things.You have made us drink the wine that makes us stagger.
B019C060V004	19	60	4	You have given a banner to those who fear you,that it may be displayed because of the truth.Selah.
B019C060V005	19	60	5	So that your beloved may be delivered,save with your right hand, and answer us.
B019C060V006	19	60	6	God has spoken from his sanctuary:"I will triumph.I will divide Shechem,and measure out the valley of Succoth.
B019C060V007	19	60	7	Gilead is mine, and Manasseh is mine.Ephraim also is the defense of my head.Judah is my scepter.
B019C060V008	19	60	8	Moab is my wash basin.I will throw my shoe on Edom.I shout in triumph over Philistia."
B019C060V009	19	60	9	Who will bring me into the strong city?Who has led me to Edom?
B019C060V010	19	60	10	Haven't you, God, rejected us?You do not go out with our armies, God.
B019C060V011	19	60	11	Give us help against the adversary,for the help of man is vain.
B019C060V012	19	60	12	Through God we shall do valiantly,for it is he who will tread down our adversaries.
B019C061V001	19	61	1	For the Chief Musician. For a stringed instrument. By David.   Hear my cry, God.Listen to my prayer.
B019C061V002	19	61	2	From the end of the earth, I will call to you, when my heart is overwhelmed.Lead me to the rock that is higher than I.
B019C061V003	19	61	3	For you have been a refuge for me,a strong tower from the enemy.
B019C061V004	19	61	4	I will dwell in your tent forever.I will take refuge in the shelter of your wings.Selah.
B019C061V005	19	61	5	For you, God, have heard my vows.You have given me the heritage of those who fear your name.
B019C061V006	19	61	6	You will prolong the king's life;his years shall be for generations.
B019C061V007	19	61	7	He shall be enthroned in God's presence forever.Appoint your loving kindness and truth, that they may preserve him.
B019C061V008	19	61	8	So I will sing praise to your name forever,that I may fulfill my vows daily.
B019C062V001	19	62	1	For the Chief Musician. To Jeduthan. A Psalm by David.   My soul rests in God alone.My salvation is from him.
B019C062V002	19	62	2	He alone is my rock and my salvation, my fortress-I will never be greatly shaken.
B019C062V003	19	62	3	How long will you assault a man,would all of you throw him down,Like a leaning wall, like a tottering fence?
B019C062V004	19	62	4	They fully intend to throw him down from his lofty place.They delight in lies.They bless with their mouth, but they curse inwardly.Selah.
B019C062V005	19	62	5	My soul, wait in silence for God alone,for my expectation is from him.
B019C062V006	19	62	6	He alone is my rock and my salvation, my fortress.I will not be shaken.
B019C062V007	19	62	7	With God is my salvation and my honor.The rock of my strength, and my refuge, is in God.
B019C062V008	19	62	8	Trust in him at all times, O people.Pour out your heart before him.God is a refuge for us.Selah.
B019C062V009	19	62	9	Surely men of low degree are just a breath,and men of high degree are a lie.In the balances they will go up.They are together lighter than a breath.
B019C062V010	19	62	10	Do not trust in oppression.Do not become vain in robbery.If riches increase,do not set your heart on them.
B019C062V011	19	62	11	God has spoken once;twice I have heard this,that power belongs to God.
B019C062V012	19	62	12	Also to you, Lord, belongs loving kindness,for you reward every man according to his work.
B019C063V001	19	63	1	A Psalm by David, when he was in the desert of Judah.   God, you are my God.I will earnestly seek you.My soul thirsts for you.My flesh longs for you,in a dry and weary land, where there is no water.
B019C063V002	19	63	2	So I have seen you in the sanctuary,watching your power and your glory.
B019C063V003	19	63	3	Because your loving kindness is better than life,my lips shall praise you.
B019C063V004	19	63	4	So I will bless you while I live.I will lift up my hands in your name.
B019C063V005	19	63	5	My soul shall be satisfied as with the richest food.My mouth shall praise you with joyful lips,
B019C063V006	19	63	6	when I remember you on my bed,and think about you in the night watches.
B019C063V007	19	63	7	For you have been my help.I will rejoice in the shadow of your wings.
B019C063V008	19	63	8	My soul stays close to you.Your right hand holds me up.
B019C063V009	19	63	9	But those who seek my soul, to destroy it,shall go into the lower parts of the earth.
B019C063V010	19	63	10	They shall be given over to the power of the sword.They shall be jackal food.
B019C063V011	19	63	11	But the king shall rejoice in God.Everyone who swears by him will praise him,for the mouth of those who speak lies shall be silenced.
B019C064V001	19	64	1	For the Chief Musician. A Psalm by David.   Hear my voice, God, in my complaint.Preserve my life from fear of the enemy.
B019C064V002	19	64	2	Hide me from the conspiracy of the wicked,from the noisy crowd of the ones doing evil;
B019C064V003	19	64	3	who sharpen their tongue like a sword,and aim their arrows, deadly words,
B019C064V004	19	64	4	to shoot innocent men from ambushes.They shoot at him suddenly and fearlessly.
B019C064V005	19	64	5	They encourage themselves in evil plans.They talk about laying snares secretly.They say, "Who will see them?"
B019C064V006	19	64	6	They plot injustice, saying, "We have made a perfect plan!"Surely man's mind and heart are cunning.
B019C064V007	19	64	7	But God will shoot at them.They will be suddenly struck down with an arrow.
B019C064V008	19	64	8	Their own tongues shall ruin them.All who see them will shake their heads.
B019C064V009	19	64	9	All mankind shall be afraid.They shall declare the work of God,and shall wisely ponder what he has done.
B019C064V010	19	64	10	The righteous shall be glad in 
B019C065V001	19	65	1	For the Chief Musician. A Psalm by David. A song.   Praise waits for you, God, in Zion.To you shall vows be performed.
B019C065V002	19	65	2	You who hear prayer,to you all men will come.
B019C065V003	19	65	3	Sins overwhelmed me,but you atoned for our transgressions.
B019C065V004	19	65	4	Blessed is one whom you choose, and cause to come near,that he may live in your courts.We will be filled with the goodness of your house,your holy temple.
B019C065V005	19	65	5	By awesome deeds of righteousness, you answer us,God of our salvation.You who are the hope of all the ends of the earth,of those who are far away on the sea;
B019C065V006	19	65	6	Who by his power forms the mountains,having armed yourself with strength;
B019C065V007	19	65	7	who stills the roaring of the seas,the roaring of their waves,and the turmoil of the nations.
B019C065V008	19	65	8	They also who dwell in faraway places are afraid at your wonders.You call the morning's dawn and the evening with songs of joy.
B019C065V009	19	65	9	You visit the earth, and water it.You greatly enrich it.The river of God is full of water.You provide them grain, for so you have ordained it.
B019C065V010	19	65	10	You drench its furrows.You level its ridges.You soften it with showers.You bless it with a crop.
B019C065V011	19	65	11	You crown the year with your bounty.Your carts overflow with abundance.
B019C065V012	19	65	12	The wilderness grasslands overflow.The hills are clothed with gladness.
B019C065V013	19	65	13	The pastures are covered with flocks.The valleys also are clothed with grain.They shout for joy!They also sing.
B019C066V001	19	66	1	For the Chief Musician. A song. A Psalm.   Make a joyful shout to God, all the earth!
B019C066V002	19	66	2	Sing to the glory of his name!Offer glory and praise!
B019C066V003	19	66	3	Tell God, "How awesome are your deeds!Through the greatness of your power, your enemies submit themselves to you.
B019C066V004	19	66	4	All the earth will worship you,and will sing to you;they will sing to your name."Selah.
B019C066V005	19	66	5	Come, and see God's deeds-awesome work on behalf of the children of men.
B019C066V006	19	66	6	He turned the sea into dry land.They went through the river on foot.There, we rejoiced in him.
B019C066V007	19	66	7	He rules by his might forever.His eyes watch the nations.Do not let the rebellious rise up against him.Selah.
B019C066V008	19	66	8	Praise our God, you peoples!Make the sound of his praise heard,
B019C066V009	19	66	9	who preserves our life among the living,and doesn't allow our feet to be moved.
B019C066V010	19	66	10	For you, God, have tested us.You have refined us, as silver is refined.
B019C066V011	19	66	11	You brought us into prison.You laid a burden on our backs.
B019C066V012	19	66	12	You allowed men to ride over our heads.We went through fire and through water,but you brought us to the place of abundance.
B019C066V013	19	66	13	I will come into your temple with burnt offerings.I will pay my vows to you,
B019C066V014	19	66	14	which my lips promised,and my mouth spoke, when I was in distress.
B019C066V015	19	66	15	I will offer to you burnt offerings of fat animals,with the offering of rams,I will offer bulls with goats.Selah.
B019C066V016	19	66	16	Come, and hear, all you who fear God.I will declare what he has done for my soul.
B019C066V017	19	66	17	I cried to him with my mouth.He was extolled with my tongue.
B019C066V018	19	66	18	If I cherished sin in my heart,the Lord wouldn't have listened.
B019C066V019	19	66	19	But most certainly, God has listened.He has heard the voice of my prayer.
B019C066V020	19	66	20	Blessed be God, who has not turned away my prayer,nor his loving kindness from me.
B019C067V001	19	67	1	For the Chief Musician. With stringed instruments. A Psalm. A song.   May God be merciful to us, bless us,and cause his face to shine on us.Selah.
B019C067V002	19	67	2	That your way may be known on earth,and your salvation among all nations,
B019C067V003	19	67	3	let the peoples praise you, God.Let all the peoples praise you.
B019C067V004	19	67	4	Oh let the nations be glad and sing for joy,for you will judge the peoples with equity,and govern the nations on earth.Selah.
B019C067V005	19	67	5	Let the peoples praise you, God.Let all the peoples praise you.
B019C067V006	19	67	6	The earth has yielded its increase.God, even our own God, will bless us.
B019C067V007	19	67	7	God will bless us.All the ends of the earth shall fear him.
B019C068V001	19	68	1	For the Chief Musician. A Psalm by David. A song.   Let God arise!Let his enemies be scattered!Let them who hate him also flee before him.
B019C068V002	19	68	2	As smoke is driven away,so drive them away.As wax melts before the fire,so let the wicked perish at the presence of God.
B019C068V003	19	68	3	But let the righteous be glad.Let them rejoice before God.Yes, let them rejoice with gladness.
B019C068V004	19	68	4	Sing to God! Sing praises to his name!Extol him who rides on the clouds:to Yah, his name!Rejoice before him!
B019C068V005	19	68	5	A father of the fatherless, and a defender of the widows,is God in his holy habitation.
B019C068V006	19	68	6	God sets the lonely in families.He brings out the prisoners with singing,but the rebellious dwell in a sun-scorched land.
B019C068V007	19	68	7	God, when you went forth before your people,when you marched through the wilderness...Selah.
B019C068V008	19	68	8	The earth trembled.The sky also poured down rain at the presence of the God of Sinai-at the presence of God, the God of Israel.
B019C068V009	19	68	9	You, God, sent a plentiful rain.You confirmed your inheritance, when it was weary.
B019C068V010	19	68	10	Your congregation lived therein.You, God, prepared your goodness for the poor.
B019C068V011	19	68	11	The Lord announced the word.The ones who proclaim it are a great company.
B019C068V012	19	68	12	"Kings of armies flee! They flee!"She who waits at home divides the spoil,
B019C068V013	19	68	13	while you sleep among the campfires,the wings of a dove sheathed with silver,her feathers with shining gold.
B019C068V014	19	68	14	When the Almighty scattered kings in her,it snowed on Zalmon.
B019C068V015	19	68	15	The mountains of Bashan are majestic mountains.The mountains of Bashan are rugged.
B019C068V016	19	68	16	Why do you look in envy, you rugged mountains,at the mountain where God chooses to reign?Yes, 
B019C068V017	19	68	17	The chariots of God are tens of thousands and thousands of thousands.The Lord is among them, from Sinai, into the sanctuary.
B019C068V018	19	68	18	You have ascended on high.You have led away captives.You have received gifts among men,yes, among the rebellious also, that Yah, God, might dwell there.
B019C068V019	19	68	19	Blessed be the Lord, who daily bears our burdens,even the God who is our salvation.Selah.
B019C068V020	19	68	20	God is to us a God of deliverance.To 
B019C068V021	19	68	21	But God will strike through the head of his enemies,the hairy scalp of such a one as still continues in his guiltiness.
B019C068V022	19	68	22	The Lord said, "I will bring you again from Bashan,I will bring you again from the depths of the sea;
B019C068V023	19	68	23	That you may crush them, dipping your foot in blood,that the tongues of your dogs may have their portion from your enemies."
B019C068V024	19	68	24	They have seen your processions, God,even the processions of my God, my King, into the sanctuary.
B019C068V025	19	68	25	The singers went before, the minstrels followed after,in the midst of the ladies playing with tambourines,
B019C068V026	19	68	26	"Bless God in the congregations,even the Lord in the assembly of Israel!"
B019C068V027	19	68	27	There is little Benjamin, their ruler,the princes of Judah, their council,the princes of Zebulun, and the princes of Naphtali.
B019C068V028	19	68	28	Your God has commanded your strength.Strengthen, God, that which you have done for us.
B019C068V029	19	68	29	Because of your temple at Jerusalem,kings shall bring presents to you.
B019C068V030	19	68	30	Rebuke the wild animal of the reeds,the multitude of the bulls, with the calves of the peoples.Being humbled, may it bring bars of silver.Scatter the nations that delight in war.
B019C068V031	19	68	31	Princes shall come out of Egypt.Ethiopia shall hurry to stretch out her hands to God.
B019C068V032	19	68	32	Sing to God, you kingdoms of the earth!Sing praises to the Lord!Selah.
B019C068V033	19	68	33	To him who rides on the heaven of heavens, which are of old;behold, he utters his voice, a mighty voice.
B019C068V034	19	68	34	Ascribe strength to God!His excellency is over Israel,his strength is in the skies.
B019C068V035	19	68	35	You are awesome, God, in your sanctuaries.The God of Israel gives strength and power to his people.Praise be to God!
B019C069V001	19	69	1	For the Chief Musician. To the tune of "Lilies." By David.   Save me, God,for the waters have come up to my neck!
B019C069V002	19	69	2	I sink in deep mire, where there is no foothold.I have come into deep waters, where the floods overflow me.
B019C069V003	19	69	3	I am weary with my crying.My throat is dry.My eyes fail, looking for my God.
B019C069V004	19	69	4	Those who hate me without a cause are more than the hairs of my head.Those who want to cut me off, being my enemies wrongfully, are mighty.I have to restore what I did not take away.
B019C069V005	19	69	5	God, you know my foolishness.My sins aren't hidden from you.
B019C069V006	19	69	6	Do not let those who wait for you be shamed through me, Lord 
B019C069V007	19	69	7	Because for your sake, I have borne reproach.Shame has covered my face.
B019C069V008	19	69	8	I have become a stranger to my brothers,a foreigner to my mother's children.
B019C069V009	19	69	9	For the zeal of your house consumes me.The reproaches of those who reproach you have fallen on me.
B019C069V010	19	69	10	When I wept and I fasted,that was to my reproach.
B019C069V011	19	69	11	When I made sackcloth my clothing,I became a byword to them.
B019C069V012	19	69	12	Those who sit in the gate talk about me.I am the song of the drunkards.
B019C069V013	19	69	13	But as for me, my prayer is to you, 
B019C069V014	19	69	14	Deliver me out of the mire, and do not let me sink.Let me be delivered from those who hate me, and out of the deep waters.
B019C069V015	19	69	15	Do not let the flood waters overwhelm me,neither let the deep swallow me up.Do not let the pit shut its mouth on me.
B019C069V016	19	69	16	Answer me, 
B019C069V017	19	69	17	Do not hide your face from your servant,for I am in distress.Answer me speedily!
B019C069V018	19	69	18	Draw near to my soul, and redeem it.Ransom me because of my enemies.
B019C069V019	19	69	19	You know my reproach, my shame, and my dishonor.My adversaries are all before you.
B019C069V020	19	69	20	Reproach has broken my heart, and I am full of heaviness.I looked for some to take pity, but there was none;for comforters, but I found none.
B019C069V021	19	69	21	They also gave me gall for my food.In my thirst, they gave me vinegar to drink.
B019C069V022	19	69	22	Let their table before them become a snare.May it become a retribution and a trap.
B019C069V023	19	69	23	Let their eyes be darkened, so that they can't see.Let their backs be continually bent.
B019C069V024	19	69	24	Pour out your indignation on them.Let the fierceness of your anger overtake them.
B019C069V025	19	69	25	Let their habitation be desolate.Let no one dwell in their tents.
B019C069V026	19	69	26	For they persecute him whom you have wounded.They tell of the sorrow of those whom you have hurt.
B019C069V027	19	69	27	Charge them with crime upon crime.Do not let them come into your righteousness.
B019C069V028	19	69	28	Let them be blotted out of the book of life,and not be written with the righteous.
B019C069V029	19	69	29	But I am in pain and distress.Let your salvation, God, protect me.
B019C069V030	19	69	30	I will praise the name of God with a song,and will magnify him with thanksgiving.
B019C069V031	19	69	31	It will please 
B019C069V032	19	69	32	The humble have seen it, and are glad.You who seek after God, let your heart live.
B019C069V033	19	69	33	For 
B019C069V034	19	69	34	Let heaven and earth praise him;the seas, and everything that moves therein!
B019C069V035	19	69	35	For God will save Zion, and build the cities of Judah.They shall settle there, and own it.
B019C069V036	19	69	36	The children also of his servants shall inherit it.Those who love his name shall dwell therein.
B019C070V001	19	70	1	For the Chief Musician. By David. A reminder.   Hurry, God, to deliver me.Come quickly to help me, 
B019C070V002	19	70	2	Let them be disappointed and confounded who seek my soul.Let those who desire my ruin be turned back in disgrace.
B019C070V003	19	70	3	Let them be turned because of their shameWho say, "Aha! Aha!"
B019C070V004	19	70	4	Let all those who seek you rejoice and be glad in you.Let those who love your salvation continually say,"Let God be exalted!"
B019C070V005	19	70	5	But I am poor and needy.Come to me quickly, God.You are my help and my deliverer.
B019C071V001	19	71	1	In you, 
B019C071V002	19	71	2	Deliver me in your righteousness, and rescue me.Turn your ear to me, and save me.
B019C071V003	19	71	3	Be to me a rock of refuge to which I may always go.Give the command to save me,for you are my rock and my fortress.
B019C071V004	19	71	4	Rescue me, my God, from the hand of the wicked,from the hand of the unrighteous and cruel man.
B019C071V005	19	71	5	For you are my hope, Lord 
B019C071V006	19	71	6	I have relied on you from the womb.You are he who took me out of my mother's womb.I will always praise you.
B019C071V007	19	71	7	I am a marvel to many,but you are my strong refuge.
B019C071V008	19	71	8	My mouth shall be filled with your praise,with your honor all the day.
B019C071V009	19	71	9	Do not reject me in my old age.Do not forsake me when my strength fails.
B019C071V010	19	71	10	For my enemies talk about me.Those who watch for my soul conspire together,
B019C071V011	19	71	11	saying, "God has forsaken him.Pursue and take him, for no one will rescue him."
B019C071V012	19	71	12	God, do not be far from me.My God, hurry to help me.
B019C071V013	19	71	13	Let my accusers be disappointed and consumed.Let them be covered with disgrace and scorn who want to harm me.
B019C071V014	19	71	14	But I will always hope,and will add to all of your praise.
B019C071V015	19	71	15	My mouth will tell about your righteousness,and of your salvation all day,though I do not know its full measure.
B019C071V016	19	71	16	I will come with the mighty acts of the Lord 
B019C071V017	19	71	17	God, you have taught me from my youth.Until now, I have declared your wondrous works.
B019C071V018	19	71	18	Yes, even when I am old and gray-haired, God, do not forsake me,until I have declared your strength to the next generation,your might to everyone who is to come.
B019C071V019	19	71	19	Your righteousness also, God, reaches to the heavens;you have done great things.God, who is like you?
B019C071V020	19	71	20	You, who have shown us many and bitter troubles,you will let me live.You will bring us up again from the depths of the earth.
B019C071V021	19	71	21	Increase my honor,and comfort me again.
B019C071V022	19	71	22	I will also praise you with the harp for your faithfulness, my God.I sing praises to you with the lyre, Holy One of Israel.
B019C071V023	19	71	23	My lips shall shout for joy!My soul, which you have redeemed, sings praises to you!
B019C071V024	19	71	24	My tongue will also talk about your righteousness all day long,for they are disappointed, and they are confounded,who want to harm me.
B019C072V001	19	72	1	By Solomon.   God, give the king your justice;your righteousness to the royal son.
B019C072V002	19	72	2	He will judge your people with righteousness,and your poor with justice.
B019C072V003	19	72	3	The mountains shall bring prosperity to the people.The hills bring the fruit of righteousness.
B019C072V004	19	72	4	He will judge the poor of the people.He will save the children of the needy,and will break the oppressor in pieces.
B019C072V005	19	72	5	They shall fear you while the sun endures;and as long as the moon, throughout all generations.
B019C072V006	19	72	6	He will come down like rain on the mown grass,as showers that water the earth.
B019C072V007	19	72	7	In his days, the righteous shall flourish,and abundance of peace, until the moon is no more.
B019C072V008	19	72	8	He shall have dominion also from sea to sea,from the River to the ends of the earth.
B019C072V009	19	72	9	Those who dwell in the wilderness shall bow before him.His enemies shall lick the dust.
B019C072V010	19	72	10	The kings of Tarshish and of the islands will bring tribute.The kings of Sheba and Seba shall offer gifts.
B019C072V011	19	72	11	Yes, all kings shall fall down before him.All nations shall serve him.
B019C072V012	19	72	12	For he will deliver the needy when he cries;the poor, who has no helper.
B019C072V013	19	72	13	He will have pity on the poor and needy.He will save the souls of the needy.
B019C072V014	19	72	14	He will redeem their soul from oppression and violence.Their blood will be precious in his sight.
B019C072V015	19	72	15	They shall live, and to him shall be given of the gold of Sheba.Men shall pray for him continually.They shall bless him all day long.
B019C072V016	19	72	16	There shall be abundance of grain throughout the land.Its fruit sways like Lebanon.Let it flourish, thriving like the grass of the field.
B019C072V017	19	72	17	His name endures forever.His name continues as long as the sun.Men shall be blessed by him.All nations will call him blessed.
B019C072V018	19	72	18	Praise be to 
B019C072V019	19	72	19	Blessed be his glorious name forever!Let the whole earth be filled with his glory!Amen and amen.
B019C072V020	19	72	20	This ends the prayers by David, the son of Jesse.  BOOK III
B019C073V001	19	73	1	A Psalm by Asaph.   Surely God is good to Israel,to those who are pure in heart.
B019C073V002	19	73	2	But as for me, my feet were almost gone.My steps had nearly slipped.
B019C073V003	19	73	3	For I was envious of the arrogant,when I saw the prosperity of the wicked.
B019C073V004	19	73	4	For there are no struggles in their death,but their strength is firm.
B019C073V005	19	73	5	They are free from burdens of men,neither are they plagued like other men.
B019C073V006	19	73	6	Therefore pride is like a chain around their neck.Violence covers them like a garment.
B019C073V007	19	73	7	Their eyes bulge with fat.Their minds pass the limits of conceit.
B019C073V008	19	73	8	They scoff and speak with malice.In arrogance, they threaten oppression.
B019C073V009	19	73	9	They have set their mouth in the heavens.Their tongue walks through the earth.
B019C073V010	19	73	10	Therefore their people return to them,and they drink up waters of abundance.
B019C073V011	19	73	11	They say, "How does God know?Is there knowledge in the Most High?"
B019C073V012	19	73	12	Behold, these are the wicked.Being always at ease, they increase in riches.
B019C073V013	19	73	13	Surely in vain I have cleansed my heart,and washed my hands in innocence,
B019C073V014	19	73	14	For all day long have I been plagued,and punished every morning.
B019C073V015	19	73	15	If I had said, "I will speak thus;"behold, I would have betrayed the generation of your children.
B019C073V016	19	73	16	When I tried to understand this,it was too painful for me;
B019C073V017	19	73	17	Until I entered God's sanctuary,and considered their latter end.
B019C073V018	19	73	18	Surely you set them in slippery places.You throw them down to destruction.
B019C073V019	19	73	19	How they are suddenly destroyed!They are completely swept away with terrors.
B019C073V020	19	73	20	As a dream when one wakes up,so, Lord, when you awake, you will despise their fantasies.
B019C073V021	19	73	21	For my soul was grieved.I was embittered in my heart.
B019C073V022	19	73	22	I was so senseless and ignorant.I was a brute beast before you.
B019C073V023	19	73	23	Nevertheless, I am continually with you.You have held my right hand.
B019C073V024	19	73	24	You will guide me with your counsel,and afterward receive me to glory.
B019C073V025	19	73	25	Who do I have in heaven?There is no one on earth who I desire besides you.
B019C073V026	19	73	26	My flesh and my heart fails,but God is the strength of my heart and my portion forever.
B019C073V027	19	73	27	For, behold, those who are far from you shall perish.You have destroyed all those who are unfaithful to you.
B019C073V028	19	73	28	But it is good for me to come close to God.I have made the Lord 
B019C074V001	19	74	1	A contemplation by Asaph.   God, why have you rejected us forever?Why does your anger smolder against the sheep of your pasture?
B019C074V002	19	74	2	Remember your congregation, which you purchased of old,which you have redeemed to be the tribe of your inheritance;Mount Zion, in which you have lived.
B019C074V003	19	74	3	Lift up your feet to the perpetual ruins,all the evil that the enemy has done in the sanctuary.
B019C074V004	19	74	4	Your adversaries have roared in the midst of your assembly.They have set up their standards as signs.
B019C074V005	19	74	5	They behaved like men wielding axes,cutting through a thicket of trees.
B019C074V006	19	74	6	Now they break all its carved work down with hatchet and hammers.
B019C074V007	19	74	7	They have burned your sanctuary to the ground.They have profaned the dwelling place of your Name.
B019C074V008	19	74	8	They said in their heart, "We will crush them completely."They have burned up all the places in the land where God was worshiped.
B019C074V009	19	74	9	We see no miraculous signs.There is no longer any prophet,neither is there among us anyone who knows how long.
B019C074V010	19	74	10	How long, God, shall the adversary reproach?Shall the enemy blaspheme your name forever?
B019C074V011	19	74	11	Why do you draw back your hand, even your right hand?Take it out of your pocket and consume them!
B019C074V012	19	74	12	Yet God is my King of old,working salvation in the midst of the earth.
B019C074V013	19	74	13	You divided the sea by your strength.You broke the heads of the sea monsters in the waters.
B019C074V014	19	74	14	You broke the heads of Leviathan in pieces.You gave him as food to people and desert creatures.
B019C074V015	19	74	15	You opened up spring and stream.You dried up mighty rivers.
B019C074V016	19	74	16	The day is yours, the night is also yours.You have prepared the light and the sun.
B019C074V017	19	74	17	You have set all the boundaries of the earth.You have made summer and winter.
B019C074V018	19	74	18	Remember this, that the enemy has mocked you, 
B019C074V019	19	74	19	Do not deliver the soul of your dove to wild beasts.Do not forget the life of your poor forever.
B019C074V020	19	74	20	Honor your covenant,for haunts of violence fill the dark places of the earth.
B019C074V021	19	74	21	Do not let the oppressed return ashamed.Let the poor and needy praise your name.
B019C074V022	19	74	22	Arise, God! Plead your own cause.Remember how the foolish man mocks you all day.
B019C074V023	19	74	23	Do not forget the voice of your adversaries.The tumult of those who rise up against you ascends continually.
B019C075V001	19	75	1	For the Chief Musician. To the tune of "Do Not Destroy." A Psalm by Asaph. A song.   We give thanks to you, God.We give thanks, for your Name is near.Men tell about your wondrous works.
B019C075V002	19	75	2	When I choose the appointed time,I will judge blamelessly.
B019C075V003	19	75	3	The earth and all its inhabitants quake.I firmly hold its pillars.Selah.
B019C075V004	19	75	4	I said to the arrogant, "Do not boast!"I said to the wicked, "Do not lift up the horn.
B019C075V005	19	75	5	Do not lift up your horn on high.Do not speak with a stiff neck."
B019C075V006	19	75	6	For neither from the east, nor from the west,nor yet from the south, comes exaltation.
B019C075V007	19	75	7	But God is the judge.He puts down one, and lifts up another.
B019C075V008	19	75	8	For in the hand of 
