B019C076V001	19	76	1	For the Chief Musician. On stringed instruments. A Psalm by Asaph. A song.   In Judah, God is known.His name is great in Israel.
B019C076V002	19	76	2	His tabernacle is also in Salem;His dwelling place in Zion.
B019C076V003	19	76	3	There he broke the flaming arrows of the bow,the shield, and the sword, and the weapons of war.Selah.
B019C076V004	19	76	4	Glorious are you, and excellent,more than mountains of game.
B019C076V005	19	76	5	Valiant men lie plundered,they have slept their last sleep.None of the men of war can lift their hands.
B019C076V006	19	76	6	At your rebuke, God of Jacob,both chariot and horse are cast into a deep sleep.
B019C076V007	19	76	7	You, even you, are to be feared.Who can stand in your sight when you are angry?
