B019C077V001	19	77	1	For the Chief Musician. To Jeduthun. A Psalm by Asaph.   My cry goes to God!Indeed, I cry to God for help,and for him to listen to me.
B019C077V002	19	77	2	In the day of my trouble I sought the Lord.My hand was stretched out in the night, and did not get tired.My soul refused to be comforted.
B019C077V003	19	77	3	I remember God, and I groan.I complain, and my spirit is overwhelmed.Selah.
B019C077V004	19	77	4	You hold my eyelids open.I am so troubled that I can't speak.
B019C077V005	19	77	5	I have considered the days of old,the years of ancient times.
B019C077V006	19	77	6	I remember my song in the night.I consider in my own heart;my spirit diligently inquires:
B019C077V007	19	77	7	"Will the Lord reject us forever?Will he be favorable no more?
B019C077V008	19	77	8	Has his loving kindness vanished forever?Does his promise fail for generations?
B019C077V009	19	77	9	Has God forgotten to be gracious?Has he, in anger, withheld his compassion?"Selah.
B019C077V010	19	77	10	Then I thought, "I will appeal to this:the years of the right hand of the Most High."
B019C077V011	19	77	11	I will remember Yah's deeds;for I will remember your wonders of old.
B019C077V012	19	77	12	I will also meditate on all your work,and consider your doings.
B019C077V013	19	77	13	Your way, God, is in the sanctuary.What god is great like God?
B019C077V014	19	77	14	You are the God who does wonders.You have made your strength known among the peoples.
B019C077V015	19	77	15	You have redeemed your people with your arm,the sons of Jacob and Joseph.Selah.
B019C077V016	19	77	16	The waters saw you, God.The waters saw you, and they writhed.The depths also convulsed.
B019C077V017	19	77	17	The clouds poured out water.The skies resounded with thunder.Your arrows also flashed around.
B019C077V018	19	77	18	The voice of your thunder was in the whirlwind.The lightnings lit up the world.The earth trembled and shook.
B019C077V019	19	77	19	Your way was through the sea;your paths through the great waters.Your footsteps were not known.
B019C077V020	19	77	20	You led your people like a flock,by the hand of Moses and Aaron.
B019C078V001	19	78	1	A contemplation by Asaph.   Hear my teaching, my people.Turn your ears to the words of my mouth.
B019C078V002	19	78	2	I will open my mouth in a parable.I will utter dark sayings of old,
B019C078V003	19	78	3	which we have heard and known,and our fathers have told us.
B019C078V004	19	78	4	We will not hide them from their children,telling to the generation to come the praises of 
B019C078V005	19	78	5	For he established a testimony in Jacob,and appointed a teaching in Israel,which he commanded our fathers,that they should make them known to their children;
B019C078V006	19	78	6	that the generation to come might know, even the children who should be born;who should arise and tell their children,
B019C078V007	19	78	7	that they might set their hope in God,and not forget the works of God,but keep his commandments,
B019C078V008	19	78	8	and might not be as their fathers,a stubborn and rebellious generation,a generation that did not make their hearts loyal,whose spirit was not steadfast with God.
B019C078V009	19	78	9	The children of Ephraim, being armed and carrying bows,turned back in the day of battle.
B019C078V010	19	78	10	They did not keep God's covenant,and refused to walk by his Law.
B019C078V011	19	78	11	They forgot his doings,his wondrous works that he had shown them.
B019C078V012	19	78	12	He did marvelous things in the sight of their fathers,in the land of Egypt, in the field of Zoan.
B019C078V013	19	78	13	He split the sea, and caused them to pass through.He made the waters stand as a heap.
B019C078V014	19	78	14	In the daytime he also led them with a cloud,and all night with a light of fire.
B019C078V015	19	78	15	He split rocks in the wilderness,and gave them drink abundantly as out of the depths.
B019C078V016	19	78	16	He brought streams also out of the rock,and caused waters to run down like rivers.
B019C078V017	19	78	17	Yet they still went on to sin against him,to rebel against the Most High in the desert.
B019C078V018	19	78	18	They tempted God in their heartby asking food according to their desire.
B019C078V019	19	78	19	Yes, they spoke against God.They said, "Can God prepare a table in the wilderness?
B019C078V020	19	78	20	Behold, he struck the rock, so that waters gushed out,and streams overflowed.Can he give bread also?Will he provide flesh for his people?"
B019C078V021	19	78	21	Therefore 
B019C078V022	19	78	22	because they did not believe in God,and did not trust in his salvation.
B019C078V023	19	78	23	Yet he commanded the skies above,and opened the doors of heaven.
B019C078V024	19	78	24	He rained down manna on them to eat,and gave them bread from heaven.
B019C078V025	19	78	25	Man ate the bread of angels.He sent them food to the full.
B019C078V026	19	78	26	He caused the east wind to blow in the sky.By his power he guided the south wind.
B019C078V027	19	78	27	He rained also flesh on them as the dust;winged birds as the sand of the seas.
B019C078V028	19	78	28	He let them fall in the midst of their camp,around their habitations.
B019C078V029	19	78	29	So they ate, and were well filled.He gave them their own desire.
B019C078V030	19	78	30	They did not turn from their cravings.Their food was yet in their mouths,
B019C078V031	19	78	31	when the anger of God went up against them,killed some of the fattest of them,and struck down the young men of Israel.
B019C078V032	19	78	32	For all this they still sinned,and did not believe in his wondrous works.
B019C078V033	19	78	33	Therefore he consumed their days in vanity,and their years in terror.
B019C078V034	19	78	34	When he killed them, then they inquired after him.They returned and sought God earnestly.
B019C078V035	19	78	35	They remembered that God was their rock,the Most High God, their redeemer.
B019C078V036	19	78	36	But they flattered him with their mouth,and lied to him with their tongue.
B019C078V037	19	78	37	For their heart was not right with him,neither were they faithful in his covenant.
B019C078V038	19	78	38	But he, being merciful, forgave iniquity, and did not destroy them.Yes, many times he turned his anger away,and did not stir up all his wrath.
B019C078V039	19	78	39	He remembered that they were but flesh,a wind that passes away, and doesn't come again.
B019C078V040	19	78	40	How often they rebelled against him in the wilderness,and grieved him in the desert!
B019C078V041	19	78	41	They turned again and tempted God,and provoked the Holy One of Israel.
B019C078V042	19	78	42	They did not remember his hand,nor the day when he redeemed them from the adversary;
B019C078V043	19	78	43	how he set his signs in Egypt,his wonders in the field of Zoan,
B019C078V044	19	78	44	he turned their rivers into blood,and their streams, so that they could not drink.
B019C078V045	19	78	45	He sent among them swarms of flies, which devoured them;and frogs, which destroyed them.
B019C078V046	19	78	46	He gave also their increase to the caterpillar,and their labor to the locust.
B019C078V047	19	78	47	He destroyed their vines with hail,their sycamore fig trees with frost.
B019C078V048	19	78	48	He gave over their livestock also to the hail,and their flocks to hot thunderbolts.
B019C078V049	19	78	49	He threw on them the fierceness of his anger,wrath, indignation, and trouble,and a band of destroying angels.
B019C078V050	19	78	50	He made a path for his anger.He did not spare their soul from death,but gave their life over to the pestilence,
B019C078V051	19	78	51	and struck all the firstborn in Egypt,the chief of their strength in the tents of Ham.
B019C078V052	19	78	52	But he led forth his own people like sheep,and guided them in the wilderness like a flock.
B019C078V053	19	78	53	He led them safely, so that they weren't afraid,but the sea overwhelmed their enemies.
B019C078V054	19	78	54	He brought them to the border of his sanctuary,to this mountain, which his right hand had taken.
B019C078V055	19	78	55	He also drove out the nations before them,allotted them for an inheritance by line,and made the tribes of Israel to dwell in their tents.
B019C078V056	19	78	56	Yet they tempted and rebelled against the Most High God,and did not keep his testimonies;
B019C078V057	19	78	57	but turned back, and dealt treacherously like their fathers.They were turned aside like a deceitful bow.
B019C078V058	19	78	58	For they provoked him to anger with their high places,and moved him to jealousy with their engraved images.
