B019C078V063	19	78	63	Fire devoured their young men.Their virgins had no wedding song.
B019C078V064	19	78	64	Their priests fell by the sword,and their widows couldn't weep.
B019C078V065	19	78	65	Then the Lord awakened as one out of sleep,like a mighty man who shouts by reason of wine.
B019C078V066	19	78	66	He struck his adversaries backward.He put them to a perpetual reproach.
B019C078V067	19	78	67	Moreover he rejected the tent of Joseph,and did not choose the tribe of Ephraim,
B019C078V068	19	78	68	But chose the tribe of Judah,Mount Zion which he loved.
B019C078V069	19	78	69	He built his sanctuary like the heights,like the earth which he has established forever.
B019C078V070	19	78	70	He also chose David his servant,and took him from the sheepfolds;
B019C078V071	19	78	71	from following the ewes that have their young,he brought him to be the shepherd of Jacob, his people,and Israel, his inheritance.
B019C078V072	19	78	72	So he was their shepherd according to the integrity of his heart,and guided them by the skillfulness of his hands.
B019C079V001	19	79	1	A Psalm by Asaph.   God, the nations have come into your inheritance.They have defiled your holy temple.They have laid Jerusalem in heaps.
B019C079V002	19	79	2	They have given the dead bodies of your servants to be food for the birds of the sky,the flesh of your holy ones to the animals of the earth.
