B019C079V004	19	79	4	We have become a reproach to our neighbors,a scoffing and derision to those who are around us.
B019C079V005	19	79	5	How long, 
B019C079V006	19	79	6	Pour out your wrath on the nations that do not know you;on the kingdoms that do not call on your name;
B019C079V007	19	79	7	For they have devoured Jacob,and destroyed his homeland.
B019C079V008	19	79	8	Do not hold the iniquities of our forefathers against us.Let your tender mercies speedily meet us,for we are in desperate need.
B019C079V009	19	79	9	Help us, God of our salvation, for the glory of your name.Deliver us, and forgive our sins, for your name's sake.
B019C079V010	19	79	10	Why should the nations say, "Where is their God?"Let it be known among the nations, before our eyes,that vengeance for your servants' blood is being poured out.
B019C079V011	19	79	11	Let the sighing of the prisoner come before you.According to the greatness of your power, preserve those who are sentenced to death.
B019C079V012	19	79	12	Pay back to our neighbors seven times into their bosomtheir reproach with which they have reproached you, Lord.
B019C079V013	19	79	13	So we, your people and sheep of your pasture,will give you thanks forever.We will praise you forever, to all generations.
