B019C148V001	19	148	1	Praise Yah!Praise 
B019C148V002	19	148	2	Praise him, all his angels!Praise him, all his army!
B019C148V003	19	148	3	Praise him, sun and moon!Praise him, all you shining stars!
B019C148V004	19	148	4	Praise him, you heavens of heavens,You waters that are above the heavens.
B019C148V005	19	148	5	Let them praise the name of 
B019C148V006	19	148	6	He has also established them forever and ever.He has made a decree which will not pass away.
B019C148V007	19	148	7	Praise 
B019C148V008	19	148	8	Lightning and hail, snow and clouds;stormy wind, fulfilling his word;
B019C148V009	19	148	9	mountains and all hills;fruit trees and all cedars;
B019C148V010	19	148	10	wild animals and all livestock;small creatures and flying birds;
B019C148V011	19	148	11	kings of the earth and all peoples;princes and all judges of the earth;
B019C148V012	19	148	12	both young men and maidens;old men and children:
B019C148V013	19	148	13	let them praise the name of 
B019C148V014	19	148	14	He has lifted up the horn of his people,the praise of all his holy ones;even of the children of Israel, a people near to him.Praise Yah!
B019C149V001	19	149	1	Praise Yah!Sing to 
B019C149V002	19	149	2	Let Israel rejoice in him who made them.Let the children of Zion be joyful in their King.
B019C149V003	19	149	3	Let them praise his name in the dance!Let them sing praises to him with tambourine and harp!
B019C149V004	19	149	4	For 
B019C149V005	19	149	5	Let the holy ones rejoice in honor.Let them sing for joy on their beds.
B019C149V006	19	149	6	May the high praises of God be in their mouths,and a two-edged sword in their hand;
B019C149V007	19	149	7	To execute vengeance on the nations,and punishments on the peoples;
B019C149V008	19	149	8	To bind their kings with chains,and their nobles with fetters of iron;
B019C149V009	19	149	9	to execute on them the written judgment.All his holy ones have this honor.Praise Yah!
B019C150V001	19	150	1	Praise Yah!Praise God in his sanctuary!Praise him in his heavens for his acts of power!
B019C150V002	19	150	2	Praise him for his mighty acts!Praise him according to his excellent greatness!
B019C150V003	19	150	3	Praise him with the sounding of the trumpet!Praise him with harp and lyre!
B019C150V004	19	150	4	Praise him with tambourine and dancing!Praise him with stringed instruments and flute!
B019C150V005	19	150	5	Praise him with loud cymbals!Praise him with resounding cymbals!
B019C150V006	19	150	6	Let everything that has breath praise Yah!Praise Yah!
B020C001V001	20	1	1	The proverbs of Solomon, the son of David, king of Israel:
B020C001V002	20	1	2	to know wisdom and instruction;to discern the words of understanding;
B020C001V003	20	1	3	to receive instruction in wise dealing,in righteousness, justice, and equity;
B020C001V004	20	1	4	to give prudence to the simple,knowledge and discretion to the young man:
B020C001V005	20	1	5	that the wise man may hear, and increase in learning;that the man of understanding may attain to sound counsel:
B020C001V006	20	1	6	to understand a proverb, and parables,the words and riddles of the wise.
B020C001V007	20	1	7	The fear of 
B020C001V008	20	1	8	My son, listen to your father's instruction,and do not forsake your mother's teaching:
B020C001V009	20	1	9	for they will be a garland to grace your head,and chains around your neck.
B020C001V010	20	1	10	My son, if sinners entice you, do not consent.
B020C001V011	20	1	11	If they say, "Come with us,Let's lie in wait for blood;let's lurk secretly for the innocent without cause;
B020C001V012	20	1	12	let's swallow them up alive like Sheol,and whole, like those who go down into the pit.
B020C001V013	20	1	13	We'll find all valuable wealth.We'll fill our houses with spoil.
B020C001V014	20	1	14	You shall cast your lot among us.We'll all have one purse."
B020C001V015	20	1	15	My son, do not walk in the way with them.Keep your foot from their path,
B020C001V016	20	1	16	for their feet run to evil.They hurry to shed blood.
B020C001V017	20	1	17	For in vain is the net spread in the sight of any bird:
B020C001V018	20	1	18	but these lie in wait for their own blood.They lurk secretly for their own lives.
B020C001V019	20	1	19	So are the ways of everyone who is greedy for gain.It takes away the life of its owners.
B020C001V020	20	1	20	Wisdom calls aloud in the street.She utters her voice in the public squares.
B020C001V021	20	1	21	She calls at the head of noisy places.At the entrance of the city gates, she utters her words:
B020C001V022	20	1	22	"How long, you simple ones, will you love simplicity?How long will mockers delight themselves in mockery,and fools hate knowledge?
B020C001V023	20	1	23	Turn at my reproof.Behold, I will pour out my spirit on you.I will make known my words to you.
B020C001V024	20	1	24	Because I have called, and you have refused;I have stretched out my hand, and no one has paid attention;
B020C001V025	20	1	25	but you have ignored all my counsel,and wanted none of my reproof;
B020C001V026	20	1	26	I also will laugh at your disaster.I will mock when calamity overtakes you;
B020C001V027	20	1	27	when calamity overtakes you like a storm,when your disaster comes on like a whirlwind;when distress and anguish come on you.
B020C001V028	20	1	28	Then will they call on me, but I will not answer.They will seek me diligently, but they will not find me;
B020C001V029	20	1	29	because they hated knowledge,and did not choose the fear of 
B020C001V030	20	1	30	They wanted none of my counsel.They despised all my reproof.
B020C001V031	20	1	31	Therefore they will eat of the fruit of their own way,and be filled with their own schemes.
B020C001V032	20	1	32	For the backsliding of the simple will kill them.The careless ease of fools will destroy them.
B020C001V033	20	1	33	But whoever listens to me will dwell securely,and will be at ease, without fear of harm."
B020C002V001	20	2	1	My son, if you will receive my words, and store up my commandments within you;
B020C002V002	20	2	2	So as to turn your ear to wisdom,and apply your heart to understanding;
B020C002V003	20	2	3	Yes, if you call out for discernment,and lift up your voice for understanding;
B020C002V004	20	2	4	If you seek her as silver,and search for her as for hidden treasures:
B020C002V005	20	2	5	then you will understand the fear of 
B020C002V006	20	2	6	For 
B020C002V007	20	2	7	He lays up sound wisdom for the upright.He is a shield to those who walk in integrity;
B020C002V008	20	2	8	that he may guard the paths of justice,and preserve the way of his holy ones.
B020C002V009	20	2	9	Then you will understand righteousness and justice,equity and every good path.
B020C002V010	20	2	10	For wisdom will enter into your heart.Knowledge will be pleasant to your soul.
B020C002V011	20	2	11	Discretion will watch over you.Understanding will keep you,
B020C002V012	20	2	12	to deliver you from the way of evil,from the men who speak perverse things;
B020C002V013	20	2	13	who forsake the paths of uprightness,to walk in the ways of darkness;
B020C002V014	20	2	14	who rejoice to do evil,and delight in the perverseness of evil;
B020C002V015	20	2	15	who are crooked in their ways,and wayward in their paths:
B020C002V016	20	2	16	To deliver you from the strange woman,even from the foreigner who flatters with her words;
B020C002V017	20	2	17	who forsakes the friend of her youth,and forgets the covenant of her God:
B020C002V018	20	2	18	for her house leads down to death,her paths to the dead.
B020C002V019	20	2	19	None who go to her return again,neither do they attain to the paths of life:
B020C002V020	20	2	20	that you may walk in the way of good men,and keep the paths of the righteous.
B020C002V021	20	2	21	For the upright will dwell in the land.The perfect will remain in it.
B020C002V022	20	2	22	But the wicked will be cut off from the land.The treacherous will be rooted out of it.
B020C003V001	20	3	1	My son, do not forget my teaching; but let your heart keep my commandments:
B020C003V002	20	3	2	for length of days, and years of life,and peace, will they add to you.
B020C003V003	20	3	3	Do not let kindness and truth forsake you.Bind them around your neck.Write them on the tablet of your heart.
B020C003V004	20	3	4	So you will find favor,and good understanding in the sight of God and man.
B020C003V005	20	3	5	Trust in 
B020C003V006	20	3	6	In all your ways acknowledge him,and he will make your paths straight.
B020C003V007	20	3	7	Do not be wise in your own eyes.Fear 
B020C003V008	20	3	8	It will be health to your body,and nourishment to your bones.
B020C003V009	20	3	9	Honor 
B020C003V010	20	3	10	so your barns will be filled with plenty,and your vats will overflow with new wine.
B020C003V011	20	3	11	My son, do not despise 
B020C003V012	20	3	12	for whom 
B020C003V013	20	3	13	Happy is the man who finds wisdom,the man who gets understanding.
B020C003V014	20	3	14	For her good profit is better than getting silver,and her return is better than fine gold.
B020C003V015	20	3	15	She is more precious than rubies.None of the things you can desire are to be compared to her.
B020C003V016	20	3	16	Length of days is in her right hand.In her left hand are riches and honor.
B020C003V017	20	3	17	Her ways are ways of pleasantness.All her paths are peace.
B020C003V018	20	3	18	She is a tree of life to those who lay hold of her.Happy is everyone who retains her.
B020C003V019	20	3	19	By wisdom 
B020C003V020	20	3	20	By his knowledge, the depths were broken up,and the skies drop down the dew.
B020C003V021	20	3	21	My son, let them not depart from your eyes.Keep sound wisdom and discretion:
B020C003V022	20	3	22	so they will be life to your soul,and grace for your neck.
B020C003V023	20	3	23	Then you shall walk in your way securely.Your foot won't stumble.
B020C003V024	20	3	24	When you lie down, you will not be afraid.Yes, you will lie down, and your sleep will be sweet.
B020C003V025	20	3	25	Do not be afraid of sudden fear,neither of the desolation of the wicked, when it comes:
B020C003V026	20	3	26	for 
B020C003V027	20	3	27	Do not withhold good from those to whom it is due,when it is in the power of your hand to do it.
B020C003V028	20	3	28	Do not say to your neighbor, "Go, and come again;tomorrow I will give it to you,"when you have it by you.
B020C003V029	20	3	29	Do not devise evil against your neighbor,seeing he dwells securely by you.
B020C003V030	20	3	30	Do not strive with a man without cause,if he has done you no harm.
B020C003V031	20	3	31	Do not envy the man of violence.Choose none of his ways.
B020C003V032	20	3	32	For the perverse is an abomination to 
B020C003V033	20	3	33	
        
B020C003V034	20	3	34	Surely he is scornful to scoffers,but he gives grace to the humble.
B020C003V035	20	3	35	The wise will inherit glory,but shame will be the promotion of fools.
B020C004V001	20	4	1	Listen, sons, to a father's instruction. Pay attention and know understanding;
B020C004V002	20	4	2	for I give you sound learning.Do not forsake my law.
B020C004V003	20	4	3	For I was a son to my father,tender and an only child in the sight of my mother.
B020C004V004	20	4	4	He taught me, and said to me:"Let your heart retain my words.Keep my commandments, and live.
B020C004V005	20	4	5	Get wisdom.Get understanding.Do not forget, neither swerve from the words of my mouth.
B020C004V006	20	4	6	Do not forsake her, and she will preserve you.Love her, and she will keep you.
B020C004V007	20	4	7	Wisdom is supreme.Get wisdom.Yes, though it costs all your possessions, get understanding.
B020C004V008	20	4	8	Esteem her, and she will exalt you.She will bring you to honor, when you embrace her.
B020C004V009	20	4	9	She will give to your head a garland of grace.She will deliver a crown of splendor to you."
B020C004V010	20	4	10	Listen, my son, and receive my sayings.The years of your life will be many.
B020C004V011	20	4	11	I have taught you in the way of wisdom.I have led you in straight paths.
B020C004V012	20	4	12	When you go, your steps will not be hampered.When you run, you will not stumble.
B020C004V013	20	4	13	Take firm hold of instruction.Do not let her go.Keep her, for she is your life.
B020C004V014	20	4	14	Do not enter into the path of the wicked.Do not walk in the way of evil men.
B020C004V015	20	4	15	Avoid it, and do not pass by it.Turn from it, and pass on.
B020C004V016	20	4	16	For they do not sleep, unless they do evil.Their sleep is taken away, unless they make someone fall.
B020C004V017	20	4	17	For they eat the bread of wickedness,and drink the wine of violence.
B020C004V018	20	4	18	But the path of the righteous is like the dawning light,that shines more and more until the perfect day.
B020C004V019	20	4	19	The way of the wicked is like darkness.They do not know what they stumble over.
B020C004V020	20	4	20	My son, attend to my words.Turn your ear to my sayings.
B020C004V021	20	4	21	Let them not depart from your eyes.Keep them in the midst of your heart.
B020C004V022	20	4	22	For they are life to those who find them,and health to their whole body.
B020C004V023	20	4	23	Keep your heart with all diligence,for out of it is the wellspring of life.
B020C004V024	20	4	24	Put away from yourself a perverse mouth.Put corrupt lips far from you.
B020C004V025	20	4	25	Let your eyes look straight ahead.Fix your gaze directly before you.
B020C004V026	20	4	26	Make the path of your feet level.Let all of your ways be established.
B020C004V027	20	4	27	Do not turn to the right hand nor to the left.Remove your foot from evil.
B020C005V001	20	5	1	My son, pay attention to my wisdom. Turn your ear to my understanding:
B020C005V002	20	5	2	that you may maintain discretion,that your lips may preserve knowledge.
B020C005V003	20	5	3	For the lips of an adulteress drip honey.Her mouth is smoother than oil,
B020C005V004	20	5	4	But in the end she is as bitter as wormwood,and as sharp as a two-edged sword.
B020C005V005	20	5	5	Her feet go down to death.Her steps lead straight to Sheol.
B020C005V006	20	5	6	She gives no thought to the way of life.Her ways are crooked, and she doesn't know it.
B020C005V007	20	5	7	Now therefore, my sons, listen to me.Do not depart from the words of my mouth.
B020C005V008	20	5	8	Remove your way far from her.Do not come near the door of her house,
B020C005V009	20	5	9	lest you give your honor to others,and your years to the cruel one;
B020C005V010	20	5	10	lest strangers feast on your wealth,and your labors enrich another man's house.
B020C005V011	20	5	11	You will groan at your latter end,when your flesh and your body are consumed,
B020C005V012	20	5	12	and say, "How I have hated instruction,and my heart despised reproof;
B020C005V013	20	5	13	neither have I obeyed the voice of my teachers,nor turned my ear to those who instructed me!
B020C005V014	20	5	14	I have come to the brink of utter ruin,in the midst of the gathered assembly."
B020C005V015	20	5	15	Drink water out of your own cistern,running water out of your own well.
B020C005V016	20	5	16	Should your springs overflow in the streets,streams of water in the public squares?
B020C005V017	20	5	17	Let them be for yourself alone,not for strangers with you.
B020C005V018	20	5	18	Let your spring be blessed.Rejoice in the wife of your youth.
B020C005V019	20	5	19	A loving doe and a graceful deer-let her breasts satisfy you at all times.Be captivated always with her love.
B020C005V020	20	5	20	For why should you, my son, be captivated with an adulteress?Why embrace the bosom of another?
B020C005V021	20	5	21	For the ways of man are before the eyes of 
B020C005V022	20	5	22	The evil deeds of the wicked ensnare him.The cords of his sin hold him firmly.
B020C005V023	20	5	23	He will die for lack of instruction.In the greatness of his folly, he will go astray.
B020C006V001	20	6	1	My son, if you have become collateral for your neighbor, if you have struck your hands in pledge for a stranger;
B020C006V002	20	6	2	You are trapped by the words of your mouth.You are ensnared with the words of your mouth.
B020C006V003	20	6	3	Do this now, my son, and deliver yourself,seeing you have come into the hand of your neighbor.Go, humble yourself.Press your plea with your neighbor.
B020C006V004	20	6	4	Give no sleep to your eyes,nor slumber to your eyelids.
B020C006V005	20	6	5	Free yourself, like a gazelle from the hand of the hunter,like a bird from the snare of the fowler.
B020C006V006	20	6	6	Go to the ant, you sluggard.Consider her ways, and be wise;
B020C006V007	20	6	7	which having no chief, overseer, or ruler,
B020C006V008	20	6	8	provides her bread in the summer,and gathers her food in the harvest.
B020C006V009	20	6	9	How long will you sleep, sluggard?When will you arise out of your sleep?
B020C006V010	20	6	10	A little sleep, a little slumber,a little folding of the hands to sleep:
B020C006V011	20	6	11	so your poverty will come as a robber,and your scarcity as an armed man.
B020C006V012	20	6	12	A worthless person, a man of iniquity,is he who walks with a perverse mouth;
B020C006V013	20	6	13	who winks with his eyes, who signals with his feet,who motions with his fingers;
B020C006V014	20	6	14	in whose heart is perverseness,who devises evil continually,who always sows discord.
B020C006V015	20	6	15	Therefore his calamity will come suddenly.He will be broken suddenly, and that without remedy.
B020C006V016	20	6	16	There are six things which 
B020C006V017	20	6	17	haughty eyes, a lying tongue,hands that shed innocent blood;
B020C006V018	20	6	18	a heart that devises wicked schemes,feet that are swift in running to mischief,
B020C006V019	20	6	19	a false witness who utters lies,and he who sows discord among brothers.
B020C006V020	20	6	20	My son, keep your father's commandment,and do not forsake your mother's teaching.
B020C006V021	20	6	21	Bind them continually on your heart.Tie them around your neck.
B020C006V022	20	6	22	When you walk, it will lead you.When you sleep, it will watch over you.When you awake, it will talk with you.
B020C006V023	20	6	23	For the commandment is a lamp,and the Law is light.Reproofs of instruction are the way of life,
B020C006V024	20	6	24	to keep you from the immoral woman,from the flattery of the wayward wife's tongue.
B020C006V025	20	6	25	Do not lust after her beauty in your heart,neither let her captivate you with her eyelids.
B020C006V026	20	6	26	For a prostitute reduces you to a piece of bread.The adulteress hunts for your precious life.
B020C006V027	20	6	27	Can a man scoop fire into his lap,and his clothes not be burned?
B020C006V028	20	6	28	Or can one walk on hot coals,and his feet not be scorched?
B020C006V029	20	6	29	So is he who goes in to his neighbor's wife.Whoever touches her will not be unpunished.
B020C006V030	20	6	30	Men do not despise a thief,if he steals to satisfy himself when he is hungry:
B020C006V031	20	6	31	but if he is found, he shall restore seven times.He shall give all the wealth of his house.
B020C006V032	20	6	32	He who commits adultery with a woman is void of understanding.He who does it destroys his own soul.
B020C006V033	20	6	33	He will get wounds and dishonor.His reproach will not be wiped away.
B020C006V034	20	6	34	For jealousy arouses the fury of the husband.He won't spare in the day of vengeance.
B020C006V035	20	6	35	He won't regard any ransom,neither will he rest content, though you give many gifts.
B020C007V001	20	7	1	My son, keep my words. Lay up my commandments within you.
B020C007V002	20	7	2	Keep my commandments and live!Guard my teaching as the apple of your eye.
B020C007V003	20	7	3	Bind them on your fingers.Write them on the tablet of your heart.
B020C007V004	20	7	4	Tell wisdom, "You are my sister."Call understanding your relative,
B020C007V005	20	7	5	that they may keep you from the strange woman,from the foreigner who flatters with her words.
B020C007V006	20	7	6	For at the window of my house,I looked out through my lattice.
B020C007V007	20	7	7	I saw among the simple ones.I discerned among the youths a young man void of understanding,
B020C007V008	20	7	8	passing through the street near her corner,he went the way to her house,
B020C007V009	20	7	9	in the twilight, in the evening of the day,in the middle of the night and in the darkness.
B020C007V010	20	7	10	Behold, there a woman met him with the attire of a prostitute,and with crafty intent.
B020C007V011	20	7	11	She is loud and defiant.Her feet do not stay in her house.
B020C007V012	20	7	12	Now she is in the streets, now in the squares,and lurking at every corner.
B020C007V013	20	7	13	So she caught him, and kissed him.With an impudent face she said to him:
B020C007V014	20	7	14	"Sacrifices of peace offerings are with me.This day I have paid my vows.
B020C007V015	20	7	15	Therefore I came out to meet you,to diligently seek your face,and I have found you.
B020C007V016	20	7	16	I have spread my couch with carpets of tapestry,with striped cloths of the yarn of Egypt.
B020C007V017	20	7	17	I have perfumed my bed with myrrh, aloes, and cinnamon.
B020C007V018	20	7	18	Come, let's take our fill of loving until the morning.Let's solace ourselves with loving.
B020C007V019	20	7	19	For my husband isn't at home.He has gone on a long journey.
B020C007V020	20	7	20	He has taken a bag of money with him.He will come home at the full moon."
B020C007V021	20	7	21	With persuasive words, she led him astray.With the flattering of her lips, she seduced him.
B020C007V022	20	7	22	He followed her immediately,as an ox goes to the slaughter,as a fool stepping into a noose.
B020C007V023	20	7	23	Until an arrow strikes through his liver,as a bird hurries to the snare,and doesn't know that it will cost his life.
B020C007V024	20	7	24	Now therefore, sons, listen to me.Pay attention to the words of my mouth.
B020C007V025	20	7	25	Do not let your heart turn to her ways.Do not go astray in her paths,
B020C007V026	20	7	26	for she has thrown down many wounded.Yes, all her slain are a mighty army.
B020C007V027	20	7	27	Her house is the way to Sheol,going down to the chambers of death.
B020C008V001	20	8	1	Doesn't wisdom cry out? Doesn't understanding raise her voice?
B020C008V002	20	8	2	On the top of high places by the way,where the paths meet, she stands.
B020C008V003	20	8	3	Beside the gates, at the entry of the city,at the entry doors, she cries aloud:
B020C008V004	20	8	4	"To you men, I call!I send my voice to the sons of mankind.
B020C008V005	20	8	5	You simple, understand prudence.You fools, be of an understanding heart.
B020C008V006	20	8	6	Hear, for I will speak excellent things.The opening of my lips is for right things.
B020C008V007	20	8	7	For my mouth speaks truth.Wickedness is an abomination to my lips.
B020C008V008	20	8	8	All the words of my mouth are in righteousness.There is nothing crooked or perverse in them.
B020C008V009	20	8	9	They are all plain to him who understands,right to those who find knowledge.
B020C008V010	20	8	10	Receive my instruction rather than silver;knowledge rather than choice gold.
B020C008V011	20	8	11	For wisdom is better than rubies.All the things that may be desired can't be compared to it.
B020C008V012	20	8	12	"I, wisdom, have made prudence my dwelling.Find out knowledge and discretion.
B020C008V013	20	8	13	The fear of 
B020C008V014	20	8	14	Counsel and sound knowledge are mine.I have understanding and power.
B020C008V015	20	8	15	By me kings reign,and princes decree justice.
B020C008V016	20	8	16	By me princes rule;nobles, and all the righteous rulers of the earth.
B020C008V017	20	8	17	I love those who love me.Those who seek me diligently will find me.
B020C008V018	20	8	18	With me are riches, honor,enduring wealth, and prosperity.
B020C008V019	20	8	19	My fruit is better than gold, yes, than fine gold;my yield than choice silver.
B020C008V020	20	8	20	I walk in the way of righteousness,in the midst of the paths of justice;
B020C008V021	20	8	21	That I may give wealth to those who love me.I fill their treasuries.
B020C008V022	20	8	22	"
B020C008V023	20	8	23	I was set up from everlasting, from the beginning,before the earth existed.
B020C008V024	20	8	24	When there were no depths, I was brought forth,when there were no springs abounding with water.
B020C008V025	20	8	25	Before the mountains were settled in place,before the hills, I was brought forth;
B020C008V026	20	8	26	while as yet he had not made the earth, nor the fields,nor the beginning of the dust of the world.
B020C008V027	20	8	27	When he established the heavens, I was there;when he set a circle on the surface of the deep,
B020C008V028	20	8	28	when he established the clouds above,when the springs of the deep became strong,
B020C008V029	20	8	29	when he gave to the sea its boundary,that the waters should not violate his commandment,when he marked out the foundations of the earth;
B020C008V030	20	8	30	then I was the craftsman by his side.I was a delight day by day,always rejoicing before him,
B020C008V031	20	8	31	Rejoicing in his whole world.My delight was with the sons of men.
B020C008V032	20	8	32	"Now therefore, my sons, listen to me,for blessed are those who keep my ways.
B020C008V033	20	8	33	Hear instruction, and be wise.Do not refuse it.
B020C008V034	20	8	34	Blessed is the man who hears me,watching daily at my gates,waiting at my door posts.
B020C008V035	20	8	35	For whoever finds me, finds life,and will obtain favor from 
B020C008V036	20	8	36	But he who sins against me wrongs his own soul.All those who hate me love death."
B020C009V001	20	9	1	Wisdom has built her house. She has carved out her seven pillars.
B020C009V002	20	9	2	She has prepared her meat.She has mixed her wine.She has also set her table.
B020C009V003	20	9	3	She has sent out her maidens.She cries from the highest places of the city:
B020C009V004	20	9	4	"Whoever is simple, let him turn in here!"As for him who is void of understanding, she says to him,
B020C009V005	20	9	5	"Come, eat some of my bread,Drink some of the wine which I have mixed!
B020C009V006	20	9	6	Leave your simple ways, and live.Walk in the way of understanding."
B020C009V007	20	9	7	He who corrects a mocker invites insult.He who reproves a wicked man invites abuse.
B020C009V008	20	9	8	Do not reprove a scoffer, lest he hate you.Reprove a wise man, and he will love you.
B020C009V009	20	9	9	Instruct a wise man, and he will be still wiser.Teach a righteous man, and he will increase in learning.
B020C009V010	20	9	10	The fear of 
B020C009V011	20	9	11	For by me your days will be multiplied.The years of your life will be increased.
B020C009V012	20	9	12	If you are wise, you are wise for yourself.If you mock, you alone will bear it.
B020C009V013	20	9	13	The foolish woman is loud,Undisciplined, and knows nothing.
B020C009V014	20	9	14	She sits at the door of her house,on a seat in the high places of the city,
B020C009V015	20	9	15	To call to those who pass by,who go straight on their ways,
B020C009V016	20	9	16	"Whoever is simple, let him turn in here."as for him who is void of understanding, she says to him,
B020C009V017	20	9	17	"Stolen water is sweet.Food eaten in secret is pleasant."
B020C009V018	20	9	18	But he doesn't know that the dead are there,that her guests are in the depths of Sheol.
B020C010V001	20	10	1	The proverbs of Solomon. A wise son makes a glad father;but a foolish son brings grief to his mother.
B020C010V002	20	10	2	Treasures of wickedness profit nothing,but righteousness delivers from death.
B020C010V003	20	10	3	
        
B020C010V004	20	10	4	He becomes poor who works with a lazy hand,but the hand of the diligent brings wealth.
B020C010V005	20	10	5	He who gathers in summer is a wise son,but he who sleeps during the harvest is a son who causes shame.
B020C010V006	20	10	6	Blessings are on the head of the righteous,but violence covers the mouth of the wicked.
B020C010V007	20	10	7	The memory of the righteous is blessed,but the name of the wicked will rot.
B020C010V008	20	10	8	The wise in heart accept commandments,but a chattering fool will fall.
B020C010V009	20	10	9	He who walks blamelessly walks surely,but he who perverts his ways will be found out.
B020C010V010	20	10	10	One winking with the eye causes sorrow,but a chattering fool will fall.
B020C010V011	20	10	11	The mouth of the righteous is a spring of life,but violence covers the mouth of the wicked.
B020C010V012	20	10	12	Hatred stirs up strife,but love covers all wrongs.
B020C010V013	20	10	13	Wisdom is found on the lips of him who has discernment,but a rod is for the back of him who is void of understanding.
B020C010V014	20	10	14	Wise men lay up knowledge,but the mouth of the foolish is near ruin.
B020C010V015	20	10	15	The rich man's wealth is his strong city.The destruction of the poor is their poverty.
B020C010V016	20	10	16	The labor of the righteous leads to life.The increase of the wicked leads to sin.
B020C010V017	20	10	17	He is in the way of life who heeds correction,but he who forsakes reproof leads others astray.
B020C010V018	20	10	18	He who hides hatred has lying lips.He who utters a slander is a fool.
B020C010V019	20	10	19	In the multitude of words there is no lack of disobedience,but he who restrains his lips does wisely.
B020C010V020	20	10	20	The tongue of the righteous is like choice silver.The heart of the wicked is of little worth.
B020C010V021	20	10	21	The lips of the righteous feed many,but the foolish die for lack of understanding.
B020C010V022	20	10	22	
        
B020C010V023	20	10	23	It is a fool's pleasure to do wickedness,but wisdom is a man of understanding's pleasure.
B020C010V024	20	10	24	What the wicked fear, will overtake them,but the desire of the righteous will be granted.
B020C010V025	20	10	25	When the whirlwind passes, the wicked is no more;but the righteous stand firm forever.
B020C010V026	20	10	26	As vinegar to the teeth, and as smoke to the eyes,so is the sluggard to those who send him.
B020C010V027	20	10	27	The fear of 
B020C010V028	20	10	28	The prospect of the righteous is joy,but the hope of the wicked will perish.
B020C010V029	20	10	29	The way of 
B020C010V030	20	10	30	The righteous will never be removed,but the wicked will not dwell in the land.
B020C010V031	20	10	31	The mouth of the righteous brings forth wisdom,but the perverse tongue will be cut off.
B020C010V032	20	10	32	The lips of the righteous know what is acceptable,but the mouth of the wicked is perverse.
B020C011V001	20	11	1	A false balance is an abomination to 
B020C011V002	20	11	2	When pride comes, then comes shame,but with humility comes wisdom.
B020C011V003	20	11	3	The integrity of the upright shall guide them,but the perverseness of the treacherous shall destroy them.
B020C011V004	20	11	4	Riches do not profit in the day of wrath,but righteousness delivers from death.
B020C011V005	20	11	5	The righteousness of the blameless will direct his way,but the wicked shall fall by his own wickedness.
B020C011V006	20	11	6	The righteousness of the upright shall deliver them,but the unfaithful will be trapped by evil desires.
B020C011V007	20	11	7	When a wicked man dies, hope perishes,and expectation of power comes to nothing.
B020C011V008	20	11	8	A righteous person is delivered out of trouble,and the wicked takes his place.
B020C011V009	20	11	9	With his mouth the godless man destroys his neighbor,but the righteous will be delivered through knowledge.
B020C011V010	20	11	10	When it goes well with the righteous, the city rejoices.When the wicked perish, there is shouting.
B020C011V011	20	11	11	By the blessing of the upright, the city is exalted,but it is overthrown by the mouth of the wicked.
B020C011V012	20	11	12	One who despises his neighbor is void of wisdom,but a man of understanding holds his peace.
B020C011V013	20	11	13	One who brings gossip betrays a confidence,but one who is of a trustworthy spirit is one who keeps a secret.
B020C011V014	20	11	14	Where there is no wise guidance, the nation falls,but in the multitude of counselors there is victory.
B020C011V015	20	11	15	He who is collateral for a stranger will suffer for it,but he who refuses pledges of collateral is secure.
B020C011V016	20	11	16	A gracious woman obtains honor,but violent men obtain riches.
B020C011V017	20	11	17	The merciful man does good to his own soul,but he who is cruel troubles his own flesh.
B020C011V018	20	11	18	Wicked people earn deceitful wages,but one who sows righteousness reaps a sure reward.
B020C011V019	20	11	19	He who is truly righteous gets life.He who pursues evil gets death.
B020C011V020	20	11	20	Those who are perverse in heart are an abomination to 
B020C011V021	20	11	21	Most certainly, the evil man will not be unpunished,but the seed of the righteous will be delivered.
B020C011V022	20	11	22	Like a gold ring in a pig's snout,is a beautiful woman who lacks discretion.
B020C011V023	20	11	23	The desire of the righteous is only good.The expectation of the wicked is wrath.
B020C011V024	20	11	24	There is one who scatters, and increases yet more.There is one who withholds more than is appropriate, but gains poverty.
B020C011V025	20	11	25	The liberal soul shall be made fat.He who waters shall be watered also himself.
B020C011V026	20	11	26	People curse someone who withholds grain,but blessing will be on the head of him who sells it.
B020C011V027	20	11	27	He who diligently seeks good seeks favor,but he who searches after evil, it shall come to him.
B020C011V028	20	11	28	He who trusts in his riches will fall,but the righteous shall flourish as the green leaf.
B020C011V029	20	11	29	He who troubles his own house shall inherit the wind.The foolish shall be servant to the wise of heart.
B020C011V030	20	11	30	The fruit of the righteous is a tree of life.He who is wise wins souls.
B020C011V031	20	11	31	Behold, the righteous shall be repaid in the earth;how much more the wicked and the sinner!
B020C012V001	20	12	1	Whoever loves correction loves knowledge, but he who hates reproof is stupid.
B020C012V002	20	12	2	A good man shall obtain favor from 
B020C012V003	20	12	3	A man shall not be established by wickedness,but the root of the righteous shall not be moved.
B020C012V004	20	12	4	A worthy woman is the crown of her husband,but a disgraceful wife is as rottenness in his bones.
B020C012V005	20	12	5	The thoughts of the righteous are just,but the advice of the wicked is deceitful.
B020C012V006	20	12	6	The words of the wicked are about lying in wait for blood,but the speech of the upright rescues them.
B020C012V007	20	12	7	The wicked are overthrown, and are no more,but the house of the righteous shall stand.
B020C012V008	20	12	8	A man shall be commended according to his wisdom,but he who has a warped mind shall be despised.
B020C012V009	20	12	9	Better is he who is lightly esteemed, and has a servant,than he who honors himself, and lacks bread.
B020C012V010	20	12	10	A righteous man regards the life of his animal,but the tender mercies of the wicked are cruel.
B020C012V011	20	12	11	He who tills his land shall have plenty of bread,but he who chases fantasies is void of understanding.
B020C012V012	20	12	12	The wicked desires the plunder of evil men,but the root of the righteous flourishes.
B020C012V013	20	12	13	An evil man is trapped by sinfulness of lips,but the righteous shall come out of trouble.
B020C012V014	20	12	14	A man shall be satisfied with good by the fruit of his mouth.The work of a man's hands shall be rewarded to him.
B020C012V015	20	12	15	The way of a fool is right in his own eyes,but he who is wise listens to counsel.
B020C012V016	20	12	16	A fool shows his annoyance the same day,but one who overlooks an insult is prudent.
B020C012V017	20	12	17	He who is truthful testifies honestly,but a false witness lies.
B020C012V018	20	12	18	There is one who speaks rashly like the piercing of a sword,but the tongue of the wise heals.
B020C012V019	20	12	19	Truth's lips will be established forever,but a lying tongue is only momentary.
B020C012V020	20	12	20	Deceit is in the heart of those who plot evil,but joy comes to the promoters of peace.
B020C012V021	20	12	21	No mischief shall happen to the righteous,but the wicked shall be filled with evil.
B020C012V022	20	12	22	Lying lips are an abomination to 
B020C012V023	20	12	23	A prudent man keeps his knowledge,but the hearts of fools proclaim foolishness.
B020C012V024	20	12	24	The hands of the diligent ones shall rule,but laziness ends in slave labor.
B020C012V025	20	12	25	Anxiety in a man's heart weighs it down,but a kind word makes it glad.
B020C012V026	20	12	26	A righteous person is cautious in friendship,but the way of the wicked leads them astray.
B020C012V027	20	12	27	The slothful man doesn't roast his game,but the possessions of diligent men are prized.
B020C012V028	20	12	28	In the way of righteousness is life;in its path there is no death.
B020C013V001	20	13	1	A wise son listens to his father's instruction, but a scoffer doesn't listen to rebuke.
B020C013V002	20	13	2	By the fruit of his lips, a man enjoys good things;but the unfaithful crave violence.
B020C013V003	20	13	3	He who guards his mouth guards his soul.One who opens wide his lips comes to ruin.
B020C013V004	20	13	4	The soul of the sluggard desires, and has nothing,but the desire of the diligent shall be fully satisfied.
B020C013V005	20	13	5	A righteous man hates lies,but a wicked man brings shame and disgrace.
B020C013V006	20	13	6	Righteousness guards the way of integrity,but wickedness overthrows the sinner.
B020C013V007	20	13	7	There are some who pretend to be rich, yet have nothing.There are some who pretend to be poor, yet have great wealth.
B020C013V008	20	13	8	The ransom of a man's life is his riches,but the poor hear no threats.
B020C013V009	20	13	9	The light of the righteous shines brightly,but the lamp of the wicked is snuffed out.
B020C013V010	20	13	10	Pride only breeds quarrels,but with ones who take advice is wisdom.
B020C013V011	20	13	11	Wealth gained dishonestly dwindles away,but he who gathers by hand makes it grow.
B020C013V012	20	13	12	Hope deferred makes the heart sick,but when longing is fulfilled, it is a tree of life.
B020C013V013	20	13	13	Whoever despises instruction will pay for it,but he who respects a command will be rewarded.
B020C013V014	20	13	14	The teaching of the wise is a spring of life,to turn from the snares of death.
B020C013V015	20	13	15	Good understanding wins favor;but the way of the unfaithful is hard.
B020C013V016	20	13	16	Every prudent man acts from knowledge,but a fool exposes folly.
B020C013V017	20	13	17	A wicked messenger falls into trouble,but a trustworthy envoy gains healing.
B020C013V018	20	13	18	Poverty and shame come to him who refuses discipline,but he who heeds correction shall be honored.
B020C013V019	20	13	19	Longing fulfilled is sweet to the soul,but fools detest turning from evil.
B020C013V020	20	13	20	One who walks with wise men grows wise,but a companion of fools suffers harm.
B020C013V021	20	13	21	Misfortune pursues sinners,but prosperity rewards the righteous.
B020C013V022	20	13	22	A good man leaves an inheritance to his children's children,but the wealth of the sinner is stored for the righteous.
B020C013V023	20	13	23	An abundance of food is in poor people's fields,but injustice sweeps it away.
B020C013V024	20	13	24	One who spares the rod hates his son,but one who loves him is careful to discipline him.
B020C013V025	20	13	25	The righteous one eats to the satisfying of his soul,but the belly of the wicked goes hungry.
B020C014V001	20	14	1	Every wise woman builds her house, but the foolish one tears it down with her own hands.
B020C014V002	20	14	2	He who walks in his uprightness fears 
B020C014V003	20	14	3	The fool's talk brings a rod to his back,but the lips of the wise protect them.
B020C014V004	20	14	4	Where no oxen are, the crib is clean,but much increase is by the strength of the ox.
B020C014V005	20	14	5	A truthful witness will not lie,but a false witness pours out lies.
B020C014V006	20	14	6	A scoffer seeks wisdom, and doesn't find it,but knowledge comes easily to a discerning person.
B020C014V007	20	14	7	Stay away from a foolish man,for you won't find knowledge on his lips.
B020C014V008	20	14	8	The wisdom of the prudent is to think about his way,but the folly of fools is deceit.
B020C014V009	20	14	9	Fools mock at making atonement for sins,but among the upright there is good will.
B020C014V010	20	14	10	The heart knows its own bitterness and joy;he will not share these with a stranger.
B020C014V011	20	14	11	The house of the wicked will be overthrown,but the tent of the upright will flourish.
B020C014V012	20	14	12	There is a way which seems right to a man,but in the end it leads to death.
B020C014V013	20	14	13	Even in laughter the heart may be sorrowful,and mirth may end in heaviness.
B020C014V014	20	14	14	The unfaithful will be repaid for his own ways;likewise a good man will be rewarded for his ways.
B020C014V015	20	14	15	A simple man believes everything,but the prudent man carefully considers his ways.
B020C014V016	20	14	16	A wise man fears, and shuns evil,but the fool is hotheaded and reckless.
B020C014V017	20	14	17	He who is quick to become angry will commit folly,and a crafty man is hated.
B020C014V018	20	14	18	The simple inherit folly,but the prudent are crowned with knowledge.
B020C014V019	20	14	19	The evil bow down before the good,and the wicked at the gates of the righteous.
B020C014V020	20	14	20	The poor person is shunned even by his own neighbor,but the rich person has many friends.
B020C014V021	20	14	21	He who despises his neighbor sins,but blessed is he who has pity on the poor.
B020C014V022	20	14	22	Do they not go astray who plot evil?But love and faithfulness belong to those who plan good.
B020C014V023	20	14	23	In all hard work there is profit,but the talk of the lips leads only to poverty.
B020C014V024	20	14	24	The crown of the wise is their riches,but the folly of fools crowns them with folly.
B020C014V025	20	14	25	A truthful witness saves souls,but a false witness is deceitful.
B020C014V026	20	14	26	In the fear of 
B020C014V027	20	14	27	The fear of 
B020C014V028	20	14	28	In the multitude of people is the king's glory,but in the lack of people is the destruction of the prince.
B020C014V029	20	14	29	He who is slow to anger has great understanding,but he who has a quick temper displays folly.
B020C014V030	20	14	30	The life of the body is a heart at peace,but envy rots the bones.
B020C014V031	20	14	31	He who oppresses the poor shows contempt for his Maker,but he who is kind to the needy honors him.
B020C014V032	20	14	32	The wicked is brought down in his calamity,but in death, the righteous has a refuge.
B020C014V033	20	14	33	Wisdom rests in the heart of one who has understanding,and is even made known in the inward part of fools.
B020C014V034	20	14	34	Righteousness exalts a nation,but sin is a disgrace to any people.
B020C014V035	20	14	35	The king's favor is toward a servant who deals wisely,but his wrath is toward one who causes shame.
B020C015V001	20	15	1	A gentle answer turns away wrath, but a harsh word stirs up anger.
B020C015V002	20	15	2	The tongue of the wise commends knowledge,but the mouth of fools gush out folly.
