B020C015V012	20	15	12	A scoffer doesn't love to be reproved;he will not go to the wise.
B020C015V013	20	15	13	A glad heart makes a cheerful face;but an aching heart breaks the spirit.
B020C015V014	20	15	14	The heart of one who has understanding seeks knowledge,but the mouths of fools feed on folly.
B020C015V015	20	15	15	All the days of the afflicted are wretched,but one who has a cheerful heart enjoys a continual feast.
B020C015V016	20	15	16	Better is little, with the fear of 
B020C015V017	20	15	17	Better is a dinner of herbs, where love is,than a fattened calf with hatred.
B020C015V018	20	15	18	A wrathful man stirs up contention,but one who is slow to anger appeases strife.
B020C015V019	20	15	19	The way of the sluggard is like a thorn patch,but the path of the upright is a highway.
B020C015V020	20	15	20	A wise son makes a father glad,but a foolish man despises his mother.
B020C015V021	20	15	21	Folly is joy to one who is void of wisdom,but a man of understanding keeps his way straight.
B020C015V022	20	15	22	Where there is no counsel, plans fail;but in a multitude of counselors they are established.
B020C015V023	20	15	23	Joy comes to a man with the reply of his mouth.How good is a word at the right time!
B020C015V024	20	15	24	The path of life leads upward for the wise,to keep him from going downward to Sheol.
B020C015V025	20	15	25	
        
B020C015V026	20	15	26	
        
B020C015V027	20	15	27	He who is greedy for gain troubles his own house,but he who hates bribes will live.
B020C015V028	20	15	28	The heart of the righteous weighs answers,but the mouth of the wicked gushes out evil.
B020C015V029	20	15	29	
        
B020C015V030	20	15	30	The light of the eyes rejoices the heart.Good news gives health to the bones.
B020C015V031	20	15	31	The ear that listens to reproof lives,and will be at home among the wise.
B020C015V032	20	15	32	He who refuses correction despises his own soul,but he who listens to reproof gets understanding.
