B023C001V012	23	1	12	When you come to appear before me,who has required this at your hand, to trample my courts?
B023C001V013	23	1	13	Bring no more vain offerings.Incense is an abomination to me;new moons, Sabbaths, and convocations:I can't bear with evil assemblies.
B023C001V014	23	1	14	My soul hates your New Moons and your appointed feasts.They are a burden to me.I am weary of bearing them.
B023C001V015	23	1	15	When you spread forth your hands, I will hide my eyes from you.Yes, when you make many prayers, I will not hear.Your hands are full of blood.
B023C001V016	23	1	16	Wash yourselves, make yourself clean.Put away the evil of your doings from before my eyes.Cease to do evil.
