B027C001V001	27	1	1	In the third year of the reign of Jehoiakim king of Judah came Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon to Jerusalem, and besieged it.
B027C001V002	27	1	2	The Lord gave Jehoiakim king of Judah into his hand, with part of the vessels of the house of God; and he carried them into the land of Shinar to the house of his god: and he brought the vessels into the treasure house of his god.
B027C001V003	27	1	3	The king spoke to Ashpenaz the master of his eunuchs, that he should bring in some of the children of Israel, even of the royal family and of the nobles;
B027C001V004	27	1	4	youths in whom was no blemish, but well-favored, and skillful in all wisdom, and endowed with knowledge, and understanding science, and such as had ability to stand in the king's palace; and that he should teach them the learning and the language of the Chaldeans.
B027C001V005	27	1	5	The king appointed for them a daily portion of the king's royal food, and of the wine which he drank, and that they should be nourished three years; that at its end they should stand before the king.
B027C001V006	27	1	6	Now among these were, of the children of Judah, Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah.
B027C001V007	27	1	7	The prince of the eunuchs gave names to them: to Daniel he gave the name of Belteshazzar; and to Hananiah, of Shadrach; and to Mishael, of Meshach; and to Azariah, of Abednego.
B027C001V008	27	1	8	But Daniel determined in his heart that he would not defile himself with the king's royal food, nor with the wine which he drank: therefore he requested of the prince of the eunuchs that he might not defile himself.
B027C001V009	27	1	9	Now God gave Daniel favor and compassion in the sight of the prince of the eunuchs.
B027C001V010	27	1	10	The prince of the eunuchs said to Daniel, "I fear my lord the king, who has appointed your food and your drink: for why should he see your faces worse looking than the youths who are of your own age? So would you endanger my head with the king."
B027C001V011	27	1	11	Then said Daniel to the steward whom the prince of the eunuchs had appointed over Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah:
B027C001V012	27	1	12	"Test your servants for ten days; and let them give us vegetables to eat, and water to drink.
B027C001V013	27	1	13	Then let our faces be looked on before you, and the face of the youths who eat of the king's royal food; and as you see, deal with your servants."
B027C001V014	27	1	14	So he listened to them in this matter, and tested them ten days.
B027C001V015	27	1	15	At the end of ten days their faces appeared better and fatter than all the youths who ate of the king's royal food.
B027C001V016	27	1	16	So the steward took away their royal food, and the wine that they should drink, and gave them vegetables.
B027C001V017	27	1	17	Now as for these four youths, God gave them knowledge and skill in all learning and wisdom: and Daniel had understanding in all visions and dreams.
B027C001V018	27	1	18	At the end of the days which the king had appointed for bringing them in, the prince of the eunuchs brought them in before Nebuchadnezzar.
B027C001V019	27	1	19	The king talked with them; and among them all was found none like Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah: therefore they entered the king's service.
B027C001V020	27	1	20	In every matter of wisdom and understanding, concerning which the king inquired of them, he found them ten times better than all the magicians and enchanters who were in all his realm.
B027C001V021	27	1	21	Daniel continued even to the first year of king Cyrus.
B027C002V001	27	2	1	In the second year of the reign of Nebuchadnezzar, Nebuchadnezzar had dreams; and his spirit was troubled, and his sleep went from him.
B027C002V002	27	2	2	Then the king commanded to call the magicians, and the enchanters, and the sorcerers, and the Chaldeans, to tell the king his dreams. So they came in and stood before the king.
B027C002V003	27	2	3	The king said to them, "I have had a dream, and my spirit is anxious to understand the dream."
B027C002V004	27	2	4	Then spoke the Chaldeans to the king in the Syrian language, "O king, live forever: tell your servants the dream, and we will show the interpretation."
B027C002V005	27	2	5	The king answered the Chaldeans, "The thing is gone from me: if you do not make known to me the dream and its interpretation, you shall be cut in pieces, and your houses shall be made a rubbish heap.
B027C002V006	27	2	6	But if you show the dream and its interpretation, you shall receive from me gifts and rewards and great honor: therefore show me the dream and its interpretation."
B027C002V007	27	2	7	They answered the second time and said, "Let the king tell his servants the dream, and we will show the interpretation."
B027C002V008	27	2	8	The king answered, "I know of a certainty that you would gain time, because you see the thing is gone from me.
B027C002V009	27	2	9	But if you do not make known to me the dream, there is but one law for you; for you have prepared lying and corrupt words to speak before me, until such time that things might change. Therefore tell me the dream, and I shall know that you can show me its interpretation."
B027C002V010	27	2	10	The Chaldeans answered before the king, and said, "There is not a man on the earth who can show the king's matter, because no king, lord, or ruler, has asked such a thing of any magician, or enchanter, or Chaldean.
B027C002V011	27	2	11	It is a rare thing that the king requires, and there is no other who can show it before the king, except the gods, whose dwelling is not with flesh."
B027C002V012	27	2	12	For this cause the king was angry and very furious, and commanded to destroy all the wise men of Babylon.
B027C002V013	27	2	13	So the decree went forth, and the wise men were to be killed; and they sought Daniel and his companions to be killed.
B027C002V014	27	2	14	Then Daniel returned an answer with counsel and prudence to Arioch the captain of the king's guard, who was gone forth to kill the wise men of Babylon;
B027C002V015	27	2	15	he answered Arioch the king's captain, "Why is the decree so urgent from the king?" Then Arioch made the thing known to Daniel.
B027C002V016	27	2	16	Daniel went in, and desired of the king that he would appoint him a time, and he would show the king the interpretation.
B027C002V017	27	2	17	Then Daniel went to his house, and made the thing known to Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah, his companions:
B027C002V018	27	2	18	that they would seek mercy from the God of heaven concerning this secret; that Daniel and his companions should not perish with the rest of the wise men of Babylon.
B027C002V019	27	2	19	Then was the secret revealed to Daniel in a vision of the night. Then Daniel blessed the God of heaven.
B027C002V020	27	2	20	Daniel answered, "Blessed be the name of God forever and ever; for wisdom and might are his.
B027C002V021	27	2	21	He changes the times and the seasons; he removes kings, and sets up kings; he gives wisdom to the wise, and knowledge to those who have understanding;
