B040C005V015	40	5	15	Neither do you light a lamp, and put it under a measuring basket, but on a stand; and it shines to all who are in the house.
B040C005V016	40	5	16	Even so, let your light shine before men; that they may see your good works, and glorify your Father who is in heaven.
B040C005V017	40	5	17	"Do not think that I came to destroy the Law or the Prophets. I did not come to destroy, but to fulfill.
B040C005V018	40	5	18	For truly, I tell you, until heaven and earth pass away, not even one smallest letter or one tiny pen stroke shall in any way pass away from the Law, until all things are accomplished.
B040C005V019	40	5	19	Whoever, therefore, shall break one of these least commandments, and teach others to do so, shall be called least in the Kingdom of Heaven; but whoever shall do and teach them shall be called great in the Kingdom of Heaven.
B040C005V020	40	5	20	For I tell you that unless your righteousness exceeds that of the scribes and Pharisees, there is no way you will enter into the Kingdom of Heaven.
B040C005V021	40	5	21	"You have heard that it was said to the ancient ones, 'You shall not murder;' and 'Whoever shall murder shall be in danger of the judgment.'
B040C005V022	40	5	22	But I tell you, that everyone who is angry with his brother shall be in danger of the judgment; and whoever shall say to his brother, 'You good-for-nothing!' shall be in danger of the council; and whoever shall say, 'You fool!' shall be in danger of the fire of hell.
B040C005V023	40	5	23	"If therefore you are offering your gift at the altar, and there remember that your brother has anything against you,
B040C005V024	40	5	24	leave your gift there before the altar, and go your way. First be reconciled to your brother, and then come and offer your gift.
B040C005V025	40	5	25	Agree with your adversary quickly, while you are with him in the way; lest perhaps the prosecutor deliver you to the judge, and the judge deliver you to the officer, and you be cast into prison.
B040C005V026	40	5	26	Truly I tell you, you shall by no means get out of there, until you have paid the last penny.
B040C005V027	40	5	27	"You have heard that it was said, 'You shall not commit adultery;'
B040C005V028	40	5	28	but I tell you that everyone who gazes at a woman to lust after her has committed adultery with her already in his heart.
B040C005V029	40	5	29	And if your right eye causes you to stumble, pluck it out and throw it away from you. For it is more profitable for you that one of your members should perish, than for your whole body to be cast into hell.
B040C005V030	40	5	30	And if your right hand causes you to stumble, cut it off, and throw it away from you. For it is more profitable for you that one of your members should perish, than for your whole body to be cast into hell.
B040C005V031	40	5	31	"It was also said, 'Whoever shall put away his wife, let him give her a writing of divorce,'
B040C005V032	40	5	32	but I tell you that whoever puts away his wife, except for the cause of sexual immorality, makes her an adulteress; and whoever marries her when she is put away commits adultery.
B040C005V033	40	5	33	"Again you have heard that it was said to them of old time, 'You shall not make false vows, but shall perform to 
B040C005V034	40	5	34	but I tell you, do not swear at all: neither by heaven, for it is the throne of God;
B040C005V035	40	5	35	nor by the earth, for it is the footstool of his feet; nor by Jerusalem, for it is the city of the great King.
B040C005V036	40	5	36	Neither shall you swear by your head, for you cannot make one hair white or black.
B040C005V037	40	5	37	But let your 'Yes' be 'Yes' and your 'No' be 'No.' Whatever is more than these is of the evil one.
B040C005V038	40	5	38	"You have heard that it was said, 'An eye for an eye, and a tooth for a tooth.'
B040C005V039	40	5	39	But I tell you, do not resist him who is evil; but whoever strikes you on your right cheek, turn to him the other also.
B040C005V040	40	5	40	And if anyone sues you to take away your coat, let him have your cloak also.
B040C005V041	40	5	41	And whoever compels you to go one mile, go with him two.
B040C005V042	40	5	42	Give to him who asks you, and do not turn away him who desires to borrow from you.
B040C005V043	40	5	43	"You have heard that it was said, 'You shall love your neighbor, and hate your enemy.'
B040C005V044	40	5	44	But I tell you, love your enemies, and pray for those who persecute you,
B040C005V045	40	5	45	that you may be children of your Father who is in heaven. For he makes his sun to rise on the evil and the good, and sends rain on the just and the unjust.
B040C005V046	40	5	46	For if you love those who love you, what reward do you have? Do not even the tax collectors do the same?
B040C005V047	40	5	47	And if you only greet your brothers, what more do you do than others? Do not even the tax collectors do the same?
B040C005V048	40	5	48	Therefore you shall be perfect, as your heavenly Father is perfect.
B040C006V001	40	6	1	"Be careful that you do not do your acts of charity before men, to be seen by them, or else you have no reward from your Father who is in heaven.
B040C006V002	40	6	2	Therefore when you do merciful deeds, do not sound a trumpet before yourself, as the hypocrites do in the synagogues and in the streets, that they may get glory from people. Truly I tell you, they have received their reward.
B040C006V003	40	6	3	But when you do merciful deeds, do not let your left hand know what your right hand does,
B040C006V004	40	6	4	so that your merciful deeds may be in secret, then your Father who sees in secret will reward you.
B040C006V005	40	6	5	"And when you pray, you shall not be as the hypocrites, for they love to stand and pray in the synagogues and in the corners of the streets, that they may be seen by others. Truly, I tell you, they have received their reward.
B040C006V006	40	6	6	But you, when you pray, enter into your inner chamber, and having shut your door, pray to your Father who is in secret, and your Father who sees in secret will reward you.
B040C006V007	40	6	7	And in praying, do not use vain repetitions, as the Gentiles do; for they think that they will be heard for their much speaking.
B040C006V008	40	6	8	Therefore do not be like them, for your Father knows what things you need, before you ask him.
B040C006V009	40	6	9	Pray like this:'Our Father in heaven, may your name be kept holy.
B040C006V010	40	6	10	Let your Kingdom come. Let your will be done, on earth as it is in heaven.
B040C006V011	40	6	11	Give us today our daily bread.
B040C006V012	40	6	12	And forgive us our debts, as we also forgive our debtors.
B040C006V013	40	6	13	Let us not come into temptation, but deliver us from the evil one. [For yours is the kingdom, the power, and the glory forever. Amen.]'
B040C006V014	40	6	14	"For if you forgive men their trespasses, your heavenly Father will also forgive you.
B040C006V015	40	6	15	But if you do not forgive men, neither will your Father forgive your trespasses.
B040C006V016	40	6	16	"Moreover when you fast, do not be like the hypocrites, with sad faces. For they disfigure their faces, that they may be seen by men to be fasting. Truly I tell you, they have received their reward.
B040C006V017	40	6	17	But you, when you fast, anoint your head, and wash your face;
B040C006V018	40	6	18	so that you are not seen by men to be fasting, but by your Father who is in secret, and your Father, who sees in secret, will reward you.
B040C006V019	40	6	19	"Do not lay up treasures for yourselves on the earth, where moth and rust consume, and where thieves break through and steal;
B040C006V020	40	6	20	but lay up for yourselves treasures in heaven, where neither moth nor rust consume, and where thieves do not break through and steal;
B040C006V021	40	6	21	for where your treasure is, there your heart will be also.
B040C006V022	40	6	22	"The lamp of the body is the eye. If therefore your eye is sound, your whole body will be full of light.
B040C006V023	40	6	23	But if your eye is bad, your whole body will be full of darkness. If therefore the light that is in you is darkness, how great is the darkness!
B040C006V024	40	6	24	"No one can serve two masters, for either he will hate the one and love the other; or else he will be devoted to one and despise the other. You cannot serve both God and Mammon.
B040C006V025	40	6	25	Therefore, I tell you, do not be anxious for your life: what you will eat, or what you will drink; nor yet for your body, what you will wear. Is not life more than food, and the body more than clothing?
B040C006V026	40	6	26	See the birds of the sky, that they do not sow, neither do they reap, nor gather into barns. Your heavenly Father feeds them. Are you not of much more value than they?
B040C006V027	40	6	27	"And which of you, by being anxious, can add one moment to his lifespan?
B040C006V028	40	6	28	And why are you anxious about clothing? Consider the lilies of the field, how they grow. They do not toil, neither do they spin,
B040C006V029	40	6	29	yet I tell you that even Solomon in all his glory was not dressed like one of these.
B040C006V030	40	6	30	But if God so clothes the grass of the field, which today exists, and tomorrow is thrown into the oven, won't he much more clothe you, you of little faith?
B040C006V031	40	6	31	"Therefore do not be anxious, saying, 'What will we eat?', 'What will we drink?' or, 'With what will we be clothed?'
B040C006V032	40	6	32	For the Gentiles seek after all these things, for your heavenly Father knows that you need all these things.
B040C006V033	40	6	33	But seek first his Kingdom, and his righteousness; and all these things will be given to you as well.
B040C006V034	40	6	34	Therefore do not be anxious for tomorrow, for tomorrow will be anxious for itself. Each day has enough trouble of its own.
B040C007V001	40	7	1	"Do not judge, so that you won't be judged.
B040C007V002	40	7	2	For with whatever judgment you judge, you will be judged; and with whatever measure you measure, it will be measured to you.
B040C007V003	40	7	3	And why do you see the speck that is in your brother's eye, but do not consider the log that is in your own eye?
B040C007V004	40	7	4	Or how will you tell your brother, 'Let me remove the speck from your eye;' and behold, the log is in your own eye?
B040C007V005	40	7	5	You hypocrite! First remove the log out of your own eye, and then you can see clearly to remove the speck out of your brother's eye.
B040C007V006	40	7	6	"Do not give that which is holy to the dogs, neither throw your pearls before the pigs, lest perhaps they trample them under their feet, and turn and tear you to pieces.
B040C007V007	40	7	7	"Ask, and it will be given you. Seek, and you will find. Knock, and it will be opened for you.
B040C007V008	40	7	8	For everyone who asks receives. He who seeks finds. To him who knocks it will be opened.
B040C007V009	40	7	9	Or who is there among you, who, if his son will ask him for bread, will give him a stone?
B040C007V010	40	7	10	Or if he will ask for a fish, who will give him a serpent?
B040C007V011	40	7	11	If you then, being evil, know how to give good gifts to your children, how much more will your Father who is in heaven give good things to those who ask him!
B040C007V012	40	7	12	Therefore whatever you desire for men to do to you, you shall also do to them; for this is the Law and the Prophets.
B040C007V013	40	7	13	"Enter in by the narrow gate; for wide is the gate and broad is the way that leads to destruction, and many are those who enter in by it.
B040C007V014	40	7	14	How narrow is the gate, and difficult is the way that leads to life! Few are those who find it.
B040C007V015	40	7	15	"Beware of false prophets, who come to you in sheep's clothing, but inwardly are ravening wolves.
B040C007V016	40	7	16	By their fruits you will know them. Do you gather grapes from thorns, or figs from thistles?
B040C007V017	40	7	17	Even so, every good tree produces good fruit; but the corrupt tree produces evil fruit.
B040C007V018	40	7	18	A good tree cannot produce evil fruit, neither can a corrupt tree produce good fruit.
B040C007V019	40	7	19	Every tree that does not grow good fruit is cut down, and thrown into the fire.
B040C007V020	40	7	20	Therefore, by their fruits you will know them.
B040C007V021	40	7	21	Not everyone who says to me, 'Lord, Lord,' will enter into the Kingdom of Heaven; but he who does the will of my Father who is in heaven.
B040C007V022	40	7	22	Many will tell me in that day, 'Lord, Lord, did not we prophesy in your name, in your name cast out demons, and in your name do many mighty works?'
B040C007V023	40	7	23	And then I will tell them, 'I never knew you. Depart from me, you who work iniquity.'
B040C007V024	40	7	24	"Everyone therefore who hears these words of mine, and does them, will be compared to a wise man, who built his house on a rock.
B040C007V025	40	7	25	And the rain came down, the floods came, and the winds blew, and beat on that house; and it did not fall, for it was founded on the rock.
B040C007V026	40	7	26	And everyone who hears these words of mine, and does not do them will be like a foolish man, who built his house on the sand.
B040C007V027	40	7	27	And the rain came down, the floods came, and the winds blew, and beat on that house; and it fell-and great was its fall."
B040C007V028	40	7	28	And it happened, when Jesus had finished saying these things, that the multitudes were astonished at his teaching,
B040C007V029	40	7	29	for he taught them with authority, and not like their scribes.
B040C008V001	40	8	1	And when he came down from the mountain, great multitudes followed him.
