B040C010V001	40	10	1	And he called to himself his twelve disciples, and gave them authority over unclean spirits, to cast them out, and to heal every disease and every sickness.
B040C010V002	40	10	2	Now the names of the twelve apostles are these. The first, Simon, who is called Peter; and Andrew his brother; and Jacob the son of Zebedee, and John his brother;
B040C010V003	40	10	3	Philip and Bartholomew; Thomas and Matthew the tax collector; Jacob the son of Alphaeus, and Thaddaeus;
B040C010V004	40	10	4	Simon the Zealot, and Judas Iscariot, who also betrayed him.
B040C010V005	40	10	5	Jesus sent these twelve out, and commanded them, saying, "Do not go among the Gentiles, and do not enter into any city of the Samaritans.
B040C010V006	40	10	6	Rather, go to the lost sheep of the house of Israel.
B040C010V007	40	10	7	And as you go, proclaim, saying, 'The Kingdom of Heaven is near!'
B040C010V008	40	10	8	Heal the sick, raise the dead, cleanse the lepers, and cast out demons. Freely you received, so freely give.
B040C010V009	40	10	9	Do not take any gold, nor silver, nor brass in your money belts.
