B040C010V019	40	10	19	But when they deliver you up, do not be anxious how or what you will say, for it will be given you in that hour what you will say.
B040C010V020	40	10	20	For it is not you who speak, but the Spirit of your Father who speaks in you.
B040C010V021	40	10	21	"And brother will deliver up brother to death, and the father his child. Children will rise up against parents, and cause them to be put to death.
B040C010V022	40	10	22	And you will be hated by all men for my name's sake, but he who endures to the end will be saved.
B040C010V023	40	10	23	But when they persecute you in this city, flee into the next, for truly I tell you, you will not have gone through the cities of Israel, until the Son of Man has come.
B040C010V024	40	10	24	"A disciple is not above his teacher, nor a servant above his lord.
B040C010V025	40	10	25	It is enough for the disciple that he be like his teacher, and the servant like his lord. If they have called the master of the house Beelzebul, how much more those of his household!
B040C010V026	40	10	26	Therefore do not be afraid of them, for there is nothing covered that will not be revealed; and hidden that will not be known.
B040C010V027	40	10	27	What I tell you in the darkness, speak in the light; and what you hear whispered in the ear, proclaim on the housetops.
B040C010V028	40	10	28	And do not be afraid of those who kill the body, but are not able to kill the soul. Rather, fear him who is able to destroy both soul and body in hell.
B040C010V029	40	10	29	"Are not two sparrows sold for an assarion coin? Not one of them falls on the ground apart from your Father's will,
B040C010V030	40	10	30	but the very hairs of your head are all numbered.
B040C010V031	40	10	31	Therefore do not be afraid. You are of more value than many sparrows.
B040C010V032	40	10	32	Everyone therefore who confesses me before men, him I will also confess before my Father who is in heaven.
B040C010V033	40	10	33	But whoever denies me before people, him I will also deny before my Father who is in heaven.
B040C010V034	40	10	34	"Do not think that I came to send peace on the earth. I did not come to send peace, but a sword.
B040C010V035	40	10	35	For I came to set a man at odds against his father, and a daughter against her mother, and a daughter-in-law against her mother-in-law.
B040C010V036	40	10	36	And a man's foes will be those of his own household.
B040C010V037	40	10	37	He who loves father or mother more than me is not worthy of me; and he who loves son or daughter more than me is not worthy of me.
B040C010V038	40	10	38	And whoever does not take his cross and follow after me, is not worthy of me.
B040C010V039	40	10	39	He who seeks his life will lose it; and he who loses his life for my sake will find it.
B040C010V040	40	10	40	He who receives you receives me, and he who receives me receives him who sent me.
B040C010V041	40	10	41	He who receives a prophet because he is a prophet will receive a prophet's reward. He who receives a righteous man because he is a righteous man will receive a righteous man's reward.
B040C010V042	40	10	42	And whoever gives one of these little ones just a cup of cold water to drink because he is a disciple, truly I tell you he will in no way lose his reward."
B040C011V001	40	11	1	And it happened that when Jesus had finished directing his twelve disciples, he departed from there to teach and proclaim in their cities.
B040C011V002	40	11	2	Now when John heard in the prison the works of the Messiah, he sent his disciples
B040C011V003	40	11	3	and said to him, "Are you the One who is to come, or should we look for another?"
B040C011V004	40	11	4	And Jesus answered them, "Go and tell John the things which you hear and see:
B040C011V005	40	11	5	the blind receive their sight, the lame walk, the lepers are cleansed, the deaf hear, the dead are raised up, and the poor have good news preached to them.
B040C011V006	40	11	6	And blessed is he who is not offended by me."
B040C011V007	40	11	7	And as these went their way, Jesus began to say to the multitudes concerning John, "What did you go out into the wilderness to see? A reed shaken by the wind?
B040C011V008	40	11	8	But what did you go out to see? A man in soft clothing? Behold, those who wear soft clothing are in kings' houses.
B040C011V009	40	11	9	But why did you go out? To see a prophet? Yes, I tell you, and much more than a prophet.
B040C011V010	40	11	10	This is the one of whom it is written, 'Behold, I send my messenger before your face, who will prepare your way before you.'
B040C011V011	40	11	11	Truly I tell you, among those who are born of women there has not arisen anyone greater than John the Baptist; yet he who is least in the Kingdom of Heaven is greater than he.
B040C011V012	40	11	12	And from the days of John the Baptist until now, the Kingdom of Heaven suffers violence, and the violent take it by force.
B040C011V013	40	11	13	For all the Prophets and the Law prophesied until John.
B040C011V014	40	11	14	And if you are willing to receive it, this is Elijah, who is to come.
B040C011V015	40	11	15	He who has ears to hear, let him hear.
B040C011V016	40	11	16	"But to what shall I compare this generation? It is like children sitting in the marketplaces, who call to their companions
B040C011V017	40	11	17	and say, 'We played the flute for you, and you did not dance. We sang a dirge, and you did not mourn.'
B040C011V018	40	11	18	For John came neither eating nor drinking, and they say, 'He has a demon.'
B040C011V019	40	11	19	The Son of Man came eating and drinking, and they say, 'Behold, a gluttonous man and a drunkard, a friend of tax collectors and sinners!' But wisdom is justified by her actions."
B040C011V020	40	11	20	Then he began to denounce the cities in which most of his mighty works had been done, because they did not repent.
B040C011V021	40	11	21	"Woe to you, Chorazin! Woe to you, Bethsaida! For if the mighty works had been done in Tyre and Sidon which were done in you, they would have repented long ago in sackcloth and ashes.
B040C011V022	40	11	22	But I tell you, it will be more tolerable for Tyre and Sidon on the day of judgment than for you.
B040C011V023	40	11	23	And you, Capernaum, who are exalted to heaven, you will go down to hell. For if the mighty works had been done in Sodom which were done in you, it would have remained until this day.
B040C011V024	40	11	24	But I tell you that it will be more tolerable for the land of Sodom, on the day of judgment, than for you."
B040C011V025	40	11	25	At that time, Jesus answered, "I thank you, Father, Lord of heaven and earth, that you hid these things from the wise and understanding, and revealed them to infants.
B040C011V026	40	11	26	Yes, Father, for so it was well-pleasing in your sight.
B040C011V027	40	11	27	All things have been delivered to me by my Father. No one knows the Son, except the Father; neither does anyone know the Father, except the Son, and he to whom the Son desires to reveal him.
B040C011V028	40	11	28	"Come to me, all you who labor and are heavily burdened, and I will give you rest.
B040C011V029	40	11	29	Take my yoke upon you, and learn from me, for I am gentle and lowly in heart; and you will find rest for your souls.
B040C011V030	40	11	30	For my yoke is easy, and my burden is light."
B040C012V001	40	12	1	At that time, Jesus went on the Sabbath day through the grain fields. His disciples were hungry and began to pluck heads of grain and to eat.
B040C012V002	40	12	2	But the Pharisees, when they saw it, said to him, "Behold, your disciples do what is not lawful to do on the Sabbath."
B040C012V003	40	12	3	But he said to them, "Have not you read what David did, when he was hungry, he and his companions;
B040C012V004	40	12	4	how he entered into the house of God, and ate the show bread, which was not lawful for him to eat, neither for those who were with him, but only for the priests?
B040C012V005	40	12	5	Or have you not read in the Law, that on the Sabbath day, the priests in the temple profane the Sabbath, and are guiltless?
B040C012V006	40	12	6	But I tell you that something greater than the temple is here.
B040C012V007	40	12	7	But if you had known what this means, 'I desire mercy, and not sacrifice,' you would not have condemned the guiltless.
B040C012V008	40	12	8	For the Son of Man is Lord of the Sabbath."
B040C012V009	40	12	9	And he departed there, and went into their synagogue.
B040C012V010	40	12	10	And behold there was a man with a withered hand. They asked him, "Is it lawful to heal on the Sabbath day?" that they might accuse him.
B040C012V011	40	12	11	And he said to them, "What man is there among you, who has one sheep, and if this one falls into a pit on the Sabbath day, won't he grab on to it, and lift it out?
B040C012V012	40	12	12	Of how much more value then is a man than a sheep! Therefore it is lawful to do good on the Sabbath day."
B040C012V013	40	12	13	Then he told the man, "Stretch out your hand." He stretched it out; and it was restored whole, just like the other.
B040C012V014	40	12	14	But the Pharisees went out, and conspired against him, how they might destroy him.
B040C012V015	40	12	15	But Jesus, perceiving that, withdrew from there. Many followed him; and he healed them all,
B040C012V016	40	12	16	and commanded them that they should not make him known:
B040C012V017	40	12	17	that it might be fulfilled which was spoken through Isaiah the prophet, saying,
B040C012V018	40	12	18	"Behold, my servant whom I have chosen;my beloved in whom my soul is well pleased:I will put my Spirit on him.And he will proclaim justice to the nations.
B040C012V019	40	12	19	He will not strive, nor shout;neither will anyone hear his voice in the streets.
B040C012V020	40	12	20	He won't break a bruised reed.And he won't quench a smoking flax,until he leads justice to victory.
B040C012V021	40	12	21	And in his name, the nations will hope." 
B040C012V022	40	12	22	Then one possessed by a demon, blind and mute, was brought to him and he healed him, so that the mute man both spoke and saw.
B040C012V023	40	12	23	And all the multitudes were amazed, and said, "Can this be the son of David?"
B040C012V024	40	12	24	But when the Pharisees heard it, they said, "This man does not cast out demons, except by Beelzebul, the prince of the demons."
B040C012V025	40	12	25	And knowing their thoughts, he said to them, "Every kingdom divided against itself is brought to desolation, and every city or house divided against itself will not stand.
B040C012V026	40	12	26	And if Satan casts out Satan, he is divided against himself. How then will his kingdom stand?
B040C012V027	40	12	27	If I by Beelzebub cast out demons, by whom do your children cast them out? Therefore they will be your judges.
B040C012V028	40	12	28	But if I by the Spirit of God cast out demons, then the Kingdom of God has come upon you.
B040C012V029	40	12	29	Or how can one enter into the house of the strong man, and carry off his possessions, unless he first bind the strong man? And then he will plunder his house.
B040C012V030	40	12	30	"He who is not with me is against me, and he who does not gather with me, scatters.
B040C012V031	40	12	31	Therefore I tell you, every sin and blasphemy will be forgiven men, but the blasphemy against the Spirit will not be forgiven.
B040C012V032	40	12	32	And whoever speaks a word against the Son of Man, it will be forgiven him; but whoever speaks against the Holy Spirit, it will not be forgiven him, neither in this age, nor in that which is to come.
B040C012V033	40	12	33	"Either make the tree good, and its fruit good, or make the tree corrupt, and its fruit corrupt; for the tree is known by its fruit.
B040C012V034	40	12	34	You offspring of vipers, how can you, being evil, speak good things? For out of the abundance of the heart, the mouth speaks.
B040C012V035	40	12	35	The good man out of his good treasure brings out good things, and the evil man out of his evil treasure brings out evil things.
B040C012V036	40	12	36	But I tell you that every idle word that men speak, they will give account of it in the day of judgment.
B040C012V037	40	12	37	For by your words you will be justified, and by your words you will be condemned."
B040C012V038	40	12	38	Then certain of the scribes and Pharisees said to him, "Teacher, we want to see a sign from you."
B040C012V039	40	12	39	But he answered them, "An evil and adulterous generation seeks after a sign, but no sign will be given it but the sign of Jonah the prophet.
B040C012V040	40	12	40	For as Jonah was three days and three nights in the belly of the whale, so will the Son of Man be three days and three nights in the heart of the earth.
B040C012V041	40	12	41	The men of Nineveh will stand up in the judgment with this generation, and will condemn it, for they repented at the proclaiming of Jonah; and behold, something greater than Jonah is here.
B040C012V042	40	12	42	The queen of the south will rise up in the judgment with this generation, and will condemn it, for she came from the ends of the earth to hear the wisdom of Solomon; and behold, someone greater than Solomon is here.
B040C012V043	40	12	43	But the unclean spirit, when he is gone out of the man, passes through waterless places, seeking rest, and does not find it.
B040C012V044	40	12	44	Then he says, 'I will return into my house from which I came out,' and when he has come back, he finds it empty, swept, and put in order.
B040C012V045	40	12	45	Then he goes, and takes with himself seven other spirits more evil than he is, and they enter in and dwell there. The last state of that man becomes worse than the first. Even so will it be also to this evil generation."
B040C012V046	40	12	46	While he was yet speaking to the multitudes, behold, his mother and his brothers stood outside, seeking to speak to him.
B040C012V047	40	12	47	Then one said to him, "Behold, your mother and your brothers stand outside, seeking to speak to you."
B040C012V048	40	12	48	But he answered him who spoke to him, "Who is my mother? Who are my brothers?"
B040C012V049	40	12	49	And he stretched out his hand towards his disciples, and said, "Behold, my mother and my brothers!
B040C012V050	40	12	50	For whoever does the will of my Father who is in heaven, he is my brother, and sister, and mother."
B040C013V001	40	13	1	On that day Jesus went out of the house, and sat by the seaside.
B040C013V002	40	13	2	And great multitudes gathered to him, so that he entered into a boat, and sat, and all the multitude stood on the beach.
B040C013V003	40	13	3	And he spoke to them many things in parables, saying, "Behold, a farmer went out to sow.
B040C013V004	40	13	4	And as he sowed, some seeds fell by the roadside, and the birds came and devoured them.
B040C013V005	40	13	5	And others fell on rocky ground, where they did not have much soil, and immediately they sprang up, because they had no depth of earth.
B040C013V006	40	13	6	But when the sun had risen, they were scorched. Because they had no root, they withered away.
B040C013V007	40	13	7	Others fell among thorns. The thorns grew up and choked them.
B040C013V008	40	13	8	Still others fell on good soil, and yielded fruit: some one hundred times as much, some sixty, and some thirty.
B040C013V009	40	13	9	He who has ears, let him hear."
B040C013V010	40	13	10	Then the disciples came, and said to him, "Why do you speak to them in parables?"
B040C013V011	40	13	11	And he answered them, "To you it is given to know the mysteries of the Kingdom of Heaven, but it is not given to them.
B040C013V012	40	13	12	For whoever has, to him will be given, and he will have abundance, but whoever does not have, from him will be taken away even that which he has.
B040C013V013	40	13	13	Therefore I speak to them in parables, because seeing they do not see, and hearing, they do not hear, neither do they understand.
B040C013V014	40	13	14	And in them the prophecy of Isaiah is fulfilled, which says, 'By hearing you will hear,and will in no way understand;Seeing you will see,and will in no way perceive:
B040C013V015	40	13	15	for this people's heart has grown callous,and their ears are dull of hearing,and they have closed their eyes;or else perhaps they might perceive with their eyes,hear with their ears,understand with their heart,and should turn again;and I would heal them.' 
B040C013V016	40	13	16	"But blessed are your eyes, for they see; and your ears, for they hear.
B040C013V017	40	13	17	For truly I tell you that many prophets and righteous men desired to see the things which you see, and did not see them; and to hear the things which you hear, and did not hear them.
B040C013V018	40	13	18	"Hear, then, the parable of the farmer.
B040C013V019	40	13	19	When anyone hears the word of the Kingdom, and does not understand it, the evil one comes, and snatches away that which has been sown in his heart. This is what was sown by the roadside.
B040C013V020	40	13	20	And what was sown on the rocky places, this is he who hears the word, and immediately with joy receives it;
B040C013V021	40	13	21	yet he has no root in himself, but endures for a while. When oppression or persecution arises because of the word, immediately he stumbles.
B040C013V022	40	13	22	And what was sown among the thorns, this is he who hears the word, but the cares of the world and the deceitfulness of riches choke the word, and he becomes unfruitful.
B040C013V023	40	13	23	And what was sown on the good ground, this is he who hears the word, and understands it, who truly bears fruit, and brings forth, some one hundred times as much, some sixty, and some thirty."
B040C013V024	40	13	24	He set another parable before them, saying, "The Kingdom of Heaven is like a man who sowed good seed in his field,
B040C013V025	40	13	25	but while people slept, his enemy came and sowed tares also among the wheat, and went away.
B040C013V026	40	13	26	But when the blade sprang up and brought forth fruit, then the tares appeared also.
B040C013V027	40	13	27	So the servants of the householder came and said to him, 'Sir, did you not sow good seed in your field? Where did these tares come from?'
B040C013V028	40	13	28	"And he said to them, 'An enemy has done this.'
B040C013V029	40	13	29	"But he said, 'No, lest perhaps while you gather up the tares, you root up the wheat with them.
B040C013V030	40	13	30	Let both grow together until the harvest, and in the harvest time I will tell the reapers, "First, gather up the tares, and bind them in bundles to burn them; but gather the wheat into my barn."'"
B040C013V031	40	13	31	He set another parable before them, saying, "The Kingdom of Heaven is like a grain of mustard seed, which a man took, and sowed in his field;
B040C013V032	40	13	32	which indeed is smaller than all seeds. But when it is grown, it is greater than the herbs, and becomes a tree, so that the birds of the air come and lodge in its branches."
B040C013V033	40	13	33	He spoke another parable to them. "The Kingdom of Heaven is like yeast, which a woman took, and hid in three measures of meal, until it was all leavened."
B040C013V034	40	13	34	Jesus spoke all these things in parables to the multitudes; and without a parable, he did not speak to them,
B040C013V035	40	13	35	that it might be fulfilled which was spoken through the prophet, saying,
B040C013V036	40	13	36	Then Jesus sent the multitudes away, and went into the house. His disciples came to him, saying, "Explain to us the parable of the tares in the field."
B040C013V037	40	13	37	And he answered them, "The one who sows the good seed is the Son of Man,
B040C013V038	40	13	38	and the field is the world; and the good seed, these are the sons of the Kingdom; and the tares are the sons of the evil one,
B040C013V039	40	13	39	and the enemy who sowed them is the devil, and the harvest is the end of the age, and the reapers are angels.
B040C013V040	40	13	40	As therefore the tares are gathered up and burned with fire; so will it be at the end of the age.
B040C013V041	40	13	41	The Son of Man will send out his angels, and they will gather out of his Kingdom all things that cause stumbling, and those who do iniquity,
B040C013V042	40	13	42	and will cast them into the furnace of fire. There will be weeping and the gnashing of teeth.
B040C013V043	40	13	43	Then the righteous will shine forth like the sun in the Kingdom of their Father. He who has ears, let him hear.
B040C013V044	40	13	44	"The Kingdom of Heaven is like a treasure hidden in the field, which a man found, and hid. In his joy, he goes and sells all that he has, and buys that field.
B040C013V045	40	13	45	"Again, the Kingdom of Heaven is like a man who is a merchant seeking fine pearls,
B040C013V046	40	13	46	and having found one pearl of great price, he went and sold all that he had, and bought it.
B040C013V047	40	13	47	"Again, the Kingdom of Heaven is like a dragnet, that was cast into the sea, and gathered some fish of every kind,
B040C013V048	40	13	48	which, when it was filled, they drew up on the beach. They sat down, and gathered the good into containers, but the bad they threw away.
B040C013V049	40	13	49	So will it be in the end of the world. The angels will come forth, and separate the wicked from among the righteous,
B040C013V050	40	13	50	and will cast them into the furnace of fire. There will be the weeping and the gnashing of teeth."
B040C013V051	40	13	51	"Have you understood all these things?"
B040C013V052	40	13	52	And he said to them, "Therefore, every scribe who has been made a disciple in the Kingdom of Heaven is like a man who is a householder, who brings out of his treasure new and old things."
B040C013V053	40	13	53	And it happened that when Jesus had finished these parables, he departed from there.
B040C013V054	40	13	54	And coming into his own country, he taught them in their synagogue, so that they were astonished, and said, "Where did this man get this wisdom, and these mighty works?
