B040C014V001	40	14	1	At that time, Herod the tetrarch heard the report concerning Jesus,
B040C014V002	40	14	2	and said to his servants, "This is John the Baptist. He is risen from the dead. That is why these powers work in him."
B040C014V003	40	14	3	For Herod had arrested John, and bound him, and put him in prison for the sake of Herodias, his brother Philip's wife.
B040C014V004	40	14	4	For John said to him, "It is not lawful for you to have her."
B040C014V005	40	14	5	And when he would have put him to death, he feared the multitude, because they counted him as a prophet.
B040C014V006	40	14	6	But when Herod's birthday came, the daughter of Herodias danced among them and pleased Herod.
B040C014V007	40	14	7	Whereupon he promised with an oath to give her whatever she should ask.
B040C014V008	40	14	8	And she, being prompted by her mother, said, "Give me here on a platter the head of John the Baptist."
