B040C015V001	40	15	1	Then the Pharisees and scribes came to Jesus from Jerusalem, saying,
B040C015V002	40	15	2	"Why do your disciples disobey the tradition of the elders? For they do not wash their hands when they eat bread."
B040C015V003	40	15	3	And he answered them, "Why do you also disobey the commandment of God because of your tradition?
B040C015V004	40	15	4	For God said, 'Honor your father and your mother,' and, 'He who speaks evil of father or mother, let him be put to death.'
B040C015V005	40	15	5	But you say, 'Whoever may tell his father or his mother, "Whatever help you might otherwise have gotten from me is a gift devoted to God,"
B040C015V006	40	15	6	he shall not honor his father or mother.' You have made the word of God void because of your tradition.
B040C015V007	40	15	7	You hypocrites! Well did Isaiah prophesy of you, saying,
B040C015V008	40	15	8	'These people honor me with their lips;but their heart is far from me.
B040C015V009	40	15	9	And in vain do they worship me,teaching as doctrine rules made by men.'" 
B040C015V010	40	15	10	He summoned the multitude, and said to them, "Hear, and understand.
B040C015V011	40	15	11	That which enters into the mouth does not defile the man; but that which proceeds out of the mouth, this defiles the man."
B040C015V012	40	15	12	Then the disciples came, and said to him, "Do you know that the Pharisees were offended, when they heard this saying?"
B040C015V013	40	15	13	But he answered, "Every plant which my heavenly Father did not plant will be uprooted.
B040C015V014	40	15	14	Leave them alone. They are blind guides of the blind. If the blind guide the blind, both will fall into a pit."
