B040C015V016	40	15	16	So he said, "Do you also still not understand?
B040C015V017	40	15	17	Do you not understand that whatever goes into the mouth passes into the belly, and then out of the body?
B040C015V018	40	15	18	But the things which proceed out of the mouth come out of the heart, and they defile the man.
B040C015V019	40	15	19	For out of the heart come forth evil thoughts, murders, adulteries, sexual sins, thefts, false testimony, and blasphemies.
B040C015V020	40	15	20	These are the things which defile the man; but to eat with unwashed hands does not defile the man."
B040C015V021	40	15	21	Jesus went out from there, and withdrew into the region of Tyre and Sidon.
B040C015V022	40	15	22	Behold, a Canaanite woman came out from those borders, and started shouting, saying, "Have mercy on me, Lord, you son of David! My daughter is severely demonized!"
B040C015V023	40	15	23	But he answered her not a word.
B040C015V024	40	15	24	But he answered, "I was not sent to anyone but the lost sheep of the house of Israel."
B040C015V025	40	15	25	But she came and worshiped him, saying, "Lord, help me."
B040C015V026	40	15	26	But he answered, "It is not appropriate to take the children's bread and throw it to the dogs."
B040C015V027	40	15	27	But she said, "Yes, Lord, but even the dogs eat the crumbs which fall from their masters' table."
B040C015V028	40	15	28	Then Jesus answered her, "Woman, great is your faith! Be it done to you even as you desire." And her daughter was healed from that hour.
