B040C018V011	40	18	11	For the Son of Man came to save what was lost.]
B040C018V012	40	18	12	"What do you think? If a man has one hundred sheep, and one of them goes astray, does not he leave the ninety-nine, go to the mountains, and seek that which has gone astray?
B040C018V013	40	18	13	If he finds it, truly I tell you, he rejoices over it more than over the ninety-nine which have not gone astray.
B040C018V014	40	18	14	Even so it is not the will of your Father who is in heaven that one of these little ones should perish.
B040C018V015	40	18	15	"If your brother sins against you, go, show him his fault between you and him alone. If he listens to you, you have gained back your brother.
B040C018V016	40	18	16	But if he does not listen, take one or two more with you, that at the mouth of two or three witnesses every word may be established.
B040C018V017	40	18	17	If he refuses to listen to them, tell it to the church. If he refuses to hear the church also, let him be to you as a Gentile or a tax collector.
B040C018V018	40	18	18	Truly I tell you, whatever things you bind on earth will have been bound in heaven, and whatever things you release on earth will have been released in heaven.
B040C018V019	40	18	19	Again, truly I tell you, that if two of you will agree on earth concerning anything that they will ask, it will be done for them by my Father who is in heaven.
B040C018V020	40	18	20	For where two or three are gathered together in my name, there I am in the midst of them."
B040C018V021	40	18	21	Then Peter came to him and said, "Lord, how often shall my brother sin against me, and I forgive him? Until seven times?"
B040C018V022	40	18	22	Jesus said to him, "I do not tell you until seven times, but, until seventy times seven.
B040C018V023	40	18	23	Therefore the Kingdom of Heaven is like a certain king, who wanted to reconcile accounts with his servants.
B040C018V024	40	18	24	When he had begun to reconcile, one was brought to him who owed him ten thousand talents.
B040C018V025	40	18	25	But because he could not pay, his lord commanded him to be sold, with his wife, his children, and all that he had, and payment to be made.
B040C018V026	40	18	26	The servant therefore fell down and kneeled before him, saying, 'Have patience with me, and I will repay you all!'
B040C018V027	40	18	27	The lord of that servant, being moved with compassion, released him, and forgave him the debt.
B040C018V028	40	18	28	"But that servant went out, and found one of his fellow servants, who owed him one hundred denarii, and he grabbed him, and took him by the throat, saying, 'Pay me what you owe!'
B040C018V029	40	18	29	"So his fellow servant fell down and begged him, saying, 'Have patience with me, and I will repay you all!'
B040C018V030	40	18	30	He would not, but went and cast him into prison, until he should pay back that which was due.
B040C018V031	40	18	31	So when his fellow servants saw what was done, they were exceedingly sorry, and came and told to their lord all that was done.
B040C018V032	40	18	32	Then his lord called him in, and said to him, 'You wicked servant! I forgave you all that debt, because you begged me.
