B040C025V019	40	25	19	"Now after a long time the lord of those servants came, and reconciled accounts with them.
B040C025V020	40	25	20	He who received the five talents came and brought another five talents, saying, 'Lord, you delivered to me five talents. Behold, I have gained another five talents.'
B040C025V021	40	25	21	"His lord said to him, 'Well done, good and faithful servant. You have been faithful over a few things, I will set you over many things. Enter into the joy of your lord.'
B040C025V022	40	25	22	"He also who got the two talents came and said, 'Lord, you delivered to me two talents. Behold, I have gained another two talents.'
B040C025V023	40	25	23	"His lord said to him, 'Well done, good and faithful servant. You have been faithful over a few things, I will set you over many things. Enter into the joy of your lord.'
B040C025V024	40	25	24	"He also who had received the one talent came and said, 'Lord, I knew you that you are a hard man, reaping where you did not sow, and gathering where you did not scatter.
B040C025V025	40	25	25	I was afraid, and went away and hid your talent in the earth. Behold, you have what is yours.'
B040C025V026	40	25	26	"But his lord answered him, 'You wicked and slothful servant. You knew that I reap where I did not sow, and gather where I did not scatter.
B040C025V027	40	25	27	You ought therefore to have deposited my money with the bankers, and at my coming I should have received back my own with interest.
B040C025V028	40	25	28	Take away therefore the talent from him, and give it to him who has the ten talents.
B040C025V029	40	25	29	For to everyone who has will be given, and he will have abundance, but from him who does not have, even that which he has will be taken away.
B040C025V030	40	25	30	Throw out the unprofitable servant into the outer darkness, where there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth.'
B040C025V031	40	25	31	"But when the Son of Man comes in his glory, and all the angels with him, then he will sit on the throne of his glory.
B040C025V032	40	25	32	Before him all the nations will be gathered, and he will separate them one from another, as a shepherd separates the sheep from the goats.
B040C025V033	40	25	33	He will set the sheep on his right hand, but the goats on the left.
B040C025V034	40	25	34	Then the King will tell those on his right hand, 'Come, blessed of my Father, inherit the Kingdom prepared for you from the foundation of the world;
B040C025V035	40	25	35	for I was hungry, and you gave me food to eat. I was thirsty, and you gave me drink. I was a stranger, and you took me in.
B040C025V036	40	25	36	I was naked, and you clothed me. I was sick, and you visited me. I was in prison, and you came to me.'
B040C025V037	40	25	37	"Then the righteous will answer him, saying, 'Lord, when did we see you hungry, and feed you; or thirsty, and give you a drink?
B040C025V038	40	25	38	When did we see you as a stranger, and take you in; or naked, and clothe you?
B040C025V039	40	25	39	When did we see you sick, or in prison, and come to you?'
B040C025V040	40	25	40	"The King will answer them, 'Truly I tell you, inasmuch as you did it to one of the least of these my brothers, you did it to me.'
B040C025V041	40	25	41	Then he will say also to those on the left hand, 'Depart from me, you cursed, into the eternal fire which is prepared for the devil and his angels;
B040C025V042	40	25	42	for I was hungry, and you did not give me food to eat; I was thirsty, and you gave me no drink;
B040C025V043	40	25	43	I was a stranger, and you did not take me in; naked, and you did not clothe me; sick, and in prison, and you did not visit me.'
B040C025V044	40	25	44	"Then they will also answer, saying, 'Lord, when did we see you hungry, or thirsty, or a stranger, or naked, or sick, or in prison, and did not help you?'
B040C025V045	40	25	45	"Then he will answer them, saying, 'Truly I tell you, inasmuch as you did not do it to one of the least of these, you did not do it to me.'
B040C025V046	40	25	46	These will go away into eternal punishment, but the righteous into eternal life."
B040C026V001	40	26	1	And it happened, when Jesus had finished all these words, that he said to his disciples,
B040C026V002	40	26	2	"You know that after two days the Passover is coming, and the Son of Man will be delivered up to be crucified."
B040C026V003	40	26	3	Then the chief priests and the elders of the people were gathered together in the court of the high priest, who was called Caiaphas.
B040C026V004	40	26	4	They took counsel together that they might take Jesus by deceit, and kill him.
B040C026V005	40	26	5	But they said, "Not during the feast, lest a riot occur among the people."
