B041C001V001	41	1	1	The beginning of the Good News of Jesus the Messiah, the Son of God.
B041C001V002	41	1	2	As it is written in Isaiah the prophet, "Behold, I send my messenger before your face,who will prepare your way before you.
B041C001V003	41	1	3	The voice of one crying in the wilderness,'Make ready the way of 
B041C001V004	41	1	4	John came baptizing in the wilderness and proclaiming the baptism of repentance for forgiveness of sins.
B041C001V005	41	1	5	All the country of Judea and all those of Jerusalem went out to him, and they were baptized by him in the Jordan river, confessing their sins.
B041C001V006	41	1	6	John was clothed with camel's hair and a leather belt around his waist. He ate locusts and wild honey.
B041C001V007	41	1	7	He preached, saying, "After me comes he who is mightier than I, the strap of whose sandals I am not worthy to stoop down and loosen.
