B042C015V001	42	15	1	Now all the tax collectors and sinners were coming close to him to hear him.
B042C015V002	42	15	2	The Pharisees and the scribes murmured, saying, "This man welcomes sinners, and eats with them."
B042C015V003	42	15	3	He told them this parable.
B042C015V004	42	15	4	"Which of you men, if you had one hundred sheep, and lost one of them, would not leave the ninety-nine in the wilderness, and go after the one that was lost, until he found it?
B042C015V005	42	15	5	When he has found it, he carries it on his shoulders, rejoicing.
B042C015V006	42	15	6	When he comes home, he calls together his friends and his neighbors, saying to them, 'Rejoice with me, for I have found my sheep which was lost!'
