B042C016V006	42	16	6	He said, 'A hundred batos of oil.' He said to him, 'Take your bill, and sit down quickly and write fifty.'
B042C016V007	42	16	7	Then said he to another, 'How much do you owe?' He said, 'A hundred cors of wheat.' He said to him, 'Take your bill, and write eighty.'
B042C016V008	42	16	8	"His lord commended the dishonest manager for his shrewdness, for the sons of this world are, in their own generation, more shrewd than the sons of light.
