B042C016V011	42	16	11	If therefore you have not been faithful in the unrighteous mammon, who will commit to your trust the true riches?
B042C016V012	42	16	12	If you have not been faithful in that which is another's, who will give you that which is your own?
B042C016V013	42	16	13	No servant can serve two masters, for either he will hate the one, and love the other; or else he will hold to one, and despise the other. You are not able to serve God and wealth."
