B042C023V053	42	23	53	He took it down, and wrapped it in a linen cloth, and placed him in a tomb that was cut in stone, where no one had ever been placed.
B042C023V054	42	23	54	It was the day of the Preparation, and the Sabbath was drawing near.
B042C023V055	42	23	55	The women, who had come with him out of Galilee, followed after, and saw the tomb, and how his body was placed.
B042C023V056	42	23	56	They returned, and prepared spices and ointments. On the Sabbath they rested according to the commandment.
B042C024V001	42	24	1	But on the first day of the week, at early dawn, they came to the tomb, bringing the spices which they had prepared.
B042C024V002	42	24	2	They found the stone rolled away from the tomb.
B042C024V003	42	24	3	They entered in, and did not find the body of the Lord Jesus.
B042C024V004	42	24	4	It happened, while they were greatly perplexed about this, behold, two men stood by them in dazzling clothing.
B042C024V005	42	24	5	Becoming terrified, they bowed their faces down to the earth.They said to them, "Why do you seek the living among the dead?
B042C024V006	42	24	6	He is not here, but is risen. Remember what he told you when he was still in Galilee,
B042C024V007	42	24	7	saying that the Son of Man must be delivered up into the hands of sinful men, and be crucified, and the third day rise again?"
B042C024V008	42	24	8	They remembered his words,
B042C024V009	42	24	9	returned from the tomb, and told all these things to the Eleven, and to all the rest.
B042C024V010	42	24	10	Now they were Mary Magdalene, Joanna, and Mary the mother of Jacob. The other women with them told these things to the apostles.
B042C024V011	42	24	11	These words seemed to them to be nonsense, and they did not believe them.
B042C024V012	42	24	12	But Peter got up and ran to the tomb. Stooping and looking in, he saw the strips of linen by themselves, and he departed to his home, wondering what had happened.
B042C024V013	42	24	13	Behold, two of them were going that very day to a village named Emmaus, which was sixty stadia from Jerusalem.
B042C024V014	42	24	14	They talked with each other about all of these things which had happened.
B042C024V015	42	24	15	It happened, while they talked and questioned together, that Jesus himself came near, and went with them.
B042C024V016	42	24	16	But their eyes were kept from recognizing him.
B042C024V017	42	24	17	He said to them, "What are you talking about as you walk?" They stood still, looking sad.
B042C024V018	42	24	18	One of them, named Cleopas, answered him, "Are you the only stranger in Jerusalem who does not know the things which have happened there in these days?"
B042C024V019	42	24	19	He said to them, "What things?"They said to him, "The things concerning Jesus, the Nazarene, a man who was a prophet mighty in deed and word before God and all the people;
B042C024V020	42	24	20	and how the chief priests and our rulers delivered him up to be condemned to death, and crucified him.
B042C024V021	42	24	21	But we were hoping that it was he who would redeem Israel. Yes, and besides all this, it is now the third day since these things happened.
B042C024V022	42	24	22	Also, certain women of our company amazed us, having arrived early at the tomb;
B042C024V023	42	24	23	and when they did not find his body, they came saying that they had also seen a vision of angels, who said that he was alive.
B042C024V024	42	24	24	Some of us went to the tomb, and found it just like the women had said, but they did not see him."
B042C024V025	42	24	25	Then he said to them, "O foolish ones, and slow of heart to believe in all that the prophets have spoken!
B042C024V026	42	24	26	Did not the Messiah have to suffer these things and to enter into his glory?"
B042C024V027	42	24	27	Beginning from Moses and from all the prophets, he explained to them in all the Scriptures the things concerning himself.
B042C024V028	42	24	28	They drew near to the village, where they were going, and he acted like he would go further.
B042C024V029	42	24	29	They urged him, saying, "Stay with us, for it is almost evening, and the day is almost over."He went in to stay with them.
B042C024V030	42	24	30	It happened, that when he had sat down at the table with them, he took the bread and gave thanks. Breaking it, he gave to them.
B042C024V031	42	24	31	Their eyes were opened, and they recognized him, and he vanished out of their sight.
B042C024V032	42	24	32	They said one to another, "Weren't our hearts burning within us, while he spoke to us along the way, and while he opened the Scriptures to us?"
B042C024V033	42	24	33	They rose up that very hour, returned to Jerusalem, and found the eleven gathered together, and those who were with them,
B042C024V034	42	24	34	saying, "The Lord is risen indeed, and has appeared to Simon!"
B042C024V035	42	24	35	They related the things that happened along the way, and how he was recognized by them in the breaking of the bread.
B042C024V036	42	24	36	As they said these things, Jesus himself stood among them, and said to them, "Peace be to you."
B042C024V037	42	24	37	But they were terrified and filled with fear, and supposed that they had seen a spirit.
B042C024V038	42	24	38	He said to them, "Why are you troubled? Why do doubts arise in your hearts?
B042C024V039	42	24	39	See my hands and my feet, that it is truly me. Touch me and see, for a spirit does not have flesh and bones, as you see that I have."
B042C024V040	42	24	40	When he had said this, he showed them his hands and his feet.
B042C024V041	42	24	41	While they still did not believe for joy, and wondered, he said to them, "Do you have anything here to eat?"
B042C024V042	42	24	42	They gave him a piece of a broiled fish.
B042C024V043	42	24	43	He took it and ate in front of them.
B042C024V044	42	24	44	He said to them, "This is what I told you, while I was still with you, that all things which are written in the Law of Moses, the Prophets, and the Psalms, concerning me must be fulfilled."
B042C024V045	42	24	45	Then he opened their minds, that they might understand the Scriptures.
B042C024V046	42	24	46	He said to them, "Thus it is written, for the Messiah to suffer and to rise from the dead the third day,
B042C024V047	42	24	47	and that repentance and remission of sins should be preached in his name to all the nations, beginning at Jerusalem.
B042C024V048	42	24	48	You are witnesses of these things.
B042C024V049	42	24	49	Behold, I send forth the promise of my Father on you. But wait in the city until you are clothed with power from on high."
B042C024V050	42	24	50	He led them out as far as Bethany, and he lifted up his hands, and blessed them.
B042C024V051	42	24	51	It happened, while he blessed them, that he withdrew from them, and was carried up into heaven.
B042C024V052	42	24	52	They worshiped him, and returned to Jerusalem with great joy,
B042C024V053	42	24	53	and were continually in the temple, blessing God.
B043C001V001	43	1	1	In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God, and the Word was God.
B043C001V002	43	1	2	The same was in the beginning with God.
B043C001V003	43	1	3	All things were made through him. Without him was not anything made that has been made.
B043C001V004	43	1	4	In him was life, and the life was the light of men.
B043C001V005	43	1	5	The light shines in the darkness, and the darkness hasn't overcome it.
B043C001V006	43	1	6	There came a man, sent from God, whose name was John.
B043C001V007	43	1	7	The same came as a witness, that he might testify about the light, that all might believe through him.
B043C001V008	43	1	8	He was not the light, but was sent that he might testify about the light.
B043C001V009	43	1	9	The true light that enlightens everyone was coming into the world.
B043C001V010	43	1	10	He was in the world, and the world was made through him, and the world did not recognize him.
B043C001V011	43	1	11	He came to his own, and those who were his own did not receive him.
B043C001V012	43	1	12	But as many as received him, to them he gave the right to become God's children, to those who believe in his name:
B043C001V013	43	1	13	who were born not of blood, nor of the will of the flesh, nor of the will of man, but of God.
B043C001V014	43	1	14	The Word became flesh, and lived among us. We saw his glory, such glory as of the one and only Son of the Father, full of grace and truth.
B043C001V015	43	1	15	John testified about him. He shouted out, saying, "This was he of whom I said, 'He who comes after me has surpassed me, for he was before me.'"
B043C001V016	43	1	16	For of his fullness we all received, and grace upon grace.
B043C001V017	43	1	17	For the Law was given through Moses, grace and truth were realized through Jesus Christ.
B043C001V018	43	1	18	No one has seen God at any time. The one and only Son, who is in the bosom of the Father, he has declared him.
B043C001V019	43	1	19	This is John's testimony, when the Jewish leaders sent to him priests and Levites from Jerusalem to ask him, "Who are you?"
B043C001V020	43	1	20	He confessed, and did not deny, but he confessed, "I am not the Messiah."
B043C001V021	43	1	21	They asked him, "What then? Are you Elijah?"
B043C001V022	43	1	22	They said therefore to him, "Who are you? Give us an answer to take back to those who sent us. What do you say about yourself?"
B043C001V023	43	1	23	He said, "I am the voice of one crying in the wilderness, 'Make straight the way of 
B043C001V024	43	1	24	The ones who had been sent were from the Pharisees.
B043C001V025	43	1	25	They asked him, "Why then do you baptize, if you are not the Messiah, nor Elijah, nor the prophet?"
B043C001V026	43	1	26	John answered them, "I baptize in water, but among you stands one whom you do not know.
B043C001V027	43	1	27	He is the one who comes after me, whose sandal strap I'm not worthy to loosen."
B043C001V028	43	1	28	These things were done in Bethany beyond the Jordan, where John was baptizing.
B043C001V029	43	1	29	The next day, he saw Jesus coming to him, and said, "Behold, the Lamb of God, who takes away the sin of the world!
B043C001V030	43	1	30	This is he of whom I said, 'After me comes a man who is preferred before me, for he was before me.'
B043C001V031	43	1	31	I did not know him, but for this reason I came baptizing in water: that he would be revealed to Israel."
B043C001V032	43	1	32	John testified, saying, "I have seen the Spirit descending like a dove out of heaven, and it remained on him.
B043C001V033	43	1	33	I did not recognize him, but he who sent me to baptize in water, he said to me, 'On whomever you will see the Spirit descending, and remaining on him, the same is he who baptizes in the Holy Spirit.'
B043C001V034	43	1	34	I have seen, and have testified that this is the Son of God. "
B043C001V035	43	1	35	Again, the next day, John was standing with two of his disciples,
B043C001V036	43	1	36	and he looked at Jesus as he walked, and said, "Behold, the Lamb of God!"
B043C001V037	43	1	37	The two disciples heard him speak, and they followed Jesus.
B043C001V038	43	1	38	Jesus turned, and saw them following, and said to them, "What are you looking for?"
B043C001V039	43	1	39	He said to them, "Come, and you will see."They came and saw where he was staying, and they stayed with him that day. It was about the tenth hour.
B043C001V040	43	1	40	One of the two who heard John, and followed him, was Andrew, Simon Peter's brother.
B043C001V041	43	1	41	He first found his own brother, Simon, and said to him, "We have found the Messiah!" (which is, being interpreted, Christ).
B043C001V042	43	1	42	He brought him to Jesus. Jesus looked at him, and said, "You are Simon the son of John. You shall be called Cephas" (which is by interpretation, Peter).
B043C001V043	43	1	43	On the next day, he was determined to go out into Galilee, and he found Philip. Jesus said to him, "Follow me."
B043C001V044	43	1	44	Now Philip was from Bethsaida, of the city of Andrew and Peter.
B043C001V045	43	1	45	Philip found Nathanael, and said to him, "We have found him, of whom Moses in the Law, and the Prophets, wrote: Jesus of Nazareth, the son of Joseph."
B043C001V046	43	1	46	Nathanael said to him, "Can any good thing come out of Nazareth?"
B043C001V047	43	1	47	Jesus saw Nathanael coming to him, and said about him, "Behold, an Israelite indeed, in whom is no deceit!"
B043C001V048	43	1	48	Nathanael said to him, "How do you know me?"
B043C001V049	43	1	49	Nathanael answered him, "Rabbi, you are the Son of God! You are King of Israel!"
B043C001V050	43	1	50	Jesus answered him, "Because I told you, 'I saw you underneath the fig tree,' do you believe? You will see greater things than these!"
B043C001V051	43	1	51	He said to him, "Truly, truly, I tell you, you will see heaven opened, and the angels of God ascending and descending on the Son of Man."
B043C002V001	43	2	1	The third day, there was a marriage in Cana of Galilee. Jesus' mother was there.
B043C002V002	43	2	2	Jesus also was invited, with his disciples, to the marriage.
B043C002V003	43	2	3	When the wine ran out, Jesus' mother said to him, "They have no wine."
B043C002V004	43	2	4	Jesus said to her, "Woman, what does that have to do with you and me? My hour has not yet come."
B043C002V005	43	2	5	His mother said to the servants, "Whatever he says to you, do it."
B043C002V006	43	2	6	Now there were six water pots of stone set there after the Jewish manner of purifying, containing two or three metretes apiece.
B043C002V007	43	2	7	Jesus said to them, "Fill the water pots with water." They filled them up to the brim.
B043C002V008	43	2	8	He said to them, "Now draw some out, and take it to the ruler of the feast." So they took it.
B043C002V009	43	2	9	When the ruler of the feast tasted the water now become wine, and did not know where it came from (but the servants who had drawn the water knew), the ruler of the feast called the bridegroom,
B043C002V010	43	2	10	and said to him, "Everyone serves the good wine first, and when the guests have drunk freely, then that which is worse. You have kept the good wine until now!"
B043C002V011	43	2	11	This beginning of his signs Jesus did in Cana of Galilee, and revealed his glory; and his disciples believed in him.
B043C002V012	43	2	12	After this, he went down to Capernaum, he, and his mother, his brothers, and his disciples; and they stayed there a few days.
B043C002V013	43	2	13	The Jewish Passover was near, and Jesus went up to Jerusalem.
B043C002V014	43	2	14	He found in the temple those who sold oxen, sheep, and doves, and the changers of money sitting.
B043C002V015	43	2	15	He made a whip of cords, and threw all out of the temple, both the sheep and the oxen; and he poured out the changers' money, and overthrew their tables.
B043C002V016	43	2	16	To those who sold the doves, he said, "Take these things out of here! Do not make my Father's house a marketplace!"
B043C002V017	43	2	17	His disciples remembered that it was written, "Zeal for your house will eat me up."
B043C002V018	43	2	18	The Jewish leaders therefore answered him, "What sign do you show us, seeing that you do these things?"
B043C002V019	43	2	19	Jesus answered them, "Destroy this temple, and in three days I will raise it up."
B043C002V020	43	2	20	The Jewish leaders therefore said, "Forty-six years was this temple in building, and will you raise it up in three days?"
B043C002V021	43	2	21	But he spoke of the temple of his body.
B043C002V022	43	2	22	When therefore he was raised from the dead, his disciples remembered that he said this, and they believed the Scripture, and the word which Jesus had said.
B043C002V023	43	2	23	Now when he was in Jerusalem at the Passover, during the feast, many believed in his name, observing his signs which he did.
B043C002V024	43	2	24	But Jesus did not trust himself to them, because he knew everyone,
B043C002V025	43	2	25	and because he did not need for anyone to testify concerning man; for he himself knew what was in man.
B043C003V001	43	3	1	Now there was a man of the Pharisees named Nicodemus, a ruler of the Jewish people.
B043C003V002	43	3	2	The same came to him by night, and said to him, "Rabbi, we know that you are a teacher come from God, for no one can do these signs that you do, unless God is with him."
B043C003V003	43	3	3	Jesus answered him, "Truly, truly, I tell you, unless one is born anew, he cannot see the Kingdom of God."
B043C003V004	43	3	4	Nicodemus said to him, "How can a man be born when he is old? Can he enter a second time into his mother's womb, and be born?"
B043C003V005	43	3	5	Jesus answered, "Truly, truly, I tell you, unless one is born of water and spirit, he cannot enter into the Kingdom of God!
B043C003V006	43	3	6	That which is born of the flesh is flesh. That which is born of the Spirit is spirit.
B043C003V007	43	3	7	Do not marvel that I said to you, 'You must be born anew.'
B043C003V008	43	3	8	The wind blows where it wants to, and you hear its sound, but do not know where it comes from and where it is going. So is everyone who is born of the Spirit."
B043C003V009	43	3	9	Nicodemus answered him, "How can these things be?"
B043C003V010	43	3	10	Jesus answered him, "Are you the teacher of Israel, and do not understand these things?
B043C003V011	43	3	11	Truly, truly, I tell you, we speak that which we know, and testify of that which we have seen, and you do not receive our witness.
B043C003V012	43	3	12	If I told you earthly things and you do not believe, how will you believe if I tell you heavenly things?
B043C003V013	43	3	13	No one has ascended into heaven, but he who descended out of heaven, the Son of Man.
B043C003V014	43	3	14	As Moses lifted up the serpent in the wilderness, even so must the Son of Man be lifted up,
B043C003V015	43	3	15	that whoever believes in him may have eternal life.
B043C003V016	43	3	16	For God so loved the world, that he gave his one and only Son, that whoever believes in him should not perish, but have eternal life.
B043C003V017	43	3	17	For God did not send his Son into the world to judge the world, but that the world should be saved through him.
B043C003V018	43	3	18	He who believes in him is not judged. He who does not believe has been judged already, because he has not believed in the name of the one and only Son of God.
B043C003V019	43	3	19	This is the judgment, that the light has come into the world, and men loved the darkness rather than the light; for their works were evil.
B043C003V020	43	3	20	For everyone who does evil hates the light, and does not come to the light, lest his works would be exposed.
B043C003V021	43	3	21	But he who does the truth comes to the light, that his works may be revealed, that they have been done in God."
B043C003V022	43	3	22	After these things, Jesus came with his disciples into the land of Judea. He stayed there with them, and baptized.
B043C003V023	43	3	23	John also was baptizing in Aenon near Salim, because there was much water there. They came, and were baptized.
B043C003V024	43	3	24	For John was not yet thrown into prison.
B043C003V025	43	3	25	There arose therefore a questioning on the part of John's disciples with a Jew about purification.
B043C003V026	43	3	26	They came to John, and said to him, "Rabbi, he who was with you beyond the Jordan, to whom you have testified, behold, the same baptizes, and everyone is coming to him."
B043C003V027	43	3	27	John answered, "A man can receive nothing, unless it has been given him from heaven.
B043C003V028	43	3	28	You yourselves bear me witness that I said, 'I am not the Messiah,' but, 'I have been sent before him.'
B043C003V029	43	3	29	He who has the bride is the bridegroom; but the friend of the bridegroom, who stands and hears him, rejoices greatly because of the bridegroom's voice. This, my joy, therefore is made full.
B043C003V030	43	3	30	He must increase, but I must decrease.
B043C003V031	43	3	31	He who comes from above is above all. He who is from the Earth belongs to the Earth, and speaks of the Earth. He who comes from heaven is above all.
B043C003V032	43	3	32	What he has seen and heard, of that he testifies; and no one receives his witness.
B043C003V033	43	3	33	He who has received his witness has set his seal to this, that God is true.
B043C003V034	43	3	34	For he whom God has sent speaks the words of God; for he gives the Spirit without measure.
B043C003V035	43	3	35	The Father loves the Son, and has given all things into his hand.
B043C003V036	43	3	36	One who believes in the Son has eternal life, but one who disobeys the Son won't see life, but the wrath of God remains on him."
B043C004V001	43	4	1	Therefore when Jesus knew that the Pharisees had heard that Jesus was making and baptizing more disciples than John
B043C004V002	43	4	2	(although Jesus himself did not baptize, but his disciples),
B043C004V003	43	4	3	he left Judea, and departed again into Galilee.
B043C004V004	43	4	4	He needed to pass through Samaria.
B043C004V005	43	4	5	So he came to a city of Samaria, called Sychar, near the parcel of ground that Jacob gave to his son, Joseph.
B043C004V006	43	4	6	Jacob's well was there. Jesus therefore, being tired from his journey, sat down by the well. It was about the sixth hour.
B043C004V007	43	4	7	A woman of Samaria came to draw water. Jesus said to her, "Give me a drink."
B043C004V008	43	4	8	For his disciples had gone away into the city to buy food.
B043C004V009	43	4	9	The Samaritan woman therefore said to him, "How is it that you, being a Jew, ask for a drink from me, a Samaritan woman?" (For Jews have no dealings with Samaritans.)
B043C004V010	43	4	10	Jesus answered her, "If you knew the gift of God, and who it is who says to you, 'Give me a drink,' you would have asked him, and he would have given you living water."
B043C004V011	43	4	11	The woman said to him, "Sir, you have nothing to draw with, and the well is deep. From where then have you that living water?
B043C004V012	43	4	12	Are you greater than our father, Jacob, who gave us the well, and drank of it himself, as did his children, and his livestock?"
B043C004V013	43	4	13	Jesus answered her, "Everyone who drinks of this water will thirst again,
B043C004V014	43	4	14	but whoever drinks of the water that I will give him will never thirst again; but the water that I will give him will become in him a well of water springing up to eternal life."
B043C004V015	43	4	15	The woman said to him, "Sir, give me this water, so that I do not get thirsty, neither come all the way here to draw."
B043C004V016	43	4	16	Jesus said to her, "Go, call your husband, and come here."
B043C004V017	43	4	17	The woman answered and said to him "I have no husband."Jesus said to her, "You said well, 'I have no husband,'
B043C004V018	43	4	18	for you have had five husbands; and he whom you now have is not your husband. This you have said truly."
B043C004V019	43	4	19	The woman said to him, "Sir, I perceive that you are a prophet.
B043C004V020	43	4	20	Our fathers worshiped in this mountain, and you say that in Jerusalem is the place where people ought to worship."
B043C004V021	43	4	21	Jesus said to her, "Woman, believe me, the hour comes, when neither in this mountain, nor in Jerusalem, will you worship the Father.
B043C004V022	43	4	22	You worship that which you do not know. We worship that which we know; for salvation is from the Jews.
B043C004V023	43	4	23	But the hour comes, and now is, when the true worshippers will worship the Father in spirit and truth, for the Father seeks such to be his worshippers.
B043C004V024	43	4	24	God is spirit, and those who worship him must worship in spirit and truth."
B043C004V025	43	4	25	The woman said to him, "I know that Messiah comes," (he who is called Christ). "When he has come, he will declare to us all things."
B043C004V026	43	4	26	Jesus said to her, "I am he, the one who speaks to you."
B043C004V027	43	4	27	At this, his disciples came. They marveled that he was speaking with a woman; yet no one said, "What are you looking for?" or, "Why do you speak with her?"
B043C004V028	43	4	28	So the woman left her water pot, and went away into the city, and said to the people,
B043C004V029	43	4	29	"Come, see a man who told me everything that I did. Can this be the Messiah?"
B043C004V030	43	4	30	They went out of the city, and were coming to him.
B043C004V031	43	4	31	In the meanwhile, the disciples urged him, saying, "Rabbi, eat."
B043C004V032	43	4	32	But he said to them, "I have food to eat that you do not know about."
B043C004V033	43	4	33	The disciples therefore said one to another, "Has anyone brought him something to eat?"
B043C004V034	43	4	34	Jesus said to them, "My food is to do the will of him who sent me, and to accomplish his work.
B043C004V035	43	4	35	Do you not say, 'There are yet four months until the harvest?' Behold, I tell you, lift up your eyes, and look at the fields, that they are white for harvest already.
B043C004V036	43	4	36	He who reaps receives wages, and gathers fruit to eternal life; that both he who sows and he who reaps may rejoice together.
B043C004V037	43	4	37	For in this the saying is true, 'One sows, and another reaps.'
B043C004V038	43	4	38	I sent you to reap that for which you have not labored. Others have labored, and you have entered into their labor."
B043C004V039	43	4	39	From that city many of the Samaritans believed in him because of the word of the woman, who testified, "He told me everything that I did."
B043C004V040	43	4	40	So when the Samaritans came to him, they begged him to stay with them. He stayed there two days.
B043C004V041	43	4	41	Many more believed because of his word.
B043C004V042	43	4	42	They said to the woman, "Now we believe, not because of your speaking; for we have heard for ourselves, and know that this is indeed the Savior of the world."
B043C004V043	43	4	43	After the two days he went out from there and went into Galilee.
B043C004V044	43	4	44	For Jesus himself testified that a prophet has no honor in his own country.
B043C004V045	43	4	45	So when he came into Galilee, the Galileans received him, having seen all the things that he did in Jerusalem at the feast, for they also went to the feast.
B043C004V046	43	4	46	Jesus came therefore again to Cana of Galilee, where he made the water into wine. There was a certain nobleman whose son was sick at Capernaum.
B043C004V047	43	4	47	When he heard that Jesus had come out of Judea into Galilee, he went to him, and begged him that he would come down and heal his son, for he was at the point of death.
B043C004V048	43	4	48	Jesus therefore said to him, "Unless you see signs and wonders, you will in no way believe."
B043C004V049	43	4	49	The nobleman said to him, "Sir, come down before my child dies."
B043C004V050	43	4	50	Jesus said to him, "Go your way. Your son lives." The man believed the word that Jesus spoke to him, and he went his way.
B043C004V051	43	4	51	As he was now going down, his servants met him, saying that his son was alive.
B043C004V052	43	4	52	So he inquired of them the hour when he began to get better. They said therefore to him, "Yesterday at the seventh hour, the fever left him."
B043C004V053	43	4	53	So the father knew that it was at that hour in which Jesus said to him, "Your son lives." He believed, as did his whole house.
B043C004V054	43	4	54	This is again the second sign that Jesus did, having come out of Judea into Galilee.
B043C005V001	43	5	1	After these things, there was a Jewish festival, and Jesus went up to Jerusalem.
B043C005V002	43	5	2	Now in Jerusalem by the sheep gate, there is a pool, which is called in Hebrew, "Bethesda," having five porches.
B043C005V003	43	5	3	In these lay a multitude of those who were sick, blind, lame, or paralyzed [waiting for the moving of the water;
B043C005V004	43	5	4	for an angel of the Lord went down at certain times into the pool, and stirred up the water. Whoever stepped in first after the stirring of the water was made whole of whatever disease he had.]
B043C005V005	43	5	5	A certain man was there, who had been sick for thirty-eight years.
B043C005V006	43	5	6	When Jesus saw him lying there, and knew that he had been sick for a long time, he asked him, "Do you want to be made well?"
B043C005V007	43	5	7	The sick man answered him, "Sir, I have no one to put me into the pool when the water is stirred up, but while I'm coming, another steps down before me."
B043C005V008	43	5	8	Jesus said to him, "Arise, take up your mat, and walk."
B043C005V009	43	5	9	Immediately, the man was made well, and took up his mat and walked.Now it was the Sabbath on that day.
B043C005V010	43	5	10	So the Jewish leaders said to him who was cured, "It is the Sabbath. It is not lawful for you to carry the mat."
B043C005V011	43	5	11	He answered them, "He who made me well, the same said to me, 'Take up your mat, and walk.'"
B043C005V012	43	5	12	Then they asked him, "Who is the man who said to you to pick it up and walk?"
B043C005V013	43	5	13	But he who was healed did not know who it was, for Jesus had withdrawn, a crowd being in the place.
B043C005V014	43	5	14	Afterward Jesus found him in the temple, and said to him, "Behold, you are made well. Sin no more, so that nothing worse happens to you."
B043C005V015	43	5	15	The man went away, and told the Jewish leaders that it was Jesus who had made him well.
B043C005V016	43	5	16	For this cause the Jewish leaders persecuted Jesus, because he did these things on the Sabbath.
B043C005V017	43	5	17	But Jesus answered them, "My Father is still working, so I am working, too."
B043C005V018	43	5	18	For this cause therefore the Jewish leaders sought all the more to kill him, because he not only broke the Sabbath, but also called God his own Father, making himself equal with God.
B043C005V019	43	5	19	Jesus therefore answered them, "Truly, truly, I tell you, the Son can do nothing of himself, but what he sees the Father doing. For whatever things he does, these the Son also does likewise.
B043C005V020	43	5	20	For the Father has affection for the Son, and shows him all things that he himself does. He will show him greater works than these, that you may marvel.
B043C005V021	43	5	21	For as the Father raises the dead and gives them life, even so the Son also gives life to whom he desires.
B043C005V022	43	5	22	For the Father judges no one, but he has given all judgment to the Son,
B043C005V023	43	5	23	that all may honor the Son, even as they honor the Father. Whoever does not honor the Son does not honor the Father who sent him.
B043C005V024	43	5	24	"Truly, truly, I tell you, he who hears my word, and believes him who sent me, has eternal life, and does not come into judgment, but has passed out of death into life.
B043C005V025	43	5	25	Truly, truly, I tell you, the hour comes, and now is, when the dead will hear the Son of God's voice; and those who hear will live.
B043C005V026	43	5	26	For as the Father has life in himself, even so he gave to the Son also to have life in himself.
B043C005V027	43	5	27	He also gave him authority to execute judgment, because he is a son of man.
B043C005V028	43	5	28	Do not marvel at this, for the hour comes, in which all that are in the tombs will hear his voice,
B043C005V029	43	5	29	and will come out; those who have done good, to the resurrection of life; and those who have done evil, to the resurrection of judgment.
B043C005V030	43	5	30	I can of myself do nothing. As I hear, I judge, and my judgment is righteous; because I do not seek my own will, but the will of the One who sent me.
B043C005V031	43	5	31	"If I testify about myself, my witness is not valid.
B043C005V032	43	5	32	It is another who testifies about me. I know that the testimony which he testifies about me is true.
B043C005V033	43	5	33	You have sent to John, and he has testified to the truth.
B043C005V034	43	5	34	But the testimony which I receive is not from man. However, I say these things that you may be saved.
B043C005V035	43	5	35	He was the burning and shining lamp, and you were willing to rejoice for a while in his light.
B043C005V036	43	5	36	But the testimony which I have is greater than that of John, for the works which the Father gave me to accomplish, the very works that I do, testify about me, that the Father has sent me.
B043C005V037	43	5	37	The Father himself, who sent me, has testified about me. You have neither heard his voice at any time, nor seen his form.
B043C005V038	43	5	38	You do not have his word living in you; because you do not believe him whom he sent.
B043C005V039	43	5	39	"You search the Scriptures, because you think that in them you have eternal life; and these are they which testify about me.
B043C005V040	43	5	40	Yet you will not come to me, that you may have life.
B043C005V041	43	5	41	I do not receive glory from men.
B043C005V042	43	5	42	But I know you, that you do not have God's love in yourselves.
B043C005V043	43	5	43	I have come in my Father's name, and you do not receive me. If another comes in his own name, you will receive him.
B043C005V044	43	5	44	How can you believe, who receive glory from one another, and you do not seek the glory that comes from the only God?
B043C005V045	43	5	45	"Do not think that I will accuse you to the Father. There is one who accuses you, even Moses, on whom you have set your hope.
B043C005V046	43	5	46	For if you believed Moses, you would believe me; for he wrote about me.
B043C005V047	43	5	47	But if you do not believe his writings, how will you believe my words?"
B043C006V001	43	6	1	After these things, Jesus went away to the other side of the sea of Galilee, which is also called the Sea of Tiberias.
B043C006V002	43	6	2	A great multitude followed him, because they saw the signs which he did on those who were sick.
B043C006V003	43	6	3	Jesus went up into the mountain, and he sat there with his disciples.
B043C006V004	43	6	4	Now the Passover, the Jewish festival, was near.
B043C006V005	43	6	5	Jesus therefore lifting up his eyes, and seeing that a great multitude was coming to him, said to Philip, "Where are we to buy bread, that these may eat?"
B043C006V006	43	6	6	This he said to test him, for he himself knew what he would do.
B043C006V007	43	6	7	Philip answered him, "Two hundred denarii worth of bread is not sufficient for them, that everyone of them may receive a little."
