B043C006V017	43	6	17	and they entered into the boat, and were going over the sea to Capernaum. It was now dark, and Jesus had not come to them.
B043C006V018	43	6	18	The sea was tossed by a great wind blowing.
B043C006V019	43	6	19	When therefore they had rowed about twenty-five or thirty stadia, they saw Jesus walking on the sea, and drawing near to the boat; and they were afraid.
B043C006V020	43	6	20	But he said to them, "It is I. Do not be afraid."
B043C006V021	43	6	21	They were willing therefore to receive him into the boat. Immediately the boat was at the land where they were going.
B043C006V022	43	6	22	On the next day, the multitude that stood on the other side of the sea saw that there was no other boat there, except one, and that Jesus had not entered with his disciples into the boat, but his disciples had gone away alone.
B043C006V023	43	6	23	However boats from Tiberias came near to the place where they ate the bread after the Lord had given thanks.
B043C006V024	43	6	24	When the multitude therefore saw that Jesus was not there, nor his disciples, they themselves got into the boats, and came to Capernaum, seeking Jesus.
B043C006V025	43	6	25	When they found him on the other side of the sea, they asked him, "Rabbi, when did you come here?"
B043C006V026	43	6	26	Jesus answered them, "Truly, truly, I tell you, you seek me, not because you saw signs, but because you ate of the loaves, and were filled.
B043C006V027	43	6	27	Do not work for the food which perishes, but for the food which remains to eternal life, which the Son of Man will give to you. For God the Father has sealed him."
B043C006V028	43	6	28	They said therefore to him, "What must we do, that we may work the works of God?"
B043C006V029	43	6	29	Jesus answered them, "This is the work of God, that you believe in him whom he has sent."
B043C006V030	43	6	30	They said therefore to him, "What then do you do for a sign, that we may see, and believe you? What work do you do?
B043C006V031	43	6	31	Our fathers ate the manna in the wilderness. As it is written, 'He gave them bread out of heaven to eat.'"
B043C006V032	43	6	32	Jesus therefore said to them, "Truly, truly, I tell you, it was not Moses who gave you the bread out of heaven, but my Father gives you the true bread out of heaven.
B043C006V033	43	6	33	For the bread of God is that which comes down out of heaven, and gives life to the world."
B043C006V034	43	6	34	They said therefore to him, "Lord, always give us this bread."
B043C006V035	43	6	35	Jesus said to them, "I am the bread of life. He who comes to me will not be hungry, and he who believes in me will never be thirsty.
