B043C006V039	43	6	39	This is the will of him who sent me, that of all he has given to me I should lose nothing, but should raise him up at the last day.
B043C006V040	43	6	40	This is the will of my Father who sent me, that everyone who sees the Son, and believes in him, should have eternal life; and I will raise him up at the last day."
B043C006V041	43	6	41	The Jewish people therefore murmured concerning him, because he said, "I am the bread which came down out of heaven."
B043C006V042	43	6	42	They said, "Is not this Jesus, the son of Joseph, whose father and mother we know? How then does he say, 'I have come down out of heaven?'"
B043C006V043	43	6	43	Therefore Jesus answered them, "Do not murmur among yourselves.
