B043C006V047	43	6	47	Truly, truly, I tell you, he who believes has eternal life.
B043C006V048	43	6	48	I am the bread of life.
B043C006V049	43	6	49	Your fathers ate the manna in the wilderness, and they died.
B043C006V050	43	6	50	This is the bread which comes down out of heaven, that anyone may eat of it and not die.
B043C006V051	43	6	51	I am the living bread which came down out of heaven. If anyone eats of this bread, he will live forever; and the bread which I will give for the life of the world is my flesh."
B043C006V052	43	6	52	The Judeans therefore contended with one another, saying, "How can this man give us his flesh to eat?"
B043C006V053	43	6	53	Jesus therefore said to them, "Truly I tell you, unless you eat the flesh of the Son of Man and drink his blood, you do not have life in yourselves.
