B043C006V055	43	6	55	For my flesh is food indeed, and my blood is drink indeed.
B043C006V056	43	6	56	He who eats my flesh and drinks my blood lives in me, and I in him.
B043C006V057	43	6	57	As the living Father sent me, and I live because of the Father; so he who feeds on me, he will also live because of me.
B043C006V058	43	6	58	This is the bread which came down out of heaven-not as the fathers ate, and died. He who eats this bread will live forever."
B043C006V059	43	6	59	He said these things in the synagogue, as he taught in Capernaum.
B043C006V060	43	6	60	Therefore many of his disciples, when they heard this, said, "This is a hard saying! Who can listen to it?"
