B043C007V001	43	7	1	After these things, Jesus was walking in Galilee, for he would not walk in Judea, because the Jewish leaders sought to kill him.
B043C007V002	43	7	2	Now the Jewish festival, the Feast of Tabernacles, was near.
B043C007V003	43	7	3	His brothers therefore said to him, "Depart from here, and go into Judea, that your disciples also may see your works which you do.
B043C007V004	43	7	4	For no one does anything in secret, and himself seeks to be known openly. If you do these things, reveal yourself to the world."
B043C007V005	43	7	5	For even his brothers did not believe in him.
