B043C012V018	43	12	18	For this cause also the multitude went and met him, because they heard that he had done this sign.
B043C012V019	43	12	19	The Pharisees therefore said among themselves, "See how you accomplish nothing. Behold, the world has gone after him."
B043C012V020	43	12	20	Now there were certain Greeks among those that went up to worship at the feast.
B043C012V021	43	12	21	These, therefore, came to Philip, who was from Bethsaida of Galilee, and asked him, saying, "Sir, we want to see Jesus."
B043C012V022	43	12	22	Philip came and told Andrew, and in turn, Andrew came with Philip, and they told Jesus.
B043C012V023	43	12	23	Jesus answered them, "The time has come for the Son of Man to be glorified.
B043C012V024	43	12	24	Truly, truly, I tell you, unless a grain of wheat falls into the earth and dies, it remains by itself alone. But if it dies, it bears much fruit.
B043C012V025	43	12	25	He who loves his life loses it. He who hates his life in this world will keep it to eternal life.
B043C012V026	43	12	26	If anyone serves me, let him follow me. Where I am, there will my servant also be. If anyone serves me, the Father will honor him.
B043C012V027	43	12	27	"Now my soul is troubled. What shall I say? 'Father, save me from this time?' But for this cause I came to this time.
B043C012V028	43	12	28	Father, glorify your name!"
B043C012V029	43	12	29	The multitude therefore, who stood by and heard it, said that it had thundered. Others said, "An angel has spoken to him."
B043C012V030	43	12	30	Jesus answered, "This voice hasn't come for my sake, but for your sakes.
B043C012V031	43	12	31	Now is the judgment of this world. Now the prince of this world will be cast out.
B043C012V032	43	12	32	And I, if I am lifted up from the earth, will draw everyone to myself."
B043C012V033	43	12	33	But he said this, signifying by what kind of death he should die.
B043C012V034	43	12	34	The multitude answered him, "We have heard out of the law that the Messiah remains forever. How can you say, 'The Son of Man must be lifted up?' Who is this Son of Man?"
B043C012V035	43	12	35	Jesus therefore said to them, "Yet a little while the light is with you. Walk while you have the light, that darkness does not overtake you. He who walks in the darkness does not know where he is going.
B043C012V036	43	12	36	While you have the light, believe in the light, that you may become children of light." Jesus said these things, and he departed and hid himself from them.
B043C012V037	43	12	37	But though he had done so many signs before them, yet they did not believe in him,
B043C012V038	43	12	38	that the word of Isaiah the prophet might be fulfilled, which he spoke,
B043C012V039	43	12	39	For this cause they could not believe, for Isaiah said again,
B043C012V040	43	12	40	"He has blinded their eyes and hardened their heart,lest they should see with their eyes,and perceive with their heart,and would turn,and I would heal them." 
B043C012V041	43	12	41	Isaiah said these things when he saw his glory, and spoke of him.
B043C012V042	43	12	42	Nevertheless even of the rulers many believed in him, but because of the Pharisees they did not confess it, so that they would not be put out of the synagogue,
B043C012V043	43	12	43	for they loved men's praise more than God's praise.
B043C012V044	43	12	44	Jesus shouted out and said, "Whoever believes in me, believes not in me, but in him who sent me.
B043C012V045	43	12	45	He who sees me sees him who sent me.
B043C012V046	43	12	46	I have come as a light into the world, that whoever believes in me may not remain in the darkness.
B043C012V047	43	12	47	If anyone listens to my sayings, and does not keep them, I do not judge him. For I came not to judge the world, but to save the world.
B043C012V048	43	12	48	He who rejects me, and does not receive my sayings, has one who judges him. The word that I spoke, the same will judge him in the last day.
B043C012V049	43	12	49	For I spoke not from myself, but the Father who sent me, he gave me a commandment, what I should say, and what I should speak.
B043C012V050	43	12	50	I know that his commandment is eternal life. The things therefore which I speak, even as the Father has said to me, so I speak."
B043C013V001	43	13	1	Now before the feast of the Passover, Jesus, knowing that his time had come that he would depart from this world to the Father, having loved his own who were in the world, he loved them to the end.
B043C013V002	43	13	2	During supper, the devil having already put into the heart of Judas Iscariot, Simon's son, to betray him,
B043C013V003	43	13	3	Jesus, knowing that the Father had given all things into his hands, and that he came forth from God, and was going to God,
B043C013V004	43	13	4	arose from supper, and laid aside his outer garments. He took a towel, and wrapped a towel around his waist.
B043C013V005	43	13	5	Then he poured water into the basin, and began to wash the disciples' feet, and to wipe them with the towel that was wrapped around him.
B043C013V006	43	13	6	Then he came to Simon Peter. He said to him, "Lord, do you wash my feet?"
B043C013V007	43	13	7	Jesus answered him, "You do not know what I am doing now, but you will understand later."
B043C013V008	43	13	8	Peter said to him, "You will never wash my feet!"
B043C013V009	43	13	9	Simon Peter said to him, "Lord, not my feet only, but also my hands and my head!"
B043C013V010	43	13	10	Jesus said to him, "Someone who has bathed only needs to have his feet washed, but is completely clean. You are clean, but not all of you."
B043C013V011	43	13	11	For he knew him who would betray him, therefore he said, "You are not all clean."
B043C013V012	43	13	12	So when he had washed their feet, put his outer garment back on, and sat down again, he said to them, "Do you know what I have done to you?
B043C013V013	43	13	13	You call me, 'Teacher' and 'Lord.' You say so correctly, for so I am.
B043C013V014	43	13	14	If I then, the Lord and the Teacher, have washed your feet, you also ought to wash one another's feet.
B043C013V015	43	13	15	For I have given you an example, that you also should do as I have done to you.
B043C013V016	43	13	16	Truly, truly, I tell you, a servant is not greater than his lord, neither one who is sent greater than he who sent him.
B043C013V017	43	13	17	If you know these things, blessed are you if you do them.
B043C013V018	43	13	18	I do not speak concerning all of you. I know whom I have chosen. But that the Scripture may be fulfilled, 'He who eats my bread has lifted up his heel against me.'
B043C013V019	43	13	19	From now on, I tell you before it happens, that when it happens, you may believe that I am he.
B043C013V020	43	13	20	Truly, truly, I tell you, he who receives whomever I send, receives me; and he who receives me, receives him who sent me."
B043C013V021	43	13	21	When Jesus had said this, he was troubled in spirit, and testified, "Truly, truly, I tell you that one of you will betray me."
B043C013V022	43	13	22	The disciples looked at one another, perplexed about whom he spoke.
B043C013V023	43	13	23	One of his disciples, whom Jesus loved, was at the table, leaning against Jesus' breast.
B043C013V024	43	13	24	Simon Peter therefore beckoned to him, and said to him, "Tell us who it is of whom he speaks."
B043C013V025	43	13	25	He, leaning back, as he was, on Jesus' breast, asked him, "Lord, who is it?"
B043C013V026	43	13	26	Jesus therefore answered, "It is he to whom I will give this piece of bread when I have dipped it." So when he had dipped the piece of bread, he gave it to Judas, the son of Simon Iscariot.
B043C013V027	43	13	27	After the piece of bread, then Satan entered into him.
B043C013V028	43	13	28	Now no man at the table knew why he said this to him.
B043C013V029	43	13	29	For some thought, because Judas had the money box, that Jesus said to him, "Buy what things we need for the feast," or that he should give something to the poor.
B043C013V030	43	13	30	Therefore, having received that morsel, he went out immediately. It was night.
B043C013V031	43	13	31	When he had gone out, Jesus said, "Now the Son of Man has been glorified, and God has been glorified in him.
B043C013V032	43	13	32	If God has been glorified in him, God will also glorify him in himself, and he will glorify him immediately.
B043C013V033	43	13	33	Little children, I will be with you a little while longer. You will seek me, and as I said to the Jewish leaders, 'Where I am going, you cannot come,' so now I tell you.
B043C013V034	43	13	34	A new commandment I give to you, that you love one another. Just as I have loved you, you also must love one another.
B043C013V035	43	13	35	By this everyone will know that you are my disciples, if you have love for one another."
B043C013V036	43	13	36	Simon Peter said to him, "Lord, where are you going?"
B043C013V037	43	13	37	Peter said to him, "Lord, why cannot I follow you now? I will lay down my life for you."
B043C013V038	43	13	38	Jesus answered him, "Will you lay down your life for me? Truly, truly, I tell you, the rooster won't crow until you have denied me three times.
B043C014V001	43	14	1	"Do not let your heart be troubled. Believe in God. Believe also in me.
