B043C014V003	43	14	3	And if I go and prepare a place for you, I will come again, and will receive you to myself; that where I am, you may be there also.
B043C014V004	43	14	4	Where I go, you know the way."
B043C014V005	43	14	5	Thomas said to him, "Lord, we do not know where you are going. How can we know the way?"
B043C014V006	43	14	6	Jesus said to him, "I am the way, the truth, and the life. No one comes to the Father, except through me.
B043C014V007	43	14	7	If you had known me, you would have known my Father also. From now on, you know him, and have seen him."
B043C014V008	43	14	8	Philip said to him, "Lord, show us the Father, and that will be enough for us."
B043C014V009	43	14	9	Jesus said to him, "Have I been with you such a long time, and do you not know me, Philip? He who has seen me has seen the Father. How can you say, 'Show us the Father?'
B043C014V010	43	14	10	Do you not believe that I am in the Father, and the Father in me? The words that I tell you, I speak not from myself; but the Father who lives in me does his works.
B043C014V011	43	14	11	Believe me that I am in the Father, and the Father in me; or else believe me for the very works' sake.
B043C014V012	43	14	12	Truly, truly, I tell you, he who believes in me, the works that I do, he will do also; and he will do greater works than these, because I am going to the Father.
B043C014V013	43	14	13	Whatever you will ask in my name, that will I do, that the Father may be glorified in the Son.
B043C014V014	43	14	14	If you will ask anything in my name, I will do it.
B043C014V015	43	14	15	If you love me, you will keep my commandments.
B043C014V016	43	14	16	I will pray to the Father, and he will give you another Counselor, that he may be with you forever,-
B043C014V017	43	14	17	the Spirit of truth, whom the world cannot receive; for it does not see him, neither knows him. You know him, for he lives with you, and will be in you.
B043C014V018	43	14	18	I will not leave you orphans. I will come to you.
B043C014V019	43	14	19	Yet a little while, and the world will see me no more; but you will see me. Because I live, you will live also.
B043C014V020	43	14	20	In that day you will know that I am in my Father, and you in me, and I in you.
B043C014V021	43	14	21	One who has my commandments, and keeps them, that person is one who loves me. One who loves me will be loved by my Father, and I will love him, and will reveal myself to him."
B043C014V022	43	14	22	Judas (not Iscariot) said to him, "Lord, what has happened that you are about to reveal yourself to us, and not to the world?"
B043C014V023	43	14	23	Jesus answered him, "If a man loves me, he will keep my word. My Father will love him, and we will come to him, and make our home with him.
B043C014V024	43	14	24	He who does not love me does not keep my words. The word which you hear is not mine, but the Father's who sent me.
B043C014V025	43	14	25	I have said these things to you, while still living with you.
