B043C015V001	43	15	1	"I am the true vine, and my Father is the farmer.
B043C015V002	43	15	2	Every branch in me that does not bear fruit, he takes away. Every branch that bears fruit, he prunes, that it may bear more fruit.
B043C015V003	43	15	3	You are already pruned clean because of the word which I have spoken to you.
B043C015V004	43	15	4	Remain in me, and I in you. As the branch cannot bear fruit by itself, unless it remains in the vine, so neither can you, unless you remain in me.
B043C015V005	43	15	5	I am the vine. You are the branches. He who remains in me, and I in him, the same bears much fruit, for apart from me you can do nothing.
B043C015V006	43	15	6	If a man does not remain in me, he is thrown out as a branch, and is withered; and they gather them, throw them into the fire, and they are burned.
B043C015V007	43	15	7	If you remain in me, and my words remain in you, ask whatever you desire, and it will be done for you.
B043C015V008	43	15	8	"In this is my Father glorified, that you bear much fruit; and so you will be my disciples.
B043C015V009	43	15	9	Even as the Father has loved me, I also have loved you. Remain in my love.
B043C015V010	43	15	10	If you keep my commandments, you will remain in my love; even as I have kept my Father's commandments, and remain in his love.
B043C015V011	43	15	11	I have spoken these things to you, that my joy may be in you, and that your joy may be made full.
B043C015V012	43	15	12	"This is my commandment, that you love one another, even as I have loved you.
B043C015V013	43	15	13	Greater love has no one than this, that someone lay down his life for his friends.
B043C015V014	43	15	14	You are my friends, if you do whatever I command you.
B043C015V015	43	15	15	No longer do I call you servants, for the servant does not know what his lord does. But I have called you friends, for everything that I heard from my Father, I have made known to you.
B043C015V016	43	15	16	You did not choose me, but I chose you, and appointed you, that you should go and bear fruit, and that your fruit should remain; that whatever you will ask of the Father in my name, he may give it to you.
B043C015V017	43	15	17	"I command these things to you, that you may love one another.
B043C015V018	43	15	18	If the world hates you, you know that it has hated me before it hated you.
B043C015V019	43	15	19	If you were of the world, the world would love its own. But because you are not of the world, since I chose you out of the world, therefore the world hates you.
B043C015V020	43	15	20	Remember the word that I said to you: 'A servant is not greater than his lord.' If they persecuted me, they will also persecute you. If they kept my word, they will keep yours also.
B043C015V021	43	15	21	But all these things will they do to you for my name's sake, because they do not know him who sent me.
B043C015V022	43	15	22	If I had not come and spoken to them, they would not have had sin; but now they have no excuse for their sin.
B043C015V023	43	15	23	He who hates me, hates my Father also.
B043C015V024	43	15	24	If I had not done among them the works which no one else did, they would not have had sin. But now have they seen and also hated both me and my Father.
B043C015V025	43	15	25	But this happened so that the word may be fulfilled which was written in their law, 'They hated me without a cause.'
B043C015V026	43	15	26	"When the Counselor has come, whom I will send to you from the Father, the Spirit of truth, who proceeds from the Father, he will testify about me.
B043C015V027	43	15	27	You will also testify, because you have been with me from the beginning.
B043C016V001	43	16	1	"These things have I spoken to you, so that you would not be caused to stumble.
B043C016V002	43	16	2	They will put you out of the synagogues. Yes, the time comes that whoever kills you will think that he offers service to God.
B043C016V003	43	16	3	They will do these things because they have not known the Father, nor me.
B043C016V004	43	16	4	But I have told you these things, so that when the time comes, you may remember that I told you about them. I did not tell you these things from the beginning, because I was with you.
B043C016V005	43	16	5	But now I am going to him who sent me, and none of you asks me, 'Where are you going?'
B043C016V006	43	16	6	But because I have told you these things, sorrow has filled your heart.
B043C016V007	43	16	7	Nevertheless I tell you the truth: It is to your advantage that I go away, for if I do not go away, the Counselor won't come to you. But if I go, I will send him to you.
