B043C016V009	43	16	9	about sin, because they do not believe in me;
B043C016V010	43	16	10	about righteousness, because I am going to the Father, and you won't see me any more;
B043C016V011	43	16	11	about judgment, because the prince of this world has been judged.
B043C016V012	43	16	12	"I have yet many things to tell you, but you cannot bear them now.
B043C016V013	43	16	13	However when he, the Spirit of truth, has come, he will guide you into all truth, for he will not speak from himself; but whatever he hears, he will speak. He will declare to you things that are coming.
B043C016V014	43	16	14	He will glorify me, for he will take from what is mine, and will declare it to you.
B043C016V015	43	16	15	All things whatever the Father has are mine; therefore I said that he takes of mine, and will declare it to you.
B043C016V016	43	16	16	A little while, and you will no longer see me. Again a little while, and you will see me."
B043C016V017	43	16	17	Some of his disciples therefore said to one another, "What is this that he says to us, 'A little while, and you won't see me, and again a little while, and you will see me;' and, 'Because I go to the Father?'"
B043C016V018	43	16	18	They said therefore, "What is this that he says, 'A little while?' We do not know what he is saying."
B043C016V019	43	16	19	Therefore Jesus perceived that they wanted to ask him, and he said to them, "Do you inquire among yourselves concerning this, that I said, 'A little while, and you won't see me, and again a little while, and you will see me?'
