B043C016V026	43	16	26	In that day you will ask in my name; and I do not say to you, that I will pray to the Father for you,
B043C016V027	43	16	27	for the Father himself loves you, because you have loved me, and have believed that I came forth from God.
B043C016V028	43	16	28	I came out from the Father, and have come into the world. Again, I leave the world, and go to the Father."
B043C016V029	43	16	29	His disciples said to him, "Behold, now you speak plainly, and speak no figures of speech.
B043C016V030	43	16	30	Now we know that you know all things, and do not need for anyone to question you. By this we believe that you came forth from God."
B043C016V031	43	16	31	Jesus answered them, "Do you now believe?
B043C016V032	43	16	32	Behold, the time is coming, yes, and has now come, that you will be scattered, everyone to his own place, and you will leave me alone. Yet I am not alone, because the Father is with me.
B043C016V033	43	16	33	I have told you these things, that in me you may have peace. In the world you have oppression; but cheer up! I have overcome the world."
B043C017V001	43	17	1	Jesus said these things, and lifting up his eyes to heaven, he said, "Father, the time has come. Glorify your Son, that your Son may also glorify you;
B043C017V002	43	17	2	even as you gave him authority over all flesh, he will give eternal life to all whom you have given him.
B043C017V003	43	17	3	This is eternal life, that they may know you, the only true God, and him whom you sent, Jesus Christ.
B043C017V004	43	17	4	I glorified you on the earth. I have accomplished the work which you have given me to do.
B043C017V005	43	17	5	Now, Father, glorify me with your own self with the glory which I had with you before the world existed.
B043C017V006	43	17	6	I revealed your name to the people whom you have given me out of the world. They were yours, and you have given them to me. They have kept your word.
B043C017V007	43	17	7	Now they have known that all things whatever you have given me are from you,
B043C017V008	43	17	8	for the words which you have given me I have given to them, and they received them, and knew for sure that I came forth from you, and they have believed that you sent me.
B043C017V009	43	17	9	I pray for them. I do not pray for the world, but for those whom you have given me, for they are yours.
B043C017V010	43	17	10	All things that are mine are yours, and yours are mine, and I am glorified in them.
B043C017V011	43	17	11	I am no more in the world, but these are in the world, and I am coming to you. Holy Father, keep them through your name which you have given me, that they may be one, even as we are.
B043C017V012	43	17	12	While I was with them, I kept them in your name which you have given me; I have kept. None of them is lost, except the son of destruction, that the Scripture might be fulfilled.
B043C017V013	43	17	13	But now I come to you, and I say these things in the world, that they may have my joy made full in themselves.
B043C017V014	43	17	14	I have given them your word. The world hated them, because they are not of the world, even as I am not of the world.
B043C017V015	43	17	15	I pray not that you would take them from the world, but that you would keep them from the evil one.
B043C017V016	43	17	16	They are not of the world even as I am not of the world.
B043C017V017	43	17	17	Sanctify them in the truth. Your word is truth.
B043C017V018	43	17	18	As you sent me into the world, even so I have sent them into the world.
B043C017V019	43	17	19	For their sakes I sanctify myself, that they themselves also may be sanctified in truth.
B043C017V020	43	17	20	Not for these only do I pray, but for those also who believe in me through their word,
B043C017V021	43	17	21	that they may all be one; even as you, Father, are in me, and I in you, that they also may be in us; that the world may believe that you sent me.
B043C017V022	43	17	22	The glory which you have given me, I have given to them; that they may be one, even as we are one;
B043C017V023	43	17	23	I in them, and you in me, that they may be perfected into one; that the world may know that you sent me, and loved them, even as you loved me.
B043C017V024	43	17	24	Father, I desire that they also whom you have given me be with me where I am, that they may see my glory, which you have given me, for you loved me before the foundation of the world.
B043C017V025	43	17	25	Righteous Father, the world hasn't known you, but I knew you; and these knew that you sent me.
B043C017V026	43	17	26	I made known to them your name, and will make it known; that the love with which you loved me may be in them, and I in them."
B043C018V001	43	18	1	When Jesus had spoken these words, he went out with his disciples over the brook Kidron, where there was a garden, into which he and his disciples entered.
B043C018V002	43	18	2	Now Judas, who betrayed him, also knew the place, for Jesus often met there with his disciples.
B043C018V003	43	18	3	Judas then, having taken a detachment of soldiers and officers from the chief priests and the Pharisees, came there with lanterns, torches, and weapons.
B043C018V004	43	18	4	Jesus therefore, knowing all the things that were happening to him, went forth, and said to them, "Who are you looking for?"
B043C018V005	43	18	5	They answered him, "Jesus of Nazareth."Judas also, who betrayed him, was standing with them.
B043C018V006	43	18	6	When therefore he said to them, "I AM," they went backward, and fell to the ground.
B043C018V007	43	18	7	Again therefore he asked them, "Who are you looking for?"
B043C018V008	43	18	8	Jesus answered, "I told you that I AM. If therefore you seek me, let these go their way,"
B043C018V009	43	18	9	that the word might be fulfilled which he spoke, "Of those whom you have given me, I have lost none."
B043C018V010	43	18	10	Simon Peter therefore, having a sword, drew it, and struck the high priest's servant, and cut off his right ear. The servant's name was Malchus.
B043C018V011	43	18	11	Jesus therefore said to Peter, "Put the sword into its sheath. The cup which the Father has given me, shall I not surely drink it?"
B043C018V012	43	18	12	So the detachment, the commanding officer, and the officers of the Jewish leaders, seized Jesus and bound him,
B043C018V013	43	18	13	and led him to Annas first, for he was father-in-law to Caiaphas, who was high priest that year.
B043C018V014	43	18	14	Now it was Caiaphas who advised the Jewish leaders that it was expedient that one man should perish for the people.
B043C018V015	43	18	15	Simon Peter followed Jesus, as did another disciple. Now that disciple was known to the high priest, and entered in with Jesus into the court of the high priest;
B043C018V016	43	18	16	but Peter was standing at the door outside. So the other disciple, who was known to the high priest, went out and spoke to her who kept the door, and brought in Peter.
B043C018V017	43	18	17	Then the maid who kept the door said to Peter, "Are you also one of this man's disciples?"
B043C018V018	43	18	18	Now the servants and the officers were standing there, having made a fire of coals, for it was cold. They were warming themselves. Peter was with them, standing and warming himself.
B043C018V019	43	18	19	The high priest therefore asked Jesus about his disciples, and about his teaching.
B043C018V020	43	18	20	Jesus answered him, "I spoke openly to the world. I always taught in synagogues, and in the temple, where all the Jewish people come together. I said nothing in secret.
B043C018V021	43	18	21	Why do you ask me? Ask those who have heard me what I said to them. Behold, these know the things which I said."
B043C018V022	43	18	22	When he had said this, one of the officers standing by slapped Jesus with his hand, saying, "Do you answer the high priest like that?"
B043C018V023	43	18	23	Jesus answered him, "If I have spoken evil, testify of the evil; but if well, why do you beat me?"
B043C018V024	43	18	24	Annas sent him bound to Caiaphas, the high priest.
B043C018V025	43	18	25	Now Simon Peter was standing and warming himself. They said therefore to him, "You are not also one of his disciples, are you?"
B043C018V026	43	18	26	One of the servants of the high priest, being a relative of him whose ear Peter had cut off, said, "Did not I see you in the garden with him?"
B043C018V027	43	18	27	Peter therefore denied it again, and immediately the rooster crowed.
B043C018V028	43	18	28	They led Jesus therefore from Caiaphas into the Praetorium. It was early, and they themselves did not enter into the Praetorium, that they might not be defiled, but might eat the Passover.
B043C018V029	43	18	29	Pilate therefore went out to them, and said, "What accusation do you bring against this man?"
B043C018V030	43	18	30	They answered him, "If this man weren't an evildoer, we would not have delivered him up to you."
B043C018V031	43	18	31	Pilate therefore said to them, "Take him yourselves, and judge him according to your law."Therefore the Jewish leaders said to him, "It is not lawful for us to put anyone to death,"
B043C018V032	43	18	32	that the word of Jesus might be fulfilled, which he spoke, signifying by what kind of death he should die.
B043C018V033	43	18	33	Pilate therefore entered again into the Praetorium, called Jesus, and said to him, "Are you the King of the Jews?"
B043C018V034	43	18	34	Jesus answered him, "Do you say this by yourself, or did others tell you about me?"
B043C018V035	43	18	35	Pilate answered, "I'm not a Jew, am I? Your own nation and the chief priests delivered you to me. What have you done?"
B043C018V036	43	18	36	Jesus answered, "My Kingdom is not of this world. If my Kingdom were of this world, then my servants would fight, that I would not be delivered to the Jewish leaders. But now my Kingdom is not from here."
B043C018V037	43	18	37	Pilate therefore said to him, "Are you a king then?"
B043C018V038	43	18	38	Pilate said to him, "What is truth?"When he had said this, he went out again to the Jewish leaders, and said to them, "I find no basis for a charge against him.
B043C018V039	43	18	39	But you have a custom, that I should release someone to you at the Passover. Therefore do you want me to release to you the King of the Jews?"
B043C018V040	43	18	40	Then they shouted again, saying, "Not this man, but Barabbas!" Now Barabbas was a robber.
B043C019V001	43	19	1	So Pilate then took Jesus, and flogged him.
B043C019V002	43	19	2	The soldiers twisted thorns into a crown, and put it on his head, and dressed him in a purple garment.
B043C019V003	43	19	3	And they kept coming up to him and saying, "Hail, King of the Jews!" and they struck him with their hands.
B043C019V004	43	19	4	Then Pilate went out again, and said to them, "Behold, I bring him out to you, that you may know that I find no basis for a charge against him."
B043C019V005	43	19	5	Jesus therefore came out, wearing the crown of thorns and the purple garment. Pilate said to them, "Behold, the man!"
B043C019V006	43	19	6	When therefore the chief priests and the officers saw him, they shouted, saying, "Crucify! Crucify!"
B043C019V007	43	19	7	The Jewish leaders answered him, "We have a law, and by that law he ought to die, because he made himself the Son of God."
B043C019V008	43	19	8	When therefore Pilate heard this saying, he was more afraid.
B043C019V009	43	19	9	He entered into the Praetorium again, and said to Jesus, "Where are you from?" But Jesus gave him no answer.
B043C019V010	43	19	10	Pilate therefore said to him, "Are not you speaking to me? Do you not know that I have power to release you, and have power to crucify you?"
B043C019V011	43	19	11	Jesus answered, "You would have no power at all against me, unless it were given to you from above. Therefore he who delivered me to you has greater sin."
B043C019V012	43	19	12	At this, Pilate was seeking to release him, but the Jewish leaders shouted, saying, "If you release this man, you are not Caesar's friend! Everyone who makes himself a king speaks against Caesar!"
B043C019V013	43	19	13	When Pilate therefore heard these words, he brought Jesus out, and sat down on the judgment seat at a place called "The Pavement," but in Hebrew, "Gabbatha."
B043C019V014	43	19	14	Now it was the Preparation Day of the Passover, at about the sixth hour. He said to the Jewish leaders, "Behold, your King!"
B043C019V015	43	19	15	They shouted, "Away with him! Away with him! Crucify him!"
B043C019V016	43	19	16	So then he delivered him to them to be crucified. So they took Jesus.
B043C019V017	43	19	17	He went out, carrying the cross himself, to the place called "The Place of a Skull," which is called in Hebrew, "Golgotha,"
B043C019V018	43	19	18	where they crucified him, and with him two others, on either side one, and Jesus in the middle.
B043C019V019	43	19	19	Pilate wrote a title also, and put it on the cross. There was written, "JESUS OF NAZARETH, THE KING OF THE JEWS."
B043C019V020	43	19	20	Therefore many Jews read this title, for the place where Jesus was crucified was near the city; and it was written in Hebrew, in Latin, and in Greek.
B043C019V021	43	19	21	The chief priests of the Jewish people therefore said to Pilate, "Do not write, 'The King of the Jews,' but, 'he said, I am King of the Jews.'"
B043C019V022	43	19	22	Pilate answered, "What I have written, I have written."
B043C019V023	43	19	23	Then the soldiers, when they had crucified Jesus, took his garments and made four parts, to every soldier a part; and also the coat. Now the coat was without seam, woven from the top throughout.
B043C019V024	43	19	24	Then they said to one another, "Let us not tear it, but cast lots for it to decide whose it will be," that the Scripture might be fulfilled, which says,Therefore the soldiers did these things.
B043C019V025	43	19	25	But there were standing by the cross of Jesus his mother, and his mother's sister, Mary the wife of Cleopas, and Mary Magdalene.
B043C019V026	43	19	26	Therefore when Jesus saw his mother, and the disciple whom he loved standing there, he said to his mother, "Woman, behold your son!"
B043C019V027	43	19	27	Then he said to the disciple, "Behold, your mother!" From that hour, the disciple took her to his own home.
B043C019V028	43	19	28	After this, Jesus, knowing that all things were now finished, that the Scripture might be fulfilled, said, "I am thirsty."
B043C019V029	43	19	29	Now a vessel full of vinegar was set there; so they put a sponge full of the vinegar on hyssop, and held it at his mouth.
B043C019V030	43	19	30	When Jesus therefore had received the vinegar, he said, "It is finished." He bowed his head, and gave up his spirit.
B043C019V031	43	19	31	Therefore the Jewish leaders, because it was the Preparation Day, so that the bodies would not remain on the cross on the Sabbath (for that Sabbath was a special one), asked of Pilate that their legs might be broken, and that they might be taken away.
B043C019V032	43	19	32	Therefore the soldiers came, and broke the legs of the first, and of the other who was crucified with him;
B043C019V033	43	19	33	but when they came to Jesus, and saw that he was already dead, they did not break his legs.
B043C019V034	43	19	34	However one of the soldiers pierced his side with a spear, and immediately blood and water came out.
B043C019V035	43	19	35	He who has seen has testified, and his testimony is true. He knows that he tells the truth, that you may believe.
B043C019V036	43	19	36	For these things happened, that the Scripture might be fulfilled, "A bone of him will not be broken."
B043C019V037	43	19	37	Again another Scripture says, "They will look on him whom they pierced."
B043C019V038	43	19	38	After these things, Joseph of Arimathaea, being a disciple of Jesus, but secretly for fear of the Jewish leaders, asked of Pilate that he might take away the body of Jesus. Pilate gave him permission. He came therefore and took away his body.
B043C019V039	43	19	39	Nicodemus, who at first came to Jesus by night, also came bringing a mixture of myrrh and aloes, about a hundred pounds.
B043C019V040	43	19	40	So they took the body of Jesus, and bound it in linen cloths with the spices, according to Jewish burial practice.
B043C019V041	43	19	41	Now in the place where he was crucified there was a garden. In the garden was a new tomb in which no man had ever yet been placed.
B043C019V042	43	19	42	Then because of the Jewish Preparation Day (for the tomb was nearby) they put Jesus there.
B043C020V001	43	20	1	Now on the first day of the week, Mary Magdalene went early, while it was still dark, to the tomb, and saw the stone taken away from the tomb.
B043C020V002	43	20	2	Therefore she ran and came to Simon Peter, and to the other disciple whom Jesus loved, and said to them, "They have taken away the Lord out of the tomb, and we do not know where they have put him!"
B043C020V003	43	20	3	Therefore Peter and the other disciple went out, and they went toward the tomb.
B043C020V004	43	20	4	They both ran together. The other disciple outran Peter, and came to the tomb first.
B043C020V005	43	20	5	Stooping and looking in, he saw the linen cloths lying, yet he did not enter in.
B043C020V006	43	20	6	Then Simon Peter came, following him, and entered into the tomb. He saw the linen cloths lying,
B043C020V007	43	20	7	and the cloth that had been on his head, not lying with the linen cloths, but rolled up in a place by itself.
B043C020V008	43	20	8	So then the other disciple who came first to the tomb also entered in, and he saw and believed.
B043C020V009	43	20	9	For as yet they did not know the Scripture, that he must rise from the dead.
B043C020V010	43	20	10	So the disciples went away again to their own homes.
B043C020V011	43	20	11	But Mary was standing outside at the tomb weeping. So, as she wept, she stooped and looked into the tomb,
B043C020V012	43	20	12	and she saw two angels in white sitting, one at the head, and one at the feet, where the body of Jesus had lain.
B043C020V013	43	20	13	They told her, "Woman, why are you weeping?"She said to them, "Because they have taken away my Lord, and I do not know where they have put him."
B043C020V014	43	20	14	When she had said this, she turned around and saw Jesus standing, and did not know that it was Jesus.
B043C020V015	43	20	15	Jesus said to her, "Woman, why are you weeping? Who are you looking for?"
B043C020V016	43	20	16	Jesus said to her, "Mary."
B043C020V017	43	20	17	Jesus said to her, "Do not touch me, for I have not yet ascended to the Father; but go to my brothers, and tell them, 'I am ascending to my Father and your Father, to my God and your God.'"
B043C020V018	43	20	18	Mary Magdalene came and told the disciples, "I have seen the Lord!," and that he had said these things to her.
B043C020V019	43	20	19	When therefore it was evening, on that day, the first day of the week, and when the doors were locked where the disciples were, for fear of the Jewish leaders, Jesus came and stood in the midst, and said to them, "Peace be to you."
B043C020V020	43	20	20	When he had said this, he showed them his hands and his side. The disciples therefore were glad when they saw the Lord.
B043C020V021	43	20	21	Jesus therefore said to them again, "Peace be to you. As the Father has sent me, even so I send you."
B043C020V022	43	20	22	When he had said this, he breathed on them, and said to them, "Receive the Holy Spirit!
B043C020V023	43	20	23	Whoever's sins you forgive, they are forgiven them. Whoever's sins you retain, they have been retained."
B043C020V024	43	20	24	But Thomas, one of the twelve, called Didymus, was not with them when Jesus came.
B043C020V025	43	20	25	The other disciples therefore said to him, "We have seen the Lord!"
B043C020V026	43	20	26	After eight days again his disciples were inside, and Thomas was with them. Jesus came, the doors being locked, and stood in the midst, and said, "Peace be to you."
B043C020V027	43	20	27	Then he said to Thomas, "Reach here your finger, and see my hands. Reach here your hand, and put it into my side. Do not be unbelieving, but believing."
B043C020V028	43	20	28	Thomas answered him, "My Lord and my God!"
B043C020V029	43	20	29	Jesus said to him, "Because you have seen me, you have believed. Blessed are those who have not seen, and have believed."
B043C020V030	43	20	30	Therefore Jesus did many other signs in the presence of his disciples, which are not written in this book;
B043C020V031	43	20	31	but these are written, that you may believe that Jesus is the Messiah, the Son of God, and that believing you may have life in his name.
B043C021V001	43	21	1	After these things, Jesus revealed himself again to the disciples at the sea of Tiberias. He revealed himself this way.
B043C021V002	43	21	2	Simon Peter, Thomas called Didymus, Nathanael of Cana in Galilee, and the sons of Zebedee, and two others of his disciples were together.
B043C021V003	43	21	3	Simon Peter said to them, "I'm going fishing."They told him, "We are also coming with you." They went out, and entered into the boat. That night, they caught nothing.
B043C021V004	43	21	4	But when day had already come, Jesus stood on the beach, yet the disciples did not know that it was Jesus.
B043C021V005	43	21	5	Jesus therefore said to them, "Children, have you anything to eat?"
B043C021V006	43	21	6	He said to them, "Cast the net on the right side of the boat, and you will find some."They cast it therefore, and now they weren't able to draw it in for the multitude of fish.
B043C021V007	43	21	7	That disciple therefore whom Jesus loved said to Peter, "It's the Lord!"So when Simon Peter heard that it was the Lord, he wrapped his coat around him (for he was naked), and threw himself into the sea.
B043C021V008	43	21	8	But the other disciples came in the little boat (for they were not far from the land, but about two hundred cubits away), dragging the net full of fish.
B043C021V009	43	21	9	So when they got out on the land, they saw a fire of coals there, and fish placed on it, and bread.
B043C021V010	43	21	10	Jesus said to them, "Bring some of the fish which you have just caught."
B043C021V011	43	21	11	Simon Peter went up, and drew the net to land, full of great fish, one hundred fifty-three; and even though there were so many, the net was not torn.
B043C021V012	43	21	12	Jesus said to them, "Come and eat breakfast."
B043C021V013	43	21	13	Then Jesus came and took the bread, gave it to them, and the fish likewise.
B043C021V014	43	21	14	This is now the third time that Jesus was revealed to his disciples, after he had risen from the dead.
B043C021V015	43	21	15	So when they had eaten their breakfast, Jesus said to Simon Peter, "Simon, son of John, do you love me more than these?"He said to him, "Feed my lambs."
B043C021V016	43	21	16	He said to him again a second time, "Simon, son of John, do you love me?"He said to him, "Tend my sheep."
B043C021V017	43	21	17	He said to him the third time, "Simon, son of John, do you have affection for me?"Jesus said to him, "Feed my sheep.
B043C021V018	43	21	18	Truly I tell you, when you were young, you dressed yourself, and walked where you wanted to. But when you are old, you will stretch out your hands, and another will dress you, and carry you where you do not want to go."
B043C021V019	43	21	19	Now he said this, signifying by what kind of death he would glorify God. When he had said this, he said to him, "Follow me."
B043C021V020	43	21	20	Then Peter, turning around, saw a disciple following. This was the disciple whom Jesus sincerely loved, the one who had also leaned on Jesus' breast at the supper and asked, "Lord, who is going to betray You?"
B043C021V021	43	21	21	Peter seeing him, said to Jesus, "Lord, what about this man?"
B043C021V022	43	21	22	Jesus said to him, "If I desire that he stay until I come, what is that to you? You follow me."
B043C021V023	43	21	23	This saying therefore went out among the brothers, that this disciple would not die. Yet Jesus did not say to him that he would not die, but, "If I desire that he stay until I come, what is that to you?"
B043C021V024	43	21	24	This is the disciple who testifies about these things, and wrote these things. We know that his witness is true.
B043C021V025	43	21	25	There are also many other things which Jesus did, which if they would all be written, I suppose that even the world itself would not have room for the books that would be written.
B044C001V001	44	1	1	The first account I wrote, Theophilus, concerned all that Jesus began both to do and to teach,
B044C001V002	44	1	2	until the day in which he was received up, after he had given commandment through the Holy Spirit to the apostles whom he had chosen.
B044C001V003	44	1	3	To these he also showed himself alive after he suffered, by many proofs, appearing to them over a period of forty days, and speaking about God's Kingdom.
B044C001V004	44	1	4	Being assembled together with them, he commanded them, "Do not depart from Jerusalem, but wait for the promise of the Father, which you heard from me.
B044C001V005	44	1	5	For John indeed baptized in water, but you will be baptized in the Holy Spirit not many days from now."
B044C001V006	44	1	6	Therefore, when they had come together, they asked him, "Lord, are you now restoring the kingdom to Israel?"
B044C001V007	44	1	7	He said to them, "It is not for you to know times or seasons which the Father has set within his own authority.
B044C001V008	44	1	8	But you will receive power when the Holy Spirit has come upon you. You will be my witnesses in Jerusalem, in all Judea and Samaria, and to the uttermost parts of the earth."
B044C001V009	44	1	9	When he had said these things, as they were looking, he was taken up, and a cloud received him out of their sight.
B044C001V010	44	1	10	While they were looking steadfastly into the sky as he went, behold, two men stood by them in white clothing,
B044C001V011	44	1	11	who also said, "You men of Galilee, why do you stand looking into the sky? This Jesus, who was received up from you into the sky will come back in the same way as you saw him going into the sky."
B044C001V012	44	1	12	Then they returned to Jerusalem from the mountain called Olivet, which is near Jerusalem, a Sabbath day's journey away.
B044C001V013	44	1	13	When they had come in, they went up into the upper room, where they were staying; that is Peter, John, Jacob, Andrew, Philip, Thomas, Bartholomew, Matthew, Jacob the son of Alphaeus, Simon the Zealot, and Judas the son of Jacob.
B044C001V014	44	1	14	All these with one accord continued steadfastly in prayer, along with the women, and Mary the mother of Jesus, and with his brothers.
B044C001V015	44	1	15	In these days, Peter stood up in the midst of the brothers (and the number of names was about one hundred twenty), and said,
B044C001V016	44	1	16	"Brothers, it was necessary that this Scripture should be fulfilled, which the Holy Spirit spoke before by the mouth of David concerning Judas, who was guide to those who took Jesus.
B044C001V017	44	1	17	For he was numbered with us, and received his portion in this ministry.
B044C001V018	44	1	18	Now this man obtained a field with the reward for his wickedness, and falling headlong, his body burst open, and all his intestines gushed out.
B044C001V019	44	1	19	It became known to everyone who lived in Jerusalem that in their language that field was called 'Hakel-Dema,' that is, 'The field of blood.'
B044C001V020	44	1	20	For it is written in the scroll of Psalms,
B044C001V021	44	1	21	"Of the men therefore who have accompanied us all the time that the Lord Jesus went in and out among us,
B044C001V022	44	1	22	beginning from the baptism of John, to the day that he was received up from us, of these one must become a witness with us of his resurrection."
B044C001V023	44	1	23	They put forward two, Joseph called Barsabbas, who was surnamed Justus, and Matthias.
B044C001V024	44	1	24	They prayed, and said, "You, Lord, who know the hearts of all men, show which one of these two you have chosen
B044C001V025	44	1	25	to take part in this ministry and office of apostle from which Judas fell away, that he might go to his own place."
B044C001V026	44	1	26	They drew lots for them, and the lot fell on Matthias, and he was numbered with the Eleven apostles.
B044C002V001	44	2	1	Now when the day of Pentecost had come, they were all together in one place.
B044C002V002	44	2	2	Suddenly there came from the sky a sound like the rushing of a mighty wind, and it filled all the house where they were sitting.
B044C002V003	44	2	3	Tongues like fire appeared and were distributed to them, and one sat on each of them.
B044C002V004	44	2	4	They were all filled with the Holy Spirit, and began to speak with other languages, as the Spirit gave them the ability to speak.
B044C002V005	44	2	5	Now there were dwelling in Jerusalem Jews, devout men, from every nation under the sky.
B044C002V006	44	2	6	When this sound was heard, the multitude came together, and were bewildered, because everyone heard them speaking in his own language.
B044C002V007	44	2	7	They were all amazed and marveled, saying, "Behold, are not all these who speak Galileans?
B044C002V008	44	2	8	How do we hear, everyone in our own native language?
