B044C017V022	44	17	22	Paul stood in the middle of the Areopagus, and said, "You men of Athens, I perceive that you are very religious in all things.
B044C017V023	44	17	23	For as I passed along, and observed the objects of your worship, I found also an altar with this inscription: 'TO AN UNKNOWN 
B044C017V024	44	17	24	The God who made the world and all things in it, he, being Lord of heaven and earth, does not dwell in temples made with hands,
B044C017V025	44	17	25	neither is he served by human hands, as though he needed anything, seeing he himself gives to all life and breath, and all things.
B044C017V026	44	17	26	He made from one every nation of men to dwell on all the surface of the earth, having determined appointed seasons, and the boundaries of their dwellings,
B044C017V027	44	17	27	that they should seek God, if perhaps they might reach out for him and find him, though he is not far from each one of us.
B044C017V028	44	17	28	'For in him we live, and move, and have our being.' As some of your own poets have said, 'For we are also his offspring.'
B044C017V029	44	17	29	Being then the offspring of God, we ought not to think that the Divine Nature is like gold, or silver, or stone, engraved by art and design of man.
B044C017V030	44	17	30	The times of ignorance therefore God overlooked. But now he commands that all people everywhere should repent,
B044C017V031	44	17	31	because he has appointed a day in which he will judge the world in righteousness by the man whom he has ordained; of which he has given assurance to all men, in that he has raised him from the dead."
B044C017V032	44	17	32	Now when they heard of the resurrection of the dead, some mocked; but others said, "We want to hear you again concerning this."
B044C017V033	44	17	33	Thus Paul went out from among them.
B044C017V034	44	17	34	But certain men joined with him, and believed, among whom also was Dionysius the Areopagite, and a woman named Damaris, and others with them.
B044C018V001	44	18	1	After these things Paul departed from Athens, and came to Corinth.
B044C018V002	44	18	2	He found a certain Jew named Aquila, a man of Pontus by race, who had recently come from Italy, with his wife Priscilla, because Claudius had commanded all the Jews to depart from Rome. He came to them,
B044C018V003	44	18	3	and because he practiced the same trade, he lived with them and worked, for by trade they were tent makers.
B044C018V004	44	18	4	He reasoned in the synagogue every Sabbath, and persuaded Jews and Greeks.
B044C018V005	44	18	5	But when Silas and Timothy came down from Macedonia, Paul was compelled by the word, testifying to the Jews that Jesus was the Messiah.
B044C018V006	44	18	6	When they opposed him and blasphemed, he shook out his clothing and said to them, "Your blood be on your own heads! I am clean. From now on, I will go to the Gentiles!"
