B045C014V014	45	14	14	I know, and am persuaded in the Lord Jesus, that nothing is unclean of itself; except that to him who considers anything to be unclean, to him it is unclean.
B045C014V015	45	14	15	Yet if because of food your brother is grieved, you walk no longer in love. Do not destroy with your food him for whom Christ died.
B045C014V016	45	14	16	Then do not let your good be slandered,
B045C014V017	45	14	17	for the Kingdom of God is not eating and drinking, but righteousness, peace, and joy in the Holy Spirit.
B045C014V018	45	14	18	For he who serves Christ in these things is acceptable to God and approved by men.
B045C014V019	45	14	19	So then, let us follow after things which make for peace, and things by which we may build one another up.
B045C014V020	45	14	20	Do not overthrow God's work for food's sake. All things indeed are clean, however it is evil for that man who creates a stumbling block by eating.
B045C014V021	45	14	21	It is good to not eat meat, drink wine, nor do anything by which your brother stumbles.
B045C014V022	45	14	22	Do you have faith? Have it to yourself before God. Happy is he who does not judge himself in that which he approves.
B045C014V023	45	14	23	But he who doubts is condemned if he eats, because it is not of faith; and whatever is not of faith is sin.
B045C015V001	45	15	1	Now we who are strong ought to bear the weaknesses of the weak, and not to please ourselves.
B045C015V002	45	15	2	Let each one of us please his neighbor for that which is good, to be building him up.
B045C015V003	45	15	3	For even Christ did not please himself. But, as it is written, "The reproaches of those who reproached you fell on me."
B045C015V004	45	15	4	For whatever things were written before were written for our learning, that through patience and through encouragement of the Scriptures we might have hope.
B045C015V005	45	15	5	Now the God of patience and of encouragement grant you to be of the same mind one with another according to Christ Jesus,
B045C015V006	45	15	6	that with one accord you may with one mouth glorify the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B045C015V007	45	15	7	Therefore accept one another, even as Christ also accepted you, to the glory of God.
B045C015V008	45	15	8	Now I say that Christ has been made a servant of the circumcision for the truth of God, that he might confirm the promises given to the fathers,
B045C015V009	45	15	9	and that the Gentiles might glorify God for his mercy. As it is written,
B045C015V010	45	15	10	Again he says,
B045C015V011	45	15	11	Again,
B045C015V012	45	15	12	Again, Isaiah says,
B045C015V013	45	15	13	Now may the God of hope fill you with all joy and peace in believing, that you may abound in hope, in the power of the Holy Spirit.
B045C015V014	45	15	14	I myself am also persuaded about you, my brothers, that you yourselves are full of goodness, filled with all knowledge, able also to admonish others.
B045C015V015	45	15	15	But I write the more boldly to you in part, as reminding you, because of the grace that was given to me by God,
B045C015V016	45	15	16	that I should be a servant of Christ Jesus to the Gentiles, serving as a priest the Good News of God, that the offering up of the Gentiles might be made acceptable, sanctified by the Holy Spirit.
B045C015V017	45	15	17	I have therefore my boasting in Christ Jesus in things pertaining to God.
B045C015V018	45	15	18	For I will not dare to speak of any things except those which Christ worked through me, for the obedience of the Gentiles, by word and deed,
B045C015V019	45	15	19	in the power of signs and wonders, in the power of the Spirit of God; so that from Jerusalem, and around as far as to Illyricum, I have fully preached the Good News of Christ;
B045C015V020	45	15	20	yes, making it my aim to proclaim the Good News, not where Christ was already named, that I might not build on another's foundation.
B045C015V021	45	15	21	But, as it is written,
B045C015V022	45	15	22	Therefore also I was hindered these many times from coming to you,
B045C015V023	45	15	23	but now, no longer having any place in these regions, and having these many years a longing to come to you,
B045C015V024	45	15	24	whenever I journey to Spain. For I hope to see you on my journey, and to be helped on my way there by you, if first I may enjoy your company for a while.
B045C015V025	45	15	25	But now, I say, I am going to Jerusalem, serving the saints.
B045C015V026	45	15	26	For it has been the good pleasure of Macedonia and Achaia to make a certain contribution for the poor among the saints who are at Jerusalem.
B045C015V027	45	15	27	Yes, it has been their good pleasure, and they are their debtors. For if the Gentiles have been made partakers of their spiritual things, they owe it to them also to serve them in fleshly things.
B045C015V028	45	15	28	When therefore I have accomplished this, and have sealed to them this fruit, I will go on by way of you to Spain.
B045C015V029	45	15	29	I know that, when I come to you, I will come in the fullness of the blessing of the Christ.
B045C015V030	45	15	30	Now I beg you, brothers, by our Lord Jesus Christ, and by the love of the Spirit, that you strive together with me in your prayers to God for me,
B045C015V031	45	15	31	that I may be delivered from those who are disobedient in Judea, and that my service which I have for Jerusalem may be acceptable to the saints;
B045C015V032	45	15	32	that I may come to you in joy through the will of God, and together with you, find rest.
B045C015V033	45	15	33	Now the God of peace be with you all. Amen.
B045C016V001	45	16	1	I commend to you Phoebe, our sister, who is a servant of the church that is at Cenchreae,
B045C016V002	45	16	2	that you receive her in the Lord, in a way worthy of the saints, and that you assist her in whatever matter she may need from you, for she herself also has been a helper of many, and of my own self.
B045C016V003	45	16	3	Greet Prisca and Aquila, my fellow workers in Christ Jesus,
B045C016V004	45	16	4	who for my life, laid down their own necks; to whom not only I give thanks, but also all the churches of the Gentiles.
B045C016V005	45	16	5	Greet the church that is in their house. Greet Epaenetus, my beloved, who is the first fruits of Asia to Christ.
B045C016V006	45	16	6	Greet Mary, who labored much for you.
B045C016V007	45	16	7	Greet Andronicus and Junias, my relatives and my fellow prisoners, who are notable among the apostles, who also were in Christ before me.
B045C016V008	45	16	8	Greet Ampliatus, my beloved in the Lord.
B045C016V009	45	16	9	Greet Urbanus, our fellow worker in Christ, and Stachys, my beloved.
B045C016V010	45	16	10	Greet Apelles, the approved in Christ. Greet those who are of the household of Aristobulus.
B045C016V011	45	16	11	Greet Herodion, my kinsman. Greet them of the household of Narcissus, who are in the Lord.
B045C016V012	45	16	12	Greet Tryphaena and Tryphosa, who labor in the Lord. Greet Persis, the beloved, who labored much in the Lord.
B045C016V013	45	16	13	Greet Rufus, the chosen in the Lord, and his mother and mine.
B045C016V014	45	16	14	Greet Asyncritus, Phlegon, Hermes, Patrobas, Hermas, and the brothers who are with them.
B045C016V015	45	16	15	Greet Philologus and Julia, Nereus and his sister, and Olympas, and all the saints who are with them.
B045C016V016	45	16	16	Greet one another with a holy kiss. The churches of Christ greet you.
B045C016V017	45	16	17	Now I beg you, brothers, look out for those who are causing the divisions and occasions of stumbling, contrary to the doctrine which you learned, and turn away from them.
B045C016V018	45	16	18	For those who are such do not serve our Lord, Jesus Christ, but their own belly; and by their smooth and flattering speech, they deceive the hearts of the innocent.
B045C016V019	45	16	19	For your obedience has become known to all. I rejoice therefore over you. But I desire to have you wise in that which is good, but innocent in that which is evil.
B045C016V020	45	16	20	And the God of peace will quickly crush Satan under your feet. The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you.
B045C016V021	45	16	21	Timothy, my fellow worker, greets you, as do Lucius, Jason, and Sosipater, my relatives.
B045C016V022	45	16	22	I, Tertius, who write the letter, greet you in the Lord.
B045C016V023	45	16	23	Gaius, my host and host of the whole church, greets you. Erastus, the treasurer of the city, greets you, as does Quartus, the brother.
B045C016V024	45	16	24	The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you all! Amen.
B045C016V025	45	16	25	Now to him who is able to establish you according to my Good News and the proclaiming of Jesus Christ, according to the revelation of the mystery which has been kept secret through long ages,
B045C016V026	45	16	26	but now is revealed, and by the Scriptures of the prophets, according to the commandment of the eternal God, is made known for obedience of faith to all the nations;
B045C016V027	45	16	27	to the only wise God, through Jesus Christ, to whom be the glory forever! Amen.
B046C001V001	46	1	1	Paul, called to be an apostle of Jesus Christ through the will of God, and our brother Sosthenes,
B046C001V002	46	1	2	to the church of God which is at Corinth; those who are sanctified in Christ Jesus, called to be saints, with all who call on the name of our Lord Jesus Christ in every place, both theirs and ours:
B046C001V003	46	1	3	Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B046C001V004	46	1	4	I always thank my God concerning you, for the grace of God which was given you in Christ Jesus;
B046C001V005	46	1	5	that in everything you were enriched in him, in all speech and all knowledge;
B046C001V006	46	1	6	even as the testimony of Christ was confirmed in you:
B046C001V007	46	1	7	so that you come behind in no gift; waiting for the revelation of our Lord Jesus Christ;
B046C001V008	46	1	8	who will also confirm you until the end, blameless in the day of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B046C001V009	46	1	9	God is faithful, through whom you were called into the fellowship of his Son, Jesus Christ, our Lord.
B046C001V010	46	1	10	Now I beg you, brothers, through the name of our Lord, Jesus Christ, that you all speak the same thing and that there be no divisions among you, but that you be perfected together in the same mind and in the same judgment.
B046C001V011	46	1	11	For it has been reported to me concerning you, my brothers, by those who are from Chloe's household, that there are contentions among you.
B046C001V012	46	1	12	Now I mean this, that each one of you says, "I follow Paul," "I follow Apollos," "I follow Cephas," and, "I follow Christ."
B046C001V013	46	1	13	Is Christ divided? Was Paul crucified for you? Or were you baptized into the name of Paul?
B046C001V014	46	1	14	I thank God that I baptized none of you, except Crispus and Gaius,
B046C001V015	46	1	15	so that no one should say that you had been baptized into my own name.
B046C001V016	46	1	16	(I also baptized the household of Stephanas; besides them, I do not know whether I baptized any other.)
B046C001V017	46	1	17	For Christ sent me not to baptize, but to proclaim the Good News-not in wisdom of words, so that the cross of Christ would not be made void.
B046C001V018	46	1	18	For the word of the cross is foolishness to those who are dying, but to us who are saved it is the power of God.
B046C001V019	46	1	19	For it is written,
B046C001V020	46	1	20	Where is the wise? Where is the scribe? Where is the Law scholar of this world? Hasn't God made foolish the wisdom of this world?
B046C001V021	46	1	21	For seeing that in the wisdom of God, the world through its wisdom did not know God, it was God's good pleasure through the foolishness of the proclaiming to save those who believe.
B046C001V022	46	1	22	For Jews ask for signs, Greeks seek after wisdom,
B046C001V023	46	1	23	but we proclaim Christ crucified; a stumbling block to Jews, and foolishness to Gentiles,
B046C001V024	46	1	24	but to those who are called, both Jews and Greeks, Christ is the power of God and the wisdom of God.
B046C001V025	46	1	25	Because the foolishness of God is wiser than men, and the weakness of God is stronger than men.
B046C001V026	46	1	26	For you see your calling, brothers, that not many are wise according to the flesh, not many mighty, and not many noble;
B046C001V027	46	1	27	but God chose the foolish things of the world that he might put to shame those who are wise. God chose the weak things of the world, that he might put to shame the things that are strong;
B046C001V028	46	1	28	and God chose the lowly things of the world, and the things that are despised, and the things that are not, that he might bring to nothing the things that are:
B046C001V029	46	1	29	that no flesh should boast before God.
B046C001V030	46	1	30	But of him, you are in Christ Jesus, who was made to us wisdom from God, and righteousness and sanctification, and redemption:
B046C001V031	46	1	31	that, according as it is written, "He who boasts, let him boast in 
B046C002V001	46	2	1	When I came to you, brothers, I did not come with excellence of speech or of wisdom, proclaiming to you the mystery of God.
B046C002V002	46	2	2	For I determined not to know anything among you, except Jesus Christ, and him crucified.
B046C002V003	46	2	3	I was with you in weakness, in fear, and in much trembling.
B046C002V004	46	2	4	My speech and my proclaiming were not in persuasive words of wisdom, but in demonstration of the Spirit and of power,
B046C002V005	46	2	5	that your faith would not stand in the wisdom of men, but in the power of God.
B046C002V006	46	2	6	We speak wisdom, however, among those who are full grown; yet a wisdom not of this world, nor of the rulers of this world, who are coming to nothing.
B046C002V007	46	2	7	But we speak God's wisdom in a mystery, the wisdom that has been hidden, which God foreordained before the worlds for our glory,
B046C002V008	46	2	8	which none of the rulers of this world has known. For had they known it, they would not have crucified the Lord of glory.
B046C002V009	46	2	9	But as it is written,
B046C002V010	46	2	10	But to us, God revealed them through the Spirit. For the Spirit searches all things, yes, the deep things of God.
B046C002V011	46	2	11	For who among men knows the things of a man, except the spirit of the man, which is in him? Even so, no one knows the things of God, except God's Spirit.
B046C002V012	46	2	12	But we received, not the spirit of the world, but the Spirit which is from God, that we might know the things that were freely given to us by God.
B046C002V013	46	2	13	Which things also we speak, not in words which man's wisdom teaches, but which the Spirit teaches, comparing spiritual things with spiritual things.
B046C002V014	46	2	14	Now the natural man does not receive the things of God's Spirit, for they are foolishness to him, and he cannot know them, because they are spiritually discerned.
B046C002V015	46	2	15	But he who is spiritual discerns all things, and he himself is judged by no one.
B046C002V016	46	2	16	"For who has known the mind of 
B046C003V001	46	3	1	Brothers, I could not speak to you as to spiritual, but as to fleshly, as to babies in Christ.
B046C003V002	46	3	2	I fed you with milk, not with meat; for you weren't yet ready. Indeed, not even now are you ready,
B046C003V003	46	3	3	for you are still fleshly. For insofar as there is jealousy, strife, and factions among you, are not you fleshly, and do you not walk in the ways of men?
B046C003V004	46	3	4	For when one says, "I follow Paul," and another, "I follow Apollos," are not you men?
B046C003V005	46	3	5	Who then is Apollos, and who is Paul, but servants through whom you believed; and each as the Lord gave to him?
B046C003V006	46	3	6	I planted. Apollos watered. But God gave the increase.
B046C003V007	46	3	7	So then neither he who plants is anything, nor he who waters, but God who gives the increase.
B046C003V008	46	3	8	Now he who plants and he who waters are the same, but each will receive his own reward according to his own labor.
B046C003V009	46	3	9	For we are God's fellow workers. You are God's farming, God's building.
B046C003V010	46	3	10	According to the grace of God which was given to me, as a wise master builder I laid a foundation, and another builds on it. But let each man be careful how he builds on it.
B046C003V011	46	3	11	For no one can lay any other foundation than that which has been laid, which is Jesus Christ.
B046C003V012	46	3	12	But if anyone builds on the foundation with gold, silver, costly stones, wood, hay, or stubble;
B046C003V013	46	3	13	each man's work will be revealed. For the Day will declare it, because it is revealed in fire; and the fire itself will test what sort of work each man's work is.
B046C003V014	46	3	14	If any man's work remains which he built on it, he will receive a reward.
B046C003V015	46	3	15	If any man's work is burned, he will suffer loss, but he himself will be saved, but as through fire.
B046C003V016	46	3	16	Do you not know that you are a temple of God, and that God's Spirit lives in you?
B046C003V017	46	3	17	If anyone destroys the temple of God, God will destroy him; for God's temple is holy, which you are.
B046C003V018	46	3	18	Let no one deceive himself. If anyone thinks that he is wise among you in this world, let him become a fool, that he may become wise.
B046C003V019	46	3	19	For the wisdom of this world is foolishness with God. For it is written, "He has taken the wise in their craftiness."
B046C003V020	46	3	20	And again, "
B046C003V021	46	3	21	Therefore let no one boast in men. For all things are yours,
B046C003V022	46	3	22	whether Paul, or Apollos, or Cephas, or the world, or life, or death, or things present, or things to come. All are yours,
B046C003V023	46	3	23	and you are Christ's, and Christ is God's.
B046C004V001	46	4	1	So let a man think of us as Christ's servants, and stewards of God's mysteries.
B046C004V002	46	4	2	Here, moreover, it is required of stewards, that they be found faithful.
B046C004V003	46	4	3	But with me it is a very small thing that I should be judged by you, or by man's judgment. Yes, I do not judge my own self.
B046C004V004	46	4	4	For I know nothing against myself. Yet I am not justified by this, but he who judges me is the Lord.
B046C004V005	46	4	5	Therefore judge nothing before the time, until the Lord comes, who will both bring to light the hidden things of darkness, and reveal the counsels of the hearts. Then each man will get his praise from God.
B046C004V006	46	4	6	Now these things, brothers, I have in a figure transferred to myself and Apollos for your sakes, that in us you might learn not to go beyond the things which are written, that none of you be puffed up against one another.
B046C004V007	46	4	7	For who makes you different? And what do you have that you did not receive? But if you did receive it, why do you boast as if you had not received it?
B046C004V008	46	4	8	You are already filled. You have already become rich. You have come to reign without us. Yes, and I wish that you did reign, that we also might reign with you.
B046C004V009	46	4	9	For, I think that God has displayed us, the apostles, last of all, like men sentenced to death. For we are made a spectacle to the world, both to angels and men.
B046C004V010	46	4	10	We are fools for Christ's sake, but you are wise in Christ. We are weak, but you are strong. You have honor, but we have dishonor.
B046C004V011	46	4	11	Even to this present hour we hunger, thirst, are naked, are beaten, and have no certain dwelling place.
B046C004V012	46	4	12	We toil, working with our own hands. When people curse us, we bless. Being persecuted, we endure.
B046C004V013	46	4	13	Being defamed, we entreat. We are made as the filth of the world, the dirt wiped off by all, even until now.
B046C004V014	46	4	14	I do not write these things to shame you, but to admonish you as my beloved children.
B046C004V015	46	4	15	For though you have ten thousand tutors in Christ, yet not many fathers. For in Christ Jesus, I became your father through the Good News.
B046C004V016	46	4	16	I beg you therefore, be imitators of me.
B046C004V017	46	4	17	Because of this I have sent Timothy to you, who is my beloved and faithful child in the Lord, who will remind you of my ways which are in Christ, even as I teach everywhere in every church.
B046C004V018	46	4	18	Now some are puffed up, as though I were not coming to you.
B046C004V019	46	4	19	But I will come to you shortly, if the Lord is willing. And I will know, not the word of those who are puffed up, but the power.
B046C004V020	46	4	20	For the Kingdom of God is not in word, but in power.
B046C004V021	46	4	21	What do you want? Shall I come to you with a rod, or in love and a spirit of gentleness?
B046C005V001	46	5	1	It is actually reported that there is sexual immorality among you, and such sexual immorality as is not even among the Gentiles, that one has his father's wife.
B046C005V002	46	5	2	You are puffed up, and did not rather mourn, that he who had done this deed might be removed from among you.
B046C005V003	46	5	3	For I most certainly, as being absent in body but present in spirit, have already, as though I were present, judged him who has done this thing.
B046C005V004	46	5	4	In the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, you being gathered together, and my spirit, with the power of our Lord Jesus Christ,
B046C005V005	46	5	5	are to deliver such a one to Satan for the destruction of the flesh, that the spirit may be saved in the day of the Lord Jesus.
B046C005V006	46	5	6	Your boasting is not good. Do you not know that a little yeast leavens the whole lump?
B046C005V007	46	5	7	Purge out the old yeast, that you may be a new lump, even as you are unleavened. For indeed Christ, our Passover, has been sacrificed.
B046C005V008	46	5	8	Therefore let us keep the feast, not with old yeast, neither with the yeast of malice and wickedness, but with the unleavened bread of sincerity and truth.
B046C005V009	46	5	9	I wrote to you in my letter to have no company with sexual sinners;
B046C005V010	46	5	10	yet not at all meaning with the sexual sinners of this world, or with the covetous and extortioners, or with idolaters; for then you would have to leave the world.
B046C005V011	46	5	11	But as it is, I wrote to you not to associate with anyone who is called a brother who is a sexual sinner, or covetous, or an idolater, or a slanderer, or a drunkard, or an extortioner. Do not even eat with such a person.
B046C005V012	46	5	12	For what have I to do with also judging those who are outside? Do you not judge those who are within?
B046C005V013	46	5	13	But those who are outside, God judges. "Put away the wicked man from among yourselves."
B046C006V001	46	6	1	Dare any of you, having a matter against his neighbor, go to law before the unrighteous, and not before the saints?
B046C006V002	46	6	2	Do you not know that the saints will judge the world? And if the world is judged by you, are you unworthy to judge the smallest matters?
B046C006V003	46	6	3	Do you not know that we will judge angels? How much more, things that pertain to this life?
B046C006V004	46	6	4	If then, you have to judge things pertaining to this life, do you set them to judge who are of no account in the church?
B046C006V005	46	6	5	I say this to move you to shame. Is not there even one wise man among you who would be able to decide between his brothers?
B046C006V006	46	6	6	But brother goes to law with brother, and that before unbelievers!
B046C006V007	46	6	7	Therefore it is already altogether a defect in you, that you have lawsuits one with another. Why not rather be wronged? Why not rather be defrauded?
B046C006V008	46	6	8	No, but you yourselves do wrong, and defraud, and that against your brothers.
B046C006V009	46	6	9	Or do you not know that the unrighteous will not inherit the Kingdom of God? Do not be deceived. Neither the sexually immoral, nor idolaters, nor adulterers, nor male prostitutes, nor men who practice sexual relations with men,
B046C006V010	46	6	10	nor thieves, nor covetous, nor drunkards, nor slanderers, nor extortioners, will inherit the Kingdom of God.
B046C006V011	46	6	11	Such were some of you, but you were washed. But you were sanctified. But you were justified in the name of the Lord Jesus, and in the Spirit of our God.
B046C006V012	46	6	12	"All things are lawful for me," but not all things are expedient. "All things are lawful for me," but I will not be brought under the power of anything.
B046C006V013	46	6	13	"Foods for the belly, and the belly for foods," but God will bring to nothing both it and them. But the body is not for sexual immorality, but for the Lord; and the Lord for the body.
B046C006V014	46	6	14	Now God raised up the Lord, and will also raise us up by his power.
B046C006V015	46	6	15	Do you not know that your bodies are members of Christ? Shall I then take the members of Christ, and make them members of a prostitute? May it never be!
B046C006V016	46	6	16	Or do you not know that he who is joined to a prostitute is one body? For, "The two," says he, "will become one flesh."
B046C006V017	46	6	17	But he who is joined to the Lord is one spirit.
B046C006V018	46	6	18	Flee sexual immorality! "Every sin that a man does is outside the body," but he who commits sexual immorality sins against his own body.
B046C006V019	46	6	19	Or do you not know that your body is a temple of the Holy Spirit which is in you, which you have from God? You are not your own,
B046C006V020	46	6	20	for you were bought with a price. Therefore glorify God in your body.
B046C007V001	46	7	1	Now concerning the things about which you wrote: it is good for a man not to touch a woman.
B046C007V002	46	7	2	But, because of sexual immoralities, let each man have his own wife, and let each woman have her own husband.
B046C007V003	46	7	3	Let the husband fulfill his marital duty to his wife, and likewise also the wife to her husband.
B046C007V004	46	7	4	The wife does not have authority over her own body, but the husband. Likewise also the husband does not have authority over his own body, but the wife.
B046C007V005	46	7	5	Do not deprive one another, unless it is by consent for a season, that you may give yourselves to prayer, and may be together again, that Satan does not tempt you because of your lack of self-control.
B046C007V006	46	7	6	But this I say by way of concession, not of commandment.
B046C007V007	46	7	7	Yet I wish that all men were like me. However each man has his own gift from God, one of this kind, and another of that kind.
B046C007V008	46	7	8	But I say to the unmarried and to widows, it is good for them if they remain even as I am.
B046C007V009	46	7	9	But if they do not have self-control, let them marry. For it's better to marry than to burn.
B046C007V010	46	7	10	But to the married I command-not I, but the Lord-that the wife not leave her husband
B046C007V011	46	7	11	(but if she departs, let her remain unmarried, or else be reconciled to her husband), and that the husband not leave his wife.
B046C007V012	46	7	12	But to the rest I-not the Lord-say, if any brother has an unbelieving wife, and she is content to live with him, let him not leave her.
B046C007V013	46	7	13	The woman who has an unbelieving husband, and he is content to live with her, let her not leave her husband.
B046C007V014	46	7	14	For the unbelieving husband is sanctified in the wife, and the unbelieving wife is sanctified by the brother. Otherwise your children would be unclean, but now they are holy.
B046C007V015	46	7	15	Yet if the unbeliever departs, let there be separation. The brother or the sister is not under bondage in such cases, but God has called us to peace.
B046C007V016	46	7	16	For how do you know, wife, whether you will save your husband? Or how do you know, husband, whether you will save your wife?
B046C007V017	46	7	17	Only, as the Lord has distributed to each man, as God has called each, so let him walk. So I command in all the churches.
B046C007V018	46	7	18	Was anyone called having been circumcised? Let him not become uncircumcised. Has anyone been called in uncircumcision? Let him not be circumcised.
B046C007V019	46	7	19	Circumcision is nothing, and uncircumcision is nothing, but the keeping of the commandments of God.
B046C007V020	46	7	20	Let each man stay in that calling in which he was called.
B046C007V021	46	7	21	Were you called being a bondservant? Do not let that bother you, but if you get an opportunity to become free, use it.
B046C007V022	46	7	22	For he who was called in the Lord being a bondservant is the Lord's free man. Likewise he who was called being free is Christ's bondservant.
B046C007V023	46	7	23	You were bought with a price. Do not become bondservants of men.
B046C007V024	46	7	24	Brothers, let each man, in whatever condition he was called, stay in that condition with God.
B046C007V025	46	7	25	Now concerning virgins, I have no commandment from the Lord, but I give my judgment as one who has obtained mercy from the Lord to be trustworthy.
B046C007V026	46	7	26	I think that it is good therefore, because of the distress that is on us, that it is good for a man to be as he is.
B046C007V027	46	7	27	Are you bound to a wife? Do not seek to be freed. Are you free from a wife? Do not seek a wife.
B046C007V028	46	7	28	But if you marry, you have not sinned. If a virgin marries, she has not sinned. Yet such will have oppression in the flesh, and I want to spare you.
B046C007V029	46	7	29	But I say this, brothers: the time is short, that from now on, both those who have wives may be as though they had none;
B046C007V030	46	7	30	and those who weep, as though they did not weep; and those who rejoice, as though they did not rejoice; and those who buy, as though they did not possess;
B046C007V031	46	7	31	and those who use the world, as not using it to the fullest. For the mode of this world passes away.
B046C007V032	46	7	32	But I desire to have you to be free from cares. He who is unmarried is concerned for the things of the Lord, how he may please the Lord;
B046C007V033	46	7	33	but he who is married is concerned about the things of the world, how he may please his wife.
B046C007V034	46	7	34	There is also a difference between a wife and a virgin. The unmarried woman cares about the things of the Lord, that she may be holy both in body and in spirit. But she who is married cares about the things of the world-how she may please her husband.
B046C007V035	46	7	35	This I say for your own profit; not that I may ensnare you, but for that which is appropriate, and that you may attend to the Lord without distraction.
B046C007V036	46	7	36	But if any man thinks that he is behaving inappropriately toward his virgin, if she is past the flower of her age, and if need so requires, let him do what he desires. He does not sin. Let them marry.
B046C007V037	46	7	37	But he who stands steadfast in his heart, having no necessity, but has power over his own heart, to keep his own virgin, does well.
B046C007V038	46	7	38	So then both he who gives his own virgin in marriage does well, and he who does not give her in marriage does better.
B046C007V039	46	7	39	A wife is bound to her husband as long as he lives; but if the husband is dead, she is free to be married to whomever she desires, only in the Lord.
B046C007V040	46	7	40	But she is happier if she stays as she is, in my judgment, and I think that I also have God's Spirit.
B046C008V001	46	8	1	Now concerning things sacrificed to idols: We know that we all have knowledge. Knowledge puffs up, but love builds up.
B046C008V002	46	8	2	But if anyone thinks that he knows anything, he does not yet know as he ought to know.
B046C008V003	46	8	3	But if anyone loves God, the same is known by him.
B046C008V004	46	8	4	Therefore concerning the eating of things sacrificed to idols, we know that no idol is anything in the world, and that there is no God but one.
B046C008V005	46	8	5	For though there are things that are called "gods," whether in the heavens or on earth; as there are many "gods" and many "lords;"
B046C008V006	46	8	6	yet to us there is one God, the Father, from whom are all things, and we for him; and one Lord, Jesus Christ, through whom are all things, and we live through him.
B046C008V007	46	8	7	However, that knowledge is not in all men. But some, being so accustomed to idols until now, eat as of a thing sacrificed to an idol, and their conscience, being weak, is defiled.
B046C008V008	46	8	8	But food will not commend us to God. For neither, if we do not eat, are we the worse; nor, if we eat, are we the better.
B046C008V009	46	8	9	But be careful that by no means does this liberty of yours become a stumbling block to the weak.
B046C008V010	46	8	10	For if a man sees you who have knowledge sitting in an idol's temple, won't his conscience, if he is weak, be emboldened to eat things sacrificed to idols?
B046C008V011	46	8	11	And through your knowledge, he who is weak perishes, the brother for whom the Christ died.
B046C008V012	46	8	12	Thus, sinning against the brothers, and wounding their conscience when it is weak, you sin against Christ.
B046C008V013	46	8	13	Therefore, if food causes my brother to stumble, I will eat no meat forevermore, that I do not cause my brother to stumble.
B046C009V001	46	9	1	Am I not free? Am I not an apostle? Have not I seen Jesus Christ, our Lord? Are not you my work in the Lord?
B046C009V002	46	9	2	If to others I am not an apostle, yet at least I am to you; for you are the seal of my office of apostle in the Lord.
B046C009V003	46	9	3	My defense to those who examine me is this.
B046C009V004	46	9	4	Have we no right to eat and to drink?
B046C009V005	46	9	5	Have we no right to take along a wife who is a believer, even as the rest of the apostles, and the brothers of the Lord, and Cephas?
B046C009V006	46	9	6	Or have only Barnabas and I no right to not work?
B046C009V007	46	9	7	What soldier ever serves at his own expense? Who plants a vineyard, and does not eat of its fruit? Or who feeds a flock, and does not drink from the flock's milk?
B046C009V008	46	9	8	Do I speak these things according to the ways of men? Or does not the Law also say the same thing?
B046C009V009	46	9	9	For it is written in the Law of Moses, "You shall not muzzle an ox while it treads out the grain." Is it for the oxen that God cares,
B046C009V010	46	9	10	or does he say it assuredly for our sake? Yes, it was written for our sake, because he who plows ought to plow in hope, and he who threshes in the hope of having a share.
B046C009V011	46	9	11	If we sowed to you spiritual things, is it a great thing if we reap your fleshly things?
B046C009V012	46	9	12	If others partake of this right over you, do not we yet more? Nevertheless we did not use this right, but we bear all things, that we may cause no hindrance to the Good News of Christ.
B046C009V013	46	9	13	Do you not know that those who serve around sacred things eat from the things of the temple, and those who wait on the altar have their portion with the altar?
B046C009V014	46	9	14	Even so the Lord ordained that those who proclaim the Good News should live from the Good News.
B046C009V015	46	9	15	But I have used none of these things, and I do not write these things that it may be done so in my case; for I would rather die, than that anyone should make my boasting void.
B046C009V016	46	9	16	For if I proclaim the Good News, I have nothing to boast about; for necessity is laid on me; but woe is to me, if I do not proclaim the Good News.
B046C009V017	46	9	17	For if I do this of my own will, I have a reward. But if not of my own will, I have a stewardship entrusted to me.
B046C009V018	46	9	18	What then is my reward? That, when I proclaim the Good News, I may present the Good News without charge, so as not to abuse my authority in the Good News.
B046C009V019	46	9	19	For though I was free from all, I brought myself under bondage to all, that I might gain the more.
B046C009V020	46	9	20	To the Jews I became as a Jew, that I might gain Jews; to those who are under the law, as under the law, not being myself under the law, that I might gain those who are under the law;
B046C009V021	46	9	21	to those who are without law, as without law (not being without law toward God, but under law toward Christ), that I might win those who are without law.
B046C009V022	46	9	22	To the weak I became as weak, that I might gain the weak. I have become all things to all men, that I may by all means save some.
B046C009V023	46	9	23	Now I do all things for the sake of the Good News, that I may be a joint partaker of it.
B046C009V024	46	9	24	Do you not know that those who run in a race all run, but one receives the prize? Run like that, that you may win.
B046C009V025	46	9	25	Every man who strives in the games exercises self-control in all things. Now they do it to receive a corruptible crown, but we an incorruptible.
B046C009V026	46	9	26	I therefore run like that, as not uncertainly. I fight like that, as not beating the air,
B046C009V027	46	9	27	but I beat my body and bring it into submission, lest by any means, after I have preached to others, I myself should be rejected.
B046C010V001	46	10	1	Now I would not have you ignorant, brothers, that our fathers were all under the cloud, and all passed through the sea;
B046C010V002	46	10	2	and were all baptized into Moses in the cloud and in the sea;
B046C010V003	46	10	3	and all ate the same spiritual food;
B046C010V004	46	10	4	and all drank the same spiritual drink. For they drank of a spiritual rock that followed them, and the rock was Christ.
B046C010V005	46	10	5	However with most of them, God was not well pleased, for they were overthrown in the wilderness.
B046C010V006	46	10	6	Now these things were our examples, to the intent we should not lust after evil things, as they also lusted.
B046C010V007	46	10	7	Neither be idolaters, as some of them were. As it is written, "The people sat down to eat and drink, and rose up to play."
B046C010V008	46	10	8	Neither let us commit sexual immorality, as some of them committed, and in one day twenty-three thousand fell.
B046C010V009	46	10	9	Neither let us test the Lord, as some of them tested, and perished by the serpents.
B046C010V010	46	10	10	Neither grumble, as some of them also grumbled, and perished by the destroyer.
B046C010V011	46	10	11	Now all these things happened to them by way of example, and they were written for our admonition, on whom the ends of the ages have come.
B046C010V012	46	10	12	Therefore let him who thinks he stands be careful that he does not fall.
B046C010V013	46	10	13	No temptation has taken you except what is common to man. God is faithful, who will not allow you to be tempted above what you are able, but will with the temptation also make the way of escape, that you may be able to endure it.
B046C010V014	46	10	14	Therefore, my beloved, flee from idolatry.
B046C010V015	46	10	15	I speak as to wise men. Judge what I say.
B046C010V016	46	10	16	The cup of blessing which we bless, is not it a sharing of the blood of Christ? The bread which we break, is not it a sharing of the body of Christ?
B046C010V017	46	10	17	Because there is one loaf of bread, we, who are many, are one body; for we all partake of the one loaf of bread.
B046C010V018	46	10	18	Consider Israel according to the flesh. Do not those who eat the sacrifices participate in the altar?
B046C010V019	46	10	19	What am I saying then? That a thing sacrificed to idols is anything, or that an idol is anything?
B046C010V020	46	10	20	But I say that the things which the Gentiles sacrifice, they sacrifice to demons, and not to God, and I do not desire that you would have fellowship with demons.
B046C010V021	46	10	21	You cannot both drink the cup of the Lord and the cup of demons. You cannot both partake of the table of the Lord, and of the table of demons.
B046C010V022	46	10	22	Or do we provoke the Lord to jealousy? Are we stronger than he?
B046C010V023	46	10	23	"All things are lawful," but not all things are profitable. "All things are lawful," but not all things build up.
B046C010V024	46	10	24	Let no one seek his own, but his neighbor's good.
B046C010V025	46	10	25	Whatever is sold in the butcher shop, eat, asking no question for the sake of conscience,
B046C010V026	46	10	26	for "the earth is the Lord's, and its fullness."
B046C010V027	46	10	27	But if one of those who do not believe invites you to a meal, and you are inclined to go, eat whatever is set before you, asking no questions for the sake of conscience.
B046C010V028	46	10	28	But if anyone says to you, "This was offered to idols," do not eat it for the sake of the one who told you, and for the sake of conscience.
B046C010V029	46	10	29	Conscience, I say, not your own, but the other's conscience. For why is my liberty judged by another conscience?
B046C010V030	46	10	30	If I partake with thankfulness, why am I denounced for that for which I give thanks?
B046C010V031	46	10	31	Whether therefore you eat, or drink, or whatever you do, do all to the glory of God.
B046C010V032	46	10	32	Give no occasions for stumbling, either to Jews, or to Greeks, or to the church of God;
B046C010V033	46	10	33	even as I also please all men in all things, not seeking my own profit, but the profit of the many, that they may be saved.
B046C011V001	46	11	1	Be imitators of me, even as I also am of Christ.
B046C011V002	46	11	2	Now I praise you, that you remember me in all things, and hold firm the traditions, even as I delivered them to you.
B046C011V003	46	11	3	But I would have you know that the head of every man is Christ, and the head of the woman is the man, and the head of Christ is God.
B046C011V004	46	11	4	Every man praying or prophesying, having his head covered, dishonors his head.
B046C011V005	46	11	5	But every woman praying or prophesying with her head unveiled dishonors her head. For it is one and the same thing as if she were shaved.
B046C011V006	46	11	6	For if a woman is not covered, let her also be shorn. But if it is shameful for a woman to be shorn or shaved, let her be covered.
B046C011V007	46	11	7	For a man indeed ought not to have his head covered, because he is the image and glory of God, but the woman is the glory of the man.
B046C011V008	46	11	8	For man is not from woman, but woman from man;
B046C011V009	46	11	9	for neither was man created for the woman, but woman for the man.
B046C011V010	46	11	10	For this cause the woman ought to have authority on her head, because of the angels.
B046C011V011	46	11	11	Nevertheless, neither is the woman independent of the man, nor the man independent of the woman, in the Lord.
B046C011V012	46	11	12	For as woman came from man, so a man also comes through a woman; but all things are from God.
B046C011V013	46	11	13	Judge for yourselves. Is it appropriate that a woman pray to God unveiled?
B046C011V014	46	11	14	Doesn't even nature itself teach you that if a man has long hair, it is a dishonor to him?
B046C011V015	46	11	15	But if a woman has long hair, it is a glory to her, for her hair is given to her for a covering.
B046C011V016	46	11	16	But if any man seems to be contentious, we have no such custom, neither do God's churches.
B046C011V017	46	11	17	But in giving you this command, I do not praise you, that you come together not for the better but for the worse.
B046C011V018	46	11	18	For first of all, when you come together in the church, I hear that divisions exist among you, and I partly believe it.
B046C011V019	46	11	19	For there also must be factions among you, that those who are approved may be revealed among you.
B046C011V020	46	11	20	When therefore you assemble yourselves together, it is not the Lord's supper that you eat.
B046C011V021	46	11	21	For in your eating each one takes his own supper first. One is hungry, and another is drunken.
B046C011V022	46	11	22	What, do you not have houses to eat and to drink in? Or do you despise God's church, and put them to shame who do not have? What shall I tell you? Shall I praise you? In this I do not praise you.
B046C011V023	46	11	23	For I received from the Lord that which also I delivered to you, that the Lord Jesus on the night in which he was betrayed took bread.
B046C011V024	46	11	24	When he had given thanks, he broke it, and said, "This is my body, which is for you. Do this in memory of me."
B046C011V025	46	11	25	In the same way he also took the cup, after supper, saying, "This cup is the New Covenant in my blood. Do this, as often as you drink, in memory of me."
B046C011V026	46	11	26	For as often as you eat this bread and drink this cup, you proclaim the Lord's death until he comes.
B046C011V027	46	11	27	Therefore whoever eats this bread or drinks the Lord's cup in a manner unworthy will be guilty of the body and the blood of the Lord.
B046C011V028	46	11	28	But let a man examine himself, and so let him eat of the bread, and drink of the cup.
B046C011V029	46	11	29	For he who eats and drinks eats and drinks judgment to himself, if he does not discern the body.
B046C011V030	46	11	30	For this cause many among you are weak and sickly, and not a few sleep.
B046C011V031	46	11	31	For if we discerned ourselves, we would not be judged.
B046C011V032	46	11	32	But when we are judged, we are punished by the Lord, that we may not be condemned with the world.
B046C011V033	46	11	33	Therefore, my brothers, when you come together to eat, wait one for another.
B046C011V034	46	11	34	But if anyone is hungry, let him eat at home, lest your coming together be for judgment. The rest I will set in order whenever I come.
B046C012V001	46	12	1	Now concerning spiritual things, brothers, I do not want you to be ignorant.
B046C012V002	46	12	2	You know that when you were heathen, you were led away to those mute idols, however you might be led.
B046C012V003	46	12	3	Therefore I make known to you that no man speaking by God's Spirit says, "Jesus is accursed." No one can say, "Jesus is Lord," but by the Holy Spirit.
B046C012V004	46	12	4	Now there are various kinds of gifts, but the same Spirit.
B046C012V005	46	12	5	There are various kinds of service, and the same Lord.
B046C012V006	46	12	6	There are various kinds of workings, but the same God, who works all things in all.
B046C012V007	46	12	7	But to each one is given the manifestation of the Spirit for the profit of all.
B046C012V008	46	12	8	For to one is given through the Spirit the word of wisdom, and to another the word of knowledge, according to the same Spirit;
B046C012V009	46	12	9	to another faith, by the same Spirit; and to another gifts of healings, by the one Spirit;
B046C012V010	46	12	10	and to another workings of miracles; and to another prophecy; and to another discerning of spirits; to another different kinds of languages; and to another the interpretation of languages.
B046C012V011	46	12	11	But the one and the same Spirit works all of these, distributing to each one separately as he desires.
B046C012V012	46	12	12	For as the body is one, and has many members, and all the members of the body, being many, are one body; so also is Christ.
B046C012V013	46	12	13	For in one Spirit we were all baptized into one body, whether Jews or Greeks, whether bond or free; and were all given to drink of one Spirit.
B046C012V014	46	12	14	For the body is not one member, but many.
B046C012V015	46	12	15	If the foot would say, "Because I'm not the hand, I'm not part of the body," it is not therefore not part of the body.
B046C012V016	46	12	16	If the ear would say, "Because I'm not the eye, I'm not part of the body," it's not therefore not part of the body.
B046C012V017	46	12	17	If the whole body were an eye, where would the hearing be? If the whole were hearing, where would the smelling be?
B046C012V018	46	12	18	But now God has set the members, each one of them, in the body, just as he desired.
B046C012V019	46	12	19	If they were all one member, where would the body be?
B046C012V020	46	12	20	But now they are many members, but one body.
B046C012V021	46	12	21	The eye cannot tell the hand, "I have no need for you," or again the head to the feet, "I have no need for you."
B046C012V022	46	12	22	No, much rather, those members of the body which seem to be weaker are necessary.
B046C012V023	46	12	23	Those parts of the body which we think to be less honorable, on those we bestow more abundant honor; and our unpresentable parts have more abundant propriety;
B046C012V024	46	12	24	whereas our presentable parts have no such need. But God composed the body together, giving more abundant honor to the inferior part,
B046C012V025	46	12	25	that there should be no division in the body, but that the members should have the same care for one another.
B046C012V026	46	12	26	When one member suffers, all the members suffer with it. Or when one member is honored, all the members rejoice with it.
B046C012V027	46	12	27	Now you are the body of Christ, and members individually.
B046C012V028	46	12	28	God has set some in the church: first apostles, second prophets, third teachers, then miracle workers, then gifts of healings, helps, governments, and various kinds of languages.
B046C012V029	46	12	29	Are all apostles? Are all prophets? Are all teachers? Are all miracle workers?
B046C012V030	46	12	30	Do all have gifts of healings? Do all speak with various languages? Do all interpret?
B046C012V031	46	12	31	But earnestly desire the greater gifts. Moreover, I show a most excellent way to you.
B046C013V001	46	13	1	If I speak with the languages of men and of angels, but do not have love, I have become sounding brass, or a clanging cymbal.
B046C013V002	46	13	2	If I have the gift of prophecy, and know all mysteries and all knowledge; and if I have all faith, so as to remove mountains, but do not have love, I am nothing.
B046C013V003	46	13	3	If I dole out all my goods to feed the poor, and if I surrender my body so that I may boast, but do not have love, it profits me nothing.
B046C013V004	46	13	4	Love is patient and is kind; love does not envy. Love does not brag, is not proud,
B046C013V005	46	13	5	doesn't behave itself inappropriately, does not seek its own way, is not provoked, takes no account of evil;
B046C013V006	46	13	6	doesn't rejoice in unrighteousness, but rejoices with the truth;
B046C013V007	46	13	7	bears all things, believes all things, hopes all things, endures all things.
B046C013V008	46	13	8	Love never fails. But where there are prophecies, they will be done away with. Where there are various languages, they will cease. Where there is knowledge, it will be done away with.
B046C013V009	46	13	9	For we know in part, and we prophesy in part;
B046C013V010	46	13	10	but when that which is complete has come, then that which is partial will be done away with.
B046C013V011	46	13	11	When I was a child, I spoke as a child, I felt as a child, I thought as a child. Now that I have become a man, I have put away childish things.
B046C013V012	46	13	12	For now we see in a mirror, dimly, but then face to face. Now I know in part, but then I will know fully, even as I was also fully known.
B046C013V013	46	13	13	But now faith, hope, and love remain-these three. The greatest of these is love.
B046C014V001	46	14	1	Follow after love, and earnestly desire spiritual gifts, but especially that you may prophesy.
B046C014V002	46	14	2	For he who speaks in another language speaks not to men, but to God; for no one understands; but in the Spirit he speaks mysteries.
B046C014V003	46	14	3	But he who prophesies speaks to men for their encouragement, strengthening, and comfort.
B046C014V004	46	14	4	He who speaks in another language edifies himself, but he who prophesies edifies the church.
B046C014V005	46	14	5	Now I desire to have you all speak with other languages, but rather that you would prophesy, and he is greater who prophesies than he who speaks with other languages, unless he interprets, that the church may be built up.
B046C014V006	46	14	6	But now, brothers, if I come to you speaking with other languages, what would I profit you, unless I speak to you either by way of revelation, or of knowledge, or of prophesying, or of teaching?
B046C014V007	46	14	7	Even things without life, giving a voice, whether pipe or harp, if they did not give a distinction in the sounds, how would it be known what is piped or harped?
B046C014V008	46	14	8	For if the trumpet gave an uncertain sound, who would prepare himself for war?
B046C014V009	46	14	9	So also you, unless you uttered by the tongue words easy to understand, how would it be known what is spoken? For you would be speaking into the air.
B046C014V010	46	14	10	There are, it may be, so many kinds of sounds in the world, and none is without meaning.
B046C014V011	46	14	11	If then I do not know the meaning of the sound, I would be to him who speaks a foreigner, and he who speaks would be a foreigner to me.
B046C014V012	46	14	12	So also you, since you are zealous for spiritual gifts, seek that you may abound to the building up of the church.
B046C014V013	46	14	13	Therefore let him who speaks in another language pray that he may interpret.
B046C014V014	46	14	14	For if I pray in another language, my spirit prays, but my understanding is unfruitful.
B046C014V015	46	14	15	What is it then? I will pray with the spirit, and I will pray with the understanding also. I will sing with the spirit, and I will sing with the understanding also.
B046C014V016	46	14	16	Otherwise if you bless with the spirit, how will he who fills the place of the unlearned say the "Amen" at your giving of thanks, seeing he does not know what you say?
B046C014V017	46	14	17	For you truly give thanks well, but the other person is not built up.
B046C014V018	46	14	18	I thank God, I speak with other languages more than you all.
B046C014V019	46	14	19	However in the church I would rather speak five words with my understanding, that I might instruct others also, than ten thousand words in another language.
B046C014V020	46	14	20	Brothers, do not be children in thoughts, yet in malice be babies, but in thoughts be mature.
B046C014V021	46	14	21	In the law it is written, "By men of strange languages and by the lips of strangers I will speak to this people. Not even thus will they hear me, says 
B046C014V022	46	14	22	Therefore other languages are for a sign, not to those who believe, but to the unbelieving; but prophesying is for a sign, not to the unbelieving, but to those who believe.
B046C014V023	46	14	23	If therefore the whole church is assembled together and all speak with other languages, and unlearned or unbelieving people come in, won't they say that you are crazy?
B046C014V024	46	14	24	But if all prophesy, and someone unbelieving or unlearned comes in, he is reproved by all, and he is judged by all.
B046C014V025	46	14	25	And thus the secrets of his heart are revealed. So he will fall down on his face and worship God, declaring that God is among you indeed.
B046C014V026	46	14	26	What is it then, brothers? When you come together, each one of you has a psalm, has a teaching, has a revelation, has another language, has an interpretation. Let all things be done to build each other up.
B046C014V027	46	14	27	If any man speaks in another language, let it be two, or at the most three, and in turn; and let one interpret.
B046C014V028	46	14	28	But if there is no interpreter, let him keep silent in the church, and let him speak to himself, and to God.
B046C014V029	46	14	29	Let the prophets speak, two or three, and let the others discern.
B046C014V030	46	14	30	But if a revelation is made to another sitting by, let the first keep silent.
B046C014V031	46	14	31	For you can all prophesy one by one, that all may learn and all may be encouraged.
B046C014V032	46	14	32	The spirits of the prophets are subject to the prophets,
B046C014V033	46	14	33	for God is not a God of confusion, but of peace.As in all the churches of the saints,
B046C014V034	46	14	34	let the women keep silent in the churches, for it has not been permitted for them to speak; but let them be in subjection, as the Law also says.
B046C014V035	46	14	35	If they desire to learn anything, let them ask their own husbands at home, for it is shameful for a woman to chatter in the church.
B046C014V036	46	14	36	What? Was it from you that the word of God went out? Or did it come to you alone?
B046C014V037	46	14	37	If any man thinks himself to be a prophet, or spiritual, let him recognize the things which I write to you, that they are the commandment of the Lord.
B046C014V038	46	14	38	But if someone does not recognize this, he is not recognized.
B046C014V039	46	14	39	Therefore, brothers, desire earnestly to prophesy, and do not forbid speaking with other languages.
B046C014V040	46	14	40	Let all things be done decently and in order.
B046C015V001	46	15	1	Now I declare to you, brothers, the Good News which I preached to you, which also you received, in which you also stand,
B046C015V002	46	15	2	by which also you are saved, if you hold firmly the word which I preached to you-unless you believed in vain.
B046C015V003	46	15	3	For I delivered to you first of all that which I also received: that Christ died for our sins according to the Scriptures,
B046C015V004	46	15	4	that he was buried, that he was raised on the third day according to the Scriptures,
B046C015V005	46	15	5	and that he appeared to Cephas, then to the twelve.
B046C015V006	46	15	6	Then he appeared to over five hundred brothers at once, most of whom remain until now, but some have also fallen asleep.
B046C015V007	46	15	7	Then he appeared to Jacob, then to all the apostles,
B046C015V008	46	15	8	and last of all, as to the child born at the wrong time, he appeared to me also.
B046C015V009	46	15	9	For I am the least of the apostles, who is not worthy to be called an apostle, because I persecuted the church of God.
B046C015V010	46	15	10	But by the grace of God I am what I am. His grace which was bestowed on me was not futile, but I worked more than all of them; yet not I, but the grace of God which was with me.
B046C015V011	46	15	11	Whether then it is I or they, so we proclaim, and so you believed.
B046C015V012	46	15	12	Now if Christ is preached, that he has been raised from the dead, how do some among you say that there is no resurrection of the dead?
B046C015V013	46	15	13	But if there is no resurrection of the dead, neither has Christ been raised.
B046C015V014	46	15	14	If Christ has not been raised, then our proclaiming is in vain, and your faith also is in vain.
B046C015V015	46	15	15	Yes, we are found false witnesses of God, because we testified about God that he raised up Christ, whom he did not raise up, if it is so that the dead are not raised.
B046C015V016	46	15	16	For if the dead are not raised, neither has Christ been raised.
B046C015V017	46	15	17	If Christ has not been raised, your faith is vain; you are still in your sins.
B046C015V018	46	15	18	Then they also who are fallen asleep in Christ have perished.
B046C015V019	46	15	19	If we have only hoped in Christ in this life, we are of all men most pitiable.
B046C015V020	46	15	20	But now Christ has been raised from the dead, the first fruits of those who are asleep.
B046C015V021	46	15	21	For since death came by man, the resurrection of the dead also came by man.
B046C015V022	46	15	22	For as in Adam all die, so also in Christ all will be made alive.
B046C015V023	46	15	23	But each in his own order: Christ the first fruits, then those who are Christ's, at his coming.
B046C015V024	46	15	24	Then the end comes, when he will deliver up the Kingdom to God, even the Father; when he will have abolished all rule and all authority and power.
B046C015V025	46	15	25	For he must reign until he has put all his enemies under his feet.
B046C015V026	46	15	26	The last enemy that will be abolished is death.
B046C015V027	46	15	27	For, "He put all things in subjection under his feet." But when he says, "All things are put in subjection," it is evident that he is excepted who subjected all things to him.
B046C015V028	46	15	28	When all things have been subjected to him, then the Son will also himself be subjected to him who subjected all things to him, that God may be all in all.
B046C015V029	46	15	29	Or else what will they do who are baptized for the dead? If the dead are not raised at all, why then are they baptized for them?
B046C015V030	46	15	30	Why do we also stand in jeopardy every hour?
B046C015V031	46	15	31	I affirm, by the boasting in you which I have in Christ Jesus our Lord, I die daily.
B046C015V032	46	15	32	If I fought with animals at Ephesus for human purposes, what does it profit me? If the dead are not raised, then "let us eat and drink, for tomorrow we die."
B046C015V033	46	15	33	Do not be deceived! "Evil companionships corrupt good morals."
B046C015V034	46	15	34	Wake up righteously, and do not sin, for some have no knowledge of God. I say this to your shame.
B046C015V035	46	15	35	But someone will say, "How are the dead raised?" and, "With what kind of body do they come?"
B046C015V036	46	15	36	You foolish one, that which you yourself sow is not made alive unless it dies.
B046C015V037	46	15	37	That which you sow, you do not sow the body that will be, but a bare grain, maybe of wheat, or of some other kind.
B046C015V038	46	15	38	But God gives it a body even as it pleased him, and to each seed a body of its own.
B046C015V039	46	15	39	All flesh is not the same flesh, but there is one flesh of men, another flesh of animals, another of fish, and another of birds.
B046C015V040	46	15	40	There are also celestial bodies, and terrestrial bodies; but the glory of the celestial differs from that of the terrestrial.
B046C015V041	46	15	41	There is one glory of the sun, another glory of the moon, and another glory of the stars; for one star differs from another star in glory.
B046C015V042	46	15	42	So also is the resurrection of the dead. It is sown in corruption; it is raised in incorruption.
B046C015V043	46	15	43	It is sown in dishonor; it is raised in glory. It is sown in weakness; it is raised in power.
B046C015V044	46	15	44	It is sown a natural body; it is raised a spiritual body. There is a natural body and there is also a spiritual body.
B046C015V045	46	15	45	So also it is written, "The first man, Adam, became a living soul." The last Adam became a life-giving spirit.
B046C015V046	46	15	46	However that which is spiritual is not first, but that which is natural, then that which is spiritual.
B046C015V047	46	15	47	The first man is of the earth, made of dust. The second man is from heaven.
B046C015V048	46	15	48	As is the one made of dust, such are those who are also made of dust; and as is the heavenly, such are they also that are heavenly.
B046C015V049	46	15	49	As we have borne the image of those made of dust, we will also bear the image of the heavenly.
B046C015V050	46	15	50	Now I say this, brothers, that flesh and blood cannot inherit the Kingdom of God; neither does corruption inherit incorruption.
B046C015V051	46	15	51	Behold, I tell you a mystery. We will not all sleep, but we will all be changed,
B046C015V052	46	15	52	in a moment, in the twinkling of an eye, at the last trumpet. For the trumpet will sound, and the dead will be raised incorruptible, and we will be changed.
B046C015V053	46	15	53	For this corruptible must put on incorruption, and this mortal must put on immortality.
B046C015V054	46	15	54	But when this corruptible will have put on incorruption, and this mortal will have put on immortality, then what is written will happen: "Death is swallowed up in victory."
B046C015V055	46	15	55	"Death, where is your victory?Death, where is your sting?" 
B046C015V056	46	15	56	The sting of death is sin, and the power of sin is the law.
B046C015V057	46	15	57	But thanks be to God, who gives us the victory through our Lord Jesus Christ.
B046C015V058	46	15	58	Therefore, my beloved brothers, be steadfast, immovable, always abounding in the Lord's work, because you know that your labor is not in vain in the Lord.
B046C016V001	46	16	1	Now concerning the collection for the saints, as I commanded the churches of Galatia, you do likewise.
B046C016V002	46	16	2	On the first day of the week, let each one of you save, as he may prosper, that no collections be made when I come.
B046C016V003	46	16	3	When I arrive, I will send whoever you approve with letters to carry your gracious gift to Jerusalem.
B046C016V004	46	16	4	If it is appropriate for me to go also, they will go with me.
B046C016V005	46	16	5	But I will come to you when I have passed through Macedonia, for I am passing through Macedonia.
B046C016V006	46	16	6	But with you it may be that I will stay, or even winter, that you may send me on my journey wherever I go.
B046C016V007	46	16	7	For I do not wish to see you now in passing, but I hope to stay a while with you, if the Lord permits.
B046C016V008	46	16	8	But I will stay at Ephesus until Pentecost,
B046C016V009	46	16	9	for a great and effective door has opened to me, and there are many adversaries.
B046C016V010	46	16	10	Now if Timothy comes, see that he is with you without fear, for he does the work of the Lord, as I also do.
B046C016V011	46	16	11	Therefore let no one despise him. But set him forward on his journey in peace, that he may come to me; for I expect him with the brothers.
B046C016V012	46	16	12	Now concerning Apollos, the brother, I strongly urged him to come to you with the brothers; and it was not at all his desire to come now; but he will come when he has an opportunity.
B046C016V013	46	16	13	Watch! Stand firm in the faith! Be courageous! Be strong!
B046C016V014	46	16	14	Let all that you do be done in love.
B046C016V015	46	16	15	Now I beg you, brothers (you know the house of Stephanas, that it is the first fruits of Achaia, and that they have set themselves to serve the saints),
B046C016V016	46	16	16	that you also be in subjection to such, and to everyone who helps in the work and labors.
B046C016V017	46	16	17	I rejoice at the coming of Stephanas, Fortunatus, and Achaicus; for that which was lacking on your part, they supplied.
B046C016V018	46	16	18	For they refreshed my spirit and yours. Therefore acknowledge those who are like that.
B046C016V019	46	16	19	The churches of Asia greet you. Aquila and Priscilla greet you much in the Lord, together with the church that is in their house.
B046C016V020	46	16	20	All the brothers greet you. Greet one another with a holy kiss.
B046C016V021	46	16	21	This greeting is by me, Paul, with my own hand.
B046C016V022	46	16	22	If any man does not love the Lord Jesus Christ, let him be accursed. Come, Lord!
B046C016V023	46	16	23	The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with you.
B046C016V024	46	16	24	My love to all of you in Christ Jesus.
B047C001V001	47	1	1	Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus through the will of God, and Timothy our brother, to the church of God which is at Corinth, with all the saints who are in the whole of Achaia:
B047C001V002	47	1	2	Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B047C001V003	47	1	3	Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Father of mercies and God of all comfort;
B047C001V004	47	1	4	who comforts us in all our affliction, that we may be able to comfort those who are in any affliction, through the comfort with which we ourselves are comforted by God.
B047C001V005	47	1	5	For as the sufferings of Christ abound to us, even so our comfort also abounds through Christ.
B047C001V006	47	1	6	But if we are afflicted, it is for your comfort and salvation. If we are comforted, it is for your comfort, which produces in you the patient enduring of the same sufferings which we also suffer.
B047C001V007	47	1	7	Our hope for you is steadfast, knowing that, since you are partakers of the sufferings, so also are you of the comfort.
B047C001V008	47	1	8	For we do not desire to have you uninformed, brothers, concerning our affliction which happened in Asia, that we were weighed down exceedingly, beyond our power, so much that we despaired even of life.
B047C001V009	47	1	9	Yes, we ourselves have had the sentence of death within ourselves, that we should not trust in ourselves, but in God who raises the dead,
B047C001V010	47	1	10	who delivered us out of so great a death, and does deliver; on whom we have set our hope that he will also still deliver us;
B047C001V011	47	1	11	you also helping together on our behalf by your supplication; that, for the gift bestowed on us by means of many, thanks may be given by many persons on our behalf.
B047C001V012	47	1	12	For our boasting is this: the testimony of our conscience, that in holiness and sincerity of God, not in fleshly wisdom but in the grace of God we behaved ourselves in the world, and more abundantly toward you.
B047C001V013	47	1	13	For we write no other things to you, than what you read or even acknowledge, and I hope you will acknowledge to the end;
B047C001V014	47	1	14	as also you acknowledged us in part, that we are your boasting, even as you also are ours, in the day of our Lord Jesus.
B047C001V015	47	1	15	In this confidence, I was determined to come first to you, that you might have a second benefit;
B047C001V016	47	1	16	and by you to pass into Macedonia, and again from Macedonia to come to you, and to be sent forward by you on my journey to Judea.
B047C001V017	47	1	17	When I therefore was thus determined, did I show fickleness? Or the things that I purpose, do I purpose according to the flesh, that with me there should be the "Yes, yes" and the "No, no?"
B047C001V018	47	1	18	But as God is faithful, our word toward you is not "Yes and no."
B047C001V019	47	1	19	For the Son of God, Jesus Christ, who was preached among you by us, by me, Silvanus, and Timothy, was not "Yes and no," but in him is "Yes."
B047C001V020	47	1	20	For however many are the promises of God, in him they are "Yes." Therefore also through him they are "Amen," to the glory of God through us.
B047C001V021	47	1	21	Now he who establishes us with you in Christ, and anointed us, is God;
B047C001V022	47	1	22	who also sealed us, and gave us the down payment of the Spirit in our hearts.
B047C001V023	47	1	23	But I call God for a witness to my soul, that I did not come to Corinth to spare you.
B047C001V024	47	1	24	Not that we have lordship over your faith, but are fellow workers with you for your joy. For you stand firm in faith.
B047C002V001	47	2	1	But I determined this for myself, that I would not come to you again in sorrow.
B047C002V002	47	2	2	For if I make you sorry, then who will make me glad but he who is made sorry by me?
B047C002V003	47	2	3	And I wrote this very thing, so that, when I came, I would not have sorrow from them of whom I ought to rejoice; having confidence in you all, that my joy would be shared by all of you.
B047C002V004	47	2	4	For out of much affliction and anguish of heart I wrote to you with many tears, not that you should be made sorry, but that you might know the love that I have so abundantly for you.
B047C002V005	47	2	5	But if any has caused sorrow, he has caused sorrow, not to me, but in part (that I not press too heavily) to you all.
B047C002V006	47	2	6	Sufficient to such a one is this punishment which was inflicted by the many;
B047C002V007	47	2	7	so that on the contrary you should rather forgive him and comfort him, lest by any means such a one should be swallowed up with his excessive sorrow.
B047C002V008	47	2	8	Therefore I beg you to confirm your love toward him.
B047C002V009	47	2	9	For to this end I also wrote, that I might know the proof of you, whether you are obedient in all things.
B047C002V010	47	2	10	Now I also forgive whomever you forgive anything. For if indeed I have forgiven anything, I have forgiven that one for your sakes in the presence of Christ,
B047C002V011	47	2	11	that no advantage may be gained over us by Satan; for we are not ignorant of his schemes.
B047C002V012	47	2	12	Now when I came to Troas for the Good News of Christ, and when a door was opened to me in the Lord,
B047C002V013	47	2	13	I had no relief for my spirit, because I did not find Titus, my brother, but taking my leave of them, I went out into Macedonia.
B047C002V014	47	2	14	Now thanks be to God, who always leads us in triumph in Christ, and reveals through us the sweet aroma of his knowledge in every place.
B047C002V015	47	2	15	For we are a sweet aroma of Christ to God, in those who are saved, and in those who perish;
B047C002V016	47	2	16	to the one a stench from death to death; to the other a sweet aroma from life to life. Who is sufficient for these things?
B047C002V017	47	2	17	For we are not as so many, peddling the word of God. But as of sincerity, but as of God, in the sight of God, we speak in Christ.
B047C003V001	47	3	1	Are we beginning again to commend ourselves? We do not need, as do some, letters of commendation to you or from you, do we?
B047C003V002	47	3	2	You are our letter, written in our hearts, known and read by all men;
B047C003V003	47	3	3	being revealed that you are a letter of Christ, served by us, written not with ink, but with the Spirit of the living God; not in tablets of stone, but in tablets that are hearts of flesh.
B047C003V004	47	3	4	Such confidence we have through Christ toward God;
B047C003V005	47	3	5	not that we are sufficient of ourselves, to account anything as from ourselves; but our sufficiency is from God;
B047C003V006	47	3	6	who also made us sufficient as servants of a New Covenant; not of the letter, but of the Spirit. For the letter kills, but the Spirit gives life.
B047C003V007	47	3	7	But if the service of death, written engraved on stones, came with glory, so that the children of Israel could not look steadfastly on the face of Moses for the glory of his face; which was passing away:
B047C003V008	47	3	8	won't service of the Spirit be with much more glory?
B047C003V009	47	3	9	For if the service of condemnation has glory, the service of righteousness exceeds much more in glory.
B047C003V010	47	3	10	For truly that which has been made glorious has not been made glorious in this respect, by reason of the glory that surpasses.
B047C003V011	47	3	11	For if that which passes away was with glory, much more that which remains is in glory.
B047C003V012	47	3	12	Having therefore such a hope, we use great boldness of speech,
B047C003V013	47	3	13	and not as Moses, who put a veil on his face, that the children of Israel would not look steadfastly on the end of that which was passing away.
B047C003V014	47	3	14	But their minds were hardened, for until this very day at the reading of the old covenant the same veil remains, because in Christ it passes away.
B047C003V015	47	3	15	But to this day, when Moses is read, a veil lies on their heart.
B047C003V016	47	3	16	But whenever one turns to 
B047C003V017	47	3	17	Now 
B047C003V018	47	3	18	But we all, with unveiled face beholding as in a mirror the glory of the Lord, are transformed into the same image from glory to glory, even as from 
B047C004V001	47	4	1	Therefore seeing we have this ministry, even as we obtained mercy, we do not faint.
B047C004V002	47	4	2	But we have renounced the hidden things of shame, not walking in craftiness, nor handling the word of God deceitfully; but by the manifestation of the truth commending ourselves to every man's conscience in the sight of God.
B047C004V003	47	4	3	Even if our Good News is veiled, it is veiled in those who perish;
B047C004V004	47	4	4	in whom the god of this world has blinded the minds of the unbelieving, to prevent the light shining from the Good News of the glory of Christ, who is the image of God.
B047C004V005	47	4	5	For we do not proclaim ourselves, but Christ Jesus as Lord, and ourselves as your servants for Jesus' sake;
B047C004V006	47	4	6	seeing it is God who said, "Light will shine out of darkness," who has shone in our hearts, to give the light of the knowledge of the glory of God in the face of Jesus Christ.
B047C004V007	47	4	7	But we have this treasure in clay vessels, that the exceeding greatness of the power may be of God, and not from ourselves.
B047C004V008	47	4	8	We are pressed on every side, yet not crushed; perplexed, yet not to despair;
B047C004V009	47	4	9	pursued, yet not forsaken; struck down, yet not destroyed;
B047C004V010	47	4	10	always carrying in the body the putting to death of the Lord Jesus, that the life of Jesus may also be revealed in our body.
B047C004V011	47	4	11	For we who live are always delivered to death for Jesus' sake, that the life also of Jesus may be revealed in our mortal flesh.
B047C004V012	47	4	12	So then death works in us, but life in you.
B047C004V013	47	4	13	But having the same spirit of faith, according to that which is written, "I believed, and therefore I spoke." We also believe, and therefore also we speak;
B047C004V014	47	4	14	knowing that he who raised the Lord Jesus will raise us also with Jesus, and will present us with you.
B047C004V015	47	4	15	For all things are for your sakes, that the grace, being multiplied through the many, may cause the thanksgiving to abound to the glory of God.
B047C004V016	47	4	16	Therefore we do not faint, but though our outward man is decaying, yet our inward man is renewed day by day.
B047C004V017	47	4	17	For our light affliction, which is for the moment, works for us more and more exceedingly an eternal weight of glory;
B047C004V018	47	4	18	while we do not look at the things which are seen, but at the things which are not seen. For the things which are seen are temporal, but the things which are not seen are eternal.
B047C005V001	47	5	1	For we know that if the earthly house of our tent is dissolved, we have a building from God, a house not made with hands, eternal, in the heavens.
B047C005V002	47	5	2	For truly in this we groan, longing to be clothed with our habitation which is from heaven;
B047C005V003	47	5	3	if so be that being clothed we will not be found naked.
B047C005V004	47	5	4	For indeed we who are in this tent do groan, being burdened; not that we desire to be unclothed, but that we desire to be clothed, that what is mortal may be swallowed up by life.
B047C005V005	47	5	5	Now he who made us for this very thing is God, who also gave to us the down payment of the Spirit.
B047C005V006	47	5	6	Therefore, we are always confident and know that while we are at home in the body, we are absent from the Lord;
B047C005V007	47	5	7	for we walk by faith, not by sight.
B047C005V008	47	5	8	We are of good courage, I say, and are willing rather to be absent from the body, and to be at home with the Lord.
B047C005V009	47	5	9	Therefore also we make it our aim, whether at home or absent, to be well pleasing to him.
B047C005V010	47	5	10	For we must all be revealed before the judgment seat of Christ; that each one may receive the things in the body, according to what he has done, whether good or bad.
B047C005V011	47	5	11	Knowing therefore the fear of the Lord, we persuade men, but we are revealed to God; and I hope that we are revealed also in your consciences.
B047C005V012	47	5	12	For we are not commending ourselves to you again, but speak as giving you occasion of boasting on our behalf, that you may have something to answer those who boast in appearance, and not in heart.
B047C005V013	47	5	13	For if we are beside ourselves, it is for God. Or if we are of sober mind, it is for you.
B047C005V014	47	5	14	For the love of Christ constrains us; because we judge thus, that one died for all, therefore all died.
B047C005V015	47	5	15	He died for all, that those who live should no longer live to themselves, but to him who for their sakes died and rose again.
B047C005V016	47	5	16	Therefore we know no one after the flesh from now on. Even though we have known Christ after the flesh, yet now we know him so no more.
B047C005V017	47	5	17	Therefore if anyone is in Christ, he is a new creation. The old things have passed away. Behold, new things have come.
B047C005V018	47	5	18	But all things are of God, who reconciled us to himself through Jesus Christ, and gave to us the ministry of reconciliation;
B047C005V019	47	5	19	namely, that God was in Christ reconciling the world to himself, not reckoning to them their trespasses, and having committed to us the word of reconciliation.
B047C005V020	47	5	20	We are therefore ambassadors on behalf of Christ, as though God were entreating by us: we beg you on behalf of Christ, be reconciled to God.
B047C005V021	47	5	21	For him who knew no sin he made to be sin on our behalf; so that in him we might become the righteousness of God.
B047C006V001	47	6	1	Working together, we entreat also that you not receive the grace of God in vain,
B047C006V002	47	6	2	for he says,Behold, now is the acceptable time. Behold, now is the day of salvation.
B047C006V003	47	6	3	We give no occasion of stumbling in anything, that our service may not be blamed,
B047C006V004	47	6	4	but in everything commending ourselves, as servants of God, in great endurance, in afflictions, in hardships, in distresses,
B047C006V005	47	6	5	in beatings, in imprisonments, in riots, in labors, in watchings, in fastings;
B047C006V006	47	6	6	in pureness, in knowledge, in patience, in kindness, in the Holy Spirit, in sincere love,
B047C006V007	47	6	7	in the word of truth, in the power of God; by the armor of righteousness on the right hand and on the left,
B047C006V008	47	6	8	by glory and dishonor, by evil report and good report; as deceivers, and yet true;
B047C006V009	47	6	9	as unknown, and yet well known; as dying, and behold, we live; as punished, and not killed;
B047C006V010	47	6	10	as sorrowful, yet always rejoicing; as poor, yet making many rich; as having nothing, and yet possessing all things.
B047C006V011	47	6	11	Our mouth is open to you, Corinthians. Our heart is enlarged.
B047C006V012	47	6	12	You are not restricted by us, but you are restricted by your own affections.
B047C006V013	47	6	13	Now in return, I speak as to my children, you also be open wide.
B047C006V014	47	6	14	Do not be unequally yoked with unbelievers, for what fellowship have righteousness and iniquity? Or what fellowship has light with darkness?
B047C006V015	47	6	15	What agreement has Christ with Belial? Or what portion has a believer with an unbeliever?
B047C006V016	47	6	16	What agreement has a temple of God with idols? For we are a temple of the living God. Even as God said, "I will dwell in them, and walk in them; and I will be their God, and they will be my people."
B047C006V017	47	6	17	Therefore, "'Come out from among them,and be separate,' says 
B047C006V018	47	6	18	I will be to you a Father.You will be to me sons and daughters,' 
B047C007V001	47	7	1	Having therefore these promises, beloved, let us cleanse ourselves from all defilement of flesh and spirit, perfecting holiness in the fear of God.
B047C007V002	47	7	2	Open your hearts to us. We wronged no one. We corrupted no one. We took advantage of no one.
B047C007V003	47	7	3	I say this not to condemn you, for I have said before, that you are in our hearts to die together and live together.
B047C007V004	47	7	4	Great is my boldness of speech toward you. Great is my boasting on your behalf. I am filled with comfort. I overflow with joy in all our affliction.
B047C007V005	47	7	5	For even when we had come into Macedonia, our flesh had no relief, but we were afflicted on every side. Fightings were outside. Fear was inside.
B047C007V006	47	7	6	Nevertheless, he who comforts the lowly, God, comforted us by the coming of Titus;
B047C007V007	47	7	7	and not by his coming only, but also by the comfort with which he was comforted in you, while he told us of your longing, your mourning, and your zeal for me; so that I rejoiced still more.
B047C007V008	47	7	8	For though I made you sorry with my letter, I do not regret it, though I did regret it. For I see that my letter made you sorry, though just for a while.
B047C007V009	47	7	9	I now rejoice, not that you were made sorry, but that you were made sorry to repentance. For you were made sorry in a godly way, that you might suffer loss by us in nothing.
B047C007V010	47	7	10	For godly sorrow works repentance to salvation, which brings no regret. But the sorrow of the world works death.
B047C007V011	47	7	11	For behold, this same thing, that you were made sorry in a godly way, what earnest care it worked in you. Yes, what defense, indignation, fear, longing, zeal, and vengeance! In everything you demonstrated yourselves to be pure in the matter.
B047C007V012	47	7	12	So although I wrote to you, I wrote not for his cause that did the wrong, nor for his cause that suffered the wrong, but that your earnest care for us might be revealed in you in the sight of God.
B047C007V013	47	7	13	Therefore we have been comforted. In our comfort we rejoiced the more exceedingly for the joy of Titus, because his spirit has been refreshed by you all.
B047C007V014	47	7	14	For if in anything I have boasted to him on your behalf, I was not disappointed. But as we spoke all things to you in truth, so our glorying also which I made before Titus was found to be truth.
B047C007V015	47	7	15	His affection is more abundantly toward you, while he remembers all of your obedience, how with fear and trembling you received him.
B047C007V016	47	7	16	I rejoice that in everything I am of good courage concerning you.
B047C008V001	47	8	1	Moreover, brothers, we make known to you the grace of God which has been given in the churches of Macedonia;
B047C008V002	47	8	2	how that in much proof of affliction the abundance of their joy and their deep poverty abounded to the riches of their liberality.
B047C008V003	47	8	3	For according to their power, I testify, yes and beyond their power, they gave of their own accord,
B047C008V004	47	8	4	begging us with much entreaty to receive this grace and the fellowship in the service to the saints.
B047C008V005	47	8	5	This was not as we had hoped, but first they gave their own selves to the Lord, and to us through the will of God.
B047C008V006	47	8	6	So we urged Titus, that as he made a beginning before, so he would also complete in you this grace.
B047C008V007	47	8	7	But as you abound in everything, in faith, utterance, knowledge, all earnestness, and in our love toward you, see that you also abound in this grace.
B047C008V008	47	8	8	I speak not by way of commandment, but as proving through the earnestness of others the sincerity also of your love.
B047C008V009	47	8	9	For you know the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ, that, though he was rich, yet for your sakes he became poor, that you through his poverty might become rich.
B047C008V010	47	8	10	I give a judgment in this: for this is expedient for you, who were the first to start a year ago, not only to do, but also to be willing.
B047C008V011	47	8	11	But now complete the doing also, that as there was the readiness to be willing, so there may be the completion also out of your ability.
B047C008V012	47	8	12	For if the readiness is there, it is acceptable according to what you have, not according to what you do not have.
B047C008V013	47	8	13	For this is not that others may be eased and you distressed,
B047C008V014	47	8	14	but for equality. Your abundance at this present time supplies their lack, that their abundance also may become a supply for your lack; that there may be equality.
B047C008V015	47	8	15	As it is written, "He who gathered much had nothing left over, and he who gathered little had no lack."
B047C008V016	47	8	16	But thanks be to God, who puts the same earnest care for you into the heart of Titus.
B047C008V017	47	8	17	For he indeed accepted our exhortation, but being himself very earnest, he went out to you of his own accord.
B047C008V018	47	8	18	We have sent together with him the brother whose praise in the Good News is known through all the churches.
B047C008V019	47	8	19	Not only so, but who was also appointed by the churches to travel with us in this grace, which is served by us to the glory of the Lord himself, and to show our readiness.
B047C008V020	47	8	20	We are avoiding this, that any man should blame us concerning this abundance which is administered by us.
B047C008V021	47	8	21	Having regard for honorable things, not only in the sight of the Lord, but also in the sight of men.
B047C008V022	47	8	22	We have sent with them our brother, whom we have many times proved earnest in many things, but now much more earnest, by reason of the great confidence which he has in you.
B047C008V023	47	8	23	As for Titus, he is my partner and fellow worker for you. As for our brothers, they are the apostles of the churches, the glory of Christ.
B047C008V024	47	8	24	Therefore show the proof of your love to them in front of the churches, and of our boasting on your behalf.
B047C009V001	47	9	1	It is indeed unnecessary for me to write to you concerning the service to the saints,
B047C009V002	47	9	2	for I know your readiness, of which I boast on your behalf to them of Macedonia, that Achaia has been prepared for a year past. Your zeal has stirred up very many of them.
B047C009V003	47	9	3	But I have sent the brothers that our boasting on your behalf may not be in vain in this respect, that, just as I said, you may be prepared,
B047C009V004	47	9	4	so that I won't by any means, if there come with me any of Macedonia and find you unprepared, we (to say nothing of you) should be disappointed in this confidence.
B047C009V005	47	9	5	I thought it necessary therefore to entreat the brothers that they would go before to you, and arrange ahead of time the generous gift that you promised before, that the same might be ready as a matter of generosity, and not of greediness.
B047C009V006	47	9	6	Remember this: he who sows sparingly will also reap sparingly. He who sows bountifully will also reap bountifully.
B047C009V007	47	9	7	Let each man give according as he has determined in his heart; not grudgingly, or under compulsion; for God loves a cheerful giver.
B047C009V008	47	9	8	And God is able to make all grace abound to you, that you, always having all sufficiency in everything, may abound to every good work.
B047C009V009	47	9	9	As it is written,
B047C009V010	47	9	10	Now he who supplies seed to the sower and bread for food, will supply and multiply your seed for sowing, and increase the fruits of your righteousness;
B047C009V011	47	9	11	you being enriched in everything to all liberality, which works through us thanksgiving to God.
B047C009V012	47	9	12	For this service of giving that you perform not only makes up for lack among the saints, but abounds also through many givings of thanks to God;
B047C009V013	47	9	13	seeing that through the proof given by this service, they glorify God for the obedience of your confession to the Good News of Christ, and for the liberality of your contribution to them and to all;
B047C009V014	47	9	14	while they themselves also, with supplication on your behalf, yearn for you by reason of the exceeding grace of God in you.
B047C009V015	47	9	15	Now thanks be to God for his unspeakable gift!
B047C010V001	47	10	1	Now I Paul, myself, entreat you by the humility and gentleness of Christ; I who in your presence am lowly among you, but being absent am of good courage toward you.
B047C010V002	47	10	2	Yes, I beg you that I may not, when present, show courage with the confidence with which I intend to be bold against some, who consider us to be walking according to the flesh.
B047C010V003	47	10	3	For though we walk in the flesh, we do not wage war according to the flesh;
B047C010V004	47	10	4	for the weapons of our warfare are not of the flesh, but mighty before God to the throwing down of strongholds,
B047C010V005	47	10	5	throwing down imaginations and every high thing that is exalted against the knowledge of God, and bringing every thought into captivity to the obedience of Christ;
B047C010V006	47	10	6	and being in readiness to avenge all disobedience, when your obedience will be made full.
B047C010V007	47	10	7	Do you look at things only as they appear in front of your face? If anyone trusts in himself that he is Christ's, let him consider this again with himself, that, even as he is Christ's, so also we are Christ's.
B047C010V008	47	10	8	For though I should boast somewhat abundantly concerning our authority, (which the Lord gave for building you up, and not for casting you down) I will not be disappointed,
B047C010V009	47	10	9	that I may not seem as if I desire to terrify you by my letters.
B047C010V010	47	10	10	For, "His letters," they say, "are weighty and strong, but his bodily presence is weak, and his speech is despised."
B047C010V011	47	10	11	Let such a person consider this, that what we are in word by letters when we are absent, such are we also in deed when we are present.
B047C010V012	47	10	12	For we are not bold to number or compare ourselves with some of those who commend themselves. But they themselves, measuring themselves by themselves, and comparing themselves with themselves, are without understanding.
B047C010V013	47	10	13	But we will not boast beyond proper limits, but within the boundaries with which God appointed to us, which reach even to you.
B047C010V014	47	10	14	For we do not stretch ourselves too much, as though we did not reach to you. For we came even as far as to you with the Good News of Christ,
B047C010V015	47	10	15	not boasting beyond proper limits in other men's labors, but having hope that as your faith grows, we will be abundantly enlarged by you in our sphere of influence,
B047C010V016	47	10	16	so as to proclaim the Good News even to the parts beyond you, not to boast in what someone else has already done.
B047C010V017	47	10	17	But "he who boasts, let him boast in 
B047C010V018	47	10	18	For it is not he who commends himself who is approved, but whom the Lord commends.
B047C011V001	47	11	1	I wish that you would bear with me in a little foolishness, but indeed you do bear with me.
B047C011V002	47	11	2	For I am jealous over you with a godly jealousy. For I married you to one husband, that I might present you as a pure virgin to Christ.
B047C011V003	47	11	3	But I am afraid that somehow, as the serpent deceived Eve in his craftiness, so your minds might be corrupted from a sincere and pure devotion to Christ.
B047C011V004	47	11	4	For if he who comes preaches another Jesus, whom we did not proclaim, or if you receive a different spirit, which you did not receive, or a different "good news", which you did not accept, you put up with that well enough.
B047C011V005	47	11	5	For I reckon that I am not at all behind the very best apostles.
B047C011V006	47	11	6	Even though I am unskilled in speech, I am not unskilled in knowledge. But in every way we have made this known to you in all things.
B047C011V007	47	11	7	Or did I commit a sin in humbling myself that you might be exalted, because I preached to you God's Good News free of charge?
B047C011V008	47	11	8	I robbed other churches, taking wages from them that I might serve you.
B047C011V009	47	11	9	When I was present with you and was in need, I was not a burden on anyone, for the brothers, when they came from Macedonia, supplied the measure of my need. In everything I kept myself from being burdensome to you, and I will continue to do so.
B047C011V010	47	11	10	As the truth of Christ is in me, no one will stop me from this boasting in the regions of Achaia.
B047C011V011	47	11	11	Why? Because I do not love you? God knows.
B047C011V012	47	11	12	But what I do, that I will do, that I may cut off occasion from them that desire an occasion, that in which they boast, they may be found even as we.
B047C011V013	47	11	13	For such men are false apostles, deceitful workers, masquerading as Christ's apostles.
B047C011V014	47	11	14	And no wonder, for even Satan masquerades as an angel of light.
B047C011V015	47	11	15	It is no great thing therefore if his servants also masquerade as servants of righteousness, whose end will be according to their works.
B047C011V016	47	11	16	I say again, let no one think me foolish. But if so, yet receive me as foolish, that I also may boast a little.
B047C011V017	47	11	17	That which I speak, I do not speak according to the Lord, but as in foolishness, in this confidence of boasting.
B047C011V018	47	11	18	Seeing that many boast after the flesh, I will also boast.
B047C011V019	47	11	19	For you bear with the foolish gladly, being wise.
B047C011V020	47	11	20	For you bear with a man, if he brings you into bondage, if he devours you, if he takes you captive, if he exalts himself, if he strikes you on the face.
B047C011V021	47	11	21	I speak by way of disparagement, as though we had been weak. Yet however any is bold (I speak in foolishness), I am bold also.
B047C011V022	47	11	22	Are they Hebrews? So am I. Are they Israelites? So am I. Are they the seed of Abraham? So am I.
B047C011V023	47	11	23	Are they servants of Christ? (I speak as one beside himself) I am more so; in labors more abundantly, in prisons more abundantly, in stripes above measure, in deaths often.
B047C011V024	47	11	24	Five times from the Jews I received forty stripes minus one.
B047C011V025	47	11	25	Three times I was beaten with rods. Once I was stoned. Three times I suffered shipwreck. I have been a night and a day in the deep.
B047C011V026	47	11	26	I have been in travels often, perils of rivers, perils of robbers, perils from my countrymen, perils from the Gentiles, perils in the city, perils in the wilderness, perils in the sea, perils among false brothers;
B047C011V027	47	11	27	in labor and travail, in watchings often, in hunger and thirst, in fastings often, and in cold and nakedness.
B047C011V028	47	11	28	Besides those things that are outside, there is that which presses on me daily, anxiety for all the churches.
B047C011V029	47	11	29	Who is weak, and I am not weak? Who is caused to stumble, and I do not burn with indignation?
B047C011V030	47	11	30	If I must boast, I will boast of the things that concern my weakness.
B047C011V031	47	11	31	The God and Father of the Lord Jesus Christ, he who is blessed forevermore, knows that I do not lie.
B047C011V032	47	11	32	In Damascus the governor under Aretas the king guarded the city of the Damascenes to arrest me.
B047C011V033	47	11	33	Through a window I was let down in a basket by the wall, and escaped his hands.
B047C012V001	47	12	1	It is necessary to boast, though it is not profitable. But I will come to visions and revelations of the Lord.
B047C012V002	47	12	2	I know a man in Christ, fourteen years ago (whether in the body, I do not know, or whether out of the body, I do not know; God knows), such a one caught up into the third heaven.
B047C012V003	47	12	3	I know such a man (whether in the body, or apart from the body, I do not know; God knows),
B047C012V004	47	12	4	how he was caught up into Paradise, and heard unspeakable words, which it is not lawful for a man to utter.
B047C012V005	47	12	5	On behalf of such a one I will boast, but on my own behalf I will not boast, except in my weaknesses.
B047C012V006	47	12	6	For if I would desire to boast, I will not be foolish; for I will speak the truth. But I refrain, so that no man may think more of me than that which he sees in me, or hears from me.
B047C012V007	47	12	7	By reason of the exceeding greatness of the revelations, that I should not be exalted excessively, there was given to me a thorn in the flesh, a messenger of Satan to torment me, that I should not be exalted excessively.
B047C012V008	47	12	8	Concerning this thing, I begged the Lord three times that it might depart from me.
B047C012V009	47	12	9	He has said to me, "My grace is sufficient for you, for power is made perfect in weakness." Most gladly therefore I will rather glory in my weaknesses, that the power of Christ may rest on me.
B047C012V010	47	12	10	Therefore I take pleasure in weaknesses, in injuries, in necessities, in persecutions, in distresses, for Christ's sake. For when I am weak, then am I strong.
B047C012V011	47	12	11	I have become foolish. You compelled me, for I ought to have been commended by you, for in nothing was I inferior to the very best apostles, though I am nothing.
B047C012V012	47	12	12	Truly the signs of an apostle were worked among you in all patience, in signs and wonders and mighty works.
B047C012V013	47	12	13	For what is there in which you were made inferior to the rest of the churches, unless it is that I myself was not a burden to you? Forgive me this wrong.
B047C012V014	47	12	14	Behold, this is the third time I am ready to come to you, and I will not be a burden to you; for I seek not what is yours, but you. For the children ought not to save up for the parents, but the parents for the children.
B047C012V015	47	12	15	I will most gladly spend and be spent for your souls. If I love you more abundantly, am I loved the less?
B047C012V016	47	12	16	But be it so, I did not myself burden you. But, being crafty, I caught you with deception.
B047C012V017	47	12	17	Did I take advantage of you by anyone of them whom I have sent to you?
B047C012V018	47	12	18	I exhorted Titus, and I sent the brother with him. Did Titus take any advantage of you? Did not we walk in the same spirit? Did not we walk in the same steps?
B047C012V019	47	12	19	Have you been thinking all this time that we have been defending ourselves before you? In the sight of God we speak in Christ; and all things, beloved, are for your edifying.
B047C012V020	47	12	20	For I am afraid that by any means, when I come, I might find you not the way I want to, and that I might be found by you as you do not desire; that by any means there would be strife, jealousy, outbursts of anger, factions, slander, whisperings, proud thoughts, riots;
B047C012V021	47	12	21	that again when I come my God would humble me before you, and I would mourn for many of those who have sinned before now, and not repented of the uncleanness and sexual immorality and lustfulness which they committed.
B047C013V001	47	13	1	This is the third time I am coming to you. "At the mouth of two or three witnesses shall every word be established."
B047C013V002	47	13	2	I have said beforehand, and I do say beforehand, as when I was present the second time, so now, being absent, to those who have sinned before now, and to all the rest, that, if I come again, I will not spare;
B047C013V003	47	13	3	seeing that you seek a proof of Christ who speaks in me; who toward you is not weak, but is powerful in you.
B047C013V004	47	13	4	For indeed he was crucified through weakness, yet he lives through the power of God. For we also are weak in him, but we will live with him through the power of God toward you.
B047C013V005	47	13	5	Test your own selves, whether you are in the faith. Test your own selves. Or do you not know as to your own selves, that Jesus Christ is in you?-unless indeed you are disqualified.
B047C013V006	47	13	6	But I hope that you will know that we are not disqualified.
B047C013V007	47	13	7	Now we pray to God that you do no evil; not that we may appear approved, but that you may do that which is honorable, though we are as reprobate.
B047C013V008	47	13	8	For we can do nothing against the truth, but for the truth.
B047C013V009	47	13	9	For we rejoice when we are weak and you are strong. And this we also pray for, even your perfecting.
B047C013V010	47	13	10	For this cause I write these things while absent, that I may not deal sharply when present, according to the authority which the Lord gave me for building up, and not for tearing down.
B047C013V011	47	13	11	Finally, brothers, rejoice. Be perfected, be comforted, be of the same mind, live in peace, and the God of love and peace will be with you.
B047C013V012	47	13	12	Greet one another with a holy kiss.
B047C013V013	47	13	13	All the saints greet you.
B047C013V014	47	13	14	The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ, the love of God, and the fellowship of the Holy Spirit, be with you all.
B048C001V001	48	1	1	Paul, an apostle (not from men, neither through man, but through Jesus Christ, and God the Father, who raised him from the dead),
B048C001V002	48	1	2	and all the brothers who are with me, to the churches of Galatia:
B048C001V003	48	1	3	Grace to you and peace from God the Father, and our Lord Jesus Christ,
B048C001V004	48	1	4	who gave himself for our sins, that he might deliver us out of this present evil age, according to the will of our God and Father-
B048C001V005	48	1	5	to whom be the glory forever and ever. Amen.
B048C001V006	48	1	6	I marvel that you are so quickly deserting him who called you in the grace of Christ to a different "good news";
B048C001V007	48	1	7	and there is not another "good news." Only there are some who trouble you, and want to pervert the Good News of Christ.
B048C001V008	48	1	8	But even though we, or an angel from heaven, should proclaim to you any "good news" other than that which we preached to you, let him be cursed.
B048C001V009	48	1	9	As we have said before, so I now say again: if any man preaches to you any "good news" other than that which you received, let him be cursed.
B048C001V010	48	1	10	For am I now seeking the favor of men, or of God? Or am I striving to please men? For if I were still pleasing men, I would not be a servant of Christ.
B048C001V011	48	1	11	But I make known to you, brothers, concerning the Good News which was preached by me, that it is not according to man.
B048C001V012	48	1	12	For neither did I receive it from man, nor was I taught it, but it came to me through revelation of Jesus Christ.
B048C001V013	48	1	13	For you have heard of my way of living in time past in Judaism, how that beyond measure I persecuted the church of God, and ravaged it.
B048C001V014	48	1	14	I advanced in Judaism beyond many of my own age among my countrymen, being more exceedingly zealous for the traditions of my fathers.
B048C001V015	48	1	15	But when it was the good pleasure of God, who separated me from my mother's womb, and called me through his grace,
B048C001V016	48	1	16	to reveal his Son in me, that I might proclaim him among the Gentiles, I did not immediately confer with flesh and blood,
B048C001V017	48	1	17	nor did I go up to Jerusalem to those who were apostles before me, but I went away into Arabia. Then I returned to Damascus.
B048C001V018	48	1	18	Then after three years I went up to Jerusalem to visit Cephas, and stayed with him fifteen days.
B048C001V019	48	1	19	But of the other apostles I saw no one, except Jacob, the Lord's brother.
B048C001V020	48	1	20	Now about the things which I write to you, behold, before God, I'm not lying.
B048C001V021	48	1	21	Then I came to the regions of Syria and Cilicia.
B048C001V022	48	1	22	I was still unknown by face to the churches of Judea which were in Christ,
B048C001V023	48	1	23	but they only heard: "He who once persecuted us now preaches the faith that he once tried to destroy."
B048C001V024	48	1	24	And they glorified God because of me.
B048C002V001	48	2	1	Then after a period of fourteen years I went up again to Jerusalem with Barnabas, taking Titus also with me.
B048C002V002	48	2	2	I went up by revelation, and I explained to them the Good News which I proclaim among the Gentiles, but privately before those who were respected, for fear that I might be running, or had run, in vain.
B048C002V003	48	2	3	But not even Titus, who was with me, being a Greek, was compelled to be circumcised.
B048C002V004	48	2	4	This was because of the false brothers secretly brought in, who stole in to spy out our liberty which we have in Christ Jesus, that they might bring us into bondage;
B048C002V005	48	2	5	to whom we gave no place in the way of subjection, not for an hour, that the truth of the Good News might continue with you.
B048C002V006	48	2	6	But from those who were reputed to be important (whatever they were, it makes no difference to me; God does not show partiality to man)-they, I say, who were respected imparted nothing to me,
B048C002V007	48	2	7	but to the contrary, when they saw that I had been entrusted with the Good News for the uncircumcision, even as Peter with the Good News for the circumcision
B048C002V008	48	2	8	(for he who appointed Peter to be an apostle of the circumcision appointed me also to the Gentiles);
B048C002V009	48	2	9	and when they perceived the grace that was given to me, Jacob and Cephas and John, they who were reputed to be pillars, gave to me and Barnabas the right hand of fellowship, that we should go to the Gentiles, and they to the circumcised.
B048C002V010	48	2	10	They only asked us to remember the poor-which very thing I was also zealous to do.
B048C002V011	48	2	11	But when Cephas came to Antioch, I resisted him to his face, because he stood condemned.
B048C002V012	48	2	12	For before some people came from Jacob, he ate with the Gentiles. But when they came, he drew back and separated himself, fearing those who were of the circumcision.
B048C002V013	48	2	13	And the rest of the Jewish believers joined him in his hypocrisy; so that even Barnabas was carried away with their hypocrisy.
B048C002V014	48	2	14	But when I saw that they did not walk uprightly according to the truth of the Good News, I said to Cephas before them all, "If you, being a Jew, live as the Gentiles do, and not as the Jews do, how can you compel the Gentiles to live as the Jews do?
B048C002V015	48	2	15	"We, being Jews by birth, and not Gentile sinners,
B048C002V016	48	2	16	yet knowing that a man is not justified by the works of the law but through faith in Jesus Christ, even we believed in Christ Jesus, that we might be justified by faith in Christ, and not by the works of the law, because no flesh will be justified by the works of the law.
B048C002V017	48	2	17	But if, while we sought to be justified in Christ, we ourselves also were found sinners, is Christ a servant of sin? Certainly not!
B048C002V018	48	2	18	For if I build up again those things which I destroyed, I prove myself a law-breaker.
B048C002V019	48	2	19	For I, through the law, died to the law, that I might live to God.
B048C002V020	48	2	20	I have been crucified with Christ, and it is no longer I that live, but Christ living in me. That life which I now live in the flesh, I live by faith in the Son of God, who loved me, and gave himself up for me.
B048C002V021	48	2	21	I do not make void the grace of God. For if righteousness is through the law, then Christ died for nothing!"
B048C003V001	48	3	1	Foolish Galatians, who has cunningly deceived you, before whose eyes Jesus Christ was openly set forth as crucified?
B048C003V002	48	3	2	I just want to learn this from you. Did you receive the Spirit by the works of the law, or by hearing of faith?
B048C003V003	48	3	3	Are you so foolish? Having begun in the Spirit, are you now completed in the flesh?
B048C003V004	48	3	4	Did you suffer so many things in vain, if it is indeed in vain?
B048C003V005	48	3	5	He therefore who supplies the Spirit to you, and works miracles among you, does he do it by the works of the law, or by hearing of faith?
B048C003V006	48	3	6	Even as Abraham "believed God, and it was counted to him for righteousness."
B048C003V007	48	3	7	Know therefore that those who are of faith, the same are children of Abraham.
B048C003V008	48	3	8	The Scripture, foreseeing that God would justify the Gentiles by faith, preached the Good News beforehand to Abraham, saying, "In you all the nations will be blessed."
B048C003V009	48	3	9	So then, those who are of faith are blessed with the faithful Abraham.
B048C003V010	48	3	10	For as many as are of the works of the law are under a curse. For it is written, "Cursed is everyone who does not continue in all things that are written in the scroll of the Law, to do them."
B048C003V011	48	3	11	Now that no man is justified by the law before God is evident, for, "The righteous will live by faith."
B048C003V012	48	3	12	The law is not of faith, but, "The man who does them will live by them."
B048C003V013	48	3	13	Christ redeemed us from the curse of the law, having become a curse for us. For it is written, "Cursed is everyone who hangs on a tree,"
B048C003V014	48	3	14	that the blessing of Abraham might come on the Gentiles through Christ Jesus; that we might receive the promise of the Spirit through faith.
B048C003V015	48	3	15	Brothers, speaking of human terms, though it is only a man's covenant, yet when it has been confirmed, no one makes it void, or adds to it.
B048C003V016	48	3	16	Now the promises were spoken to Abraham and to his seed. He does not say, "To seeds," as of many, but as of one, "To your seed," which is Christ.
B048C003V017	48	3	17	Now I say this. A covenant confirmed beforehand by God, the law, which came four hundred thirty years after, does not annul, so as to make the promise of no effect.
B048C003V018	48	3	18	For if the inheritance is of the law, it is no more of promise; but God has granted it to Abraham by promise.
B048C003V019	48	3	19	What then is the law? It was added because of transgressions, until the seed should come to whom the promise has been made. It was ordained through angels by the hand of a mediator.
B048C003V020	48	3	20	Now a mediator is not between one, but God is one.
B048C003V021	48	3	21	Is the law then against the promises of God? Certainly not! For if there had been a law given which could make alive, most certainly righteousness would have been of the law.
B048C003V022	48	3	22	But the Scriptures imprisoned all things under sin, that the promise by faith in Jesus Christ might be given to those who believe.
B048C003V023	48	3	23	But before faith came, we were kept in custody under the law, confined for the faith which should afterwards be revealed.
B048C003V024	48	3	24	So that the law has become our tutor to bring us to Christ, that we might be justified by faith.
B048C003V025	48	3	25	But now that faith has come, we are no longer under a tutor.
B048C003V026	48	3	26	For you are all children of God, through faith in Christ Jesus.
B048C003V027	48	3	27	For as many of you as were baptized into Christ have put on Christ.
B048C003V028	48	3	28	There is neither Jew nor Greek, there is neither slave nor free man, there is neither male nor female; for you are all one in Christ Jesus.
B048C003V029	48	3	29	If you are Christ's, then you are Abraham's seed and heirs according to promise.
B048C004V001	48	4	1	But I say that so long as the heir is a child, he is no different from a bondservant, though he is lord of all;
B048C004V002	48	4	2	but is under guardians and stewards until the day appointed by the father.
B048C004V003	48	4	3	So we also, when we were children, were held in bondage under the elemental principles of the world.
B048C004V004	48	4	4	But when the fullness of the time came, God sent out his Son, born to a woman, born under the law,
B048C004V005	48	4	5	that he might redeem those who were under the law, that we might receive the adoption of children.
B048C004V006	48	4	6	And because you are children, God sent out the Spirit of his Son into our hearts, crying, "Abba, Father!"
B048C004V007	48	4	7	So you are no longer a bondservant, but a son; and if a son, then an heir of God.
B048C004V008	48	4	8	However at that time, not knowing God, you were in bondage to those who by nature are not gods.
B048C004V009	48	4	9	But now that you have come to know God, or rather to be known by God, why do you turn back again to the weak and miserable elemental principles, to which you desire to be in bondage all over again?
B048C004V010	48	4	10	You observe days, months, seasons, and years.
B048C004V011	48	4	11	I am afraid for you, that I might have wasted my labor for you.
B048C004V012	48	4	12	I beg you, brothers, become as I am, for I also have become as you are. You did me no wrong,
B048C004V013	48	4	13	but you know that because of weakness of the flesh I preached the Good News to you the first time;
B048C004V014	48	4	14	and though my condition was a trial to you, you did not despise nor reject; but you received me as an angel of God, even as Christ Jesus.
B048C004V015	48	4	15	Where was the blessing you enjoyed? For I testify to you that, if possible, you would have plucked out your eyes and given them to me.
B048C004V016	48	4	16	So then, have I become your enemy by telling you the truth?
B048C004V017	48	4	17	They zealously seek you, but for no good purpose; they desire to alienate you, that you may be zealous for them.
B048C004V018	48	4	18	But it is always good to be zealous in a good cause, and not only when I am present with you.
B048C004V019	48	4	19	My children, of whom I am again in travail until Christ is formed in you-
B048C004V020	48	4	20	but I could wish to be present with you now, and to change my tone, for I am perplexed about you.
B048C004V021	48	4	21	Tell me, you that desire to be under the law, do you not listen to the law?
B048C004V022	48	4	22	For it is written that Abraham had two sons, one by the handmaid, and one by the free woman.
B048C004V023	48	4	23	However, the son by the handmaid was born according to the flesh, but the son by the free woman was born through promise.
B048C004V024	48	4	24	These things contain an allegory, for these are two covenants. One is from Mount Sinai, bearing children to bondage, which is Hagar.
B048C004V025	48	4	25	For this Hagar is Mount Sinai in Arabia, and answers to the Jerusalem that exists now, for she is in bondage with her children.
B048C004V026	48	4	26	But the Jerusalem that is above is free, and she is our mother.
B048C004V027	48	4	27	For it is written,
B048C004V028	48	4	28	Now you, brothers, as Isaac was, are children of promise.
B048C004V029	48	4	29	But as then, he who was born according to the flesh persecuted him who was born according to the Spirit, so also it is now.
B048C004V030	48	4	30	However what does the Scripture say? "Throw out the handmaid and her son, for the son of the handmaid will not inherit with the son of the free woman."
B048C004V031	48	4	31	So then, brothers, we are not children of a handmaid, but of the free woman.
B048C005V001	48	5	1	Stand firm therefore in the liberty by which Christ has made us free, and do not be entangled again with a yoke of bondage.
B048C005V002	48	5	2	Behold, I, Paul, tell you that if you receive circumcision, Christ will profit you nothing.
B048C005V003	48	5	3	Yes, I testify again to every man who receives circumcision, that he is a debtor to do the whole law.
B048C005V004	48	5	4	You are alienated from Christ, you who desire to be justified by the law. You have fallen away from grace.
B048C005V005	48	5	5	For we, through the Spirit, by faith wait for the hope of righteousness.
B048C005V006	48	5	6	For in Christ Jesus neither circumcision amounts to anything, nor uncircumcision, but faith working through love.
B048C005V007	48	5	7	You were running well! Who interfered with you that you should not obey the truth?
B048C005V008	48	5	8	This persuasion is not from him who calls you.
B048C005V009	48	5	9	A little yeast grows through the whole lump.
B048C005V010	48	5	10	I have confidence toward you in the Lord that you will think no other way. But he who troubles you will bear his judgment, whoever he is.
B048C005V011	48	5	11	But I, brothers, if I still proclaim circumcision, why am I still persecuted? Then the stumbling block of the cross has been removed.
B048C005V012	48	5	12	I wish that those who disturb you would cut themselves off.
B048C005V013	48	5	13	For you, brothers, were called for freedom. Only do not use your freedom for gain to the flesh, but through love be servants to one another.
B048C005V014	48	5	14	For the whole law is fulfilled in one word, in this: "You shall love your neighbor as yourself."
B048C005V015	48	5	15	But if you bite and devour one another, be careful that you do not consume one another.
B048C005V016	48	5	16	But I say, walk by the Spirit, and you will not carry out the desires of the flesh.
B048C005V017	48	5	17	For the flesh lusts against the Spirit, and the Spirit against the flesh; and these are contrary to one another, that you may not do the things that you desire.
B048C005V018	48	5	18	But if you are led by the Spirit, you are not under the law.
B048C005V019	48	5	19	Now the works of the flesh are obvious, which are: sexual immorality, uncleanness, lustfulness,
B048C005V020	48	5	20	idolatry, sorcery, hatred, strife, jealousies, outbursts of anger, rivalries, divisions, heresies,
B048C005V021	48	5	21	envyings, drunkenness, orgies, and things like these; of which I forewarn you, even as I also forewarned you, that those who practice such things will not inherit the Kingdom of God.
B048C005V022	48	5	22	But the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, faith,
B048C005V023	48	5	23	gentleness, and self-control. Against such things there is no law.
B048C005V024	48	5	24	Those who belong to Christ have crucified the flesh with its passions and lusts.
B048C005V025	48	5	25	If we live by the Spirit, let us also walk by the Spirit.
B048C005V026	48	5	26	Let us not become conceited, provoking one another, and envying one another.
B048C006V001	48	6	1	Brothers, even if a man is caught in some fault, you who are spiritual must restore such a one in a spirit of gentleness; looking to yourself so that you also are not tempted.
B048C006V002	48	6	2	Bear one another's burdens, and so fulfill the Law of Christ.
B048C006V003	48	6	3	For if a man thinks himself to be something when he is nothing, he deceives himself.
B048C006V004	48	6	4	But let each man test his own work, and then he will take pride in himself and not in his neighbor.
B048C006V005	48	6	5	For each man will bear his own burden.
B048C006V006	48	6	6	But let him who is taught in the word share all good things with him who teaches.
B048C006V007	48	6	7	Do not be deceived. God is not mocked, for whatever a man sows, that he will also reap.
B048C006V008	48	6	8	For he who sows to his own flesh will from the flesh reap corruption. But he who sows to the Spirit will from the Spirit reap eternal life.
B048C006V009	48	6	9	Let us not be weary in doing good, for we will reap in due season, if we do not give up.
B048C006V010	48	6	10	So then, as we have opportunity, let us do what is good toward all men, and especially toward those who are of the household of the faith.
B048C006V011	48	6	11	See with what large letters I write to you with my own hand.
B048C006V012	48	6	12	As many as desire to look good in the flesh, they compel you to be circumcised; only that they may not be persecuted for the cross of Christ.
B048C006V013	48	6	13	For even they who receive circumcision do not keep the law themselves, but they desire to have you circumcised, that they may boast in your flesh.
B048C006V014	48	6	14	But far be it from me to boast, except in the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ, through which the world has been crucified to me, and I to the world.
B048C006V015	48	6	15	For neither is circumcision anything, nor uncircumcision, but a new creation.
B048C006V016	48	6	16	As many as walk by this rule, peace and mercy be on them, and on God's Israel.
B048C006V017	48	6	17	From now on, let no one cause me any trouble, for I bear the marks of the Lord Jesus branded on my body.
B048C006V018	48	6	18	The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit, brothers. Amen.
B049C001V001	49	1	1	Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus through the will of God,to the saints who are at Ephesus, and the faithful in Christ Jesus:
B049C001V002	49	1	2	Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B049C001V003	49	1	3	Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who has blessed us with every spiritual blessing in the heavenly places in Christ;
B049C001V004	49	1	4	even as he chose us in him before the foundation of the world, that we would be holy and without blemish before him in love;
B049C001V005	49	1	5	having predestined us for adoption as children through Jesus Christ to himself, according to the good pleasure of his desire,
B049C001V006	49	1	6	to the praise of the glory of his grace, which he freely bestowed on us in the Beloved One,
B049C001V007	49	1	7	in whom we have our redemption through his blood, the forgiveness of our trespasses, according to the riches of his grace,
B049C001V008	49	1	8	which he made to abound toward us in all wisdom and prudence,
B049C001V009	49	1	9	making known to us the mystery of his will, according to his good pleasure which he purposed in him
B049C001V010	49	1	10	to an administration of the fullness of the times, to sum up all things in Christ, the things in the heavens, and the things on the earth, in him;
B049C001V011	49	1	11	in whom also we were assigned an inheritance, having been foreordained according to the purpose of him who works all things after the counsel of his will;
B049C001V012	49	1	12	to the end that we should be to the praise of his glory, we who had before hoped in Christ:
B049C001V013	49	1	13	in whom you also, having heard the word of the truth, the Good News of your salvation,-in whom, having also believed, you were sealed with the Holy Spirit of promise,
B049C001V014	49	1	14	who is a pledge of our inheritance, to the redemption of God's own possession, to the praise of his glory.
B049C001V015	49	1	15	For this cause I also, having heard of the faith in the Lord Jesus which is among you, and the love which you have toward all the saints,
B049C001V016	49	1	16	do not cease to give thanks for you, making mention of you in my prayers,
B049C001V017	49	1	17	that the God of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Father of glory, may give to you a spirit of wisdom and revelation in the knowledge of him;
B049C001V018	49	1	18	having the eyes of your hearts enlightened, that you may know what is the hope of his calling, and what are the riches of the glory of his inheritance in the saints,
B049C001V019	49	1	19	and what is the exceeding greatness of his power toward us who believe, according to that working of the strength of his might
B049C001V020	49	1	20	which he worked in Christ, when he raised him from the dead, and made him to sit at his right hand in the heavenly places,
B049C001V021	49	1	21	far above all rule, and authority, and power, and dominion, and every name that is named, not only in this age, but also in that which is to come.
B049C001V022	49	1	22	He put all things in subjection under his feet, and gave him to be head over all things for the church,
B049C001V023	49	1	23	which is his body, the fullness of him who fills all in all.
B049C002V001	49	2	1	You were made alive when you were dead in your transgressions and sins,
B049C002V002	49	2	2	in which you once walked according to the course of this world, according to the prince of the power of the air, the spirit who now works in the children of disobedience;
B049C002V003	49	2	3	among whom we also all once lived in the lust of our flesh, doing the desires of the flesh and of the mind, and were by nature children of wrath, even as the rest.
B049C002V004	49	2	4	But God, being rich in mercy, for his great love with which he loved us,
B049C002V005	49	2	5	even when we were dead through our trespasses, made us alive together with Christ (by grace you have been saved),
B049C002V006	49	2	6	and raised us up with him, and made us to sit with him in the heavenly places in Christ Jesus,
B049C002V007	49	2	7	that in the ages to come he might show the exceeding riches of his grace in kindness toward us in Christ Jesus;
B049C002V008	49	2	8	for by grace you have been saved through faith, and that not of yourselves; it is the gift of God,
B049C002V009	49	2	9	not of works, that no one would boast.
B049C002V010	49	2	10	For we are his workmanship, created in Christ Jesus for good works, which God prepared before that we would walk in them.
B049C002V011	49	2	11	Therefore remember that once you, the Gentiles in the flesh, who are called "uncircumcision" by that which is called "circumcision," (in the flesh, made by hands);
B049C002V012	49	2	12	that you were at that time separate from Christ, alienated from the commonwealth of Israel, and strangers from the covenants of the promise, having no hope and without God in the world.
B049C002V013	49	2	13	But now in Christ Jesus you who once were far off are made near in the blood of Christ.
B049C002V014	49	2	14	For he is our peace, who made both one, and broke down the middle wall of partition,
B049C002V015	49	2	15	having abolished in the flesh the hostility, the law of commandments contained in ordinances, that he might create in himself one new man of the two, making peace;
B049C002V016	49	2	16	and might reconcile them both in one body to God through the cross, having killed the hostility thereby.
B049C002V017	49	2	17	He came and preached peace to you who were far off and peace to those who were near.
B049C002V018	49	2	18	For through him we both have our access in one Spirit to the Father.
B049C002V019	49	2	19	So then you are no longer strangers and foreigners, but you are fellow citizens with the saints, and of the household of God,
B049C002V020	49	2	20	being built on the foundation of the apostles and prophets, Christ Jesus himself being the chief cornerstone;
B049C002V021	49	2	21	in whom the whole building, fitted together, grows into a holy temple in the Lord;
B049C002V022	49	2	22	in whom you also are built together for a habitation of God in the Spirit.
B049C003V001	49	3	1	For this cause I, Paul, am the prisoner of Christ Jesus on behalf of you Gentiles,
B049C003V002	49	3	2	if it is so that you have heard of the administration of that grace of God which was given me toward you;
B049C003V003	49	3	3	how that by revelation the mystery was made known to me, as I wrote before in few words,
B049C003V004	49	3	4	by which, when you read, you can perceive my understanding in the mystery of Christ;
B049C003V005	49	3	5	which in other generations was not made known to the children of men, as it has now been revealed to his holy apostles and prophets in the Spirit;
B049C003V006	49	3	6	that the Gentiles are fellow heirs, and fellow members of the body, and fellow partakers of the promise in Christ Jesus through the Good News,
B049C003V007	49	3	7	of which I was made a servant, according to the gift of that grace of God which was given me according to the working of his power.
B049C003V008	49	3	8	To me, the very least of all saints, was this grace given, to proclaim to the Gentiles the unsearchable riches of Christ,
B049C003V009	49	3	9	and to make all men see what is the administration of the mystery which for ages has been hidden in God, who created all things;
B049C003V010	49	3	10	to the intent that now through the church the manifold wisdom of God might be made known to the principalities and the powers in the heavenly places,
B049C003V011	49	3	11	according to the eternal purpose which he purposed in Christ Jesus our Lord;
B049C003V012	49	3	12	in whom we have boldness and access in confidence through our faith in him.
B049C003V013	49	3	13	Therefore I ask that you may not lose heart at my troubles for you, which are your glory.
B049C003V014	49	3	14	For this cause, I bow my knees before the Father,
B049C003V015	49	3	15	from whom every family in heaven and on earth is named,
B049C003V016	49	3	16	that he would grant you, according to the riches of his glory, that you may be strengthened with power through his Spirit in the inward man;
B049C003V017	49	3	17	that Christ may dwell in your hearts through faith; to the end that you, being rooted and grounded in love,
B049C003V018	49	3	18	may be strengthened to comprehend with all the saints what is the breadth and length and height and depth,
B049C003V019	49	3	19	and to know Christ's love which surpasses knowledge, that you may be filled with all the fullness of God.
B049C003V020	49	3	20	Now to him who is able to do exceedingly abundantly above all that we ask or think, according to the power that works in us,
B049C003V021	49	3	21	to him be the glory in the church and in Christ Jesus to all generations forever and ever. Amen.
B049C004V001	49	4	1	I therefore, the prisoner in the Lord, beg you to walk worthily of the calling with which you were called,
B049C004V002	49	4	2	with all lowliness and humility, with patience, bearing with one another in love;
B049C004V003	49	4	3	being eager to keep the unity of the Spirit in the bond of peace.
B049C004V004	49	4	4	There is one body, and one Spirit, even as you also were called in one hope of your calling;
B049C004V005	49	4	5	one Lord, one faith, one baptism,
B049C004V006	49	4	6	one God and Father of all, who is over all, and through all, and in all.
B049C004V007	49	4	7	But to each one of us was the grace given according to the measure of the gift of Christ.
B049C004V008	49	4	8	Therefore he says, "When he ascended on high, he led captivity captive, and gave gifts to men."
B049C004V009	49	4	9	Now this, "He ascended," what is it but that he also descended into the lower parts of the earth?
B049C004V010	49	4	10	He who descended is the one who also ascended far above all the heavens, that he might fill all things.
B049C004V011	49	4	11	He gave some to be apostles; and some, prophets; and some, evangelists; and some, shepherds and teachers;
B049C004V012	49	4	12	for the perfecting of the saints, to the work of serving, to the building up of the body of Christ;
B049C004V013	49	4	13	until we all attain to the unity of the faith, and of the knowledge of the Son of God, to a full grown man, to the measure of the stature of the fullness of Christ;
B049C004V014	49	4	14	that we may no longer be children, tossed back and forth and carried about with every wind of doctrine, by the trickery of men, in craftiness, after the wiles of error;
B049C004V015	49	4	15	but speaking truth in love, we may grow up in all things into him, who is the head, Christ;
B049C004V016	49	4	16	from whom all the body, being fitted and knit together through that which every joint supplies, according to the proper working of each individual part, makes the body increase to the building up of itself in love.
B049C004V017	49	4	17	This I say therefore, and testify in the Lord, that you no longer walk as the rest of the Gentiles also walk, in the futility of their mind,
B049C004V018	49	4	18	being darkened in their understanding, alienated from the life of God, because of the ignorance that is in them, because of the hardening of their hearts;
B049C004V019	49	4	19	who having become callous gave themselves up to lust, to work all uncleanness with greediness.
B049C004V020	49	4	20	But you did not learn Christ that way;
B049C004V021	49	4	21	if indeed you heard him, and were taught in him, even as truth is in Jesus:
B049C004V022	49	4	22	that you put away, as concerning your former way of life, the old man, that grows corrupt after the lusts of deceit;
B049C004V023	49	4	23	and that you be renewed in the spirit of your mind,
B049C004V024	49	4	24	and put on the new man, who in the likeness of God has been created in righteousness and holiness of truth.
B049C004V025	49	4	25	Therefore, putting away falsehood, speak truth each one with his neighbor. For we are members of one another.
B049C004V026	49	4	26	"Be angry, and do not sin." Do not let the sun go down on your wrath,
B049C004V027	49	4	27	neither give place to the devil.
B049C004V028	49	4	28	Let him who stole steal no more; but rather let him labor, working with his hands the thing that is good, that he may have something to give to him who has need.
B049C004V029	49	4	29	Let no corrupt speech proceed out of your mouth, but such as is good for building up as the need may be, that it may give grace to those who hear.
B049C004V030	49	4	30	Do not grieve the Holy Spirit of God, in whom you were sealed for the day of redemption.
B049C004V031	49	4	31	Let all bitterness, wrath, anger, outcry, and slander, be put away from you, with all malice.
B049C004V032	49	4	32	And be kind to one another, tenderhearted, forgiving each other, just as God also in Christ forgave you.
B049C005V001	49	5	1	Be therefore imitators of God, as beloved children.
B049C005V002	49	5	2	Walk in love, even as Christ also loved you, and gave himself up for us, an offering and a sacrifice to God for a sweet-smelling fragrance.
B049C005V003	49	5	3	But sexual immorality, and all uncleanness, or covetousness, let it not even be mentioned among you, as becomes saints;
B049C005V004	49	5	4	nor filthiness, nor foolish talking, nor jesting, which are not appropriate; but rather giving of thanks.
B049C005V005	49	5	5	Know this for sure, that no sexually immoral person, nor unclean person, nor covetous man, who is an idolater, has any inheritance in the Kingdom of Christ and God.
B049C005V006	49	5	6	Let no one deceive you with empty words. For because of these things, the wrath of God comes on the children of disobedience.
B049C005V007	49	5	7	Therefore do not be partakers with them.
B049C005V008	49	5	8	For you were once darkness, but are now light in the Lord. Walk as children of light,
B049C005V009	49	5	9	for the fruit of the light is in all goodness and righteousness and truth,
B049C005V010	49	5	10	proving what is well pleasing to the Lord.
B049C005V011	49	5	11	Have no fellowship with the unfruitful works of darkness, but rather even reprove them.
B049C005V012	49	5	12	For the things which are done by them in secret, it is a shame even to speak of.
B049C005V013	49	5	13	But all things, when they are reproved, are revealed by the light, for everything that reveals is light.
B049C005V014	49	5	14	Therefore he says, "Awake, you who sleep, and arise from the dead, and Christ will shine on you."
B049C005V015	49	5	15	Therefore watch carefully how you walk, not as unwise, but as wise;
B049C005V016	49	5	16	redeeming the time, because the days are evil.
B049C005V017	49	5	17	Therefore do not be foolish, but understand what the will of the Lord is.
B049C005V018	49	5	18	Do not be drunken with wine, in which is dissipation, but be filled with the Spirit,
B049C005V019	49	5	19	speaking to one another in psalms, hymns, and spiritual songs; singing, and singing praises in your heart to the Lord;
B049C005V020	49	5	20	giving thanks always concerning all things in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ to God the Father;
B049C005V021	49	5	21	subjecting yourselves one to another in the fear of Christ.
B049C005V022	49	5	22	Wives, be subject to your own husbands, as to the Lord.
B049C005V023	49	5	23	For the husband is the head of the wife, and Christ also is the head of the church, being himself the savior of the body.
B049C005V024	49	5	24	But as the church is subject to Christ, so let the wives also be to their own husbands in everything.
B049C005V025	49	5	25	Husbands, love your wives, even as Christ also loved the church, and gave himself up for it;
B049C005V026	49	5	26	that he might sanctify it, having cleansed it by the washing of water with the word,
B049C005V027	49	5	27	that he might present the church to himself gloriously, not having spot or wrinkle or any such thing; but that it should be holy and without blemish.
B049C005V028	49	5	28	Even so husbands also ought to love their own wives as their own bodies. He who loves his own wife loves himself.
B049C005V029	49	5	29	For no man ever hated his own flesh; but nourishes and cherishes it, even as Christ also does the church;
B049C005V030	49	5	30	because we are members of his body.
B049C005V031	49	5	31	"For this cause a man will leave his father and mother, and will be joined to his wife. The two will become one flesh."
B049C005V032	49	5	32	This mystery is great, but I speak concerning Christ and of the church.
B049C005V033	49	5	33	Nevertheless each of you must also love his own wife even as himself; and let the wife see that she respects her husband.
B049C006V001	49	6	1	Children, obey your parents in the Lord, for this is right.
B049C006V002	49	6	2	"Honor your father and mother," which is the first commandment with a promise:
B049C006V003	49	6	3	"that it may be well with you, and you may live long on the earth."
B049C006V004	49	6	4	You fathers, do not provoke your children to wrath, but nurture them in the discipline and instruction of the Lord.
B049C006V005	49	6	5	Servants, be obedient to those who according to the flesh are your masters, with fear and trembling, in singleness of your heart, as to Christ;
B049C006V006	49	6	6	not in the way of service only when eyes are on you, as men pleasers; but as servants of Christ, doing the will of God from the heart;
B049C006V007	49	6	7	with good will doing service, as to the Lord, and not to men;
B049C006V008	49	6	8	knowing that whatever good thing each one does, he will receive the same again from the Lord, whether he is bound or free.
B049C006V009	49	6	9	You masters, do the same things to them, and give up threatening, knowing that he who is both their Master and yours is in heaven, and there is no partiality with him.
B049C006V010	49	6	10	Finally, be strong in the Lord, and in the strength of his might.
B049C006V011	49	6	11	Put on the whole armor of God, that you may be able to stand against the wiles of the devil.
B049C006V012	49	6	12	For our wrestling is not against flesh and blood, but against the principalities, against the powers, against the world's rulers of this darkness, and against the spiritual forces of wickedness in the heavenly places.
B049C006V013	49	6	13	Therefore, put on the whole armor of God, that you may be able to withstand in the evil day, and, having done all, to stand.
B049C006V014	49	6	14	Stand therefore, having the utility belt of truth buckled around your waist, and having put on the breastplate of righteousness,
B049C006V015	49	6	15	and having fitted your feet with the preparation of the Good News of peace;
B049C006V016	49	6	16	above all, taking up the shield of faith, with which you will be able to quench all the fiery darts of the evil one.
B049C006V017	49	6	17	And take the helmet of salvation, and the sword of the Spirit, which is the spoken word of God;
B049C006V018	49	6	18	with all prayer and requests, praying at all times in the Spirit, and being watchful to this end in all perseverance and requests for all the saints:
B049C006V019	49	6	19	on my behalf, that utterance may be given to me in opening my mouth, to make known with boldness the mystery of the Good News,
B049C006V020	49	6	20	for which I am an ambassador in chains; that in it I may speak boldly, as I ought to speak.
B049C006V021	49	6	21	But that you also may know my affairs, how I am doing, Tychicus, the beloved brother and faithful servant in the Lord, will make known to you all things;
B049C006V022	49	6	22	whom I have sent to you for this very purpose, that you may know our state, and that he may comfort your hearts.
B049C006V023	49	6	23	Peace be to the brothers, and love with faith, from God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B049C006V024	49	6	24	Grace be with all those who love our Lord Jesus Christ with incorruptible love.
B050C001V001	50	1	1	Paul and Timothy, servants of Jesus Christ;To all the saints in Christ Jesus who are at Philippi, with the overseers and servants:
B050C001V002	50	1	2	Grace to you, and peace from God, our Father, and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B050C001V003	50	1	3	I thank my God whenever I remember you,
B050C001V004	50	1	4	always in every request of mine on behalf of you all making my requests with joy,
B050C001V005	50	1	5	for your partnership in furtherance of the Good News from the first day until now;
B050C001V006	50	1	6	being confident of this very thing, that he who began a good work in you will complete it until the day of Jesus Christ.
B050C001V007	50	1	7	It is even right for me to think this way on behalf of all of you, because I have you in my heart, because, both in my bonds and in the defense and confirmation of the Good News, you all are partakers with me of grace.
B050C001V008	50	1	8	For God is my witness, how I long after all of you in the tender mercies of Christ Jesus.
B050C001V009	50	1	9	This I pray, that your love may abound yet more and more in knowledge and all discernment;
B050C001V010	50	1	10	so that you may approve the things that are excellent; that you may be sincere and without offense to the day of Christ;
B050C001V011	50	1	11	being filled with the fruit of righteousness, which are through Jesus Christ, to the glory and praise of God.
B050C001V012	50	1	12	Now I desire to have you know, brothers, that the things which happened to me have turned out rather to the progress of the Good News;
B050C001V013	50	1	13	so that it became evident to the whole praetorian guard, and to all the rest, that my bonds are in Christ;
B050C001V014	50	1	14	and that most of the brothers in the Lord, being confident through my bonds, are more abundantly bold to speak the word of God without fear.
B050C001V015	50	1	15	Some indeed proclaim Christ even out of envy and strife, and some also out of good will.
B050C001V016	50	1	16	The former insincerely proclaim Christ from selfish ambition, thinking that they add affliction to my chains;
B050C001V017	50	1	17	but the latter out of love, knowing that I am appointed for the defense of the Good News.
B050C001V018	50	1	18	What does it matter? Only that in every way, whether out of false motives or in truth, Christ is proclaimed. I rejoice in this, yes, and will rejoice.
B050C001V019	50	1	19	For I know that this will turn out to my salvation, through your supplication and the supply of the Spirit of Jesus Christ,
B050C001V020	50	1	20	according to my earnest expectation and hope, that I will in no way be disappointed, but with all boldness, as always, now also Christ will be magnified in my body, whether by life, or by death.
B050C001V021	50	1	21	For to me to live is Christ, and to die is gain.
B050C001V022	50	1	22	But if I live on in the flesh, this will bring fruit from my work; yet I do not make known what I will choose.
B050C001V023	50	1	23	But I am in a dilemma between the two, having the desire to depart and be with Christ, which is far better.
B050C001V024	50	1	24	Yet, to remain in the flesh is more needful for your sake.
B050C001V025	50	1	25	Having this confidence, I know that I will remain, yes, and remain with you all, for your progress and joy in the faith,
B050C001V026	50	1	26	that your rejoicing may abound in Christ Jesus in me through my presence with you again.
B050C001V027	50	1	27	Only let your manner of life be worthy of the Good News of Christ, that, whether I come and see you or am absent, I may hear of your state, that you stand firm in one spirit, with one soul striving for the faith of the Good News;
B050C001V028	50	1	28	and in nothing frightened by the adversaries, which is for them a proof of destruction, but to you of salvation, and that from God.
B050C001V029	50	1	29	Because it has been granted to you on behalf of Christ, not only to believe in him, but also to suffer on his behalf,
B050C001V030	50	1	30	having the same conflict which you saw in me, and now hear is in me.
B050C002V001	50	2	1	If there is therefore any exhortation in Christ, if any consolation of love, if any fellowship of the Spirit, if any tender mercies and compassion,
B050C002V002	50	2	2	make my joy full, by being like-minded, having the same love, being of one accord, of one mind;
B050C002V003	50	2	3	doing nothing through rivalry or through conceit, but in humility, each counting others better than himself;
B050C002V004	50	2	4	each of you not just looking to his own things, but each of you also to the things of others.
B050C002V005	50	2	5	Have this in your mind, which was also in Christ Jesus,
B050C002V006	50	2	6	who, existing in the form of God, did not consider equality with God a thing to be grasped,
B050C002V007	50	2	7	but emptied himself, taking the form of a servant, being made in the likeness of men.
B050C002V008	50	2	8	And being found in human form, he humbled himself, becoming obedient to death, yes, the death of the cross.
B050C002V009	50	2	9	Therefore God also highly exalted him, and gave to him the name which is above every name;
B050C002V010	50	2	10	that at the name of Jesus every knee should bow, of those in heaven, those on earth, and those under the earth,
B050C002V011	50	2	11	and that every tongue should confess that Jesus Christ is 
B050C002V012	50	2	12	So then, my beloved, even as you have always obeyed, not only in my presence, but now much more in my absence, work out your own salvation with fear and trembling.
B050C002V013	50	2	13	For it is God who works in you both to will and to work, for his good pleasure.
B050C002V014	50	2	14	Do all things without murmurings and disputes,
B050C002V015	50	2	15	that you may become blameless and harmless, children of God without blemish in the midst of a crooked and perverse generation, among whom you are seen as lights in the world,
B050C002V016	50	2	16	holding up the word of life; that I may have something to boast in the day of Christ, that I did not run in vain nor labor in vain.
B050C002V017	50	2	17	Yes, and if I am poured out on the sacrifice and service of your faith, I rejoice, and rejoice with you all.
B050C002V018	50	2	18	In the same way, you also rejoice, and rejoice with me.
B050C002V019	50	2	19	But I hope in the Lord Jesus to send Timothy to you soon, that I also may be cheered up when I know how you are doing.
B050C002V020	50	2	20	For I have no one else like-minded, who will truly care about you.
B050C002V021	50	2	21	For they all seek their own, not the things of Jesus Christ.
B050C002V022	50	2	22	But you know the proof of him, that, as a child serves a father, so he served with me in furtherance of the Good News.
B050C002V023	50	2	23	Therefore I hope to send him at once, as soon as I see how it will go with me.
B050C002V024	50	2	24	But I trust in the Lord that I myself also will come shortly.
B050C002V025	50	2	25	But I counted it necessary to send to you Epaphroditus, my brother, fellow worker, fellow soldier, and your apostle and servant of my need;
B050C002V026	50	2	26	since he longed for you all, and was very troubled, because you had heard that he was sick.
B050C002V027	50	2	27	For indeed he was sick, nearly to death, but God had mercy on him; and not on him only, but on me also, that I might not have sorrow on sorrow.
B050C002V028	50	2	28	I have sent him therefore the more diligently, that, when you see him again, you may rejoice, and that I may be the less sorrowful.
B050C002V029	50	2	29	Receive him therefore in the Lord with all joy, and hold such in honor,
B050C002V030	50	2	30	because for the work of Christ he came near to death, risking his life to supply that which was lacking in your service toward me.
B050C003V001	50	3	1	Finally, my brothers, rejoice in the Lord. To write the same things to you, to me indeed is not tiresome, but for you it is safe.
B050C003V002	50	3	2	Beware of the dogs, beware of the evil workers, beware of the false circumcision.
B050C003V003	50	3	3	For we are the circumcision, who worship God in the Spirit, and rejoice in Christ Jesus, and have no confidence in the flesh;
B050C003V004	50	3	4	though I myself might have confidence even in the flesh. If any other man thinks that he has confidence in the flesh, I yet more:
B050C003V005	50	3	5	circumcised the eighth day, of the stock of Israel, of the tribe of Benjamin, a Hebrew of Hebrews; concerning the law, a Pharisee;
B050C003V006	50	3	6	concerning zeal, persecuting the church; concerning the righteousness which is in the law, found blameless.
B050C003V007	50	3	7	However, what things were gain to me, these have I counted loss for Christ.
B050C003V008	50	3	8	More than that, I count all things to be loss for the excellency of the knowledge of Christ Jesus, my Lord, for whom I suffered the loss of all things, and count them nothing but refuse, that I may gain Christ
B050C003V009	50	3	9	and be found in him, not having a righteousness of my own, that which is of the law, but that which is through faith in Christ, the righteousness which is from God by faith;
B050C003V010	50	3	10	that I may know him, and the power of his resurrection, and the fellowship of his sufferings, becoming conformed to his death;
B050C003V011	50	3	11	if by any means I may attain to the resurrection from the dead.
B050C003V012	50	3	12	Not that I have already obtained, or am already made perfect; but I press on, if it is so that I may take hold of that for which also I was taken hold of by Christ Jesus.
B050C003V013	50	3	13	Brothers, I do not regard myself as yet having taken hold, but one thing I do. Forgetting the things which are behind, and reaching forward to the things which are ahead,
B050C003V014	50	3	14	I press on toward the goal for the prize of the high calling of God in Christ Jesus.
B050C003V015	50	3	15	Let us therefore, as many as are perfect, think this way. If in anything you think otherwise, God will also reveal that to you.
B050C003V016	50	3	16	Nevertheless, to what we have attained, to the same continue on.
B050C003V017	50	3	17	Brothers, be imitators together of me, and note those who walk this way, even as you have us for an example.
B050C003V018	50	3	18	For many walk, of whom I told you often, and now tell you even weeping, as the enemies of the cross of Christ,
B050C003V019	50	3	19	whose end is destruction, whose god is the belly, and whose glory is in their shame, who think about earthly things.
B050C003V020	50	3	20	For our citizenship is in heaven, from where we also wait for a Savior, the Lord Jesus Christ;
B050C003V021	50	3	21	who will change our lowly bodies into the likeness of his glorious body, according to the working by which he is able even to subject all things to himself.
B050C004V001	50	4	1	Therefore, my brothers, beloved and longed for, my joy and crown, so stand firm in the Lord, my beloved.
B050C004V002	50	4	2	I exhort Euodia, and I exhort Syntyche, to think the same way in the Lord.
B050C004V003	50	4	3	Yes, I beg you also, true yokefellow, help these women, for they labored with me in the Good News, with Clement also, and the rest of my fellow workers, whose names are in the book of life.
B050C004V004	50	4	4	Rejoice in the Lord always! Again I will say, Rejoice!
B050C004V005	50	4	5	Let your gentleness be known to all men. The Lord is near.
B050C004V006	50	4	6	In nothing be anxious, but in everything, by prayer and petition with thanksgiving, let your requests be made known to God.
B050C004V007	50	4	7	And the peace of God, which surpasses all understanding, will guard your hearts and your thoughts in Christ Jesus.
B050C004V008	50	4	8	Finally, brothers, whatever things are true, whatever things are honorable, whatever things are just, whatever things are pure, whatever things are lovely, whatever things are of good report; if there is any virtue, and if there is any praise, think about these things.
B050C004V009	50	4	9	The things which you learned, received, heard, and saw in me: do these things, and the God of peace will be with you.
B050C004V010	50	4	10	But I rejoice in the Lord greatly, that now at length you have revived your thought for me; in which you did indeed take thought, but you lacked opportunity.
B050C004V011	50	4	11	Not that I speak in respect to lack, for I have learned in whatever state I am, to be content in it.
B050C004V012	50	4	12	I know how to be humbled, and I know also how to abound. In everything and in all things I have learned the secret both to be filled and to be hungry, both to abound and to be in need.
B050C004V013	50	4	13	I can do all things through him who strengthens me.
B050C004V014	50	4	14	However you did well that you shared in my affliction.
B050C004V015	50	4	15	You yourselves also know, you Philippians, that in the beginning of the Good News, when I departed from Macedonia, no church shared with me in the matter of giving and receiving but you only.
B050C004V016	50	4	16	For even in Thessalonica you sent once and again to my need.
B050C004V017	50	4	17	Not that I seek for the gift, but I seek for the fruit that increases to your account.
B050C004V018	50	4	18	But I have all things, and abound. I am filled, having received from Epaphroditus the things that came from you, a sweet-smelling fragrance, an acceptable and well-pleasing sacrifice to God.
B050C004V019	50	4	19	My God will supply every need of yours according to his riches in glory in Christ Jesus.
B050C004V020	50	4	20	Now to our God and Father be the glory forever and ever! Amen.
B050C004V021	50	4	21	Greet every holy one in Christ Jesus. The brothers who are with me greet you.
B050C004V022	50	4	22	All the saints greet you, especially those who are of Caesar's household.
B050C004V023	50	4	23	The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit.
B051C001V001	51	1	1	Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus through the will of God, and Timothy our brother,
B051C001V002	51	1	2	to the saints and faithful brothers in Christ at Colossae: Grace to you and peace from God our Father.
B051C001V003	51	1	3	We give thanks to God the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, praying always for you,
B051C001V004	51	1	4	having heard of your faith in Christ Jesus, and of the love which you have toward all the saints,
B051C001V005	51	1	5	because of the hope which is laid up for you in the heavens, of which you heard before in the word of the truth of the Good News,
B051C001V006	51	1	6	which has come to you; even as it is in all the world and is bearing fruit and growing, as it does in you also, since the day you heard and knew the grace of God in truth;
B051C001V007	51	1	7	even as you learned of Epaphras our beloved fellow servant, who is a faithful servant of Christ on our behalf,
B051C001V008	51	1	8	who also declared to us your love in the Spirit.
B051C001V009	51	1	9	For this cause, we also, since the day we heard this, do not cease praying and making requests for you, that you may be filled with the knowledge of his will in all spiritual wisdom and understanding,
B051C001V010	51	1	10	that you may walk worthily of the Lord, to please him in all respects, bearing fruit in every good work, and increasing in the knowledge of God;
B051C001V011	51	1	11	strengthened with all power, according to the might of his glory, for all endurance and perseverance with joy;
B051C001V012	51	1	12	giving thanks to the Father, who made you fit to be partakers of the inheritance of the saints in light;
B051C001V013	51	1	13	who delivered us out of the power of darkness, and translated us into the Kingdom of the Son of his love;
B051C001V014	51	1	14	in whom we have our redemption, the forgiveness of our sins;
B051C001V015	51	1	15	who is the image of the invisible God, existing before all creation.
B051C001V016	51	1	16	For by him all things were created, in the heavens and on the earth, things visible and things invisible, whether thrones or dominions or principalities or powers; all things have been created through him, and for him.
B051C001V017	51	1	17	He is before all things, and in him all things are held together.
B051C001V018	51	1	18	He is the head of the body, the church, who is the beginning, the firstborn from the dead; that in all things he might have the preeminence.
B051C001V019	51	1	19	For all the fullness was pleased to dwell in him;
B051C001V020	51	1	20	and through him to reconcile all things to himself, by him, whether things on the earth, or things in the heavens, having made peace through the blood of his cross.
B051C001V021	51	1	21	You, being in past times alienated and enemies in your mind in your evil works,
B051C001V022	51	1	22	yet now he has reconciled in the body of his flesh through death, to present you holy and without blemish and blameless before him,
B051C001V023	51	1	23	if it is so that you continue in the faith, grounded and steadfast, and not moved away from the hope of the Good News which you heard, which is being proclaimed in all creation under heaven; of which I, Paul, was made a servant.
B051C001V024	51	1	24	Now I rejoice in my sufferings for your sake, and fill up on my part that which is lacking of the afflictions of Christ in my flesh for his body's sake, which is the church;
B051C001V025	51	1	25	of which I was made a servant, according to the stewardship of God which was given me toward you, to fulfill the word of God,
B051C001V026	51	1	26	the mystery which has been hidden for ages and generations. But now it has been revealed to his saints,
B051C001V027	51	1	27	to them God was pleased to make known what are the riches of the glory of this mystery among the Gentiles, which is Christ in you, the hope of glory;
B051C001V028	51	1	28	whom we proclaim, admonishing every man and teaching every man in all wisdom, that we may present every man perfect in Christ Jesus;
B051C001V029	51	1	29	for which I also labor, striving according to his working, which works in me mightily.
B051C002V001	51	2	1	For I desire to have you know how greatly I struggle for you, and for those at Laodicea, and for as many as have not seen my face in the flesh;
B051C002V002	51	2	2	that their hearts may be comforted, they being knit together in love, and gaining all riches of the full assurance of understanding, that they may know the mystery of God, which is Christ,
B051C002V003	51	2	3	in whom are all the treasures of wisdom and knowledge hidden.
B051C002V004	51	2	4	Now this I say that no one may delude you with persuasiveness of speech.
B051C002V005	51	2	5	For though I am absent in the flesh, yet am I with you in the spirit, rejoicing and seeing your order, and the steadfastness of your faith in Christ.
B051C002V006	51	2	6	As therefore you received Christ Jesus, the Lord, walk in him,
B051C002V007	51	2	7	rooted and built up in him, and established in the faith, even as you were taught, abounding in it in thanksgiving.
B051C002V008	51	2	8	Be careful that you do not let anyone rob you through his philosophy and vain deceit, after the tradition of men, after the elements of the world, and not after Christ.
B051C002V009	51	2	9	For in him all the fullness of God's nature dwells bodily,
B051C002V010	51	2	10	and in him you are made full, who is the head of all principality and power;
B051C002V011	51	2	11	in whom you were also circumcised with a circumcision not made with hands, in the putting off of the body of the flesh, in the circumcision of Christ;
B051C002V012	51	2	12	having been buried with him in baptism, in which you were also raised with him through faith in the working of God, who raised him from the dead.
B051C002V013	51	2	13	You were dead through your trespasses and the uncircumcision of your flesh. He made you alive together with him, having forgiven us all our trespasses,
B051C002V014	51	2	14	wiping out the handwriting in ordinances which was against us; and he has taken it out of the way, nailing it to the cross;
B051C002V015	51	2	15	having stripped the principalities and the powers, he made a show of them openly, triumphing over them in it.
B051C002V016	51	2	16	Let no man therefore judge you in eating, or in drinking, or with respect to a feast day or a new moon or a Sabbath day,
B051C002V017	51	2	17	which are a shadow of the things to come; but the body is Christ's.
B051C002V018	51	2	18	Let no one rob you of your prize by a voluntary humility and worshipping of the angels, dwelling in the things which he has seen, vainly puffed up by his fleshly mind,
B051C002V019	51	2	19	and not holding firmly to the Head, from whom all the body, being supplied and knit together through the joints and ligaments, grows with God's growth.
B051C002V020	51	2	20	If you died with Christ from the elements of the world, why, as though living in the world, do you subject yourselves to ordinances,
B051C002V021	51	2	21	"Do not handle, nor taste, nor touch"
B051C002V022	51	2	22	(all of which perish with use), according to the precepts and doctrines of men?
B051C002V023	51	2	23	Which things indeed appear like wisdom in self-imposed worship, and humility, and severity to the body; but are not of any value against the indulgence of the flesh.
B051C003V001	51	3	1	If then you were raised together with Christ, seek the things that are above, where Christ is, seated on the right hand of God.
B051C003V002	51	3	2	Set your mind on the things that are above, not on the things that are on the earth.
B051C003V003	51	3	3	For you died, and your life is hidden with Christ in God.
B051C003V004	51	3	4	When Christ, your life, is revealed, then you will also be revealed with him in glory.
B051C003V005	51	3	5	Put to death, therefore, whatever is worldly in you: sexual immorality, impurity, lust, evil desire, and covetousness, which is idolatry;
B051C003V006	51	3	6	for which things' sake the wrath of God comes on the children of disobedience.
B051C003V007	51	3	7	You also once walked in those, when you lived in them;
B051C003V008	51	3	8	but now you also put them all away: anger, wrath, malice, slander, and shameful speaking out of your mouth.
B051C003V009	51	3	9	Do not lie to one another, seeing that you have put off the old man with his doings,
B051C003V010	51	3	10	and have put on the new man, who is being renewed in knowledge after the image of his Creator,
B051C003V011	51	3	11	where there cannot be Greek and Jew, circumcision and uncircumcision, barbarian, Scythian, bondservant, freeman; but Christ is all, and in all.
B051C003V012	51	3	12	Put on therefore, as God's chosen ones, holy and beloved, a heart of compassion, kindness, lowliness, humility, and perseverance;
B051C003V013	51	3	13	bearing with one another, and forgiving each other, if anyone has a complaint against another; even as the Lord forgave you, so you also do.
B051C003V014	51	3	14	Above all these things, walk in love, which is the bond of perfection.
B051C003V015	51	3	15	And let the peace of Christ rule in your hearts, to which also you were called in one body; and be thankful.
B051C003V016	51	3	16	Let the word of Christ dwell in you richly; in all wisdom teaching and admonishing one another with psalms, hymns, and spiritual songs, singing with grace in your heart to God.
B051C003V017	51	3	17	Whatever you do, in word or in deed, do all in the name of the Lord Jesus, giving thanks to God the Father, through him.
B051C003V018	51	3	18	Wives, be in subjection to your husbands, as is fitting in the Lord.
B051C003V019	51	3	19	Husbands, love your wives, and do not be bitter against them.
B051C003V020	51	3	20	Children, obey your parents in all things, for this pleases the Lord.
B051C003V021	51	3	21	Fathers, do not provoke your children, so that they won't be discouraged.
B051C003V022	51	3	22	Servants, obey in all things those who are your masters according to the flesh, not just when they are looking, as men pleasers, but in singleness of heart, fearing the Lord.
B051C003V023	51	3	23	And whatever you do, work heartily, as for the Lord, and not for men,
B051C003V024	51	3	24	knowing that from the Lord you will receive the reward of the inheritance; for you serve the Lord Christ.
B051C003V025	51	3	25	But he who does wrong will receive again for the wrong that he has done, and there is no partiality.
B051C004V001	51	4	1	Masters, give to your servants that which is just and equal, knowing that you also have a Master in heaven.
B051C004V002	51	4	2	Continue steadfastly in prayer, watching therein with thanksgiving;
B051C004V003	51	4	3	praying together for us also, that God may open to us a door for the word, to speak the mystery of Christ, for which I am also in bonds;
B051C004V004	51	4	4	that I may reveal it as I ought to speak.
B051C004V005	51	4	5	Walk in wisdom toward those who are outside, redeeming the time.
B051C004V006	51	4	6	Let your speech always be with grace, seasoned with salt, that you may know how you ought to answer each one.
B051C004V007	51	4	7	All my affairs will be made known to you by Tychicus, the beloved brother, faithful servant, and fellow bondservant in the Lord.
B051C004V008	51	4	8	I am sending him to you for this very purpose, that you may know our circumstances and that he may encourage your hearts,
B051C004V009	51	4	9	together with Onesimus, the faithful and beloved brother, who is one of you. They will make known to you everything that is going on here.
B051C004V010	51	4	10	Aristarchus, my fellow prisoner greets you, and Mark, the cousin of Barnabas (concerning whom you received commandments, "if he comes to you, receive him"),
B051C004V011	51	4	11	and Jesus who is called Justus, who are of the circumcision. These are my only fellow workers for the Kingdom of God, men who have been a comfort to me.
B051C004V012	51	4	12	Epaphras, who is one of you, a servant of Christ, salutes you, always striving for you in his prayers, that you may stand perfect and fully assured in all the will of God.
B051C004V013	51	4	13	For I testify about him, that he has worked hard for you, and for those in Laodicea, and for those in Hierapolis.
B051C004V014	51	4	14	Luke, the beloved physician, and Demas greet you.
B051C004V015	51	4	15	Greet the brothers who are in Laodicea, and to Nympha and the church that is in her house.
B051C004V016	51	4	16	When this letter has been read among you, cause it to be read also in the church of the Laodiceans; and that you also read the letter from Laodicea.
B051C004V017	51	4	17	Tell Archippus, "Take heed to the ministry which you have received in the Lord, that you fulfill it."
B051C004V018	51	4	18	The salutation of me, Paul, with my own hand: remember my bonds. Grace be with you.
B052C001V001	52	1	1	Paul, Silvanus, and Timothy, to the church of the Thessalonians in God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ: Grace to you and peace.
B052C001V002	52	1	2	We always give thanks to God for all of you, mentioning you in our prayers,
B052C001V003	52	1	3	remembering without ceasing your work of faith and labor of love and patience of hope in our Lord Jesus Christ, before our God and Father.
B052C001V004	52	1	4	We know, brothers loved by God, that you are chosen,
B052C001V005	52	1	5	and that our Good News came to you not in word only, but also in power, and in the Holy Spirit, and with much assurance. You know what kind of men we showed ourselves to be among you for your sake.
B052C001V006	52	1	6	You became imitators of us, and of the Lord, having received the word in much affliction, with joy of the Holy Spirit,
B052C001V007	52	1	7	so that you became an example to all who believe in Macedonia and in Achaia.
B052C001V008	52	1	8	For from you the word of the Lord has been declared, not only in Macedonia and Achaia, but also in every place your faith toward God has gone out; so that we need not to say anything.
B052C001V009	52	1	9	For they themselves report concerning us what kind of a reception we had from you; and how you turned to God from idols, to serve a living and true God,
B052C001V010	52	1	10	and to wait for his Son from heaven, whom he raised from the dead-Jesus, who delivers us from the wrath to come.
B052C002V001	52	2	1	For you yourselves know, brothers, our visit to you was not in vain,
B052C002V002	52	2	2	but having suffered before and been shamefully treated, as you know, at Philippi, we grew bold in our God to tell you the Good News of God in much conflict.
B052C002V003	52	2	3	For our exhortation is not of error, nor of uncleanness, nor in deception.
B052C002V004	52	2	4	But even as we have been approved by God to be entrusted with the Good News, so we speak; not as pleasing men, but God, who tests our hearts.
B052C002V005	52	2	5	For neither were we at any time found using words of flattery, as you know, nor a cloak of covetousness (God is witness),
B052C002V006	52	2	6	nor seeking glory from men (neither from you nor from others), when we might have claimed authority as apostles of Christ.
B052C002V007	52	2	7	But we were like children among you, like a nursing mother cherishes her own children.
B052C002V008	52	2	8	Even so, affectionately longing for you, we were well pleased to impart to you, not the Good News of God only, but also our own souls, because you had become very dear to us.
B052C002V009	52	2	9	For you remember, brothers, our labor and travail; for working night and day, that we might not burden any of you, we preached to you the Good News of God.
B052C002V010	52	2	10	You are witnesses with God, how holy, righteously, and blamelessly we behaved ourselves toward you who believe.
B052C002V011	52	2	11	As you know, as a father with his own children,
B052C002V012	52	2	12	we exhorted, comforted, and implored every one of you to lead a life worthy of God, who calls you into his own Kingdom and glory.
B052C002V013	52	2	13	For this cause we also thank God without ceasing, that, when you received from us the word of the message of God, you accepted it not as the word of men, but, as it is in truth, the word of God, which also works in you who believe.
B052C002V014	52	2	14	For you, brothers, became imitators of the churches of God which are in Judea in Christ Jesus; for you also suffered the same things from your own countrymen, even as they did from the Judeans;
B052C002V015	52	2	15	who killed both the Lord Jesus and the prophets, and drove us out, and did not please God, and are contrary to all men;
B052C002V016	52	2	16	forbidding us to speak to the Gentiles that they may be saved; to fill up their sins always. But wrath has come on them to the uttermost.
B052C002V017	52	2	17	But we, brothers, being bereaved of you for a short season, in presence, not in heart, tried even harder to see your face with great desire,
B052C002V018	52	2	18	because we wanted to come to you-indeed, I, Paul, once and again-but Satan hindered us.
B052C002V019	52	2	19	For what is our hope, or joy, or crown of rejoicing? Is not it even you, before our Lord Jesus at his coming?
B052C002V020	52	2	20	For you are our glory and our joy.
B052C003V001	52	3	1	Therefore, when we could not stand it any longer, we thought it good to be left behind at Athens alone,
B052C003V002	52	3	2	and sent Timothy, our brother and God's fellow worker in the Good News of Christ, to establish you, and to comfort you concerning your faith;
B052C003V003	52	3	3	that no one be moved by these afflictions. For you know that we are appointed to this task.
B052C003V004	52	3	4	For truly, when we were with you, we told you beforehand that we are to suffer affliction, even as it happened, and you know.
B052C003V005	52	3	5	For this cause I also, when I could not stand it any longer, sent that I might know your faith, for fear that by any means the tempter had tempted you, and our labor would have been in vain.
B052C003V006	52	3	6	But when Timothy came just now to us from you, and brought us glad news of your faith and love, and that you have good memories of us always, longing to see us, even as we also long to see you;
B052C003V007	52	3	7	for this cause, brothers, we were comforted over you in all our distress and affliction through your faith.
B052C003V008	52	3	8	For now we live, since you stand firm in the Lord.
B052C003V009	52	3	9	For what thanksgiving can we render again to God for you, for all the joy with which we rejoice for your sakes before our God;
B052C003V010	52	3	10	night and day praying exceedingly that we may see your face, and may perfect that which is lacking in your faith?
B052C003V011	52	3	11	Now may our God and Father himself, and our Lord Jesus Christ, direct our way to you;
B052C003V012	52	3	12	and the Lord make you to increase and abound in love one toward another, and toward all men, even as we also do toward you,
B052C003V013	52	3	13	to the end he may establish your hearts blameless in holiness before our God and Father, at the coming of our Lord Jesus with all his saints.
B052C004V001	52	4	1	Finally then, brothers, we beg and exhort you in the Lord Jesus, that as you received from us how you ought to live and to please God, even as you are living, that you excel more and more.
B052C004V002	52	4	2	For you know what instructions we gave you through the Lord Jesus.
B052C004V003	52	4	3	For this is the will of God: your sanctification, that you abstain from sexual immorality,
B052C004V004	52	4	4	that each one of you know how to possess himself of his own vessel in sanctification and honor,
B052C004V005	52	4	5	not in the passion of lust, even as the Gentiles who do not know God;
B052C004V006	52	4	6	that no one should take advantage of and wrong a brother or sister in this matter; because the Lord is an avenger in all these things, as also we forewarned you and testified.
B052C004V007	52	4	7	For God called us not for uncleanness, but in sanctification.
B052C004V008	52	4	8	Therefore he who rejects this does not reject man, but God, who has also given his Holy Spirit to you.
B052C004V009	52	4	9	But concerning brotherly love, you have no need that one write to you. For you yourselves are taught by God to love one another,
B052C004V010	52	4	10	for indeed you do it toward all the brothers who are in all Macedonia. But we exhort you, brothers, that you abound more and more;
B052C004V011	52	4	11	and that you make it your ambition to lead a quiet life, and to do your own business, and to work with your own hands, even as we instructed you;
B052C004V012	52	4	12	that you may walk properly toward those who are outside, and may have need of nothing.
B052C004V013	52	4	13	But we do not want you to be ignorant, brothers, concerning those who have fallen asleep, so that you do not grieve like the rest, who have no hope.
B052C004V014	52	4	14	For if we believe that Jesus died and rose again, even so God will bring with him those who have fallen asleep in Jesus.
B052C004V015	52	4	15	For this we tell you by the word of the Lord, that we who are alive, who are left to the coming of the Lord, will in no way precede those who have fallen asleep.
B052C004V016	52	4	16	For the Lord himself will descend from heaven with a shout, with the voice of the archangel, and with God's trumpet. The dead in Christ will rise first,
B052C004V017	52	4	17	then we who are alive, who are left, will be caught up together with them in the clouds, to meet the Lord in the air. So we will be with the Lord forever.
B052C004V018	52	4	18	Therefore comfort one another with these words.
B052C005V001	52	5	1	But concerning the times and the seasons, brothers, you have no need that anything be written to you.
B052C005V002	52	5	2	For you yourselves know well that the day of the Lord comes like a thief in the night.
B052C005V003	52	5	3	For when they are saying, "Peace and safety," then sudden destruction will come on them, like birth pains on a pregnant woman; and they will in no way escape.
B052C005V004	52	5	4	But you, brothers, are not in darkness, that the day should overtake you like a thief.
B052C005V005	52	5	5	You are all children of light, and children of the day. We do not belong to the night, nor to darkness,
B052C005V006	52	5	6	so then let us not sleep, as the rest do, but let us watch and be sober.
B052C005V007	52	5	7	For those who sleep, sleep in the night, and those who are drunk are drunk in the night.
B052C005V008	52	5	8	But let us, since we belong to the day, be sober, putting on the breastplate of faith and love, and, for a helmet, the hope of salvation.
B052C005V009	52	5	9	For God did not appoint us to wrath, but to the obtaining of salvation through our Lord Jesus Christ,
B052C005V010	52	5	10	who died for us, that, whether we wake or sleep, we should live together with him.
B052C005V011	52	5	11	Therefore exhort one another, and build each other up, even as you also do.
B052C005V012	52	5	12	But we beg you, brothers, to know those who labor among you, and are over you in the Lord, and admonish you,
B052C005V013	52	5	13	and to respect and honor them in love for their work's sake.Be at peace among yourselves.
B052C005V014	52	5	14	We exhort you, brothers, admonish the disorderly, encourage the fainthearted, support the weak, be patient toward all.
B052C005V015	52	5	15	See that no one returns evil for evil to anyone, but always follow after that which is good, for one another, and for all.
B052C005V016	52	5	16	Rejoice always.
B052C005V017	52	5	17	Pray without ceasing.
B052C005V018	52	5	18	In everything give thanks, for this is the will of God in Christ Jesus toward you.
B052C005V019	52	5	19	Do not quench the Spirit.
B052C005V020	52	5	20	Do not despise prophesies.
B052C005V021	52	5	21	Test all things, and hold firmly that which is good.
B052C005V022	52	5	22	Abstain from every form of evil.
B052C005V023	52	5	23	May the God of peace himself sanctify you completely. May your whole spirit, soul, and body be preserved blameless at the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B052C005V024	52	5	24	He who calls you is faithful, who will also do it.
B052C005V025	52	5	25	Brothers, pray for us.
B052C005V026	52	5	26	Greet all the brothers with a holy kiss.
B052C005V027	52	5	27	I solemnly command you by the Lord that this letter be read to all the brothers.
B052C005V028	52	5	28	The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you.
B053C001V001	53	1	1	Paul, Silvanus, and Timothy, to the church of the Thessalonians in God our Father, and the Lord Jesus Christ:
B053C001V002	53	1	2	Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B053C001V003	53	1	3	We are bound to always give thanks to God for you, brothers, even as it is appropriate, because your faith grows exceedingly, and the love of each and every one of you towards one another abounds;
B053C001V004	53	1	4	so that we ourselves boast about you in the churches of God for your patience and faith in all your persecutions and in the afflictions which you endure.
B053C001V005	53	1	5	This is an obvious sign of the righteous judgment of God, to the end that you may be counted worthy of the Kingdom of God, for which you also suffer.
B053C001V006	53	1	6	Since it is a righteous thing with God to repay affliction to those who afflict you,
B053C001V007	53	1	7	and to give relief to you who are afflicted with us, when the Lord Jesus is revealed from heaven with his mighty angels in flaming fire,
B053C001V008	53	1	8	giving vengeance to those who do not know God, and to those who do not obey the Good News of our Lord Jesus,
B053C001V009	53	1	9	who will pay the penalty: eternal destruction from the face of the Lord and from the glory of his might,
B053C001V010	53	1	10	when he comes to be glorified in his saints, and to be admired among all those who have believed (because our testimony to you was believed) in that day.
B053C001V011	53	1	11	To this end we also pray always for you, that our God may count you worthy of your calling, and fulfill every desire of goodness and work of faith, with power;
B053C001V012	53	1	12	that the name of our Lord Jesus may be glorified in you, and you in him, according to the grace of our God and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B053C002V001	53	2	1	Now, brothers, concerning the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ, and our gathering together to him, we ask you
B053C002V002	53	2	2	not to be quickly shaken in your mind, nor yet be troubled, either by spirit, or by word, or by letter as from us, saying that the day of the Lord had come.
B053C002V003	53	2	3	Let no one deceive you in any way. For it will not be, unless the departure comes first, and the man of lawlessness is revealed, the son of destruction,
B053C002V004	53	2	4	he who opposes and exalts himself against all that is called God or that is worshiped; so that he sits in the temple of God, setting himself up as God.
B053C002V005	53	2	5	Do you not remember that, when I was still with you, I told you these things?
B053C002V006	53	2	6	Now you know what is restraining him, to the end that he may be revealed in his own season.
B053C002V007	53	2	7	For the mystery of lawlessness already works. Only there is one who restrains now, until he is taken out of the way.
B053C002V008	53	2	8	Then the lawless one will be revealed, whom the Lord will kill with the breath of his mouth, and destroy by the manifestation of his coming;
B053C002V009	53	2	9	even he whose coming is according to the working of Satan with all power and signs and lying wonders,
B053C002V010	53	2	10	and with all deception of wickedness for those who are being lost, because they did not receive the love of the truth, that they might be saved.
B053C002V011	53	2	11	Because of this, God sends them a working of error, that they should believe a lie;
B053C002V012	53	2	12	that they all might be judged who did not believe the truth, but had pleasure in unrighteousness.
B053C002V013	53	2	13	But we are bound to always give thanks to God for you, brothers loved by the Lord, because God chose you as first fruits for salvation through sanctification of the Spirit and belief in the truth;
B053C002V014	53	2	14	to which he called you through our Good News, for the obtaining of the glory of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B053C002V015	53	2	15	So then, brothers, stand firm, and hold the traditions which you were taught by us, whether by word, or by letter.
B053C002V016	53	2	16	Now our Lord Jesus Christ himself, and God our Father, who loved us and gave us eternal comfort and good hope through grace,
B053C002V017	53	2	17	comfort your hearts and establish you in every good work and word.
B053C003V001	53	3	1	Finally, brothers, pray for us, that the word of the Lord may spread rapidly and be glorified, even as also with you;
B053C003V002	53	3	2	and that we may be delivered from unreasonable and evil men; for not all have faith.
B053C003V003	53	3	3	But the Lord is faithful, who will establish you, and guard you from the evil one.
B053C003V004	53	3	4	We have confidence in the Lord concerning you, that you both do and will do the things we command.
B053C003V005	53	3	5	May the Lord direct your hearts into the love of God, and into the patience of Christ.
B053C003V006	53	3	6	Now we command you, brothers, in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, that you withdraw yourselves from every brother who walks in rebellion, and not after the tradition which they received from us.
B053C003V007	53	3	7	For you know how you ought to imitate us. For we did not behave ourselves rebelliously among you,
B053C003V008	53	3	8	neither did we eat bread from anyone's hand without paying for it, but in labor and travail worked night and day, that we might not burden any of you;
B053C003V009	53	3	9	not because we do not have the right, but to make ourselves an example to you, that you should imitate us.
B053C003V010	53	3	10	For even when we were with you, we commanded you this: "If anyone will not work, neither let him eat."
B053C003V011	53	3	11	For we hear of some who walk among you in rebellion, who do not work at all, but are busybodies.
B053C003V012	53	3	12	Now those who are that way, we command and exhort in the Lord Jesus Christ, that with quietness they work, and eat their own bread.
B053C003V013	53	3	13	But you, brothers, do not be weary in doing well.
B053C003V014	53	3	14	If any man does not obey our word in this letter, note that man, that you have no company with him, to the end that he may be ashamed.
B053C003V015	53	3	15	Do not count him as an enemy, but admonish him as a brother.
B053C003V016	53	3	16	Now may the Lord of peace himself give you peace at all times in all ways. The Lord be with you all.
B053C003V017	53	3	17	The greeting of me, Paul, with my own hand, which is the sign in every letter: this is how I write.
B053C003V018	53	3	18	The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you all.
B054C001V001	54	1	1	Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus according to the commandment of God our Savior, and Christ Jesus our hope;
B054C001V002	54	1	2	to Timothy, my true child in faith: Grace, mercy, and peace, from God the Father and Christ Jesus our Lord.
B054C001V003	54	1	3	As I urged you when I was going into Macedonia, stay at Ephesus that you might command certain men not to teach a different doctrine,
B054C001V004	54	1	4	neither to pay attention to myths and endless genealogies, which cause speculation, rather than God's stewardship, which is in faith-
B054C001V005	54	1	5	but the goal of this command is love, out of a pure heart and a good conscience and unfeigned faith;
B054C001V006	54	1	6	from which things some, having missed the mark, have turned aside to vain talking;
B054C001V007	54	1	7	desiring to be teachers of the law, though they understand neither what they say, nor about what they strongly affirm.
B054C001V008	54	1	8	But we know that the law is good, if a man uses it lawfully,
B054C001V009	54	1	9	as knowing this, that law is not made for a righteous man, but for the lawless and insubordinate, for the ungodly and sinners, for the unholy and profane, for murderers of fathers and murderers of mothers, for manslayers,
B054C001V010	54	1	10	for the sexually immoral, nor men who practice sexual relations with men, for slave-traders, for liars, for perjurers, and for any other thing contrary to the sound doctrine;
B054C001V011	54	1	11	according to the Good News of the glory of the blessed God, which was committed to my trust.
B054C001V012	54	1	12	And I thank him who enabled me, Christ Jesus our Lord, because he counted me faithful, appointing me to service;
B054C001V013	54	1	13	although I was before a blasphemer, a persecutor, and insolent. However, I obtained mercy, because I did it ignorantly in unbelief.
B054C001V014	54	1	14	The grace of our Lord abounded exceedingly with faith and love which is in Christ Jesus.
B054C001V015	54	1	15	The saying is faithful and worthy of all acceptance, that Christ Jesus came into the world to save sinners; of whom I am chief.
B054C001V016	54	1	16	However, for this cause I obtained mercy, that in me first, Jesus Christ might display all his patience, for an example of those who were going to believe in him for eternal life.
B054C001V017	54	1	17	Now to the King eternal, immortal, invisible, the only God, be honor and glory forever and ever. Amen.
B054C001V018	54	1	18	This instruction I commit to you, my child Timothy, according to the prophecies which led the way to you, that by them you may wage the good warfare;
B054C001V019	54	1	19	holding faith and a good conscience; which some having thrust away made a shipwreck concerning the faith;
B054C001V020	54	1	20	of whom is Hymenaeus and Alexander; whom I delivered to Satan, that they might be taught not to blaspheme.
B054C002V001	54	2	1	I exhort therefore, first of all, that petitions, prayers, intercessions, and givings of thanks, be made for all men:
B054C002V002	54	2	2	for kings and all who are in high places; that we may lead a tranquil and quiet life in all godliness and reverence.
B054C002V003	54	2	3	For this is good and acceptable in the sight of God our Savior;
B054C002V004	54	2	4	who desires all people to be saved and come to full knowledge of the truth.
B054C002V005	54	2	5	For there is one God, and one mediator between God and men, the man Christ Jesus,
B054C002V006	54	2	6	who gave himself as a ransom for all; the testimony in its own times;
B054C002V007	54	2	7	to which I was appointed a proclaimer and an apostle (I am telling the truth, I am not lying), a teacher of the Gentiles in faith and truth.
B054C002V008	54	2	8	I desire therefore that the men in every place pray, lifting up holy hands without anger and doubting.
B054C002V009	54	2	9	In the same way, that women also adorn themselves in decent clothing, with modesty and propriety; not just with braided hair, gold, pearls, or expensive clothing;
B054C002V010	54	2	10	but (which becomes women professing godliness) with good works.
B054C002V011	54	2	11	Let a woman learn in quietness with all subjection.
B054C002V012	54	2	12	But I do not permit a woman to teach, nor to exercise authority over a man, but to be in quietness.
B054C002V013	54	2	13	For Adam was first formed, then Eve.
B054C002V014	54	2	14	Adam was not deceived, but the woman, being deceived, has fallen into disobedience;
B054C002V015	54	2	15	but she will be saved through her childbearing, if they continue in faith, love, and sanctification with sobriety.
B054C003V001	54	3	1	This is a faithful saying: if a man seeks the office of an overseer, he desires a good work.
B054C003V002	54	3	2	The overseer therefore must be without reproach, the husband of one wife, temperate, sensible, modest, hospitable, good at teaching;
B054C003V003	54	3	3	not a drunkard, not violent, but gentle, not quarrelsome, not a lover of money;
B054C003V004	54	3	4	one who rules his own house well, having children in subjection with all reverence;
B054C003V005	54	3	5	(but if a man does not know how to rule his own house, how will he take care of the church of God?)
B054C003V006	54	3	6	not a new convert, lest being puffed up he fall into the same condemnation as the devil.
B054C003V007	54	3	7	Moreover he must have good testimony from those who are outside, to avoid falling into reproach and the snare of the devil.
B054C003V008	54	3	8	Servants, in the same way, must be reverent, not double-tongued, not addicted to much wine, not greedy for money;
B054C003V009	54	3	9	holding the mystery of the faith in a pure conscience.
B054C003V010	54	3	10	Let them also first be tested; then let them serve if they are blameless.
B054C003V011	54	3	11	Their wives in the same way must be reverent, not slanderers, temperate, faithful in all things.
B054C003V012	54	3	12	Let servants be husbands of one wife, ruling their children and their own houses well.
B054C003V013	54	3	13	For those who have served well gain for themselves a good standing, and great boldness in the faith which is in Christ Jesus.
B054C003V014	54	3	14	These things I write to you, hoping to come to you shortly;
B054C003V015	54	3	15	but if I wait long, that you may know how men ought to behave themselves in the house of God, which is the church of the living God, the pillar and ground of the truth.
B054C003V016	54	3	16	Without controversy, the mystery of godliness is great: He was revealed in the flesh,justified in the spirit,seen by angels,preached among the nations,believed on in the world,and received up in glory.
B054C004V001	54	4	1	But the Spirit says expressly that in later times some will fall away from the faith, paying attention to seducing spirits and doctrines of demons,
B054C004V002	54	4	2	through the hypocrisy of men who speak lies, branded in their own conscience as with a hot iron;
B054C004V003	54	4	3	forbidding marriage and commanding to abstain from foods which God created to be received with thanksgiving by those who believe and know the truth.
B054C004V004	54	4	4	For every creature of God is good, and nothing is to be rejected, if it is received with thanksgiving.
B054C004V005	54	4	5	For it is sanctified through the word of God and prayer.
B054C004V006	54	4	6	If you instruct the brothers of these things, you will be a good servant of Christ Jesus, nourished in the words of the faith, and of the good doctrine which you have followed.
B054C004V007	54	4	7	But refuse profane and old wives' tales. Exercise yourself toward godliness.
B054C004V008	54	4	8	For bodily exercise has some value, but godliness has value in all things, having the promise of the life which is now, and of that which is to come.
B054C004V009	54	4	9	This saying is faithful and worthy of all acceptance.
B054C004V010	54	4	10	For to this end we both labor and strive, because we have set our trust in the living God, who is the Savior of all men, especially of those who believe.
B054C004V011	54	4	11	Command and teach these things.
B054C004V012	54	4	12	Let no man despise your youth; but be an example to those who believe, in word, in your way of life, in love, in faith, and in purity.
B054C004V013	54	4	13	Until I come, pay attention to reading, to exhortation, and to teaching.
B054C004V014	54	4	14	Do not neglect the gift that is in you, which was given to you by prophecy, with the laying on of the hands of the elders.
B054C004V015	54	4	15	Be diligent in these things. Give yourself wholly to them, that your progress may be revealed to all.
B054C004V016	54	4	16	Pay attention to yourself, and to your teaching. Continue in these things, for in doing this you will save both yourself and those who hear you.
B054C005V001	54	5	1	Do not rebuke an older man, but exhort him as a father; the younger men as brothers;
B054C005V002	54	5	2	the elder women as mothers; the younger as sisters, in all purity.
B054C005V003	54	5	3	Honor widows who are widows indeed.
B054C005V004	54	5	4	But if any widow has children or grandchildren, let them learn first to show piety towards their own family, and to repay their parents, for this is acceptable in the sight of God.
B054C005V005	54	5	5	Now she who is a widow indeed, and desolate, has her hope set on God, and continues in petitions and prayers night and day.
B054C005V006	54	5	6	But she who gives herself to pleasure is dead while she lives.
B054C005V007	54	5	7	Also command these things, that they may be without reproach.
B054C005V008	54	5	8	But if anyone does not provide for his own, and especially his own household, he has denied the faith, and is worse than an unbeliever.
B054C005V009	54	5	9	Let no one be enrolled as a widow under sixty years old, having been the wife of one man,
B054C005V010	54	5	10	being approved by good works, if she has brought up children, if she has been hospitable to strangers, if she has washed the saints' feet, if she has relieved the afflicted, and if she has diligently followed every good work.
B054C005V011	54	5	11	But refuse younger widows, for when they have grown wanton against Christ, they desire to marry;
B054C005V012	54	5	12	having condemnation, because they have rejected their first pledge.
B054C005V013	54	5	13	Besides, they also learn to be idle, going about from house to house. Not only idle, but also gossips and busybodies, saying things which they ought not.
B054C005V014	54	5	14	I desire therefore that the younger widows marry, bear children, rule the household, and give no occasion to the adversary for reviling.
B054C005V015	54	5	15	For already some have turned aside after Satan.
B054C005V016	54	5	16	If any woman who believes has widows, let her assist them, and do not let the church be burdened; that it might help those widows who are truly in need.
B054C005V017	54	5	17	Let the elders who rule well be counted worthy of double honor, especially those who labor in the word and in teaching.
B054C005V018	54	5	18	For the Scripture says, "You shall not muzzle the ox when it treads out the grain." And, "The laborer is worthy of his wages."
B054C005V019	54	5	19	Do not receive an accusation against an elder, except at the word of two or three witnesses.
B054C005V020	54	5	20	Those who sin, reprove in the sight of all, that the rest also may be in fear.
B054C005V021	54	5	21	I command you in the sight of God, and Christ Jesus, and the chosen angels, that you observe these things without prejudice, doing nothing by partiality.
B054C005V022	54	5	22	Lay hands hastily on no one, neither be a participant in other men's sins. Keep yourself pure.
B054C005V023	54	5	23	Be no longer a drinker of water only, but use a little wine for your stomach's sake and your frequent infirmities.
B054C005V024	54	5	24	Some men's sins are evident, preceding them to judgment, and some also follow later.
B054C005V025	54	5	25	In the same way also there are good works that are obvious, and those that are otherwise cannot be hidden.
B054C006V001	54	6	1	Let as many as are bondservants under the yoke count their own masters worthy of all honor, that the name of God and the doctrine not be blasphemed.
B054C006V002	54	6	2	Those who have believing masters, let them not despise them, because they are brothers, but rather let them serve them, because those who partake of the benefit are believing and beloved. Teach and exhort these things.
B054C006V003	54	6	3	If anyone teaches a different doctrine, and does not consent to sound words, the words of our Lord Jesus Christ, and to the doctrine which is according to godliness,
B054C006V004	54	6	4	he is conceited, knowing nothing, but obsessed with arguments, disputes, and word battles, from which come envy, strife, reviling, evil suspicions,
B054C006V005	54	6	5	constant friction of people of corrupt minds and destitute of the truth, who suppose that godliness is a means of gain.
B054C006V006	54	6	6	But godliness with contentment is great gain.
B054C006V007	54	6	7	For we brought nothing into the world, so neither can we carry anything out.
B054C006V008	54	6	8	But having food and clothing, we will be content with that.
B054C006V009	54	6	9	But those who are determined to be rich fall into a temptation and a snare and many foolish and harmful lusts, such as drown men in ruin and destruction.
B054C006V010	54	6	10	For the love of money is a root of all kinds of evil. Some have been led astray from the faith in their greed, and have pierced themselves through with many sorrows.
B054C006V011	54	6	11	But you, man of God, flee these things, and follow after righteousness, godliness, faith, love, patience, and gentleness.
B054C006V012	54	6	12	Fight the good fight of faith. Lay hold of the eternal life to which you were called, and you confessed the good confession in the sight of many witnesses.
B054C006V013	54	6	13	I command you before God, who gives life to all things, and before Christ Jesus, who before Pontius Pilate testified the good confession,
B054C006V014	54	6	14	that you keep the commandment without spot, blameless, until the appearing of our Lord Jesus Christ;
B054C006V015	54	6	15	which in its own times he will show, who is the blessed and only Ruler, the King of kings, and Lord of lords;
B054C006V016	54	6	16	who alone has immortality, dwelling in unapproachable light; whom no man has seen, nor can see: to whom be honor and eternal power. Amen.
B054C006V017	54	6	17	Charge those who are rich in this present world that they not be haughty, nor have their hope set on the uncertainty of riches, but on God, who richly provides us with everything to enjoy;
B054C006V018	54	6	18	that they do good, that they be rich in good works, that they be ready to distribute, willing to communicate;
B054C006V019	54	6	19	laying up in store for themselves a good foundation against the time to come, that they may lay hold of that which is truly life.
B054C006V020	54	6	20	Timothy, guard that which is committed to you, turning away from the empty chatter and oppositions of the knowledge which is falsely so called;
B054C006V021	54	6	21	which some professing have erred concerning the faith. Grace be with you.
B055C001V001	55	1	1	Paul, an apostle of Jesus Christ through the will of God, according to the promise of the life which is in Christ Jesus,
B055C001V002	55	1	2	to Timothy, my beloved child: Grace, mercy, and peace, from God the Father and Christ Jesus our Lord.
B055C001V003	55	1	3	I thank God, whom I serve as my forefathers did, with a pure conscience. How unceasing is my memory of you in my petitions, night and day
B055C001V004	55	1	4	longing to see you, remembering your tears, that I may be filled with joy;
B055C001V005	55	1	5	having been reminded of the unfeigned faith that is in you; which lived first in your grandmother Lois, and your mother Eunice, and, I am persuaded, in you also.
B055C001V006	55	1	6	For this cause, I remind you that you should stir up the gift of God which is in you through the laying on of my hands.
B055C001V007	55	1	7	For God did not give us a spirit of fear, but of power, love, and self-control.
B055C001V008	55	1	8	Therefore do not be ashamed of the testimony of our Lord, nor of me his prisoner; but endure hardship for the Good News according to the power of God,
B055C001V009	55	1	9	who saved us and called us with a holy calling, not according to our works, but according to his own purpose and grace, which was given to us in Christ Jesus before times eternal,
B055C001V010	55	1	10	but has now been revealed by the appearing of our Savior, Christ Jesus, who abolished death, and brought life and immortality to light through the Good News.
B055C001V011	55	1	11	For this, I was appointed as a proclaimer, an apostle, and a teacher.
B055C001V012	55	1	12	For this cause I also suffer these things.
B055C001V013	55	1	13	Hold the pattern of sound words which you have heard from me, in faith and love which is in Christ Jesus.
B055C001V014	55	1	14	That good thing which was committed to you, guard through the Holy Spirit who dwells in us.
B055C001V015	55	1	15	This you know, that all who are in Asia turned away from me; of whom are Phygelus and Hermogenes.
B055C001V016	55	1	16	May the Lord grant mercy to the house of Onesiphorus, for he often refreshed me, and was not ashamed of my chain,
B055C001V017	55	1	17	but when he was in Rome, he sought me diligently, and found me
B055C001V018	55	1	18	(the Lord grant to him to find 
B055C002V001	55	2	1	You therefore, my child, be strengthened in the grace that is in Christ Jesus.
B055C002V002	55	2	2	The things which you have heard from me among many witnesses, commit the same to faithful men, who will be able to teach others also.
B055C002V003	55	2	3	You therefore must share in hardship, as a good soldier of Christ Jesus.
B055C002V004	55	2	4	No soldier on duty entangles himself in the affairs of life, that he may please him who enrolled him as a soldier.
B055C002V005	55	2	5	Also, if anyone competes in athletics, he is not crowned unless he has competed by the rules.
B055C002V006	55	2	6	The farmers who labor must be the first to get a share of the crops.
B055C002V007	55	2	7	Consider what I say, for the Lord will give you understanding in all things.
B055C002V008	55	2	8	Remember Jesus Christ, risen from the dead, of the seed of David, according to my Good News,
B055C002V009	55	2	9	in which I suffer hardship to the point of chains as a criminal. But God's word is not chained.
B055C002V010	55	2	10	Therefore I endure all things for the chosen ones' sake, that they also may obtain the salvation which is in Christ Jesus with eternal glory.
B055C002V011	55	2	11	This saying is faithful: "For if we died with him,we will also live with him.
B055C002V012	55	2	12	If we endure,we will also reign with him.If we deny him,he also will deny us.
B055C002V013	55	2	13	If we are faithless,he remains faithful,for he cannot deny himself." 
B055C002V014	55	2	14	Remind them of these things, charging them in the presence of God, that they do not argue about words, to no profit, to the subverting of those who hear.
B055C002V015	55	2	15	Give diligence to present yourself approved by God, a workman who does not need to be ashamed, properly handling the Word of Truth.
B055C002V016	55	2	16	But shun empty chatter, for they will proceed further in ungodliness,
B055C002V017	55	2	17	and their word will consume like gangrene, of whom is Hymenaeus and Philetus;
B055C002V018	55	2	18	men who have erred concerning the truth, saying that the resurrection is already past, and overthrowing the faith of some.
B055C002V019	55	2	19	However God's firm foundation stands, having this seal, "The Lord knows those who are his," and, "Let every one who names the name of the Lord depart from unrighteousness."
B055C002V020	55	2	20	Now in a large house there are not only vessels of gold and of silver, but also of wood and of clay. Some are for honor, and some for dishonor.
B055C002V021	55	2	21	If anyone therefore purges himself from these, he will be a vessel for honor, sanctified, and suitable for the master's use, prepared for every good work.
B055C002V022	55	2	22	Flee from youthful lusts; but pursue righteousness, faith, love, and peace with those who call on the Lord out of a pure heart.
B055C002V023	55	2	23	But refuse foolish and ignorant questionings, knowing that they generate strife.
B055C002V024	55	2	24	The Lord's servant must not quarrel, but be gentle towards all, able to teach, patient,
B055C002V025	55	2	25	in gentleness correcting those who oppose him: perhaps God may give them repentance leading to a full knowledge of the truth,
B055C002V026	55	2	26	and they may recover themselves out of the devil's snare, having been taken captive by him to his will.
B055C003V001	55	3	1	But know this, that in the last days, grievous times will come.
B055C003V002	55	3	2	For men will be lovers of self, lovers of money, boastful, arrogant, blasphemers, disobedient to parents, unthankful, unholy,
B055C003V003	55	3	3	without natural affection, unforgiving, slanderers, without self-control, fierce, no lovers of good,
B055C003V004	55	3	4	traitors, headstrong, conceited, lovers of pleasure rather than lovers of God;
B055C003V005	55	3	5	holding a form of godliness, but having denied the power thereof. Turn away from these, also.
B055C003V006	55	3	6	For of these are those who creep into houses, and take captive gullible women loaded down with sins, led away by various lusts,
B055C003V007	55	3	7	always learning, and never able to come to the knowledge of the truth.
B055C003V008	55	3	8	Even as Jannes and Jambres opposed Moses, so do these also oppose the truth; men corrupted in mind, reprobate concerning the faith.
B055C003V009	55	3	9	But they will proceed no further. For their folly will be evident to all men, as theirs also came to be.
B055C003V010	55	3	10	But you did follow my teaching, conduct, purpose, faith, patience, love, steadfastness,
B055C003V011	55	3	11	persecutions, and sufferings: those things that happened to me at Antioch, Iconium, and Lystra. I endured those persecutions. Out of them all the Lord delivered me.
B055C003V012	55	3	12	Yes, and all who desire to live godly in Christ Jesus will suffer persecution.
B055C003V013	55	3	13	But evil men and impostors will grow worse and worse, deceiving and being deceived.
B055C003V014	55	3	14	But you remain in the things which you have learned and have been assured of, knowing from whom you have learned them.
B055C003V015	55	3	15	From infancy, you have known the holy Scriptures which are able to make you wise for salvation through faith, which is in Christ Jesus.
B055C003V016	55	3	16	Every Scripture is God-breathed and profitable for teaching, for reproof, for correction, and for instruction in righteousness,
B055C003V017	55	3	17	that the man of God may be complete, thoroughly equipped for every good work.
B055C004V001	55	4	1	I command you therefore before God and the Lord Jesus Christ, who will judge the living and the dead, and by his appearing and his Kingdom:
B055C004V002	55	4	2	proclaim the word; be urgent in season and out of season; reprove, rebuke, and exhort, with all patience and teaching.
B055C004V003	55	4	3	For the time will come when they will not listen to the sound doctrine, but, having itching ears, will heap up for themselves teachers after their own lusts;
B055C004V004	55	4	4	and will turn away their ears from the truth, and turn aside to myths.
B055C004V005	55	4	5	But you be sober in all things, suffer hardship, do the work of an evangelist, and fulfill your ministry.
B055C004V006	55	4	6	For I am already being offered, and the time of my departure has come.
B055C004V007	55	4	7	I have fought the good fight. I have finished the course. I have kept the faith.
B055C004V008	55	4	8	From now on, there is stored up for me the crown of righteousness, which the Lord, the righteous judge, will give to me on that day; and not to me only, but also to all those who have loved his appearing.
B055C004V009	55	4	9	Be diligent to come to me soon,
B055C004V010	55	4	10	for Demas left me, having loved this present world, and went to Thessalonica; Crescens to Galatia, and Titus to Dalmatia.
B055C004V011	55	4	11	Only Luke is with me. Take Mark, and bring him with you, for he is useful to me for service.
B055C004V012	55	4	12	But I sent Tychicus to Ephesus.
B055C004V013	55	4	13	Bring the cloak that I left at Troas with Carpus when you come, and the books, especially the parchments.
B055C004V014	55	4	14	Alexander, the coppersmith, did much evil to me. The Lord will repay him according to his works,
B055C004V015	55	4	15	of whom you also must beware; for he greatly opposed our words.
B055C004V016	55	4	16	At my first defense, no one came to help me, but all left me. May it not be held against them.
B055C004V017	55	4	17	But the Lord stood by me, and strengthened me, that through me the message might be fully proclaimed, and that all the Gentiles might hear; and I was delivered out of the mouth of the lion.
B055C004V018	55	4	18	And the Lord will deliver me from every evil work, and will preserve me for his heavenly Kingdom; to whom be the glory forever and ever. Amen.
B055C004V019	55	4	19	Greet Prisca and Aquila, and the house of Onesiphorus.
B055C004V020	55	4	20	Erastus remained at Corinth, but I left Trophimus at Miletus sick.
B055C004V021	55	4	21	Be diligent to come before winter. Eubulus salutes you, as do Pudens, Linus, Claudia, and all the brothers.
B055C004V022	55	4	22	The Lord be with your spirit. Grace be with you.
B056C001V001	56	1	1	Paul, a servant of God, and an apostle of Jesus Christ, according to the faith of God's chosen ones, and the knowledge of the truth which is according to godliness,
B056C001V002	56	1	2	in hope of eternal life, which God, who cannot lie, promised before time began;
B056C001V003	56	1	3	but in his own time revealed his word in the message with which I was entrusted according to the commandment of God our Savior;
B056C001V004	56	1	4	to Titus, my true child according to a common faith: Grace and peace from God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ our Savior.
B056C001V005	56	1	5	I left you in Crete for this reason, that you would set in order the things that were lacking, and appoint elders in every city, as I directed you;
B056C001V006	56	1	6	if anyone is blameless, the husband of one wife, having children who believe, who are not accused of loose or unruly behavior.
B056C001V007	56	1	7	For the overseer must be blameless, as God's steward; not self-pleasing, not easily angered, not given to wine, not violent, not greedy for dishonest gain;
B056C001V008	56	1	8	but given to hospitality, as a lover of good, sober minded, fair, holy, self-controlled;
B056C001V009	56	1	9	holding to the faithful word which is according to the teaching, that he may be able to exhort in the sound doctrine, and to convict those who contradict him.
B056C001V010	56	1	10	For there are also many unruly men, vain talkers and deceivers, especially those of the circumcision,
B056C001V011	56	1	11	whose mouths must be stopped; men who overthrow whole houses, teaching things which they ought not, for dishonest gain's sake.
B056C001V012	56	1	12	One of them, a prophet of their own, said, "Cretans are always liars, evil beasts, and idle gluttons."
B056C001V013	56	1	13	This testimony is true. For this cause, reprove them sharply, that they may be sound in the faith,
B056C001V014	56	1	14	not paying attention to Jewish myths and commandments of men who turn away from the truth.
B056C001V015	56	1	15	To the pure, all things are pure; but to those who are defiled and unbelieving, nothing is pure; but both their mind and their conscience are defiled.
B056C001V016	56	1	16	They profess that they know God, but by their works they deny him, being abominable, disobedient, and unfit for any good work.
B056C002V001	56	2	1	But say the things which fit sound doctrine,
B056C002V002	56	2	2	that older men should be temperate, sensible, sober minded, sound in faith, in love, and in patience:
B056C002V003	56	2	3	and that older women likewise be reverent in behavior, not slanderers nor enslaved to much wine, teachers of that which is good;
B056C002V004	56	2	4	that they may train the young women to love their husbands, to love their children,
B056C002V005	56	2	5	to be sober minded, chaste, workers at home, kind, being in subjection to their own husbands, that God's word may not be blasphemed.
B056C002V006	56	2	6	Likewise, exhort the younger men to be sober minded;
B056C002V007	56	2	7	in all things showing yourself an example of good works. In your teaching show integrity, seriousness,
B056C002V008	56	2	8	and a sound message that cannot be condemned; that he who opposes you may be ashamed, having no evil thing to say about us.
B056C002V009	56	2	9	Exhort servants to be in subjection to their own masters, and to be well-pleasing in all things; not contradicting;
B056C002V010	56	2	10	not stealing, but showing all good fidelity; that they may adorn the doctrine of God, our Savior, in all things.
B056C002V011	56	2	11	For the grace of God has appeared, bringing salvation to all men,
B056C002V012	56	2	12	instructing us to the intent that, denying ungodliness and worldly lusts, we would live soberly, righteously, and godly in this present world;
B056C002V013	56	2	13	looking for the blessed hope and appearing of the glory of our great God and Savior, Jesus Christ;
B056C002V014	56	2	14	who gave himself for us, that he might redeem us from all iniquity, and purify for himself a people for his own possession, zealous for good works.
B056C002V015	56	2	15	Say these things and exhort and reprove with all authority. Let no man despise you.
B056C003V001	56	3	1	Remind them to be in subjection to rulers and to authorities, to be obedient, to be ready for every good work,
B056C003V002	56	3	2	to speak evil of no one, not to be contentious, to be gentle, showing all humility toward all men.
B056C003V003	56	3	3	For we were also once foolish, disobedient, deceived, serving various lusts and pleasures, living in malice and envy, hateful, and hating one another.
B056C003V004	56	3	4	But when the kindness of God our Savior and his love toward mankind appeared,
B056C003V005	56	3	5	not by works of righteousness, which we did ourselves, but according to his mercy, he saved us, through the washing of rebirth and renewing by the Holy Spirit,
B056C003V006	56	3	6	whom he poured out on us richly, through Jesus Christ our Savior;
B056C003V007	56	3	7	that, being justified by his grace, we might be made heirs according to the hope of eternal life.
B056C003V008	56	3	8	This saying is faithful, and concerning these things I desire that you affirm confidently, so that those who have believed God may be careful to maintain good works. These things are good and profitable to men;
B056C003V009	56	3	9	but shun foolish questionings, genealogies, strife, and disputes about the law; for they are unprofitable and vain.
B056C003V010	56	3	10	Avoid a factious man after a first and second warning;
B056C003V011	56	3	11	knowing that such a one is perverted, and sins, being self-condemned.
B056C003V012	56	3	12	When I send Artemas to you, or Tychicus, be diligent to come to me to Nicopolis, for I have determined to winter there.
B056C003V013	56	3	13	Send Zenas, the Law scholar, and Apollos on their journey speedily, that nothing may be lacking for them.
B056C003V014	56	3	14	Let our people also learn to maintain good works for necessary uses, that they may not be unfruitful.
B056C003V015	56	3	15	All who are with me greet you. Greet those who love us in faith. Grace be with you all.
B057C001V001	57	1	1	Paul, a prisoner of Christ Jesus, and Timothy our brother, to Philemon, our beloved fellow worker,
B057C001V002	57	1	2	and to Apphia our sister, to Archippus, our fellow soldier, and to the church in your house:
B057C001V003	57	1	3	Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B057C001V004	57	1	4	I thank my God always, making mention of you in my prayers,
B057C001V005	57	1	5	hearing of your love, and of the faith which you have toward the Lord Jesus, and toward all the saints;
B057C001V006	57	1	6	that the fellowship of your faith may become effective, in the knowledge of every good thing which is in us in Christ.
B057C001V007	57	1	7	For I have much joy and comfort in your love, because the hearts of the saints have been refreshed through you, brother.
B057C001V008	57	1	8	Therefore, though I have all boldness in Christ to command you that which is appropriate,
B057C001V009	57	1	9	yet for love's sake I rather beg, being such a one as Paul, the aged, but also a prisoner of Jesus Christ.
B057C001V010	57	1	10	I beg you for my child, whom I have become the father of in my chains, Onesimus,
B057C001V011	57	1	11	who once was useless to you, but now is useful to you and to me.
B057C001V012	57	1	12	I am sending back to you, him who is my very heart,
B057C001V013	57	1	13	whom I desired to keep with me, that on your behalf he might serve me in my chains for the Good News.
B057C001V014	57	1	14	But I was willing to do nothing without your consent, that your goodness would not be as of necessity, but of free will.
B057C001V015	57	1	15	For perhaps he was therefore separated from you for a while, that you would have him forever,
B057C001V016	57	1	16	no longer as a slave, but more than a slave, a beloved brother, especially to me, but how much rather to you, both in the flesh and in the Lord.
B057C001V017	57	1	17	If then you count me a partner, receive him as you would receive me.
B057C001V018	57	1	18	But if he has wronged you at all, or owes you anything, put that to my account.
B057C001V019	57	1	19	I, Paul, write this with my own hand: I will repay it (not to mention to you that you owe to me even your own self besides).
B057C001V020	57	1	20	Yes, brother, let me have joy from you in the Lord. Refresh my heart in Christ.
B057C001V021	57	1	21	Having confidence in your obedience, I write to you, knowing that you will do even beyond what I say.
B057C001V022	57	1	22	Also, prepare a guest room for me, for I hope that through your prayers I will be restored to you.
B057C001V023	57	1	23	Epaphras, my fellow prisoner in Christ Jesus, greets you,
B057C001V024	57	1	24	as do Mark, Aristarchus, Demas, and Luke, my fellow workers.
B057C001V025	57	1	25	The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit.
B058C001V001	58	1	1	God, having in the past spoken to the fathers through the prophets at many times and in various ways,
B058C001V002	58	1	2	has at the end of these days spoken to us by his Son, whom he appointed heir of all things, through whom also he made the worlds.
B058C001V003	58	1	3	His Son is the radiance of his glory, the very image of his substance, and upholding all things by the word of his power, when he had made, through himself, purification for sins, sat down on the right hand of the Majesty on high;
B058C001V004	58	1	4	having become so much better than the angels, as he has inherited a more excellent name than they have.
B058C001V005	58	1	5	For to which of the angels did he say at any time,
B058C001V006	58	1	6	Again, when he brings in the firstborn into the world he says, "Let all the angels of God worship him."
B058C001V007	58	1	7	Of the angels he says,
B058C001V008	58	1	8	But of the Son he says, "Your throne, O God, is forever and ever.The scepter of uprightness is the scepter of your Kingdom.
B058C001V009	58	1	9	You have loved righteousness, and hated iniquity;therefore God, your God, has anointed you with the oil of gladness above your fellows." 
B058C001V010	58	1	10	And, "You, Lord, in the beginning, laid the foundation of the earth.The heavens are the works of your hands.
B058C001V011	58	1	11	They will perish, but you continue.They all will grow old like a garment does.
B058C001V012	58	1	12	As a mantle, you will roll them up,and like a garment they will be changed.But you remain the same, andyour years will have no end." 
B058C001V013	58	1	13	But which of the angels has he told at any time,
B058C001V014	58	1	14	Are not they all serving spirits, sent out to do service for the sake of those who will inherit salvation?
B058C002V001	58	2	1	Therefore we ought to pay greater attention to the things that were heard, so that we will not drift away.
B058C002V002	58	2	2	For if the word spoken through angels proved steadfast, and every transgression and disobedience received a just recompense;
B058C002V003	58	2	3	how will we escape if we neglect so great a salvation-which at the first having been spoken through the Lord, was confirmed to us by those who heard;
B058C002V004	58	2	4	God also testifying with them, both by signs and wonders, by various works of power, and by gifts of the Holy Spirit, according to his own will?
B058C002V005	58	2	5	For he did not subject the world to come, of which we speak, to angels.
B058C002V006	58	2	6	But one has somewhere testified, saying, "What is man, that you think of him?Or the son of man, that you care for him?
B058C002V007	58	2	7	You made him a little lower than the angels.You crowned him with glory and honor.
B058C002V008	58	2	8	[You have put all things in subjection under his feet.]" For in that he subjected all things to him, he left nothing that is not subject to him. But now we do not see all things subjected to him, yet.
B058C002V009	58	2	9	But we see him who has been made a little lower than the angels, Jesus, because of the suffering of death crowned with glory and honor, that by the grace of God he should taste of death for everyone.
B058C002V010	58	2	10	For it became him, for whom are all things, and through whom are all things, in bringing many children to glory, to make the author of their salvation perfect through sufferings.
B058C002V011	58	2	11	For both he who sanctifies and those who are sanctified are all from one, for which cause he is not ashamed to call them brothers,
B058C002V012	58	2	12	saying,
B058C002V013	58	2	13	Again, "I will put my trust in him." Again, "Behold, here I am with the children whom God has given me."
B058C002V014	58	2	14	Since then the children have shared in flesh and blood, he also himself in like manner partook of the same, that through death he might bring to nothing him who had the power of death, that is, the devil,
B058C002V015	58	2	15	and might deliver all of them who through fear of death were all their lifetime subject to bondage.
B058C002V016	58	2	16	For, truly, he did not come to help the angels, but to help the seed of Abraham.
B058C002V017	58	2	17	Therefore he was obligated in all things to be made like his brothers, that he might become a merciful and faithful high priest in things pertaining to God, to make atonement for the sins of the people.
B058C002V018	58	2	18	For in that he himself has suffered being tempted, he is able to help those who are tempted.
B058C003V001	58	3	1	Therefore, holy brothers, partakers of a heavenly calling, consider the Apostle and High Priest of our confession, Jesus;
B058C003V002	58	3	2	who was faithful to him who appointed him, as also was Moses in all his house.
B058C003V003	58	3	3	For he has been counted worthy of more glory than Moses, inasmuch as he who built the house has more honor than the house.
B058C003V004	58	3	4	For every house is built by someone; but he who built all things is God.
B058C003V005	58	3	5	Moses indeed was faithful in all his house as a servant, for a testimony of those things which were afterward to be spoken,
B058C003V006	58	3	6	but Christ is faithful as a Son over his house; whose house we are, if we hold fast our confidence and the glorying of our hope firm to the end.
B058C003V007	58	3	7	Therefore, even as the Holy Spirit says, "Today if you will hear his voice,
B058C003V008	58	3	8	do not harden your hearts, as in the provocation,like as in the day of the trial in the wilderness,
B058C003V009	58	3	9	where your fathers tested me and challenged me,and saw my works for forty years.
B058C003V010	58	3	10	Therefore I was displeased with this generation,and said, 'They always err in their heart,but they did not know my ways;'
B058C003V011	58	3	11	as I swore in my wrath,'They will not enter into my rest.'" 
B058C003V012	58	3	12	Beware, brothers, lest perhaps there be in any one of you an evil heart of unbelief, in falling away from the living God;
B058C003V013	58	3	13	but exhort one another day by day, so long as it is called "today;" lest any one of you be hardened by the deceitfulness of sin.
B058C003V014	58	3	14	For we have become partakers of Christ, if we hold fast the beginning of our confidence firm to the end:
B058C003V015	58	3	15	while it is said,
B058C003V016	58	3	16	For who, when they heard, rebelled? No, did not all those who came out of Egypt by Moses?
B058C003V017	58	3	17	With whom was he displeased forty years? Was not it with those who sinned, whose bodies fell in the wilderness?
B058C003V018	58	3	18	To whom did he swear that they would not enter into his rest, but to those who were disobedient?
B058C003V019	58	3	19	We see that they were not able to enter in because of unbelief.
B058C004V001	58	4	1	Let us fear therefore, lest perhaps anyone of you should seem to have come short of a promise of entering into his rest.
B058C004V002	58	4	2	For indeed we have had good news preached to us, even as they also did, but the word they heard did not profit them, because they were not united by faith with those who heard.
B058C004V003	58	4	3	For we who have believed do enter into that rest, even as he has said, "As I swore in my wrath, they will not enter into my rest;" although the works were finished from the foundation of the world.
B058C004V004	58	4	4	For he has said this somewhere about the seventh day, "God rested on the seventh day from all his works;"
B058C004V005	58	4	5	and in this place again, "They will not enter into my rest."
B058C004V006	58	4	6	Seeing therefore it remains that some should enter therein, and they to whom the good news was before preached failed to enter in because of disobedience,
B058C004V007	58	4	7	he again defines a certain day, "Today," saying through David so long a time afterward (just as has been said),
B058C004V008	58	4	8	For if Joshua had given them rest, he would not have spoken afterward of another day.
B058C004V009	58	4	9	There remains therefore a Sabbath rest for the people of God.
B058C004V010	58	4	10	For he who has entered into his rest has himself also rested from his works, as God did from his.
B058C004V011	58	4	11	Let us therefore give diligence to enter into that rest, lest anyone fall after the same example of disobedience.
B058C004V012	58	4	12	For the word of God is living, and active, and sharper than any two-edged sword, and piercing even to the dividing of soul and spirit, of both joints and marrow, and is able to discern the thoughts and intentions of the heart.
B058C004V013	58	4	13	There is no creature that is hidden from his sight, but all things are naked and laid open before the eyes of him with whom we have to do.
B058C004V014	58	4	14	Having then a great high priest, who has passed through the heavens, Jesus, the Son of God, let us hold tightly to our confession.
B058C004V015	58	4	15	For we do not have a high priest who cannot be touched with the feeling of our infirmities, but one who has been in all points tempted like we are, yet without sin.
B058C004V016	58	4	16	Let us therefore draw near with boldness to the throne of grace, that we may receive mercy, and may find grace for help in time of need.
B058C005V001	58	5	1	For every high priest, being taken from among men, is appointed for men in things pertaining to God, that he may offer both gifts and sacrifices for sins.
B058C005V002	58	5	2	The high priest can deal gently with those who are ignorant and going astray, because he himself is also surrounded with weakness.
B058C005V003	58	5	3	Because of this, he must offer sacrifices for sins for the people, as well as for himself.
B058C005V004	58	5	4	Nobody takes this honor on himself, but he is called by God, just like Aaron was.
B058C005V005	58	5	5	So also Christ did not glorify himself to be made a high priest, but it was he who said to him,
B058C005V006	58	5	6	As he says also in another place,
B058C005V007	58	5	7	He, in the days of his flesh, having offered up prayers and petitions with strong crying and tears to him who was able to save him from death, and having been heard for his godly fear,
B058C005V008	58	5	8	though he was a Son, yet learned obedience by the things which he suffered.
B058C005V009	58	5	9	Having been made perfect, he became to all of those who obey him the author of eternal salvation,
B058C005V010	58	5	10	named by God a high priest after the order of Melchizedek.
B058C005V011	58	5	11	About him we have many words to say, and hard to interpret, seeing you have become dull of hearing.
B058C005V012	58	5	12	For when by reason of the time you ought to be teachers, you again need to have someone teach you the rudiments of the first principles of the oracles of God. You have come to need milk, and not solid food.
B058C005V013	58	5	13	For everyone who lives on milk is not experienced in the word of righteousness, for he is a baby.
B058C005V014	58	5	14	But solid food is for those who are full grown, who by reason of use have their senses exercised to discern good and evil.
B058C006V001	58	6	1	Therefore leaving the doctrine of the first principles of Christ, let us press on to perfection-not laying again a foundation of repentance from dead works, of faith toward God,
B058C006V002	58	6	2	of the teaching of washings, of laying on of hands, of resurrection of the dead, and of eternal judgment.
B058C006V003	58	6	3	This will we do, if God permits.
B058C006V004	58	6	4	For concerning those who were once enlightened and tasted of the heavenly gift, and were made partakers of the Holy Spirit,
B058C006V005	58	6	5	and tasted the good word of God, and the powers of the age to come,
B058C006V006	58	6	6	and then fell away, it is impossible to renew them again to repentance; seeing they crucify the Son of God for themselves again, and put him to open shame.
B058C006V007	58	6	7	For the land which has drunk the rain that comes often on it, and brings forth a crop suitable for them for whose sake it is also tilled, receives blessing from God;
B058C006V008	58	6	8	but if it bears thorns and thistles, it is rejected and near being cursed, whose end is to be burned.
B058C006V009	58	6	9	But, beloved, we are persuaded of better things for you, and things that accompany salvation, even though we speak like this.
B058C006V010	58	6	10	For God is not unrighteous, so as to forget your work and the love which you showed toward his name, in that you served the saints, and still do serve them.
B058C006V011	58	6	11	We desire that each one of you may show the same diligence to the fullness of hope even to the end,
B058C006V012	58	6	12	that you won't be sluggish, but imitators of those who through faith and patience inherited the promises.
B058C006V013	58	6	13	For when God made a promise to Abraham, since he could swear by none greater, he swore by himself,
B058C006V014	58	6	14	saying, "Surely blessing I will bless you, and multiplying I will multiply you."
B058C006V015	58	6	15	Thus, having patiently endured, he obtained the promise.
B058C006V016	58	6	16	For men swear by a greater one, and in every dispute of theirs the oath is final for confirmation.
B058C006V017	58	6	17	In this way God, being determined to show more abundantly to the heirs of the promise the immutability of his counsel, interposed with an oath;
B058C006V018	58	6	18	that by two immutable things, in which it is impossible for God to lie, we may have a strong encouragement, who have fled for refuge to take hold of the hope set before us.
B058C006V019	58	6	19	This hope we have as an anchor of the soul, a hope both sure and steadfast and entering into that which is within the veil;
B058C006V020	58	6	20	where as a forerunner Jesus entered for us, having become a high priest forever after the order of Melchizedek.
B058C007V001	58	7	1	For this Melchizedek, king of Salem, priest of God Most High, who met Abraham returning from the slaughter of the kings and blessed him,
B058C007V002	58	7	2	to whom also Abraham divided a tenth part of all (being first, by interpretation, king of righteousness, and then also king of Salem, which is king of peace;
B058C007V003	58	7	3	without father, without mother, without genealogy, having neither beginning of days nor end of life, but made like the Son of God), remains a priest continually.
B058C007V004	58	7	4	Now consider how great this man was, to whom even Abraham, the patriarch, gave a tenth out of the best spoils.
B058C007V005	58	7	5	They indeed of the sons of Levi who receive the priest's office have a commandment to take tithes of the people according to the Law, that is, of their brothers, though these have come out of the body of Abraham,
