B058C011V001	58	11	1	Now faith is assurance of things hoped for, proof of things not seen.
B058C011V002	58	11	2	For by this, the elders obtained testimony.
B058C011V003	58	11	3	By faith, we understand that the universe has been framed by the word of God, so that what is seen has not been made out of things which are visible.
B058C011V004	58	11	4	By faith, Abel offered to God a more excellent sacrifice than Cain, through which he had testimony given to him that he was righteous, God testifying with respect to his gifts; and through it he, being dead, still speaks.
B058C011V005	58	11	5	By faith, Enoch was taken away, so that he would not see death, and he was not found, because God took him away. For he has had testimony given to him that before his translation he had been well pleasing to God.
B058C011V006	58	11	6	Without faith it is impossible to be well pleasing to  him , for he who comes to God must believe that he exists, and that he is a rewarder of those who seek him.
B058C011V007	58	11	7	By faith, Noah, being warned about things not yet seen, moved with godly fear, prepared a ship for the saving of his house, through which he condemned the world, and became heir of the righteousness which is according to faith.
B058C011V008	58	11	8	By faith, Abraham, when he was called, obeyed to go out to a place which he was to receive for an inheritance. He went out, not knowing where he went.
B058C011V009	58	11	9	By faith, he lived as a foreigner in the land of promise, as in a land not his own, dwelling in tents, with Isaac and Jacob, the heirs with him of the same promise.
B058C011V010	58	11	10	For he looked for the city which has the foundations, whose builder and maker is God.
B058C011V011	58	11	11	By faith he received power to procreate when he was past age, and Sarah herself was barren. He regarded him faithful who had promised.
B058C011V012	58	11	12	Therefore as many as the stars of the sky in multitude, and as innumerable as the sand which is by the sea shore, were fathered by one man, and him as good as dead.
