B058C011V018	58	11	18	even he to whom it was said, "In Isaac will your seed be called;"
B058C011V019	58	11	19	concluding that God is able to raise up even from the dead. Figuratively speaking, he also did receive him back from the dead.
B058C011V020	58	11	20	By faith, Isaac blessed Jacob and Esau, even concerning things to come.
B058C011V021	58	11	21	By faith, Jacob, when he was dying, blessed each of the sons of Joseph, and worshiped, leaning on the top of his staff.
B058C011V022	58	11	22	By faith, Joseph, when his end was near, made mention of the departure of the children of Israel; and gave instructions concerning his bones.
B058C011V023	58	11	23	By faith, Moses, when he was born, was hidden for three months by his parents, because they saw that he was a beautiful child, and they were not afraid of the king's commandment.
B058C011V024	58	11	24	By faith, Moses, when he had grown up, refused to be called the son of Pharaoh's daughter,
B058C011V025	58	11	25	choosing rather to share ill treatment with God's people, than to enjoy the pleasures of sin for a time;
B058C011V026	58	11	26	accounting the reproach of Christ greater riches than the treasures of Egypt; for he looked to the reward.
B058C011V027	58	11	27	By faith, he left Egypt, not fearing the wrath of the king; for he endured, as seeing him who is invisible.
B058C011V028	58	11	28	By faith, he kept the Passover, and the sprinkling of the blood, that the destroyer of the firstborn should not touch them.
B058C011V029	58	11	29	By faith, they passed through the Red Sea as on dry land. When the Egyptians tried to do so, they were swallowed up.
B058C011V030	58	11	30	By faith, the walls of Jericho fell down, after they had been encircled for seven days.
B058C011V031	58	11	31	By faith, Rahab the prostitute, did not perish with those who were disobedient, having received the spies in peace.
