B058C012V001	58	12	1	Therefore let us also, seeing we are surrounded by so great a cloud of witnesses, lay aside every weight and the sin which so easily entangles us, and let us run with patience the race that is set before us,
B058C012V002	58	12	2	looking to Jesus, the author and perfecter of faith, who for the joy that was set before him endured the cross, disregarding its shame, and has sat down at the right hand of the throne of God.
B058C012V003	58	12	3	For consider him who has endured such hostility from sinners against himself, that you do not grow weary, fainting in your souls.
B058C012V004	58	12	4	You have not yet resisted to blood, striving against sin;
B058C012V005	58	12	5	and you have forgotten the exhortation which reasons with you as with children, "My son, do not take lightly the chastening of 
B058C012V006	58	12	6	For whom 
B058C012V007	58	12	7	It is for discipline that you endure. God deals with you as with children, for what son is there whom his father does not discipline?
B058C012V008	58	12	8	But if you are without discipline, of which all have been made partakers, then are you illegitimate, and not children.
B058C012V009	58	12	9	Furthermore, we had the fathers of our flesh to chasten us, and we paid them respect. Shall we not much rather be in subjection to the Father of spirits, and live?
B058C012V010	58	12	10	For they indeed, for a few days, punished us as seemed good to them; but he for our profit, that we may be partakers of his holiness.
B058C012V011	58	12	11	All chastening seems for the present to be not joyous but grievous; yet afterward it yields the peaceful fruit of righteousness to those who have been exercised thereby.
B058C012V012	58	12	12	Therefore, lift up the hands that hang down and the feeble knees,
B058C012V013	58	12	13	and make straight paths for your feet, so that which is lame may not be dislocated, but rather be healed.
B058C012V014	58	12	14	Follow after peace with all men, and the sanctification without which no man will see the Lord,
B058C012V015	58	12	15	looking carefully lest there be any man who falls short of the grace of God; lest any root of bitterness springing up trouble you, and many be defiled by it;
B058C012V016	58	12	16	lest there be any sexually immoral person, or profane person, like Esau, who sold his own birthright for one meal.
B058C012V017	58	12	17	For you know that even when he afterward desired to inherit the blessing, he was rejected, for he found no place for a change of mind though he sought it diligently with tears.
B058C012V018	58	12	18	For you have not come to something that might be touched, and that burned with fire, and darkness, gloom, and storm,
B058C012V019	58	12	19	the sound of a trumpet, and the voice of words; which those who heard it begged that not one more word should be spoken to them,
B058C012V020	58	12	20	for they could not stand that which was commanded, "If even an animal touches the mountain, it shall be stoned;"
B058C012V021	58	12	21	and so fearful was the appearance, that Moses said, "I am terrified and trembling."
B058C012V022	58	12	22	But you have come to Mount Zion, and to the city of the living God, the heavenly Jerusalem, and to innumerable multitudes of angels,
B058C012V023	58	12	23	to the assembly of the firstborn who are enrolled in heaven, to God the Judge of all, to the spirits of just men made perfect,
B058C012V024	58	12	24	to Jesus, the mediator of a New Covenant, and to the blood of sprinkling that speaks better than that of Abel.
B058C012V025	58	12	25	See that you do not refuse him who speaks. For if they did not escape when they refused him who warned on the Earth, how much more will we not escape who turn away from him who warns from heaven,
B058C012V026	58	12	26	whose voice shook the earth then, but now he has promised, saying, "Yet once more I will shake not only the earth, but also the heavens."
B058C012V027	58	12	27	This phrase, "Yet once more," signifies the removing of those things that are shaken, as of things that have been made, that those things which are not shaken may remain.
B058C012V028	58	12	28	So since we are receiving a Kingdom that cannot be shaken, let us give thanks, through which we may offer service pleasing to God, with reverence and awe,
B058C012V029	58	12	29	for our God is a consuming fire.
B058C013V001	58	13	1	Let brotherly love continue.
B058C013V002	58	13	2	Do not forget to show hospitality to strangers, for in doing so, some have entertained angels without knowing it.
B058C013V003	58	13	3	Remember those who are in bonds, as bound with them; and those who are ill-treated, since you are also in the body.
B058C013V004	58	13	4	Let marriage be held in honor among all, and let the bed be undefiled: for God will judge the sexually immoral and adulterers.
B058C013V005	58	13	5	Be free from the love of money, content with such things as you have, for he has said, "I will never leave you or forsake you."
B058C013V006	58	13	6	So that with good courage we say,
B058C013V007	58	13	7	Remember your leaders, men who spoke to you the word of God, and considering the results of their conduct, imitate their faith.
B058C013V008	58	13	8	Jesus Christ is the same yesterday, today, and forever.
B058C013V009	58	13	9	Do not be carried away by all kinds of strange teachings, for it is good that the heart be established by grace, not by food, through which those who were so occupied were not benefited.
B058C013V010	58	13	10	We have an altar from which those who serve the holy tabernacle have no right to eat.
B058C013V011	58	13	11	For the bodies of those animals, whose blood is brought into the holy place by the high priest as an offering for sin, are burned outside of the camp.
B058C013V012	58	13	12	Therefore Jesus also, that he might sanctify the people through his own blood, suffered outside of the gate.
B058C013V013	58	13	13	Let us therefore go out to him outside of the camp, bearing his reproach.
B058C013V014	58	13	14	For we do not have here an enduring city, but we seek that which is to come.
B058C013V015	58	13	15	Through him, then, let us offer up a sacrifice of praise to God continually, that is, the fruit of lips which proclaim allegiance to his name.
B058C013V016	58	13	16	But do not forget to be doing good and sharing, for with such sacrifices God is well pleased.
B058C013V017	58	13	17	Obey your leaders and submit to them, for they watch on behalf of your souls, as those who will give account, that they may do this with joy, and not with groaning, for that would be unprofitable for you.
B058C013V018	58	13	18	Pray for us, for we are persuaded that we have a good conscience, desiring to live honorably in all things.
B058C013V019	58	13	19	I strongly urge you to do this, that I may be restored to you sooner.
B058C013V020	58	13	20	Now may the God of peace, who brought again from the dead the great shepherd of the sheep with the blood of an eternal covenant, our Lord Jesus,
B058C013V021	58	13	21	make you complete in every good thing to do his will, working in us that which is well pleasing in his sight, through Jesus Christ, to whom be the glory forever. Amen.
B058C013V022	58	13	22	But I exhort you, brothers, endure the word of exhortation, for I have written to you in few words.
B058C013V023	58	13	23	Know that our brother Timothy has been freed, with whom, if he comes shortly, I will see you.
B058C013V024	58	13	24	Greet all of your leaders and all the saints. Those from Italy send you greetings.
B058C013V025	58	13	25	Grace be with you all.
B059C001V001	59	1	1	Jacob, a servant of God and of the Lord Jesus Christ, to the twelve tribes which are in the Diaspora: Greetings.
B059C001V002	59	1	2	Count it all joy, my brothers, when you fall into various temptations,
B059C001V003	59	1	3	knowing that the testing of your faith produces endurance.
B059C001V004	59	1	4	Let endurance have its perfect work, that you may be perfect and complete, lacking in nothing.
B059C001V005	59	1	5	But if any of you lacks wisdom, let him ask of God, who gives to all liberally and without reproach; and it will be given to him.
B059C001V006	59	1	6	But let him ask in faith, without any doubting, for he who doubts is like a wave of the sea, driven by the wind and tossed.
B059C001V007	59	1	7	For let that man not think that he will receive anything from the Lord.
B059C001V008	59	1	8	He is a double-minded man, unstable in all his ways.
B059C001V009	59	1	9	But let the brother in humble circumstances glory in his high position;
B059C001V010	59	1	10	and the rich, in that he is made humble, because like the flower in the grass, he will pass away.
B059C001V011	59	1	11	For the sun arises with the scorching wind, and withers the grass, and the flower in it falls, and the beauty of its appearance perishes. So also will the rich man fade away in his pursuits.
B059C001V012	59	1	12	Blessed is the man who endures temptation, for when he has been approved, he will receive the crown of life, which he promised to those who love him.
B059C001V013	59	1	13	Let no man say when he is tempted, "I am tempted by God," for God cannot be tempted by evil, and he himself tempts no one.
B059C001V014	59	1	14	But each one is tempted, when he is drawn away by his own lust, and enticed.
B059C001V015	59	1	15	Then the lust, when it has conceived, bears sin; and the sin, when it is full grown, brings forth death.
B059C001V016	59	1	16	Do not be deceived, my beloved brothers.
B059C001V017	59	1	17	Every good gift and every perfect gift is from above, coming down from the Father of lights, with whom can be no variation, nor turning shadow.
B059C001V018	59	1	18	Of his own will he brought us forth by the word of truth, that we should be a kind of first fruits of his creatures.
B059C001V019	59	1	19	This you know, my beloved brothers. But let every man be swift to hear, slow to speak, and slow to anger;
B059C001V020	59	1	20	for the anger of man does not accomplish the righteousness of God.
B059C001V021	59	1	21	Therefore, putting away all filthiness and overflowing of wickedness, receive with humility the implanted word, which is able to save your souls.
B059C001V022	59	1	22	But be doers of the word, and not only hearers, deluding your own selves.
B059C001V023	59	1	23	For if anyone is a hearer of the word and not a doer, he is like a man looking at his natural face in a mirror;
B059C001V024	59	1	24	for he sees himself, and goes away, and immediately forgets what kind of man he was.
B059C001V025	59	1	25	But he who looks into the perfect Law of freedom, and continues, not being a hearer who forgets, but a doer of the work, this man will be blessed in what he does.
B059C001V026	59	1	26	If anyone thinks himself to be religious while he does not bridle his tongue, but deceives his heart, this man's religion is worthless.
B059C001V027	59	1	27	Pure religion and undefiled before our God and Father is this: to visit the fatherless and widows in their affliction, and to keep oneself unstained by the world.
B059C002V001	59	2	1	My brothers, do not hold the faith of our Lord Jesus Christ of glory with partiality.
B059C002V002	59	2	2	For if a man with a gold ring, in fine clothing, comes into your synagogue, and a poor man in filthy clothing also comes in;
B059C002V003	59	2	3	and you pay special attention to him who wears the fine clothing, and say, "Sit here in a good place;" but you tell the poor man, "Stand there," or "Sit by my footstool;"
B059C002V004	59	2	4	haven't you shown partiality among yourselves, and become judges with evil thoughts?
B059C002V005	59	2	5	Listen, my beloved brothers. Did not God choose those who are poor in this world to be rich in faith, and heirs of the Kingdom which he promised to those who love him?
B059C002V006	59	2	6	But you have dishonored the poor man. Do not the rich oppress you, and personally drag you before the courts?
B059C002V007	59	2	7	Do not they blaspheme the honorable name by which you are called?
B059C002V008	59	2	8	However, if you fulfill the royal law, according to the Scripture, "You shall love your neighbor as yourself," you do well.
B059C002V009	59	2	9	But if you show partiality, you commit sin, being convicted by the law as transgressors.
B059C002V010	59	2	10	For whoever keeps the whole law, and yet stumbles in one point, he has become guilty of all.
B059C002V011	59	2	11	For he who said, "Do not commit adultery," also said, "Do not commit murder." Now if you do not commit adultery, but murder, you have become a transgressor of the law.
B059C002V012	59	2	12	So speak, and so do, as men who are to be judged by a law of freedom.
B059C002V013	59	2	13	For judgment is without mercy to him who has shown no mercy. Mercy triumphs over judgment.
B059C002V014	59	2	14	What good is it, my brothers, if a man says he has faith, but has no works? Can faith save him?
B059C002V015	59	2	15	And if a brother or sister is naked and in lack of daily food,
B059C002V016	59	2	16	and one of you tells them, "Go in peace, be warmed and filled;" and yet you did not give them the things the body needs, what good is it?
B059C002V017	59	2	17	Even so faith, if it has no works, is dead in itself.
B059C002V018	59	2	18	Yes, a man will say, "You have faith, and I have works." Show me your faith without works, and I by my works will show you my faith.
B059C002V019	59	2	19	You believe that God is one. You do well. The demons also believe, and shudder.
B059C002V020	59	2	20	But do you want to know, foolish man, that faith apart from works is dead?
B059C002V021	59	2	21	Wasn't Abraham our father justified by works, in that he offered up Isaac his son on the altar?
B059C002V022	59	2	22	You see that faith worked with his works, and by works faith was perfected;
B059C002V023	59	2	23	and the Scripture was fulfilled which says, "Abraham believed God, and it was accounted to him as righteousness;" and he was called the friend of God.
B059C002V024	59	2	24	You see then that by works, a man is justified, and not only by faith.
B059C002V025	59	2	25	In like manner was not Rahab the prostitute also justified by works, in that she received the messengers, and sent them out another way?
B059C002V026	59	2	26	For as the body apart from the spirit is dead, even so faith apart from works is dead.
B059C003V001	59	3	1	Let not many of you be teachers, my brothers, knowing that we will receive heavier judgment.
B059C003V002	59	3	2	For in many things we all stumble. If anyone does not stumble in word, the same is a perfect man, able to bridle the whole body also.
B059C003V003	59	3	3	Now if we put bits into the horses' mouths so that they may obey us, we guide their whole body.
B059C003V004	59	3	4	Behold, the ships also, though they are so big and are driven by fierce winds, are yet guided by a very small rudder, wherever the pilot desires.
B059C003V005	59	3	5	So the tongue is also a little member, and boasts great things. See how a small fire can spread to a large forest!
B059C003V006	59	3	6	And the tongue is a fire. The world of iniquity among our members is the tongue, which defiles the whole body, and sets on fire the course of nature, and is set on fire by hell.
B059C003V007	59	3	7	For every kind of animal, bird, creeping thing, and thing in the sea, is tamed, and has been tamed by mankind.
B059C003V008	59	3	8	But nobody can tame the tongue. It is a restless evil, full of deadly poison.
B059C003V009	59	3	9	With it we bless our 
B059C003V010	59	3	10	Out of the same mouth comes forth blessing and cursing. My brothers, these things ought not to be so.
B059C003V011	59	3	11	Does a spring send out from the same opening fresh and bitter water?
B059C003V012	59	3	12	Can a fig tree, my brothers, yield olives, or a vine figs? Nor is salt water able to produce sweet.
B059C003V013	59	3	13	Who is wise and understanding among you? Let him show by his good conduct that his deeds are done in gentleness of wisdom.
B059C003V014	59	3	14	But if you have bitter jealousy and selfish ambition in your heart, do not boast and do not lie against the truth.
B059C003V015	59	3	15	This wisdom is not that which comes down from above, but is earthly, sensual, and demonic.
B059C003V016	59	3	16	For where jealousy and selfish ambition are, there is confusion and every evil deed.
B059C003V017	59	3	17	But the wisdom that is from above is first pure, then peaceful, gentle, reasonable, full of mercy and good fruits, without partiality, without hypocrisy.
B059C003V018	59	3	18	Now the fruit of righteousness is sown in peace by those who make peace.
B059C004V001	59	4	1	Where do wars and fightings among you come from? Do not they come from your pleasures that war in your members?
B059C004V002	59	4	2	You lust, and do not have. You kill, covet, and cannot obtain. You fight and make war. You do not have, because you do not ask.
B059C004V003	59	4	3	You ask, and do not receive, because you ask with wrong motives, so that you may spend it for your pleasures.
B059C004V004	59	4	4	You adulteresses, do you not know that friendship with the world is enmity with God? Whoever therefore wants to be a friend of the world makes himself an enemy of God.
B059C004V005	59	4	5	Or do you think that the Scripture says in vain, "The Spirit which He made to dwell in us yearns jealously"?
B059C004V006	59	4	6	But He gives more grace. Therefore it says, "God resists the proud, but gives grace to the humble."
B059C004V007	59	4	7	Be subject therefore to God. But resist the devil, and he will flee from you.
B059C004V008	59	4	8	Draw near to God, and he will draw near to you. Cleanse your hands, you sinners; and purify your hearts, you double-minded.
B059C004V009	59	4	9	Lament, mourn, and weep. Let your laughter be turned to mourning, and your joy to gloom.
B059C004V010	59	4	10	Humble yourselves in the sight of the Lord, and he will exalt you.
B059C004V011	59	4	11	Do not speak against one another, brothers. He who speaks against a brother or judges his brother, speaks against the law and judges the law. But if you judge the law, you are not a doer of the law, but a judge.
B059C004V012	59	4	12	Only one is the lawgiver and judge, who is able to save and to destroy. But who are you to judge your neighbor?
B059C004V013	59	4	13	Come now, you who say, "Today or tomorrow let us go into this city, and spend a year there, trade, and make a profit."
B059C004V014	59	4	14	Whereas you do not know what your life will be like tomorrow. For what is your life? For you are a vapor, that appears for a little time, and then vanishes away.
B059C004V015	59	4	15	For you ought to say, "If 
B059C004V016	59	4	16	But now you glory in your boasting. All such boasting is evil.
B059C004V017	59	4	17	To him therefore who knows to do good, and does not do it, to him it is sin.
B059C005V001	59	5	1	Come now, you rich, weep and howl for your miseries that are coming on you.
B059C005V002	59	5	2	Your riches are corrupted and your garments are moth-eaten.
B059C005V003	59	5	3	Your gold and your silver are corroded, and their corrosion will be for a testimony against you, and will eat your flesh like fire. You have laid up your treasure in the last days.
B059C005V004	59	5	4	Behold, the wages of the laborers who mowed your fields, which you have kept back by fraud, cry out, and the cries of those who reaped have entered into the ears of 
B059C005V005	59	5	5	You have lived delicately on the earth, and taken your pleasure. You have nourished your hearts in a day of slaughter.
B059C005V006	59	5	6	You have condemned, you have murdered the righteous one. He does not resist you.
B059C005V007	59	5	7	Be patient therefore, brothers, until the coming of the Lord. Behold, the farmer waits for the precious fruit of the earth, being patient over it, until it receives the early and late rain.
B059C005V008	59	5	8	You also be patient. Establish your hearts, for the coming of the Lord is near.
B059C005V009	59	5	9	Do not grumble, brothers, against one another, so that you won't be judged. Behold, the judge stands at the door.
B059C005V010	59	5	10	Take, brothers, for an example of suffering and of patience, the prophets who spoke in the name of the Lord.
B059C005V011	59	5	11	Behold, we call them blessed who endured. You have heard of the patience of Job, and have seen 
B059C005V012	59	5	12	But above all things, my brothers, do not swear, neither by heaven, nor by the earth, nor by any other oath; but let your "yes" be "yes," and your "no," "no;" so that you do not fall under judgment.
B059C005V013	59	5	13	Is any among you suffering? Let him pray. Is any cheerful? Let him sing praises.
B059C005V014	59	5	14	Is any among you sick? Let him call for the elders of the church, and let them pray over him, anointing him with oil in the name of the Lord,
B059C005V015	59	5	15	and the prayer of faith will heal him who is sick, and the Lord will raise him up. If he has committed sins, he will be forgiven.
B059C005V016	59	5	16	Therefore confess your sins to one another, and pray for one another, that you may be healed. The insistent prayer of a righteous person is powerfully effective.
B059C005V017	59	5	17	Elijah was a man with a nature like ours, and he prayed earnestly that it might not rain, and it did not rain on the earth for three years and six months.
B059C005V018	59	5	18	He prayed again, and the sky gave rain, and the earth brought forth its fruit.
B059C005V019	59	5	19	My brothers, if any among you wanders from the truth, and someone turns him back,
B059C005V020	59	5	20	let him know that he who turns a sinner from the error of his way will save his soul from death, and will cover a multitude of sins.
B060C001V001	60	1	1	Peter, an apostle of Jesus Christ, to the chosen ones who are living as foreigners in the Diaspora in Pontus, Galatia, Cappadocia, Asia, and Bithynia,
B060C001V002	60	1	2	according to the foreknowledge of God the Father, in sanctification of the Spirit, that you may obey Jesus Christ and be sprinkled with his blood: Grace to you and peace be multiplied.
B060C001V003	60	1	3	Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who according to his great mercy became our father again to a living hope through the resurrection of Jesus Christ from the dead,
B060C001V004	60	1	4	to an incorruptible and undefiled inheritance that does not fade away, reserved in Heaven for you,
B060C001V005	60	1	5	who by the power of God are guarded through faith for a salvation ready to be revealed in the last time.
B060C001V006	60	1	6	Wherein you greatly rejoice, though now for a little while, if need be, you have been put to grief in various trials,
B060C001V007	60	1	7	that the proof of your faith, which is more precious than gold that perishes even though it is tested by fire, may be found to result in praise, glory, and honor at the revelation of Jesus Christ-
B060C001V008	60	1	8	whom not having seen you love; in whom, though now you do not see him, yet believing, you rejoice greatly with joy unspeakable and full of glory-
B060C001V009	60	1	9	receiving the result of your faith, the salvation of your souls.
B060C001V010	60	1	10	Concerning this salvation, the prophets sought and searched diligently, who prophesied of the grace that would come to you,
B060C001V011	60	1	11	searching for who or what kind of time the Spirit of Christ, which was in them, pointed to, when he predicted the sufferings of Christ, and the glories that would follow them.
B060C001V012	60	1	12	To them it was revealed, that not to themselves, but to you, they ministered these things, which now have been announced to you through those who preached the Good News to you by the Holy Spirit sent out from heaven; which things angels desire to look into.
B060C001V013	60	1	13	Therefore, prepare your minds for action, be sober and set your hope fully on the grace that will be brought to you at the revelation of Jesus Christ-
B060C001V014	60	1	14	as children of obedience, not conforming yourselves according to your former lusts as in your ignorance,
B060C001V015	60	1	15	but just as he who called you is holy, you yourselves also be holy in all of your behavior;
B060C001V016	60	1	16	because it is written, "You shall be holy; for I am holy."
B060C001V017	60	1	17	If you call on him as Father, who without respect of persons judges according to each man's work, pass the time of your living as foreigners here in reverent fear:
B060C001V018	60	1	18	knowing that you were redeemed, not with corruptible things, with silver or gold, from the useless way of life handed down from your fathers,
B060C001V019	60	1	19	but with precious blood, as of a faultless and pure lamb, the blood of Christ;
B060C001V020	60	1	20	who was foreknown indeed before the foundation of the world, but was revealed at the end of times for your sake,
B060C001V021	60	1	21	who through Him are believers in God, who raised Him from the dead, and gave Him glory; so that your faith and hope might be in God.
B060C001V022	60	1	22	Seeing you have purified your souls in your obedience to the truth in sincere brotherly affection, love one another from a pure heart fervently:
B060C001V023	60	1	23	having been born again, not of corruptible seed, but of incorruptible, through the living and abiding Word of God.
B060C001V024	60	1	24	For, "All flesh is like grass,and all it's glory like the flower in the grass.The grass withers, and its flower falls;
B060C001V025	60	1	25	but the word of 
B060C002V001	60	2	1	Putting away therefore all wickedness, all deceit, hypocrisies, envies, and all evil speaking,
B060C002V002	60	2	2	as newborn babies, long for the pure milk of the Word, that you may grow thereby,
B060C002V003	60	2	3	if indeed you have tasted that 
B060C002V004	60	2	4	coming to him, a living stone, rejected indeed by men, but chosen by God, precious.
B060C002V005	60	2	5	You also, as living stones, are built up as a spiritual house, to be a holy priesthood, to offer up spiritual sacrifices, acceptable to God through Jesus Christ.
B060C002V006	60	2	6	Because it is contained in Scripture,
B060C002V007	60	2	7	For you who believe therefore is the honor, but for those who do not believe,
B060C002V008	60	2	8	and,For they stumble at the word, being disobedient, to which also they were appointed.
B060C002V009	60	2	9	But you are a chosen race, a royal priesthood, a holy nation, a people for God's own possession, that you may proclaim the excellence of him who called you out of darkness into his marvelous light:
B060C002V010	60	2	10	who in time past were no people, but now are God's people, who had not obtained mercy, but now have obtained mercy.
B060C002V011	60	2	11	Beloved, I beg you as foreigners and pilgrims, to abstain from fleshly lusts, which war against the soul;
B060C002V012	60	2	12	having good behavior among the nations, so in that of which they speak against you as evildoers, they may by your good works, which they see, glorify God in the day of visitation.
B060C002V013	60	2	13	Subject yourselves to every ordinance of man for the Lord's sake: whether to the king, as supreme;
B060C002V014	60	2	14	or to governors, as sent by him for vengeance on evildoers and for praise to those who do well.
B060C002V015	60	2	15	For this is the will of God, that by well-doing you should put to silence the ignorance of foolish men:
B060C002V016	60	2	16	as free, and not using your freedom for a cloak of wickedness, but as bondservants of God.
B060C002V017	60	2	17	Honor all men. Love the brotherhood. Fear God. Honor the king.
B060C002V018	60	2	18	Servants, be in subjection to your masters with all fear; not only to the good and gentle, but also to the wicked.
B060C002V019	60	2	19	For it is commendable if someone endures pain, suffering unjustly, because of conscience toward God.
B060C002V020	60	2	20	For what glory is it if, when you sin, you patiently endure beating? But if, when you do well, you patiently endure suffering, this is commendable with God.
B060C002V021	60	2	21	For to this you were called, because Christ also suffered for you, leaving you an example, that you should follow his steps,
B060C002V022	60	2	22	who did not sin, "neither was deceit found in his mouth."
B060C002V023	60	2	23	Who, when he was cursed, did not curse back. When he suffered, did not threaten, but committed himself to him who judges righteously;
B060C002V024	60	2	24	who his own self bore our sins in his body on the tree, that we, having died to sins, might live to righteousness; by his stripes you were healed.
B060C002V025	60	2	25	For you were going astray like sheep; but now have returned to the Shepherd and Overseer of your souls.
B060C003V001	60	3	1	In like manner, wives, be in subjection to your own husbands; so that, even if any do not obey the Word, they may be won by the behavior of their wives without a word;
B060C003V002	60	3	2	seeing your pure behavior in fear.
B060C003V003	60	3	3	Let your beauty be not just the outward adorning of braiding the hair, and of wearing jewels of gold, or of putting on fine clothing;
B060C003V004	60	3	4	but in the hidden person of the heart, in the incorruptible adornment of a gentle and quiet spirit, which is in the sight of God very precious.
B060C003V005	60	3	5	For this is how the holy women before, who hoped in God also adorned themselves, being in subjection to their own husbands:
B060C003V006	60	3	6	as Sarah obeyed Abraham, calling him lord, whose children you now are, if you do well, and are not put in fear by any terror.
B060C003V007	60	3	7	You husbands, in like manner, live with your wives according to knowledge, giving honor to the woman, as to the weaker vessel, as being also joint heirs of the grace of life; that your prayers may not be hindered.
B060C003V008	60	3	8	Finally, be all like-minded, compassionate, loving as brothers, tenderhearted, humble,
B060C003V009	60	3	9	not rendering evil for evil, or reviling for reviling; but instead blessing; because to this were you called, that you may inherit a blessing.
B060C003V010	60	3	10	For, "He who would love life,and see good days,let him keep his tongue from evil,and his lips from speaking deceit.
B060C003V011	60	3	11	Let him turn away from evil, and do good.Let him seek peace, and pursue it.
B060C003V012	60	3	12	For the eyes of 
B060C003V013	60	3	13	Now who is he who will harm you, if you become zealous of that which is good?
B060C003V014	60	3	14	But even if you should suffer for righteousness' sake, you are blessed. "Do not fear what they fear, neither be troubled."
B060C003V015	60	3	15	But sanctify in your hearts Christ as Lord; and always be ready to give an answer to everyone who asks you a reason concerning the hope that is in you, yet with humility and fear:
B060C003V016	60	3	16	having a good conscience; so that when they speak evil against you, they may be put to shame who slander your good manner of life in Christ.
B060C003V017	60	3	17	For it is better, if it is God's will, that you suffer for doing well than for doing evil.
B060C003V018	60	3	18	Because Christ also suffered for sins once, the righteous for the unrighteous, that he might bring you to God; being put to death in the flesh, but made alive in the spirit;
B060C003V019	60	3	19	in which he also went and preached to the spirits in prison,
B060C003V020	60	3	20	who before were disobedient, when God waited patiently in the days of Noah, while the ship was being built. In it, few, that is, eight souls, were saved through water.
B060C003V021	60	3	21	This is a symbol of baptism, which now saves you-not the putting away of the filth of the flesh, but the answer of a good conscience toward God, through the resurrection of Jesus Christ,
B060C003V022	60	3	22	who is at the right hand of God, having gone into heaven, angels and authorities and powers being made subject to him.
B060C004V001	60	4	1	Forasmuch then as Christ suffered in the flesh, arm yourselves also with the same mind; for he who has suffered in the flesh has ceased from sin;
B060C004V002	60	4	2	that you no longer should live the rest of your time in the flesh for the lusts of men, but for the will of God.
B060C004V003	60	4	3	For enough time in the past has been spent doing the will of the Gentiles, and having walked in lewdness, lusts, drunken binges, orgies, carousings, and abominable idolatries.
B060C004V004	60	4	4	They think it is strange that you do not run with them into the same excess of riot, blaspheming:
B060C004V005	60	4	5	who will give account to him who is ready to judge the living and the dead.
B060C004V006	60	4	6	For to this end the Good News was preached even to the dead, that they might be judged indeed as men in the flesh, but live as to God in the spirit.
B060C004V007	60	4	7	But the end of all things is near. Therefore be of sound mind, self-controlled, and sober in prayer.
B060C004V008	60	4	8	Above all things be earnest in your love among yourselves, for love covers a multitude of sins.
B060C004V009	60	4	9	Be hospitable to one another without grumbling.
B060C004V010	60	4	10	As each has received a gift, employ it in serving one another, as good managers of the grace of God in its various forms.
B060C004V011	60	4	11	If anyone speaks, let it be as it were the very words of God. If anyone serves, let it be as of the strength which God supplies, that in all things God may be glorified through Jesus Christ, to whom belong the glory and the dominion forever and ever. Amen.
B060C004V012	60	4	12	Beloved, do not be astonished at the fiery trial which has come upon you, to test you, as though a strange thing happened to you.
B060C004V013	60	4	13	But because you are partakers of Christ's sufferings, rejoice; that at the revelation of his glory you also may rejoice with exceeding joy.
B060C004V014	60	4	14	If you are insulted for the name of Christ, you are blessed; because the Spirit of glory and of God rests on you.
B060C004V015	60	4	15	For let none of you suffer as a murderer, or a thief, or an evil doer, or a meddler in other men's matters.
B060C004V016	60	4	16	But if one of you suffers for being a Christian, let him not be ashamed; but let him glorify God in this name.
B060C004V017	60	4	17	For the time has come for judgment to begin with the household of God. If it begins first with us, what will happen to those who do not obey the Good News of God?
B060C004V018	60	4	18	"If it is hard for the righteous to be saved, what will happen to the ungodly and the sinner?"
B060C004V019	60	4	19	Therefore let them also who suffer according to the will of God in doing good entrust their souls to him, as to a faithful Creator.
B060C005V001	60	5	1	Therefore, I exhort the elders among you, as a fellow elder, and a witness of the sufferings of Christ, and who will also share in the glory that will be revealed.
B060C005V002	60	5	2	Shepherd the flock of God which is among you, exercising the oversight, not under compulsion, but voluntarily, according to God; not for dishonest gain, but willingly;
B060C005V003	60	5	3	neither as lording it over those entrusted to you, but making yourselves examples to the flock.
B060C005V004	60	5	4	When the chief Shepherd is revealed, you will receive the crown of glory that does not fade away.
B060C005V005	60	5	5	Likewise, you younger ones, be subject to the elder. Yes, all of you clothe yourselves with humility, towards one another; for "God resists the proud, but gives grace to the humble."
B060C005V006	60	5	6	Humble yourselves therefore under the mighty hand of God, that he may exalt you in due time;
B060C005V007	60	5	7	casting all your worries on him, because he cares for you.
B060C005V008	60	5	8	Be sober and self-controlled. Be watchful. Your adversary the devil, walks around like a roaring lion, seeking whom he may devour.
B060C005V009	60	5	9	Withstand him steadfast in your faith, knowing that your brothers who are in the world are undergoing the same sufferings.
B060C005V010	60	5	10	And the God of all grace, who called you to his eternal glory in Christ, after you have suffered a little while, will himself restore, confirm, strengthen and establish you.
B060C005V011	60	5	11	To him be the power forever. Amen.
B060C005V012	60	5	12	Through Silvanus, our faithful brother, as I consider him, I have written to you briefly, exhorting, and testifying that this is the true grace of God. Stand firm in it!
B060C005V013	60	5	13	She who is in Babylon, chosen together with you, greets you; and so does Mark, my son.
B060C005V014	60	5	14	Greet one another with a kiss of love. Peace be to you all who are in Christ.
B061C001V001	61	1	1	Simon Peter, a servant and apostle of Jesus Christ, to those who have obtained a like precious faith with us in the righteousness of our God and Savior, Jesus Christ:
B061C001V002	61	1	2	Grace to you and peace be multiplied in the knowledge of God and of Jesus our Lord,
B061C001V003	61	1	3	seeing that his divine power has granted to us all things that pertain to life and godliness, through the knowledge of him who called us by his own glory and virtue;
B061C001V004	61	1	4	by which he has granted to us his precious and exceedingly great promises; that through these you may become partakers of the divine nature, having escaped from the corruption that is in the world by lust.
B061C001V005	61	1	5	Yes, and for this very cause adding on your part all diligence, in your faith supply moral excellence; and in moral excellence, knowledge;
B061C001V006	61	1	6	and in knowledge, self-control; and in self-control patience; and in patience godliness;
B061C001V007	61	1	7	and in godliness brotherly affection; and in brotherly affection, love.
B061C001V008	61	1	8	For if these things are yours and abound, they make you to be not idle nor unfruitful to the knowledge of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B061C001V009	61	1	9	For he who lacks these things is blind, seeing only what is near, having forgotten the cleansing from his old sins.
B061C001V010	61	1	10	Therefore, brothers, be more diligent to make your calling and election sure. For if you do these things, you will never stumble.
B061C001V011	61	1	11	For thus you will be richly supplied with the entrance into the eternal Kingdom of our Lord and Savior, Jesus Christ.
B061C001V012	61	1	12	Therefore I will be ready always to remind you of these things, though you know them, and are established in the present truth.
B061C001V013	61	1	13	I think it right, as long as I am in this tent, to stir you up by reminding you;
B061C001V014	61	1	14	knowing that the putting off of my tent comes swiftly, even as our Lord Jesus Christ made clear to me.
B061C001V015	61	1	15	Yes, I will make every effort that you may always be able to remember these things even after my departure.
B061C001V016	61	1	16	For we did not follow cunningly devised tales, when we made known to you the power and coming of our Lord Jesus Christ, but we were eyewitnesses of his majesty.
B061C001V017	61	1	17	For he received from God the Father honor and glory, when the voice came to him from the Majestic Glory, "This is my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased."
B061C001V018	61	1	18	We heard this voice come out of heaven when we were with him on the holy mountain.
B061C001V019	61	1	19	We have the more sure word of prophecy; and you do well that you heed it, as to a lamp shining in a dark place, until the day dawns, and the morning star arises in your hearts:
B061C001V020	61	1	20	knowing this first, that no prophecy of Scripture is of private interpretation.
B061C001V021	61	1	21	For no prophecy ever came by the will of man: but men spoke from God, being moved by the Holy Spirit.
B061C002V001	61	2	1	But false prophets also arose among the people, as false teachers will also be among you, who will secretly bring in destructive heresies, denying even the Master who bought them, bringing on themselves swift destruction.
B061C002V002	61	2	2	Many will follow their immoral ways, and as a result, the way of the truth will be maligned.
B061C002V003	61	2	3	In covetousness they will exploit you with deceptive words: whose sentence now from of old does not linger, and their destruction is not asleep.
B061C002V004	61	2	4	For if God did not spare angels when they sinned, but cast them down to the lower parts of hell, and committed them to pits of darkness, to be reserved for judgment;
B061C002V005	61	2	5	and did not spare the ancient world, but preserved Noah with seven others, a proclaimer of righteousness, when he brought a flood on the world of the ungodly;
B061C002V006	61	2	6	and turning the cities of Sodom and Gomorrah into ashes, condemned them to destruction, having made them an example to those who would live ungodly;
B061C002V007	61	2	7	and delivered righteous Lot, who was very distressed by the lustful life of the wicked
B061C002V008	61	2	8	(for that righteous man dwelling among them, was tormented in his righteous soul from day to day with seeing and hearing lawless deeds):
B061C002V009	61	2	9	the Lord knows how to deliver the godly out of temptation and to keep the unrighteous under punishment for the day of judgment;
B061C002V010	61	2	10	but chiefly those who walk after the flesh in the lust of defilement, and despise authority. Daring, self-willed, they are not afraid to speak evil of dignitaries;
B061C002V011	61	2	11	whereas angels, though greater in might and power, do not bring a railing judgment against them before the Lord.
B061C002V012	61	2	12	But these, as unreasoning creatures, born natural animals to be taken and destroyed, speaking evil in matters about which they are ignorant, will in their destroying surely be destroyed,
B061C002V013	61	2	13	suffering the penalty as the wages of evil; people who count it pleasure to revel in the daytime, spots and blemishes, reveling in their deceit while they feast with you;
B061C002V014	61	2	14	having eyes full of adultery, and who cannot cease from sin; enticing unsettled souls; having a heart trained in greed; children of cursing;
B061C002V015	61	2	15	forsaking the right way, they went astray, having followed the way of Balaam the son of Beor, who loved the wages of wrongdoing;
B061C002V016	61	2	16	but he was rebuked for his own disobedience. A mute donkey spoke with a man's voice and stopped the madness of the prophet.
B061C002V017	61	2	17	These are wells without water, and mists driven by a storm; for whom the blackness of darkness has been reserved.
B061C002V018	61	2	18	For, uttering great swelling words of emptiness, they entice in the lusts of the flesh, by licentiousness, those who barely escape from those who live in error;
B061C002V019	61	2	19	promising them liberty, while they themselves are bondservants of corruption; for a man is brought into bondage by whoever overcomes him.
B061C002V020	61	2	20	For if, after they have escaped the defilement of the world through the knowledge of the Lord and Savior Jesus Christ, they are again entangled in it and overcome, the last state has become worse for them than the first.
B061C002V021	61	2	21	For it would be better for them not to have known the way of righteousness, than, after knowing it, to turn back from the holy commandment delivered to them.
B061C002V022	61	2	22	It has happened to them according to the true proverb, "The dog turns to his own vomit again," and "the sow that has washed to wallowing in the mire."
B061C003V001	61	3	1	This is now, beloved, the second letter that I have written to you; and in both of them I stir up your sincere mind by reminding you;
B061C003V002	61	3	2	that you should remember the words which were spoken before by the holy prophets, and the commandment of the Lord and Savior through your apostles:
B061C003V003	61	3	3	knowing this first, that in the last days scoffers will come, mocking and walking after their own lusts,
B061C003V004	61	3	4	and saying, "Where is the promise of his coming? For, from the day that the fathers fell asleep, all things continue as they were from the beginning of the creation."
B061C003V005	61	3	5	For this they willfully forget, that there were heavens from of old, and an earth formed out of water and amid water, by the word of God;
B061C003V006	61	3	6	by which means the world that then was, being overflowed with water, perished.
B061C003V007	61	3	7	But the heavens that now are, and the earth, by the same word have been stored up for fire, being reserved against the day of judgment and destruction of ungodly men.
B061C003V008	61	3	8	But do not forget this one thing, beloved, that one day is with the Lord as a thousand years, and a thousand years as one day.
B061C003V009	61	3	9	The Lord is not slow concerning his promise, as some count slowness; but is patient with you, not wishing that any should perish, but that all should come to repentance.
B061C003V010	61	3	10	But the day of the Lord will come as a thief; in which the heavens will pass away with a great noise, and the elements will be dissolved with fervent heat, and the earth and the works that are in it will be disclosed.
B061C003V011	61	3	11	Therefore since all these things will be destroyed like this, what kind of people ought you to be in holy living and godliness,
B061C003V012	61	3	12	looking for and earnestly desiring the coming of the day of God, which will cause the burning heavens to be dissolved, and the elements will melt with fervent heat?
B061C003V013	61	3	13	But, according to his promise, we look for new heavens and a new earth, in which righteousness dwells.
B061C003V014	61	3	14	Therefore, beloved, seeing that you look for these things, be diligent to be found in peace, without blemish and blameless in his sight.
B061C003V015	61	3	15	Regard the patience of our Lord as salvation; even as our beloved brother Paul also, according to the wisdom given to him, wrote to you;
B061C003V016	61	3	16	as also in all of his letters, speaking in them of these things. In those, there are some things that are hard to understand, which the ignorant and unsettled twist, as they also do to the other Scriptures, to their own destruction.
B061C003V017	61	3	17	You therefore, beloved, knowing these things beforehand, beware, lest being carried away with the error of the wicked, you fall from your own steadfastness.
B061C003V018	61	3	18	But grow in the grace and knowledge of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ. To him be the glory both now and forever. Amen.
B062C001V001	62	1	1	That which was from the beginning, that which we have heard, that which we have seen with our eyes, that which we saw, and our hands touched, concerning the Word of life
B062C001V002	62	1	2	(and the life was revealed, and we have seen, and testify, and declare to you the life, the eternal life, which was with the Father, and was revealed to us);
B062C001V003	62	1	3	that which we have seen and heard we declare to you also, that you also may have fellowship with us. Yes, and our fellowship is with the Father, and with his Son, Jesus Christ.
B062C001V004	62	1	4	And we write these things, that our joy may be fulfilled.
B062C001V005	62	1	5	This is the message which we have heard from him and announce to you, that God is light, and in him is no darkness at all.
B062C001V006	62	1	6	If we say that we have fellowship with him and walk in the darkness, we lie, and do not tell the truth.
B062C001V007	62	1	7	But if we walk in the light, as he is in the light, we have fellowship with one another, and the blood of Jesus, his Son, cleanses us from all sin.
B062C001V008	62	1	8	If we say that we have no sin, we deceive ourselves, and the truth is not in us.
B062C001V009	62	1	9	If we confess our sins, he is faithful and righteous to forgive us the sins, and to cleanse us from all unrighteousness.
B062C001V010	62	1	10	If we say that we have not sinned, we make him a liar, and his word is not in us.
B062C002V001	62	2	1	My little children, I write these things to you so that you may not sin. If anyone sins, we have an Advocate with the Father, Jesus Christ, the righteous.
B062C002V002	62	2	2	And he is the atoning sacrifice for our sins, and not for ours only, but also for the whole world.
B062C002V003	62	2	3	This is how we know that we know him: if we keep his commandments.
B062C002V004	62	2	4	One who says, "I know him," and does not keep his commandments, is a liar, and the truth is not in him.
B062C002V005	62	2	5	But whoever keeps his word, God's love has truly been perfected in him. This is how we know that we are in him:
B062C002V006	62	2	6	he who says he remains in him ought himself also to walk just like he walked.
B062C002V007	62	2	7	Beloved, I write no new commandment to you, but an old commandment which you had from the beginning. The old commandment is the word which you heard.
B062C002V008	62	2	8	Again, I write a new commandment to you, which is true in him and in you; because the darkness is passing away, and the true light already shines.
B062C002V009	62	2	9	He who says he is in the light and hates his brother, is in the darkness even until now.
B062C002V010	62	2	10	He who loves his brother remains in the light, and there is no occasion for stumbling in him.
B062C002V011	62	2	11	But he who hates his brother is in the darkness, and walks in the darkness, and does not know where he is going, because the darkness has blinded his eyes.
B062C002V012	62	2	12	I write to you, little children, because your sins are forgiven you for his name's sake.
B062C002V013	62	2	13	I am writing to you, fathers, because you know him who is from the beginning.
B062C002V014	62	2	14	I have written to you, fathers, because you know him who is from the beginning.
B062C002V015	62	2	15	Do not love the world, neither the things that are in the world. If anyone loves the world, the Father's love is not in him.
B062C002V016	62	2	16	For all that is in the world, the lust of the flesh, the lust of the eyes, and the pride of life, is not the Father's, but is the world's.
B062C002V017	62	2	17	The world is passing away with its lusts, but he who does God's will remains forever.
B062C002V018	62	2	18	Little children, these are the end times, and as you heard that the Anti-Christ is coming, even now many anti-Christs have arisen. By this we know that it is the final hour.
B062C002V019	62	2	19	They went out from us, but they did not belong to us; for if they had belonged to us, they would have continued with us. But they left, that they might be revealed that none of them belong to us.
B062C002V020	62	2	20	You have an anointing from the Holy One, and you all have knowledge.
B062C002V021	62	2	21	I have not written to you because you do not know the truth, but because you know it, and because no lie is of the truth.
B062C002V022	62	2	22	Who is the liar but he who denies that Jesus is the Christ? This is the Anti-Christ, he who denies the Father and the Son.
B062C002V023	62	2	23	Whoever denies the Son, the same does not have the Father. He who confesses the Son has the Father also.
B062C002V024	62	2	24	As for you, let that remain in you which you heard from the beginning. If that which you heard from the beginning remains in you, you also will remain in the Son, and in the Father.
B062C002V025	62	2	25	This is the promise which he promised us, the eternal life.
B062C002V026	62	2	26	These things I have written to you concerning those who would lead you astray.
B062C002V027	62	2	27	As for you, the anointing which you received from him remains in you, and you do not need for anyone to teach you. But as his anointing teaches you concerning all things, and is true, and is no lie, and even as it taught you, you remain in him.
B062C002V028	62	2	28	Now, little children, remain in him, that when he appears, we may have boldness, and not be ashamed before him at his coming.
B062C002V029	62	2	29	If you know that he is righteous, you know that everyone also who practices righteousness is born of him.
B062C003V001	62	3	1	Behold, how great a love the Father has bestowed on us, that we should be called children of God; and such we are. For this cause the world does not know us, because it did not know him.
B062C003V002	62	3	2	Beloved, now we are children of God, and it is not yet revealed what we will be. We know that, when he is revealed, we will be like him; for we will see him just as he is.
B062C003V003	62	3	3	Everyone who has this hope set on him purifies himself, even as he is pure.
B062C003V004	62	3	4	Everyone who sins also commits lawlessness. Sin is lawlessness.
B062C003V005	62	3	5	You know that he was revealed to take away sins, and in him is no sin.
B062C003V006	62	3	6	Whoever remains in him does not sin. Whoever sins hasn't seen him, neither knows him.
B062C003V007	62	3	7	Little children, let no one lead you astray. He who does righteousness is righteous, even as he is righteous.
B062C003V008	62	3	8	He who sins is of the devil, for the devil has been sinning from the beginning. To this end the Son of God was revealed, that he might destroy the works of the devil.
B062C003V009	62	3	9	Whoever is born of God does not commit sin, because his seed remains in him; and he cannot sin, because he is born of God.
B062C003V010	62	3	10	In this the children of God are revealed, and the children of the devil. Whoever does not do righteousness is not of God, neither is he who does not love his brother.
B062C003V011	62	3	11	For this is the message which you heard from the beginning, that we should love one another;
B062C003V012	62	3	12	unlike Cain, who was of the evil one, and killed his brother. Why did he kill him? Because his works were evil, and his brother's righteous.
B062C003V013	62	3	13	Do not be surprised, brothers, if the world hates you.
B062C003V014	62	3	14	We know that we have passed out of death into life, because we love the brothers. He who does not love remains in death.
B062C003V015	62	3	15	Whoever hates his brother is a murderer, and you know that no murderer has eternal life remaining in him.
B062C003V016	62	3	16	By this we know love, because he laid down his life for us. And we ought to lay down our lives for the brothers.
B062C003V017	62	3	17	But whoever has the world's goods, and sees his brother in need, and closes his heart of compassion against him, how does the love of God remain in him?
B062C003V018	62	3	18	Little children, let us not love in word only, neither with the tongue only, but in deed and truth.
B062C003V019	62	3	19	And by this we will know that we are of the truth, and persuade our heart before him,
B062C003V020	62	3	20	because if our heart condemns us, God is greater than our heart, and knows all things.
B062C003V021	62	3	21	Beloved, if our hearts do not condemn us, we have boldness toward God;
B062C003V022	62	3	22	and whatever we ask, we receive from him, because we keep his commandments and do the things that are pleasing in his sight.
B062C003V023	62	3	23	This is his commandment, that we should believe in the name of his Son, Jesus Christ, and love one another, even as he commanded us.
B062C003V024	62	3	24	He who keeps his commandments remains in him, and he in him. By this we know that he remains in us, by the Spirit which he gave us.
B062C004V001	62	4	1	Beloved, do not believe every spirit, but test the spirits, whether they are of God, because many false prophets have gone out into the world.
B062C004V002	62	4	2	By this you know the Spirit of God: every spirit who confesses that Jesus Christ has come in the flesh is of God,
B062C004V003	62	4	3	and every spirit who does not confess Jesus is not of God, and this is the spirit of the Anti-Christ, of whom you have heard that it comes. Now it is in the world already.
B062C004V004	62	4	4	You are of God, little children, and have overcome them; because greater is he who is in you than he who is in the world.
B062C004V005	62	4	5	They are of the world. Therefore they speak of the world, and the world hears them.
B062C004V006	62	4	6	We are of God. He who knows God listens to us. He who is not of God does not listen to us. By this we know the spirit of truth, and the spirit of error.
B062C004V007	62	4	7	Beloved, let us love one another, for love is of God; and everyone who loves is born of God, and knows God.
B062C004V008	62	4	8	He who does not love does not know God, for God is love.
B062C004V009	62	4	9	By this God's love was revealed in us, that God has sent his one and only Son into the world that we might live through him.
B062C004V010	62	4	10	In this is love, not that we loved God, but that he loved us, and sent his Son as the atoning sacrifice for our sins.
B062C004V011	62	4	11	Beloved, if God loved us in this way, we also ought to love one another.
B062C004V012	62	4	12	No one has seen God at any time. If we love one another, God remains in us, and his love has been perfected in us.
B062C004V013	62	4	13	By this we know that we remain in him and he in us, because he has given us of his Spirit.
B062C004V014	62	4	14	We have seen and testify that the Father has sent the Son as the Savior of the world.
B062C004V015	62	4	15	Whoever confesses that Jesus is the Son of God, God remains in him, and he in God.
B062C004V016	62	4	16	We know and have believed the love which God has for us. God is love, and he who remains in love remains in God, and God remains in him.
B062C004V017	62	4	17	In this love has been made perfect among us, that we may have boldness in the day of judgment, because as he is, even so are we in this world.
B062C004V018	62	4	18	There is no fear in love; but perfect love casts out fear, because fear has punishment. He who fears is not made perfect in love.
B062C004V019	62	4	19	We love, because he first loved us.
B062C004V020	62	4	20	If a man says, "I love God," and hates his brother, he is a liar; for he who does not love his brother whom he has seen, cannot love God whom he has not seen.
B062C004V021	62	4	21	This commandment we have from him, that he who loves God should also love his brother.
B062C005V001	62	5	1	Whoever believes that Jesus is the Christ is born of God. Whoever loves the Father also loves the child who is born of him.
B062C005V002	62	5	2	By this we know that we love the children of God, when we love God and do his commandments.
B062C005V003	62	5	3	For this is the love of God, that we keep his commandments. His commandments are not grievous.
B062C005V004	62	5	4	For whatever is born of God overcomes the world. This is the victory that has overcome the world: our faith.
B062C005V005	62	5	5	Who is he who overcomes the world, but he who believes that Jesus is the Son of God?
B062C005V006	62	5	6	This is he who came by water and blood, Jesus Christ; not with the water only, but with the water and the blood. It is the Spirit who testifies, because the Spirit is the truth.
B062C005V007	62	5	7	For there are three who testify:
B062C005V008	62	5	8	the Spirit, the water, and the blood; and the three agree as one.
B062C005V009	62	5	9	If we receive the witness of men, the witness of God is greater; for this is God's testimony that he has testified concerning his Son.
B062C005V010	62	5	10	He who believes in the Son of God has the testimony in himself. He who does not believe God has made him a liar, because he has not believed in the testimony that God has given concerning his Son.
B062C005V011	62	5	11	The testimony is this, that God gave to us eternal life, and this life is in his Son.
B062C005V012	62	5	12	He who has the Son has the life. He who does not have God's Son does not have the life.
B062C005V013	62	5	13	These things I have written to you who believe in the name of the Son of God, that you may know that you have eternal life.
B062C005V014	62	5	14	This is the boldness which we have toward him, that, if we ask anything according to his will, he listens to us.
B062C005V015	62	5	15	And if we know that he listens to us, whatever we ask, we know that we have the petitions which we have asked of him.
B062C005V016	62	5	16	If anyone sees his brother sinning a sin not leading to death, he shall ask, and God will give him life for those who sin not leading to death. There is a sin leading to death. I do not say that he should make a request concerning this.
B062C005V017	62	5	17	All unrighteousness is sin, and there is a sin not leading to death.
B062C005V018	62	5	18	We know that whoever is born of God does not sin, but he who was born of God protects him, and the evil one does not touch him.
B062C005V019	62	5	19	We know that we are of God, and the whole world lies in the power of the evil one.
B062C005V020	62	5	20	We know that the Son of God has come, and has given us an understanding, that we know him who is true, and we are in him who is true, in his Son Jesus Christ. This is the true God, and eternal life.
B062C005V021	62	5	21	Little children, keep yourselves from idols.
B063C001V001	63	1	1	The elder, to the chosen lady and her children, whom I love in truth; and not I only, but also all those who know the truth;
B063C001V002	63	1	2	for the truth's sake, which remains in us, and it will be with us forever:
B063C001V003	63	1	3	Grace, mercy, and peace will be with us, from God the Father, and from Jesus Christ, the Son of the Father, in truth and love.
B063C001V004	63	1	4	I rejoice greatly that I have found some of your children walking in truth, even as we have been commanded by the Father.
B063C001V005	63	1	5	Now I beg you, dear lady, not as though I wrote to you a new commandment, but that which we had from the beginning, that we love one another.
B063C001V006	63	1	6	This is love, that we should walk according to his commandments. This is the commandment, even as you heard from the beginning, that you should walk in it.
B063C001V007	63	1	7	For many deceivers have gone out into the world, those who do not confess that Jesus Christ came in the flesh. This is the deceiver and the Anti-Christ.
B063C001V008	63	1	8	Watch yourselves, that you do not lose the things which we have accomplished, but that you receive a full reward.
B063C001V009	63	1	9	Whoever goes on and does not remain in the teaching of Christ, does not have God. He who remains in the teaching, the same has both the Father and the Son.
B063C001V010	63	1	10	If anyone comes to you, and does not bring this teaching, do not receive him into your house, and do not welcome him,
B063C001V011	63	1	11	for he who welcomes him participates in his evil works.
B063C001V012	63	1	12	Having many things to write to you, I do not want to do so with paper and ink, but I hope to come to you, and to speak face to face, that our joy may be made full.
B063C001V013	63	1	13	The children of your chosen sister greet you.
B064C001V001	64	1	1	The elder to Gaius the beloved, whom I love in truth.
B064C001V002	64	1	2	Beloved, I pray that you may prosper in all things and be healthy, even as your soul prospers.
B064C001V003	64	1	3	For I rejoiced greatly, when brothers came and testified about your truth, even as you walk in truth.
B064C001V004	64	1	4	I have no greater joy than this, to hear about my children walking in truth.
B064C001V005	64	1	5	Beloved, you do a faithful work in whatever you accomplish for those who are brothers and strangers.
B064C001V006	64	1	6	They have testified about your love before the church. You will do well to send them forward on their journey in a manner worthy of God,
B064C001V007	64	1	7	because for the sake of the Name they went out, taking nothing from the pagans.
B064C001V008	64	1	8	We therefore ought to receive such, that we may be fellow workers for the truth.
B064C001V009	64	1	9	I wrote something to the church, but Diotrephes, who loves to be first among them, does not accept what we say.
B064C001V010	64	1	10	Therefore, if I come, I will call attention to his deeds which he does, unjustly accusing us with wicked words. Not content with this, neither does he himself receive the brothers, and those who would, he forbids and throws out of the church.
B064C001V011	64	1	11	Beloved, do not imitate that which is evil, but that which is good. He who does good is of God. He who does evil hasn't seen God.
B064C001V012	64	1	12	Demetrius has the testimony of all, and of the truth itself; yes, we also testify, and you know that our testimony is true.
B064C001V013	64	1	13	I had many things to write to you, but I am unwilling to write to you with ink and pen;
B064C001V014	64	1	14	but I hope to see you soon, and we will speak face to face. Peace be to you. The friends greet you. Greet the friends by name.
B065C001V001	65	1	1	Jude, a servant of Jesus Christ, and brother of Jacob, to those who are called, loved by God the Father, and kept for Jesus Christ:
B065C001V002	65	1	2	Mercy to you and peace and love be multiplied.
B065C001V003	65	1	3	Beloved, while I was very eager to write to you about our common salvation, I was constrained to write to you exhorting you to contend earnestly for the faith which was once for all delivered to the saints.
B065C001V004	65	1	4	For there are certain men who crept in secretly, even those who were long ago written about for this condemnation: ungodly men, turning the grace of our God into lasciviousness, and denying our only Master and Lord, Jesus Christ.
B065C001V005	65	1	5	Now I desire to remind you, though you already know this, that 
B065C001V006	65	1	6	Angels who did not keep their first domain, but deserted their own dwelling place, he has kept in everlasting bonds under darkness for the judgment of the great day.
B065C001V007	65	1	7	Even as Sodom and Gomorrah, and the cities around them, having, in the same way as these, given themselves over to sexual immorality and gone after strange flesh, are set forth as an example, suffering the punishment of eternal fire.
B065C001V008	65	1	8	Yet in like manner these also in their dreaming defile the flesh, despise authority, and slander celestial beings.
B065C001V009	65	1	9	But Michael, the archangel, when contending with the devil and arguing about the body of Moses, dared not bring against him an abusive condemnation, but said, "May 
B065C001V010	65	1	10	But these speak evil of whatever things they do not know. What they understand naturally, like the creatures without reason, they are destroyed in these things.
B065C001V011	65	1	11	Woe to them! For they went in the way of Cain, and ran riotously in the error of Balaam for hire, and perished in Korah's rebellion.
B065C001V012	65	1	12	These are hidden rocky reefs in your love feasts when they feast with you, shepherds who without fear feed themselves; clouds without water, carried along by winds; autumn leaves without fruit, twice dead, plucked up by the roots;
B065C001V013	65	1	13	wild waves of the sea, foaming out their own shame; wandering stars, for whom the blackness of darkness has been reserved forever.
B065C001V014	65	1	14	About these also Enoch, the seventh from Adam, prophesied, saying, "Behold, 
B065C001V015	65	1	15	to execute judgment on all, and to convict all the ungodly of all their works of ungodliness which they have done in an ungodly way, and of all the hard things which ungodly sinners have spoken against him."
B065C001V016	65	1	16	These are murmurers and complainers, walking after their lusts (and their mouth speaks proud things), showing respect of persons to gain advantage.
B065C001V017	65	1	17	But you, beloved, remember the words which have been spoken before by the apostles of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B065C001V018	65	1	18	They said to you that "In the last time there will be mockers, walking after their own ungodly lusts."
B065C001V019	65	1	19	These are they who cause divisions, and are sensual, not having the Spirit.
B065C001V020	65	1	20	But you, beloved, keep building up yourselves on your most holy faith, praying in the Holy Spirit.
B065C001V021	65	1	21	Keep yourselves in the love of God, looking for the mercy of our Lord Jesus Christ to eternal life.
B065C001V022	65	1	22	On some have compassion, who are in doubt,
B065C001V023	65	1	23	and some save, snatching them out of the fire, and on some have mercy with fear; hating even the clothing stained by the flesh.
B065C001V024	65	1	24	Now to him who is able to keep you from stumbling, and to present you faultless before the presence of his glory in great joy,
B065C001V025	65	1	25	to the only God our Savior, through Jesus Christ our Lord, be glory and majesty, dominion and power, both now and forever. Amen.
B066C001V001	66	1	1	This is the Revelation of Jesus Christ, which God gave him to show to his servants the things which must happen soon, which he sent and made known by his angel to his servant, John,
B066C001V002	66	1	2	who testified to God's word, and of the testimony of Jesus Christ, about everything that he saw.
B066C001V003	66	1	3	Blessed is he who reads and those who hear the words of the prophecy, and keep the things that are written in it, for the time is near.
B066C001V004	66	1	4	John, to the seven churches that are in Asia: Grace to you and peace, from him who is and who was and who is to come; and from the seven Spirits who are before his throne;
B066C001V005	66	1	5	and from Jesus Christ, the faithful witness, the firstborn of the dead, and the ruler of the kings of the earth. To him who loves us, and washed us from our sins by his blood;
B066C001V006	66	1	6	and he made us to be a Kingdom, priests to his God and Father; to him be the glory and the dominion forever and ever. Amen.
B066C001V007	66	1	7	Behold, he is coming with the clouds, and every eye will see him, including those who pierced him. All the tribes of the earth will mourn over him. Even so, Amen.
B066C001V008	66	1	8	"I am the Alpha and the Omega," says 
B066C001V009	66	1	9	I John, your brother and partner with you in persecution, Kingdom, and patient endurance in Jesus, was on the island that is called Patmos because of the word of God and the testimony of Jesus.
B066C001V010	66	1	10	I was in the Spirit on the Lord's day, and I heard behind me a loud voice, like a trumpet
B066C001V011	66	1	11	saying, "What you see, write in a scroll and send to the seven churches: to Ephesus, Smyrna, Pergamum, Thyatira, Sardis, Philadelphia, and to Laodicea."
B066C001V012	66	1	12	I turned to see the voice that spoke with me. Having turned, I saw seven golden lampstands.
B066C001V013	66	1	13	And among the lampstands was one like a son of man, clothed with a robe reaching down to his feet, and with a golden sash around his chest.
B066C001V014	66	1	14	His head and his hair were white as white wool, like snow. His eyes were like a flame of fire.
B066C001V015	66	1	15	His feet were like burnished brass, as if it had been refined in a furnace. His voice was like the voice of many waters.
B066C001V016	66	1	16	He had seven stars in his right hand. Out of his mouth proceeded a sharp two-edged sword. His face was like the sun shining at its brightest.
B066C001V017	66	1	17	When I saw him, I fell at his feet like a dead man.He laid his right hand on me, saying, "Do not be afraid. I am the first and the last,
B066C001V018	66	1	18	and the Living one. I was dead, and behold, I am alive forevermore. I have the keys of Death and of hell.
B066C001V019	66	1	19	Write therefore the things which you have seen, and the things which are, and the things which will happen hereafter;
B066C001V020	66	1	20	the mystery of the seven stars which you saw in my right hand, and the seven golden lampstands. The seven stars are the angels of the seven churches. The seven lampstands are seven churches.
B066C002V001	66	2	1	"To the angel of the church in Ephesus write:
B066C002V002	66	2	2	"I know your works, and your toil and perseverance, and that you cannot tolerate evil men, and have tested those who call themselves apostles, and they are not, and found them false.
B066C002V003	66	2	3	You have perseverance and have endured for my name's sake, and have not grown weary.
B066C002V004	66	2	4	But I have this against you, that you left your first love.
B066C002V005	66	2	5	Remember therefore from where you have fallen, and repent and do the first works; or else I am coming to you, and will move your lampstand out of its place, unless you repent.
B066C002V006	66	2	6	But this you have, that you hate the works of the Nicolaitans, which I also hate.
B066C002V007	66	2	7	He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches. To him who overcomes I will give to eat of the tree of life, which is in the Paradise of God.
B066C002V008	66	2	8	"To the angel of the church in Smyrna write:
B066C002V009	66	2	9	"I know your afflictions and your poverty (but you are rich), and the blasphemy of those who say they are Jews, and they are not, but are a synagogue of Satan.
B066C002V010	66	2	10	Do not be afraid of the things which you are about to suffer. Behold, the devil is about to throw some of you into prison, that you may be tested; and you will have oppression for ten days. Be faithful to death, and I will give you the crown of life.
B066C002V011	66	2	11	He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches. He who overcomes won't be harmed by the second death.
B066C002V012	66	2	12	"To the angel of the church in Pergamum write:
B066C002V013	66	2	13	"I know where you dwell, where Satan's throne is. You hold firmly to my name, and did not deny my faith in the days of Antipas my witness, my faithful one, who was killed among you, where Satan dwells.
B066C002V014	66	2	14	But I have a few things against you, because you have there some who hold the teaching of Balaam, who taught Balak to throw a stumbling block before the children of Israel, to eat things sacrificed to idols, and to commit sexual immorality.
B066C002V015	66	2	15	So you also have some who hold to the teaching of the Nicolaitans likewise.
B066C002V016	66	2	16	Repent therefore, or else I am coming to you quickly, and I will make war against them with the sword of my mouth.
B066C002V017	66	2	17	He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches. To him who overcomes, to him I will give of the hidden manna, and I will give him a white stone, and on the stone a new name written, which no one knows but he who receives it.
B066C002V018	66	2	18	"To the angel of the church in Thyatira write:
B066C002V019	66	2	19	"I know your works, your love, faith, service, patient endurance, and that your last works are more than the first.
B066C002V020	66	2	20	But I have this against you, that you tolerate the woman, Jezebel, who calls herself a prophetess. She teaches and seduces my servants to commit sexual immorality, and to eat things sacrificed to idols.
B066C002V021	66	2	21	I gave her time to repent, but she refuses to repent of her sexual immorality.
B066C002V022	66	2	22	Behold, I will throw her into a sickbed, and those who commit adultery with her into great oppression, unless they repent of their works.
B066C002V023	66	2	23	I will kill her children with Death, and all the churches will know that I am he who searches the minds and hearts. I will give to each one of you according to your deeds.
B066C002V024	66	2	24	But to you I say, to the rest who are in Thyatira, as many as do not have this teaching, who do not know what some call 'the deep things of Satan,' to you I say, I am not putting any other burden on you.
B066C002V025	66	2	25	Nevertheless, hold that which you have firmly until I come.
B066C002V026	66	2	26	He who overcomes, and he who keeps my works to the end, to him I will give authority over the nations.
B066C002V027	66	2	27	He will rule them with a rod of iron, shattering them like clay pots; as I also have received of my Father:
B066C002V028	66	2	28	and I will give him the morning star.
B066C002V029	66	2	29	He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches.
B066C003V001	66	3	1	"And to the angel of the church in Sardis write:"I know your works, that you have a reputation of being alive, but you are dead.
B066C003V002	66	3	2	Wake up, and keep the things that remain, which were about to die, for I have found no works of yours perfected before my God.
B066C003V003	66	3	3	Remember therefore how you have received and heard. Keep it, and repent. If therefore you do not wake up, I will come as a thief, and you won't know what hour I will come to you.
B066C003V004	66	3	4	Nevertheless you have a few names in Sardis that did not defile their garments. They will walk with me in white, for they are worthy.
B066C003V005	66	3	5	He who overcomes will be arrayed in white garments, and I will in no way blot his name out of the book of life, and I will confess his name before my Father, and before his angels.
B066C003V006	66	3	6	He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches.
B066C003V007	66	3	7	"To the angel of the church in Philadelphia write:
B066C003V008	66	3	8	"I know your works (behold, I have set before you an open door, which no one can shut), that you have a little power, and kept my word, and did not deny my name.
B066C003V009	66	3	9	Behold, I give of the synagogue of Satan, of those who say they are Jews, and they are not, but lie. Behold, I will make them to come and worship before your feet, and to know that I have loved you.
B066C003V010	66	3	10	Because you kept my command to endure, I also will keep you from the hour of testing, which is to come on the whole world, to test those who dwell on the earth.
B066C003V011	66	3	11	I am coming quickly! Hold firmly that which you have, so that no one takes your crown.
B066C003V012	66	3	12	He who overcomes, I will make him a pillar in the temple of my God, and he will go out from there no more. I will write on him the name of my God, and the name of the city of my God, the new Jerusalem, which comes down out of heaven from my God, and my own new name.
B066C003V013	66	3	13	He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches.
B066C003V014	66	3	14	"To the angel of the church in Laodicea write:
B066C003V015	66	3	15	"I know your works, that you are neither cold nor hot. I wish you were cold or hot.
B066C003V016	66	3	16	So, because you are lukewarm, and neither hot nor cold, I will vomit you out of my mouth.
B066C003V017	66	3	17	Because you say, 'I am rich, and have gotten riches, and have need of nothing;' and do not know that you are wretched, miserable, poor, blind, and naked;
B066C003V018	66	3	18	I counsel you to buy from me gold refined by fire, that you may become rich; and white garments, that you may clothe yourself, and that the shame of your nakedness may not be revealed; and eye salve to put on your eyes, that you may see.
B066C003V019	66	3	19	As many as I love, I rebuke and discipline. Be zealous therefore, and repent.
