B066C017V007	66	17	7	The angel said to me, "Why do you wonder? I will tell you the mystery of the woman, and of the beast that carries her, which has the seven heads and the ten horns.
B066C017V008	66	17	8	The beast that you saw was, and is not; and is about to come up out of the abyss and to go into destruction. Those who dwell on the earth and whose names have not been written in the book of life from the foundation of the world will marvel when they see that the beast was, and is not, but is to come.
B066C017V009	66	17	9	Here is the mind that has wisdom. The seven heads are seven mountains, on which the woman sits.
B066C017V010	66	17	10	They are seven kings. Five have fallen, the one is, the other has not yet come. When he comes, he must continue a little while.
B066C017V011	66	17	11	The beast that was, and is not, is himself also an eighth, and is of the seven; and he goes to destruction.
B066C017V012	66	17	12	The ten horns that you saw are ten kings who have received no kingdom as yet, but they receive authority as kings, with the beast, for one hour.
B066C017V013	66	17	13	These have one mind, and they give their power and authority to the beast.
B066C017V014	66	17	14	These will war against the Lamb, and the Lamb will overcome them, for he is Lord of lords, and King of kings. They also will overcome who are with him, called and chosen and faithful."
B066C017V015	66	17	15	He said to me, "The waters which you saw, where the prostitute sits, are peoples, multitudes, nations, and languages.
B066C017V016	66	17	16	The ten horns which you saw, and the beast, these will hate the prostitute, and will make her desolate and naked, and will eat her flesh, and will burn her utterly with fire.
B066C017V017	66	17	17	For God has put in their hearts to do what he has in mind, and to be of one mind, and to give their kingdom to the beast, until the words of God should be accomplished.
B066C017V018	66	17	18	The woman whom you saw is the great city, which reigns over the kings of the earth."
B066C018V001	66	18	1	After these things, I saw another angel coming down out of the sky, having great authority. The earth was illuminated with his glory.
B066C018V002	66	18	2	He shouted with a mighty voice, saying, "Fallen, fallen is Babylon the great, and she has become a habitation of demons, a cage of every unclean spirit, and a cage of every unclean and hateful bird!
B066C018V003	66	18	3	For all the nations have drunk of the wine of the wrath of her sexual immorality, the kings of the earth committed sexual immorality with her, and the merchants of the earth grew rich from the abundance of her luxury."
B066C018V004	66	18	4	I heard another voice from heaven, saying, "Come out of her, my people, that you have no participation in her sins, and that you do not receive of her plagues,
B066C018V005	66	18	5	for her sins have reached to the sky, and God has remembered her iniquities.
B066C018V006	66	18	6	Return to her just as she returned, and repay her double as she did, and according to her works. In the cup which she mixed, mix to her double.
B066C018V007	66	18	7	However much she glorified herself, and grew wanton, so much give her of torment and mourning. For she says in her heart, 'I sit a queen, and am no widow, and will in no way see mourning.'
B066C018V008	66	18	8	Therefore in one day her plagues will come: death, mourning, and famine; and she will be utterly burned with fire; for 
B066C018V009	66	18	9	The kings of the earth, who committed sexual immorality and lived wantonly with her, will weep and wail over her, when they look at the smoke of her burning,
B066C018V010	66	18	10	standing far away for the fear of her torment, saying, 'Woe, woe, the great city, Babylon, the strong city! For your judgment has come in one hour.'
B066C018V011	66	18	11	The merchants of the earth weep and mourn over her, for no one buys their merchandise any more;
B066C018V012	66	18	12	merchandise of gold, silver, precious stones, pearls, fine linen, purple, silk, scarlet, all expensive wood, every vessel of ivory, every vessel made of most precious wood, and of brass, and iron, and marble;
B066C018V013	66	18	13	and cinnamon, spice, incense, perfume, frankincense, wine, olive oil, fine flour, wheat, cattle, sheep, horses, chariots, slaves and human lives.
B066C018V014	66	18	14	The fruits which your soul lusted after have been lost to you, and all things that were dainty and sumptuous have perished from you, and you will find them no more at all.
B066C018V015	66	18	15	The merchants of these things, who were made rich by her, will stand far away for the fear of her torment, weeping and mourning;
B066C018V016	66	18	16	saying, 'Woe, woe, the great city, she who was dressed in fine linen, purple, and scarlet, and decked with gold and precious stones and pearls!
B066C018V017	66	18	17	For in an hour such great riches are made desolate.' Every shipmaster, and everyone who sails anywhere, and mariners, and as many as gain their living by sea, stood far away,
B066C018V018	66	18	18	and exclaimed as they looked at the smoke of her burning, saying, 'What is like the great city?'
B066C018V019	66	18	19	They cast dust on their heads, and shouting, weeping and mourning, saying, 'Woe, woe, the great city, in which all who had their ships in the sea were made rich by reason of her great wealth!' For in one hour is she made desolate.
B066C018V020	66	18	20	"Rejoice over her, O heaven, you saints, apostles, and prophets; for God has judged your judgment on her."
B066C018V021	66	18	21	A mighty angel took up a stone like a great millstone and cast it into the sea, saying, "Thus with violence will Babylon, the great city, be thrown down, and will be found no more at all.
B066C018V022	66	18	22	The voice of harpists, minstrels, flute players, and trumpeters will be heard no more at all in you. No craftsman, of whatever craft, will be found any more at all in you. The sound of a mill will be heard no more at all in you.
B066C018V023	66	18	23	The light of a lamp will shine no more at all in you. The voice of the bridegroom and of the bride will be heard no more at all in you; for your merchants were the princes of the earth; for with your sorcery all the nations were deceived.
B066C018V024	66	18	24	In her was found the blood of prophets and of saints, and of all who have been slain on the earth."
B066C019V001	66	19	1	After these things I heard something like a loud voice of a great multitude in heaven, saying, "Hallelujah! Salvation, glory, and power belong to our God:
B066C019V002	66	19	2	for true and righteous are his judgments. For he has judged the great prostitute, who corrupted the earth with her sexual immorality, and he has avenged the blood of his servants at her hand."
B066C019V003	66	19	3	A second said, "Hallelujah! Her smoke goes up forever and ever."
B066C019V004	66	19	4	The twenty-four elders and the four living creatures fell down and worshiped God who sits on the throne, saying, "Amen! Hallelujah!"
B066C019V005	66	19	5	A voice came forth from the throne, saying, "Give praise to our God, all you his servants, you who fear him, the small and the great!"
B066C019V006	66	19	6	I heard something like the voice of a great multitude, and like the voice of many waters, and like the voice of mighty thunders, saying, "Hallelujah! For 
B066C019V007	66	19	7	Let us rejoice and be exceedingly glad, and let us give the glory to him. For the marriage of the Lamb has come, and his wife has made herself ready."
B066C019V008	66	19	8	It was given to her that she would array herself in bright, pure, fine linen: for the fine linen is the righteous acts of the saints.
