B066C021V011	66	21	11	having the glory of God. Her light was like a most precious stone, as if it was a jasper stone, clear as crystal;
B066C021V012	66	21	12	having a great and high wall; having twelve gates, and at the gates twelve angels; and names written on them, which are the names of the twelve tribes of the children of Israel.
B066C021V013	66	21	13	On the east were three gates; and on the north three gates; and on the south three gates; and on the west three gates.
B066C021V014	66	21	14	The wall of the city had twelve foundations, and on them twelve names of the twelve apostles of the Lamb.
B066C021V015	66	21	15	He who spoke with me had for a measure, a golden reed, to measure the city, its gates, and its wall.
B066C021V016	66	21	16	The city lies foursquare, and its length is as great as its breadth. He measured the city with the reed, twelve thousand stadia. Its length, breadth, and height are equal.
B066C021V017	66	21	17	Its wall is one hundred forty-four cubits, by the measure of a man, that is, of an angel.
B066C021V018	66	21	18	The construction of its wall was jasper. The city was pure gold, like pure glass.
B066C021V019	66	21	19	The foundations of the city's wall were adorned with all kinds of precious stones. The first foundation was jasper; the second, sapphire; the third, chalcedony; the fourth, emerald;
B066C021V020	66	21	20	the fifth, sardonyx; the sixth, sardius; the seventh, chrysolite; the eighth, beryl; the ninth, topaz; the tenth, chrysoprasus; the eleventh, jacinth; and the twelfth, amethyst.
B066C021V021	66	21	21	The twelve gates were twelve pearls. Each one of the gates was made of one pearl. The street of the city was pure gold, like transparent glass.
B066C021V022	66	21	22	I saw no temple in it, for 
B066C021V023	66	21	23	The city has no need for the sun, neither of the moon, to shine, for the very glory of God illuminated it, and its lamp is the Lamb.
B066C021V024	66	21	24	The nations will walk in its light. The kings of the earth bring their splendor into it.
